	(11864, 6, 1, 1, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The demon has many names and each name has held special meaning at one time or another. While the details were sometimes insignificant, the end result was always the same: death.$B$BBut it is now, nearly fifty years after it all began, that the details will find the devil and lead to his downfall.$B$BThis time, we have him... There will be no escape for Nesingwary.$B$BNorthrend will be the battleground for our war. The hunter will become the hunted!', 15354),
	(11865, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You do the Earth Mother\'s work, $N, but do not revel in this victory for too long. We have discovered the hiding place of the trapper leader.', 15354),
	(11866, 1, 5, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will hang around my neck. Let them hear our message and let these ears be the vessels that carry our truths!', 15354),
	(11867, 1, 5, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will hang around my neck. Let them hear our message and let these ears be the vessels that carry our truths!', 15354),
	(11868, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps her death will serve as an example to others that dare slay animals for sport and riches.', 15354),
	(11869, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now let us see how their nerve holds up when they see what became of their companions!', 15354),
	(11870, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Cenius sent you? Well you\'re not a moment too soon!\n', 15354),
	(11871, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A job well done, $N. Now we strike at the pirate leader!\n', 15354),
	(11872, 1, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $N. We are closing in on Nesingwary!', 15354),
	(11873, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Fizzcrank listens to your report, looking somewhat relieved.>$B$BI should\'ve gone with them. We might\'ve been able to complete the mission without losing any pilots.$B$BTailspin is right, though, we have you to thank for what you\'ve been able to salvage. Your efforts may just make the difference in the fight against the Nerubians.', 0),
	(11875, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for your help, $n. No contribution to the war effort is too small. Our men are going to need every advantage they can get in this battle.', 0),
	(11876, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Arch Druid Lathorius wipes away his tears.>$B$BThey never stood a chance. Now orphaned, they will surely die on their own.', 15354),
	(11877, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lord Torvos accepts the plans and looks over them.>$B$BYou\'ve done the offensive a great service, $N, but we should not rest. I wouldn\'t put it beyond our foes to plan more mischief in the future.', 15595),
	(11878, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You hear a voice in your head. It is Khu\'nok.>$B$BYour name has been heard in the whistling winds, $N. You have done a great thing for my kin. For this we will consider you an ally. Alas, our torment cannot end without bloodshed and violence.$B$BThe price of peace for the mammoths will be the death of Kaw...\n', 15354),
	(11879, 6, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lathorius takes the halberd from you.>$B$BIs this what I think it is?$B$B<Lathorius grins.>$B$BSmashing! Outstanding! Another of Nesingwary\'s lackeys brought to justice!', 15354),
	(11880, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for your help. You don\'t know what it\'s like to have to deal with "Doctor" Wafflefry over there. In between his "checkups" on my progress, he\'s busy hawking some gadget or another derived from his military inventions.', 0),
	(11881, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Fezzix looks over the salvage.>$B$BJenny\'s a little roughed up, but she\'ll be fine. As for the salvage, it\'s a bit more... piecemeal than I had hoped, but I should be able to find a use for it. You\'re not off the hook yet, though. We\'re going to rebuild this baby.', 0),
	(11882, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well met. You\'ve come to learn some new ways to handle fire?', 15595),
	(11884, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At least for now the rhinos will know peace. Thank you, $N.', 15354),
	(11885, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! Take this. I\'ve prepared this bundle with items symbolizing the foes you\'ve defeated. They will allow you to summon Terokk.$b$bBeware, $n. He is the most powerful arakkoa to ever exist. Do not underestimate him!', 0),
	(11886, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is worrisome, friend. It hints at a much larger plot beyond simple agitation of the local fire and water elements, and something here bears investigation...', 15595),
	(11887, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gnomish tools? For me? These should make rebuilding that flying machine even easier than I expected.', 0),
	(11888, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It does not surprise me that the orc chieftain does not have time to hear of our troubles. The ambassador\'s efforts will likely be like so much mist blowing in the wind.$B$BBut you are here now. We shall see if he chose well in sending you.', 0),
	(11889, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ll beat them if they come by land and we\'ll beat them if they come by air.  If these motherless undead come by sea we\'re going to give them the beating of their lives.', 15595),
	(11890, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Troubling news indeed.$B$BMy people are leaving this place soon. We are going to break through the Scourge lines to get to our capital, Icemist, in the Dragonblight.$B$BBut, before we do that, we must deal with what the gnomes in their insanity have wrought.', 0),
	(11891, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They seek to summon a frost lord into our world? No! They cannot tip the balance!', 15595),
	(11892, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alas, Nesingwary is gone. Perhaps he was never here to begin with...$B$B<Lathorius sighs.>$B$BThe demon is a slippery one, but his days are numbered. We will find him and when we do...', 15354),
	(11893, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Dorain nods.>$B$BGood. This should be sufficient to show Fezzix exactly what I\'ve been trying to tell him.', 0),
	(11894, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fantastic! A few more tweaks and I\'ll be an airborne goblin!', 0),
	(11895, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I feel the power of the storm coursing through you!$B$BYou are ready, $N. Let us begin.', 0),
	(11896, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With their robotic minions dealt with, it is time for us to move on to bigger prey. Unfortunately, even now I feel the power of the storm waning from within you.$B$BNevertheless, it served its purpose, and I think that you\'re more than capable of taking the next step without it.', 0),
	(11897, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $N.  Without you, Valiance Keep might\'ve not held against the attackers.  Thanks to your help we\'ll live to fight another day.', 15595),
	(11898, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the prince defeated, the Scourge presence in Borean Tundra is broken. I have no illusions that they will stay away for long, which is why I must focus on preparing Durm to lead the villagers on their way to Icemist.$B$B<The chieftain shakes his head slowly.>$B$BFor all the disagreements I\'ve had with Durm, I trust his judgment and his abilities. I cannot bring myself to abandon Taunka\'le, so I will defend it until I am slain.', 0),
	(11899, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now we must free the souls that you have captured.', 0),
	(11900, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is worse than I expected.$b$bMalygos is channeling too much power to this place. If he\'s not stopped, Azeroth will be the next Outlands!$b$bFortunately, I believe that I\'ve engineered a temporary solution....', 0),
	(11901, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your stomach feels uneasy as you approach the grain.  The smell is nearly unbearable.', 15595),
	(11902, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those poor lads... they never had a chance!$B$BThis sure sounds like an inside job.  Probably a Cult of the Damned infiltrator.  Curse those madmen!', 15595),
	(11903, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve communicated with the Scourge in the only language they understand: violence and death.  Unfortunately they just keep coming!', 0),
	(11904, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $N.  This ore will be of vital importance to the Alliance in the times to come.  I\'d like to think we\'ve made a difference today.', 0),
	(11905, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n. The tremors have already begun to subside.$b$bWith any luck, your efforts have granted us sufficient time to find a way to thwart Malygos\' efforts.', 15595),
	(11906, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is the taunka way to leave the land pristine before we move on.$B$BWe will be traveling to our capital, Icemist, very soon. You have helped by allowing us to depart that much more quickly.$B$BThank you.', 0),
	(11907, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N.$B$BWith these odd creatures destroyed, dealing with the rest of the pools should now be a simple matter.$B$BWe owe you a debt of gratitude.', 0),
	(11908, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent!  The information I need should be in here.', 0),
	(11909, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The greatmother breathes a heavy sigh of relief.>$B$BIt is done then... you have saved us! If you hadn\'t stopped him here, then who knows how far this mistake of the gnomes would have spread?$B$BWith the threats from the blue dragons and the Nexus War, not to mention the Lich King, the last thing we need is a mad creation of the Titans running loose!$B$BThank you, $N.', 0),
	(11910, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes. These shall do nicely.$b$bThank you, $r.', 0),
	(11911, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fascinating!$b$bAnd they\'re aggressive too, you say. That would suggest that some intelligence is behind this manipulation.$B$BIt may not be natural at all....', 15595),
	(11912, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, it\'s not much, but it should keep us alive for another day.$b$bI believe you\'ll find this to be a fair price for your efforts.', 0),
	(11913, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $N.  I would hate to see survivors of the attack on Farshire stumble upon plagued grain.', 0),
	(11914, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your service to Dalaran will not go unnoticed, $r.$b$bI hope you find this payment sufficient.', 0),
	(11915, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings. You\'ve come to learn some new ways to handle fire?', 15595),
	(11916, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I fear that you may be too late, champion. Many of my brothers and sisters have already abandoned Taunka\'le, seeking shelter in the Dragonblight, far to the east.$B$BThere is much work left to be done here and few willing to lend us their strength...', 15354),
	(11917, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well. It may seem a small act, but even this can aid the fight as a whole. Take this with my blessing, and return later, as I may have more for you to do.', 0),
	(11918, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alright, $c, now that you\'ve become familiar with the enemy it\'s time for you to get to work.', 0),
	(11919, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The fate of these young drakes need not burden your conscience, $r. Malygos alone is accountable for this.$b$bI am working ceaselessly to discover the secrets of these runes. We shall take no more lives than we must.', 0),
	(11920, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Cultists?  Below deck?  I ought to have my whole crew flogged!$B$BListen... why don\'t we have Admiral Cantlebree take care of this... situation?', 15595),
	(11921, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done!  You\'ll be a fire juggler faster than the fuse on a ground flower!  Now gird yourself!  The next test is when things really heat up...', 0),
	(11922, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done!  You\'ll be a fire juggler faster than the fuse on a ground flower!  Now gird yourself!  The next test is when things really heat up...', 15595),
	(11923, 6, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you get burned?  If you did, then maybe you\'ll think twice before playing with fire...$B$BJust kidding!  Well done!  It\'s official.  You\'re a bona fide fire juggler.  Now get out there and have some fun!', 15595),
	(11924, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Torch catching is a lot of fun, don\'t you think? But have care! You don\'t want to get singed!', 0),
	(11925, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Torch catching is a lot of fun, don\'t you think? But have care! You don\'t want to get singed!', 0),
	(11926, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done!  You\'ll be a fire juggler faster than the fuse on a ground flower!  Now gird yourself!  The next test is when things really heat up...', 0),
	(11927, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for coming to see me.  I didn\'t know who else to contact.', 0),
	(11928, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re here to help?  You\'re just in time then!', 15595),
	(11929, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Mother Tauranook wipes her tears away.>$B$BThere was once a time when I could walk across this tundra and the snow would fill my view for as far as I could see.$B$BBut the snow has left us - signaling that our time here has come to an end. We leave behind Taunka\'le Village and the Borean Tundra with many happy memories...$B$B<Mother Tauranook whimpers.>$B$BPerhaps the future will welcome our return - along with the snow.', 0),
	(11930, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Wartook looks upon you grimly.>$B$BIcemist is no more...', 15354),
	(11931, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, $r.$b$bLet us hope for a clue that we can use against Malygos.', 0),
	(11932, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I remember the man you speak of.  He bore the marks of Karkut.$B$BMay Karkut protect our fallen.', 0),
	(11933, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This fire seems new... Yet, you say it came from the Exodar? Fascinating! To make your way into that ship...  Of course, I\'ll pay you for this. If you find anything else like this, be sure to speak with me again.', 15595),
	(11935, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a glorious fire! You received this from Silvermoon, you say? Unbelievable! With the flames of all four cities, who knows what we could accomplish?', 15595),
	(11936, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It pains me to order the destruction of dragon eggs, enemy or no.$b$bMay the ends of this war justify the means....', 0),
	(11938, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should buy us some time.  Isidorus has been cooperative, but I really needed that alone time with the lich.', 0),
	(11940, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The fate of these young drakes need not burden your conscience, $r. Malygos alone is accountable for this.$b$bI am working ceaselessly to discover the secrets of these runes.$b$bRest assured, we shall take no more lives than we must.', 0),
	(11941, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It was wise of you to bring this to me, $n.$b$b<Raelorasz eyes the fragment and slowly nods.>$b$bIf you truly desire to contribute to our efforts, no matter the risk, I shall share with you its meaning.', 0),
	(11942, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $N.  Now for one last bit of information.', 0),
	(11943, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The pieces you\'ve collected begin to glow brightly in Raelorasz\' hands.>$b$bIt is done.$b$bI sense a strong presence within this prison. Let us hope it proves to be an ally.', 0),
	(11944, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should buy us some time, $N.  We\'ll hope against hope for reinforcements from Valiance Keep.', 0),
	(11945, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $N.  These supplies will feed our cousins and children.  Even if Kaskala falls, our tribes must carry on.', 15595),
	(11946, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We cannot wait for me to regain my strength.$b$bI must rely on you to make our preparations....', 0),
	(11947, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well. It may seem a small act, but even this can aid the fight as a whole. Take this with my blessing, and return later, as I may have more for you to do.', 0),
	(11948, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well. It may seem a small act, but even this can aid the fight as a whole. Take this with my blessing, and return later, as I may have more for you to do.', 0),
	(11949, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $N.  I will be deeply in your debt if we ever make it out of here alive.', 15354),
	(11950, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ataika sent you, didn\'t he?  I am not to be swayed.$B$BAll is not lost.  The spirits are still with us.', 15354),
	(11951, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n.$b$bI am drained from the effects of my confinement and my strength is returning ever so slowly.$b$bI shall use the power from these crystals wisely. They are a byproduct of Malygos\' malevolent schemes. With luck, they will play a part in his undoing.', 0),
	(11952, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well. It may seem a small act, but even this can aid the fight as a whole. Take this with my blessing, and return later, as I may have more for you to do.', 0),
	(11953, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well. It may seem a small act, but even this can aid the fight as a whole. Take this with my blessing, and return later, as I may have more for you to do.', 0),
	(11954, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well. It may seem a small act, but even this can aid the fight as a whole. Take this with my blessing, and return later, as I may have more for you to do.', 15595),
	(11955, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank the spirits you\'re here! We must summon Ahune quickly before it\'s too late...', 0),
	(11956, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just in time, $N.  Pinning down a lich is not as easy as it looks.', 0),
	(11957, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This world is a better place now that Saragosa is no more, but our work is not yet finished.$b$bThe time has come to strike at Malygos himself!', 0),
	(11958, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will not say that I am pleased to ask you to do such things on our behalf. It is all we can do to prepare quickly for our departure, though we know not yet where we go.$B$BMy sorcerers tell me that you are here to save the land from He Who Walks in Shadow.$B$BI trust that you will save the peoples of the land as well.', 15595),
	(11959, 2, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Loguhn\'s honorable sacrifice at your hands is exactly what my people need. Now we will make the most of the wolvar in-fighting for his place.$B$BIt will have to be enough.', 15595),
	(11960, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, I guess you saved plenty of them. Thank you, $r.$B$BNow the wolvar will have a chance of surviving along with us. If we survive at all, that is.$B$BDo you think that you could return tomorrow so that we can save more of the pups?', 15595),
	(11961, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Can you feel Issliruk\'s presence, $N?  He does not want his children to perish at the hand of the mist-walkers.', 15354),
	(11962, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ore from Farshire?  We weren\'t scheduled for a shipment just yet.  Is something wrong?', 0),
	(11963, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hilda\'s sending us weapons?  That\'s excellent news, $N.  I was about ready to tell the lads to pack things up.', 0),
	(11964, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, and what is this?  Such a delightful aroma!  I am sure it will burn with a flame pure and bright!$B$BTake this blossom, $n.  Take it, and leave me be... I must attend to this precious fuel...', 15595),
	(11965, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks once again for aiding us, $N.  The people of Farshire will always remember you.', 0),
	(11966, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, and what is this?  Such a delightful aroma!  I am sure it will burn with a flame pure and bright!$B$BTake this blossom, $n.  Take it, and leave me be... I must attend to this precious fuel...', 15595),
	(11967, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Word of Keristrasza\'s rescue has reached my ears. You are to be commended.$b$bI am eager to speak with her again.', 0),
	(11968, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done us a great favor, $r.  The fight is not yet won, but my people now have a chance.', 15354),
	(11969, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have dealt a blow to Malygos, but it has come at a high price.', 0),
	(11970, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll be happy to tell you what I know.', 0),
	(11971, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll be happy to tell you what I know.', 15595),
	(11972, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, these shards hold the final essence of the Frost Lord in this land.  We will dispose of them and banish Ahune to the nether regions of cold.$B$BThank you, $N.  Your name will echo in the chants of the Earthen Ring for days without end.  Please honor us by accepting this vestige, a symbol of your kinship with warmth and light.', 15595),
	(11973, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, it is done then....$b$bOur kind shall never forget the sacrifice Keristrasza has made for this cause.', 15595),
	(11975, 1, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you see that?  They were cheering for me!!$B$BNow I know how they feel when they are up on stage singing!  I felt the power and the energy!$B$BJust like they say in their song!$B$BMy mind is made up, I am going to be a rock star when I grow up!', 15595),
	(11977, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What you see here is all that remains of the taunka from the Borean Tundra and the Dragonblight. They are a broken people... battered and brought to the brink of extinction by the Scourge.$B$B<Brighthoof shakes her head.>$B$BOnly the Horde can save them now. Only the Horde can mend their broken spirits. We will nurse them back to full health and they will in turn strengthen the Horde in Northrend.', 0),
	(11978, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is exactly what we need, $N! Brandishing Horde arms will lift their spirits and give them the protection they need against the Scourge.$B$BAre you prepared for the ceremony of initiation?$B$B<Brighthoof nods.>$B$BYou will be the one to admit our new allies into the Horde.', 15595),
	(11979, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What you see here is all that remains of the taunka from the Borean Tundra and the Dragonblight. They are a broken people... battered and brought to the brink of extinction.$B$B<Brighthoof shakes her head.>$B$BOnly the Horde can save them now. Only the Horde can mend their broken spirits. We will nurse them back to full health and they will in turn strengthen the Horde in Northrend.', 0),
	(11980, 66, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Roh\'kill salutes you.>$B$BYou have preserved our honor, $N. Tor\'zin and I both thank you for this selfless act!', 15595),
	(11981, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You tell Kurun about the message given to you by the fallen Earthen.>$B$BThey fight bravely, but he is right. We will not overcome the iron dwarves of Thor Modan without help. My giants and the Earthen have long struggled against iron\'s evil, but our forces are not numerous enough to win the battle for Thor Modan. Will you aid us?', 15595),
	(11982, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As quickly as we\'re able to fill the trench, the iron dwarves keep clearing it. Our assault from above will not take the city alone. You must aid the earthen fighting in the plaza below.', 15595),
	(11983, 1, 1, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for doing this, Commander $N. They had nothing left. You have given them purpose and with purpose comes hope... Hope for a new tomorrow... for a new life.', 15595),
	(11984, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great work, $c. Looks like we\'ll be keepin\' Budd around a little longer.$b$bWe\'ll have your cage picked up right away. Here\'s your share of the bounty.$b$bOh, and welcome to the camp. Stick around and I\'m sure we\'ll find a use for ya....', 15595),
	(11985, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N. The loss of the iron dwarf commander should be enough to break the remaining defenders. The Earthen should be able to deal with the survivors.', 15595),
	(11986, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found Brann\'s journal? Incredible! The league hasn\'t gotten a report from him in some time, and we began to fear he may have been captured or killed. What did he discover inside Thor Modan?', 15595),
	(11988, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Torthen works quickly to assemble the fragments you retrieved.>$B$BThis is incomplete, but it should still allow us to get most of the information from the plate.', 15595),
	(11989, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There!$b$bNow we be connected by blood, mon. A true bond we be havin\'.$b$bYou lissen carefully to Drakuru, $r. There be much to do.', 15595),
	(11990, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Drakuru takes the ingredients and deftly combines them in the vial.>$b$bThis should do it, mon. Now it be time to get to work.', 15595),
	(11991, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, yes. Ya done good, mon.$b$bI be readin\' the walls just fine from here....', 15595),
	(11993, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Torthen listens as you recount the contents of the runic plates.>$B$BBy Madoran\'s hammer, he\'s discovered a whole new titan city!$B$B\'The cradle of stone and iron.\'$B$B\'Ulduar nestled in the storm.\'$B$BWhat d\'you suppose that means? Could it be where we come from, after all these years?$B$BWe have to follow him! We have to find him!', 15595),
	(11995, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve been expecting you, $c. We have much work to do, you and I.', 0),
	(11996, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What took you so long? Time waits only for Aspects, $r.$B$BWe have much work to do, you and I.', 15354),
	(11998, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let me get this straight -- a $r I don\'t know brings me a cask of the finest booze in this miserable forest. Ok, then, what are you after?', 15595),
	(11999, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Curious, they seek an accord with the Ethereum. The ethereals could prove a powerful ally for Malygos and his madness.$B$BThis will not do!', 15595),
	(12000, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Curious, they seek an accord with the Ethereum. The ethereals could prove a powerful ally for Malygos and his madness.$B$BThis will not do!', 0),
	(12002, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Brugar listens to your report.>$B$BIt sounds like things may be calming down there a bit. We\'ll start looking for entrances to the iron dwarves\' tunnel system.', 15595),
	(12003, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Brugar utters a stream of foul dwarven words.>$B$BNo entrances? None?$B$BNo, of course it couldn\'t be that easy. Well, I suppose there\'s no avoiding a foray into the city proper. My boys\'ll never get back to their real work.', 15595),
	(12004, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Unfortunate that Goramosh indicated the accord had already been reached.$B$BNonetheless, that\'s two less worms we\'ll have to worry about. Let us get to more important business.', 0),
	(12005, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'That\'s alright, $c, just put them down on the ground there in front of Agmar\'s throne.$B$B<You can practically sense the smile hidden behind the archmage\'s helm.>$B$BUnfortunate that Goramosh indicated the accord had already been reached.$B$BNonetheless, that\'s two less worms we\'ll have to worry about. Let us get on to more important business.', 15595),
	(12006, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well, you have satisfied my request if nothing more.$B$BThank you, $r.', 0),
	(12007, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Dis be it, mon!$b$bIt be even more precious than I hoped. Dis be sure to bring mah people hope in dese dark times.$b$bNo time to waste, now. Let\'s be seein\' where da next artifact be hidin\'.', 15595),
	(12008, 6, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'While you have undoubtedly championed the cause of the Horde elsewhere, many more have been working towards expanding our grasp deeper into Northrend. Even now we have forces establishing bases in the frozen reaches of this desolate wasteland.$B$BWe surround the Scourge on all sides. Victory nears as our armies amass at the foot of the Wrathgate, Angrathar. Soon we will tear down the gate and breach Icecrown.$B$BBut there is much work left to be done...$B$BFirst we stop the Nerubians!', 15595),
	(12009, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m a simple trapper. The world has turned upside-down all of a sudden. It doesn\'t make sense.$B$BI hope that you\'ll be able to set it right again.', 15595),
	(12010, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A quick examination of the body reveals that the surveyor has been dead for some time. Looking through his pack, you stumble upon Orlond\'s handwritten notes.', 15595),
	(12011, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s not the news I wanted to hear, $r.$B$BNo, no... it\'s good that you told me, but I fear my old nemesis has returned to these waters.', 15595),
	(12012, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is grave news indeed. We must do everything in our power to stop this war from coming to pass.', 15595),
	(12013, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my deepest gratitude, $N.$B$BIf you haven\'t already, you should alert your betters to the danger that the blue dragonflight has unleashed. By blowing apart the ley line anchor underneath the gardens, they threaten to destroy us all!', 0),
	(12014, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Brugar looks over the report.>$B$BThis isn\'t good at all. Even if we could excavate the tunnels behind the blockage, there\'s no guarantee they wouldn\'t collapse again. It looks like some of these areas haven\'t been used in generations. We\'ll have to give Captain Gryan the bad news.', 15595),
	(12016, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You were able to slay Kili\'ua... perhaps you\'ll be able to do the same to Tu\'u\'gwar.$B$BPerhaps not.', 15595),
	(12017, 53, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We shall rejoice at your success, my young friend! There\'s blood in the water and it is our enemy\'s!$B$BYou have the eternal gratitude of this old fisherman, and most certainly of all the Kalu\'ak once I spread the word!$B$BHere now, I insist, take something as a reward, please.', 15595),
	(12019, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did well, $N.  I was hoping to leave my sister out of all this.  Thanks to you she is alive and well.$B$BMy obligations to my king and my army have been fulfilled.  It is clear I\'m not welcome among my comrades anymore.  I will have to find my own way, fighting no wars but my own and following no orders but my heart\'s.$B$BPerhaps we shall meet again, $c.  Until then, take this as a token of my gratitude.', 0),
	(12020, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you managed to stop the Dark Irons... While drunk too? That, $c, is truly the spirit of Brewfest! I guess in keeping with the spirit of Brewfest you want your prize tokens.$b$bThanks for your help, $n. Enjoy the rest of Brewfest.', 0),
	(12022, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you know what that was? Gnomish engineering at its finest! S.T.O.U.T. took the abuse like a champ!$b$bI think you\'re ready now to take on the Dark Irons if they show up again.', 0),
	(12026, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Who is this Brann Bronzebeard? The iron dwarves found no reason to treat with him, but I have no idea why we\'d be interested in his writings.', 15595),
	(12027, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank goodness you found Emmy! When she left without me, I was worried she\'d get lost.$B$BI\'m glad to see Mr. Floppy\'s back safe and sound, too.', 0),
	(12028, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ghosts and gibbering madness? This cannot be!$B$BWe must seek further guidance.', 15595),
	(12029, 11, 11, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Well done!$b$b<Mack laughs hysterically for a moment.>$b$bAww, come on now. That was funny...<hic>.', 15595),
	(12030, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve been expecting you, $r. I saw your spirit fly by and sensed the mystic watching behind your eyes.$B$BYour fate and that of the Kalu\'ak are now tied together.', 15595),
	(12031, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not the most pleasant task, but necessary and merciful.$B$BAnd now there is something else that you are destined to do for the Kalu\'ak.', 15595),
	(12032, 15, 1, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You spoke with Oacha\'noa?!$B$BIf it is her will that we stand with your people then so be it. Elder Ko\'nani will accept this as our destiny, for weal or woe.$B$BMy people believe that all souls are one with the magic of the world. We must oppose the blue dragon attempts to control the magic or we are all doomed!$B$BI never thought that a $r would be the champion of the Kalu\'ak, but you have proven me wrong. On behalf of my people, I give you thanks, $N.$B$BMay the gods smile upon you and keep you safe.', 15595),
	(12033, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Torvus nods at you.>$B$BSo we are understood? I will return to my lord and tell him that you have accepted.', 15595),
	(12034, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By land and by air, that\'s how we will end the Anub\'ar threat.', 15595),
	(12035, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice job!  I finally feel useful again... and that\'s sayin\' something.', 0),
	(12036, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That damned sinkhole must be directly connected to Azjol-Nerub. This is worse than I thought.$B$B<Juktok pauses to think for a moment.>$B$BSeek and destroy... That\'ll be the next course of action.', 15595),
	(12037, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew it!$b$bEven my going missing wasn\'t enough to get those spineless weasels to come in here after me.$b$bWell, they sent you. We\'ll have to get through this together.', 15595),
	(12038, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done!$B$B<Mack laughs hysterically for a moment.>$B$BAww, come on now. That was funny...hic.', 0),
	(12039, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s so light... As if it weighs nothing at all! I\'ll need time to analyze the metal and see if I can do anything with it! Tests! I need to run tests!$B$BI\'ll keep in contact, $N. If anything comes of this, you\'ll be the first to know.', 15595),
	(12040, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There are thousands more and they spill out from every dark crevice in Northrend. Alone you stand no chance, but together... Maybe...', 0),
	(12041, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Overlord Agmar looks over the document.>$B$BIs this what I think it is? With the information contained within these pages we will CRUSH the Anub\'ar assault!$B$BYou have done well to bring this document to me, $N. Perhaps you will be allowed to watch or even participate in the final battle at Angrathar! LOK\'TAR!', 0),
	(12042, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This unfortunate goblin must have unearthed the Heart of the Ancients during his excavations in the region.$b$bIt\'s doubtless that he had no clue as to its nature.$b$bYou determine that it must have been overlooked in the chaos sweeping through the area.', 15595),
	(12043, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh!  Yeah, the undead.  Here\'s your coin, bugger off.', 15050),
	(12044, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah!  That\'s quite a load!  Your back feeling alright?', 15050),
	(12045, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent!  They\'re even sharper than I expected them to be.  I\'ll pack them in the snow until the bomb is ready.$b$bLet\'s see... what next...\n', 15050),
	(12046, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good... good... these should do fine.  The shrapnel bombs are almost finished. $b$bWait... what happened to my ice shards?  Narf told me shards from those elementals should be enchanted, but they\'re melting just like the ones hanging from Narf\'s grumpy chin!', 15050),
	(12047, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent!  That should be the last thing I need to test out the new bombs.  Just a moment and I\'ll try this out!', 15050),
	(12048, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are in excellent condition, $N. I\'ll get to work right away. If anything comes of this, you will be the first to know!', 15595),
	(12049, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha ha!  One of those meat slabs landed clear over here!  Nice work there!\n', 15050),
	(12050, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'If a tree falls in the forest, and you can\'t hear it through the saw blade, does it really make a sound?', 15595),
	(12052, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should make those uglies think twice.  Here... take your reward and get away with ya.', 15595),
	(12053, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have crushed them by land! Soon we will crush them by air!', 15595),
	(12054, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N. I\'ll prepare the incense and then we\'ll see what exactly this royal dwarf was doing so far from home.', 15595),
	(12055, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N, if I\'m not mistaken, you\'ve uncovered the key to allow us to discern exactly what the mage hunter forces are up to!', 0),
	(12056, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Gort holds the head up and stares into its dead eyes.>$B$BI told you we\'d get you...$B$BHere\'s your reward, $c. That\'s one less headache for us to worry about.', 15595),
	(12057, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Gort takes the tome from you.>$B$BSavages... Bound in orc flesh... This language... Its existence has never been proven. It is the language of death... The tongue of the Scourge.', 15595),
	(12058, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sage Paluna listens as you recall the translations of the plates.>$B$BSo Brann thinks he\'s discovered a new titan city?$B$B\'The cradle of stone and iron.\'$B$B\'Ulduar nestled in the storm.\'$B$BI will ask the chieftain to dispatch longrunners to the Storm Peaks. My people know these lands well and have the best chance of tracking down this wayward dwarf.', 15595),
	(12059, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N, if I\'m not mistaken, you\'ve uncovered the key to allow us to discern exactly what the mage hunter forces are up to!', 15595),
	(12060, 5, 1, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What you\'re describing... that\'s a projection of the Arcanomicon!$B$B<The archmage\'s show of concern is quickly masked behind an impassive countenance.>$B$BThe Arcanomicon is a map of all of the magical ley line intersections in the world. The blue dragonflight has been using it to find and destroy ley line \'anchors\' to send the magical power back to the Nexus.$B$BThe question is, why is the path of destruction leading east when it should be heading west instead?', 0),
	(12061, 5, 1, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What you\'re describing... that\'s a projection of the Arcanomicon!$B$B<The archmage\'s show of concern is quickly masked behind an impassive countenance.>$B$BThe Arcanomicon is a map of all of the magical ley line intersections in the world. The blue dragonflight has been using it to find and destroy ley line \'anchors\' to send the magical power back to the Nexus.$B$BThe question is, why is the path of destruction leading east when it should be heading west instead?', 15595),
	(12062, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What? What did you say? How dare you! My beer can stand up to any of that rot they serve at Brewfest!$b$bYou\'ll pay for this insult, $c!', 0),
	(12063, 1, 1, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My father still lives! We must save him! I cannot do it alone, $r. You must help me!', 15595),
	(12064, 1, 1, 69, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, this will work.$B$B<Banthok expertly manipulates the key fragments.>$B$BHere it is, $c. With this key, my father will be freed of the Anub\'ar prison.', 15595),
	(12065, 1, 1, 6, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How very odd that it imprinted this information upon you magically.$B$BSo, not only do we know that they\'ve redirected the flow of the power coming out of the Moonrest Gardens, but we now know that the power is being purposefully changed in some way. Just what are they up to with all of that magic?$B$BI don\'t like where this is leading, $N, not one bit!', 0),
	(12066, 1, 1, 6, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How very odd that it imprinted this information upon you magically.$B$BSo, not only do we know that they\'ve redirected the flow of the power coming out of the Moonrest Gardens, but we now know that the power is being purposefully changed in some way. Just what are they up to with all of that magic?$B$BI don\'t like where this is leading, $N.', 15595),
	(12067, 274, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh no... and we sent you down there to kill her, didn\'t we?$B$B<The commander shakes her head and sighs.>$B$BI\'m sorry. I\'ll see to it that the letter is delivered to her father, Archmage Malin in Stormwind, right away. Don\'t worry, you won\'t be implicated... it wasn\'t your fault.$B$BTry to put it out of your mind. There was no way that you could have known, $N.', 0),
	(12068, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve done it, $n!$b$bWe have all of the components we need to perform the cleansing ritual.', 15595),
	(12069, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a brave $c, $N. You\'ve done the Horde a great service by rescuing the High Chief.', 15595),
	(12070, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have given our allies the strength to fight on, and for that you have my thanks. Even so, we must begin planning a way to end this battle before we are overrun.', 15595),
	(12071, 66, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Valnok salutes.>$B$BSo you\'re the hot shot, eh?', 15595),
	(12072, 66, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Valnok salutes.>$B$BAnd now they have been crushed by air! Perhaps soon you will be called to Angrathar, hero!', 15595),
	(12073, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Scout Vor\'takh smiles.>$B$BThor Modan is on the verge of collapse, then?$B$BVery well. We will soon turn our attention to Dun Argol.', 15595),
	(12074, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You introduce yourself to Kurun.>$B$BSo the sons of iron are your enemies as well?$B$BMy forces have the iron dwarves pinned inside their city, but we could use help in pressing the attack. Will you aid us?', 15595),
	(12075, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is perfect.  Thank you, $c.', 15595),
	(12076, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Still fresh.  Just a moment and I will mix this with the rest of the elixir that I have prepared.', 15595),
	(12077, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will be blunt little one - I do not trust this mixture, and I will not use it. Keep it... if you find more trust in the green runt than I do, perhaps it will be of use to you.', 15595),
	(12078, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will do nicely. Perhaps after I grow these beasts to full size, I will bring them back and introduce them to the giants personally.$b$bBunch of useless rocks if you ask me.', 15595),
	(12079, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A satisfying display of slaughter. ', 15595),
	(12080, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So she is dead. As it should be. Your intentions do indeed prove nobler than those of the runt.$B$BThrough the north canyon you will find Crystalsong Forest.  It is a cursed and dangerous place, $r. Should that be your next destination, proceed with caution. $b$bTake this for your efforts, little one, and leave this conflicted land with my blessing.', 15595),
	(12081, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I know Kurun is glad for your help. The defeat of Thor Modan will be a great achievement for us, but it will not free our brothers.', 15595),
	(12082, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, yah survived a little adventure with our good friend, did yah?$b$bThat should be reward enough in itself, but here - I\'m feelin\' generous.', 15595),
	(12083, 6, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'re empowering their forces with it? That doesn\'t make any sense; the mage hunters aren\'t that powerful.$B$BThis must mean that they\'re only using the magic at the terminus of wherever they\'ve redirected the ley line to.$B$BWe\'re going to need more information if we\'re to have a chance at finding and stopping them!', 0),
	(12084, 6, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'re empowering their forces with it? That doesn\'t make any sense at all; the mage hunters aren\'t that powerful!$B$BThis must mean that they\'re only using the magic at the terminus of wherever they\'ve redirected the ley line to.$B$BWe\'re going to need more information if I\'m to devise a plan to stop them!', 15595),
	(12085, 11, 5, 25, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Ahahahaha... boo hoo, how touching.$B$B<The condescension in the overlord\'s deep-throated laughter is palpable.>$B$BWhat did I say? Traitors! Still, I knew Deino once upon a time. She at least is a troll with honor!$B$BI\'ll see to it that she finds out what happened to her brother. I\'ll even forget to tell her that you\'re the one that killed him.$B$B<Agmar fixes you with a calculated stare.>$B$BBut I own you now, $c!', 15595),
	(12086, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thassarian?  Yeah he was here... what of it?  We have more pressing problems right now, my friend.', 0),
	(12088, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Leryssa... is looking for me?  You must help me, $N.  We must finish this before she gets hurt.', 0),
	(12089, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He wasn\'t the first of those sissy spell casters to betray us, and he certainly won\'t be the last. Damned shame, too... He was one of our best mages. He\'d summon a buffet that would make your mouth water and your heart jump for joy...$B$BBAH!', 15595),
	(12090, 6, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You got that ugly son-of-a-horse, eh? Well that\'s one less nuisance our soldiers will have to deal with out in the frozen wastes.', 15595),
	(12091, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'About time someone put a stop to that filthy beast\'s killing spree! A job well done, $N.', 15595),
	(12092, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $r! We\'ve lost so much already. You\'ve ensured that we won\'t lose the most majestic of Northrend\'s children.$B$BI\'ll soon leave to speak with the ancients you saved and see if they will help us in our time of need.', 0),
	(12093, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Now, we must act swiftly, before the sons of iron realize that their runes have been rendered harmless.', 15595),
	(12094, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can detect the power you\'ve imbued in the shard and I hope it will be enough to break the runic magic.', 15595),
	(12095, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What make you tink dat you succeed where Rokhan fail?', 15595),
	(12096, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my thanks, $c.$B$BAs soon as I am done observing what these disgusting apothecaries are up to, I\'ll head to the woods and see if I can convince these ancients to side with us.$B$BOr, if nothing else, I\'ll convince them not to attack those that saved them!', 15595),
	(12097, 4, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'HA! You did it! The soldiers at the Wrathgate are indebted to you, $N! This\'ll surely buy a few of them another day above ground.', 15595),
	(12098, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You find the corpse of the mage hunter commander here.$B$BJudging by his appearance, and the condition of the forces around him, you would guess that they didn\'t drown. Rather, when they summoned the focus in, they didn\'t expect the elementals that arose from the rents in the lake bed to attack.$B$BIt would appear that the mage hunter forces were the architects of their own demise.', 0),
	(12099, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So it\'s an uncertain thing? I wish it was not a matter of chance, but at least we\'re on the right path. Without your help, this wouldn\'t have ever been possible. Should you learn any more about the machinations of the iron dwarves and their plans toward the children of stone, seek us out and we will hear you, $N.', 15595),
	(12100, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It pains me to put animals down, but it is a service that must be performed. Now we must move on to the next step: Inoculation.', 15595),
	(12101, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The oafish man-cow actually acquired a rot resistant organ? Curses... I was certain that task would keep his malformed mind occupied well into the next millennium.$B$BWell give it here, $g boy:girl;. I have much to do without your feeble needs getting in the way.', 15595),
	(12102, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That wasn\'t so difficult, now was it?$B$BNow give me a moment to prepare the vaccine.', 15595),
	(12104, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Soar holds the vial up to the sky and examines its contents.>$B$BOnly one thing left to do now.', 15595),
	(12105, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I imagined there would be more to this than just an isolated town of hostiles.$B$BWe have men near Hollowstone Mine, perhaps it would be in our interest to do a little research.', 15595),
	(12106, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You find the corpse of the mage hunter commander here.$B$BJudging by his appearance, and the condition of the forces around him, you would guess that they didn\'t drown. Rather, when they summoned the focus in, they didn\'t expect the elementals that arose from the rents in the lake bed to attack.$B$BIt would appear that the mage hunter forces were the architects of their own demise.', 15595),
	(12107, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'WHAT?!$B$B<The image before you distorts for a moment as the archmage attempts to regain her composure.>$B$BOf course, we should have guessed that this was what they were up to all along. Quickly, there\'s no time to waste.$B$BWyrmrest must be warned!', 0),
	(12109, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dumont sent you?  Very well.  Let\'s see what you can do for us.', 15595),
	(12110, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'WHAT?!$B$B<The image before you distorts for a moment as the archmage attempts to regain his composure.>$B$BOf course, we should have guessed that this was what they were up to all along. Quickly, there\'s no time to waste.$B$BWyrmrest must be warned!', 15595),
	(12111, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done an honorable thing, $N. Please, choose a reward.', 15595),
	(12112, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can think of some uses for you, go ahead and stay for a bit.', 15595),
	(12113, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Outstanding!$b$bNuthin\' better with a pint than a hot morsel of meat.', 15595),
	(12114, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thankyeh, $c.$b$bWhen time allows I\'ll git up and have meself a look around.', 15595),
	(12115, 396, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There are only two things in life that interest me, peon, and neither of them involve translating a Scourge tome for you.$B$BHowever... perhaps we could work something out that would benefit the both of us.$B$B<Koltira unsheathes his weapon.>$B$BThis is my runeblade, Byfrost. Byfrost thirsts for the blood of the Lich King and his minions, but first I must etch upon it runes of power: symbols of frost, blood, and unholy. Bring me suitable sources of power and I will translate your tome.', 15595),
	(12116, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Entrails? An interesting choice, $r.$b$bKraz shall see what is to be learned from them. Thank you for braving the depths of that place.', 15595),
	(12117, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s that you say, $r? Hotawa sent you?$B$BGood, good... there\'s much to do. We can use all of the help that we can get!', 15354),
	(12118, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s that you say, $r? Anuniaq sent you?$B$BGood, good... there\'s much to do. We can use all of the help that we can get!', 0),
	(12119, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A letter of introduction to meet with the queen? Let me see that.$B$BWhatever your business is, I hope that it\'s important.  The skies are full of attacking blues today!', 0),
	(12120, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well thus far, $n, but now comes the true test.', 15595),
	(12121, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your coming has been foretold, friend. It was good of you to come.', 15595),
	(12122, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A letter of introduction to meet with the queen? Let me see that.$B$BWhatever your business is, I hope that it\'s important.  The skies are full of attacking blues today!', 15595),
	(12123, 1, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are very courageous to bring us this information. I was beginning to wonder why the blue dragonflight had so boldly initiated an attack upon the temple itself. Now we know that they are using enormous amounts of the very magic they view as such a threat to Azeroth.$B$B<The queen shakes her head in seeming resignation.>$B$BHypocritical, but so be it. If Malygos will not come to his senses, we have no choice but to take action in response to their assault.', 0),
	(12124, 1, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 'You are very courageous to bring us this information. I was beginning to wonder why the blue dragonflight had so boldly initiated an attack upon the temple itself. Now we know that they are using enormous amounts of the very magic they view as such a threat to Azeroth.$B$B<The queen shakes her head in seeming resignation.>$B$BHypocritical, but so be it. If Malygos will not come to his senses, we have no choice but to take action in response to their assault.', 15595),
	(12125, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A simple task for a simpleton. You have performed within my expectations.', 15595),
	(12126, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Koltira\'s eyes widen.>$B$BImpressive. You bested a deathknight of Arthas... Clearly you were not alone... but still...', 15595),
	(12127, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can already feel the cold coursing through me, $N.', 15595),
	(12128, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm... you don\'t look like a research assistant, which is just as well. The iron dwarves look to be preparing for war, and my research team hasn\'t returned. We could use some help around here.', 15595),
	(12129, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You got all of them? Brilliant! I can\'t wait to see the looks on their faces when the golem\'s done.', 15595),
	(12130, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Raegar wipes his forehead with the back of his hand.>$B$BOh, no. This is going to be harder than I thought. These things don\'t have serial numbers or anything, do they?$B$BNever a gnome around when you need one...', 15595),
	(12131, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Raegar takes the batteries from you.>$B$BExcellent! We should be all ready to go.', 15595),
	(12132, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The power I hold comes at a great cost, $N. Many knights, light and dark alike, lost their lives in the final battle at Light\'s Hope. The prospect of the future looks grim, but at least now I know what I face. The Lich King will never release his grasp and for that alone he must die!', 15595),
	(12133, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found this inside the Headless Horseman\'s jack-o-lantern?  It is an old symbol of the Light.  If must have been the Horseman\'s, before he was cursed and turned into the monster he is today.  Thank you, $N.  This symbol deserves to be with paladins.  I will make sure they get it.$B$BOh, and I almost forgot!  You have a secret admirer...$B$BOne of the children wanted you to have this.  She was too shy to give it to you herself.', 0),
	(12134, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Killing these monsters won\'t bring my father back... but that\'s not the point now, is it?', 15595),
	(12135, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, thank you! May the Light bless your good works, kind $Gsir:lady;. The shadow of the Dark Horseman yet looms, but at least, for now, the village is safe from his flames.', 0),
	(12136, 1, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Gort takes the tome from you and begins reading.>$B$BWHAT! This can\'t be right. I\'ve known some of these orcs for years!$B$BLeave me, $N. I have much work to do and many traitors to execute.$B$BTake one of these items for your trouble. You\'ve done a great service for the Horde this day.', 15595),
	(12137, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well.$b$bPlease, sit and listen. There are many things we must discuss.', 15595),
	(12138, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Finally, it\'s ready. I only hope it holds together long enough to get the job done. If we don\'t take out the thane leading Dun Argol, Captain Gryan\'ll be in for a nasty surprise.', 15595),
	(12139, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The fires are out! You and your fire brigade were victorious! Hah!$B$BThe Headless Horseman\'s attack has failed, but until he and his head are destroyed together, he will return.$B$BUntil then, however, let\'s take comfort in the safety you brought our children. I am honored to have watched your brave work today.', 0),
	(12140, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the aid of such a powerful shaman, we are sure to be victorious at the Wrathgate!', 15595),
	(12141, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve come to my aid?  I thank you, $N.', 15595),
	(12142, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good riddance.', 13623),
	(12143, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Chilltusk, eh?  I\'ve heard his name before.  That\'s some good work, $c.  Hopefully we can turn our attention back to the dragon menace now.  ', 13623),
	(12144, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good riddance, mon.', 15595),
	(12145, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Icefist, eh?  I\'ve heard his name before.  Dat\'s some good work, mon.  Hopefully we Darkspear can turn our attention back to dat dragon menace now.  ', 15595),
	(12146, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is indeed strange for any magnataur to carry an item such as this... and very concerning. I am glad that you have shown this to me. ', 13623),
	(12147, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is indeed strange for any magnataur to carry an item such as this... and very concerning. I am glad that you have shown this to me.', 15595),
	(12148, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So it is true. They could not have chosen better timing for such an attack... between the Scourge and the blue flight, it is unlikely that anyone else has noticed yet.', 15595),
	(12149, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work. No one could tell me who this leader might be, but I was able to uncover the name of someone who will have our answer.', 15595),
	(12150, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Grom\'thar the Thunderbringer. Good. Let\'s end any threat these magnataur might pose here and now.', 15595),
	(12151, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are formidable indeed.$B$BWith Grom\'thar the Thunderbringer gone, we can leave the remaining magnataur to fight among themselves and turn our attentions back towards more prominent threats.$B$BImpressive work, $c. ', 15595),
	(12152, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'It is done.$b$bYour selflessness has brought eternal peace to many souls, ending eons of misery.$b$bMay this act lighten your own soul and lessen your burdens, for I see that there are yet many perils you must face.$b$bFarewell, $n.', 15595),
	(12153, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It worked?$B$B<Raegar clears his throat.>$B$BI mean... of course it worked! This is incredible!$B$BYears from now, Explorers\' League initiates will hear the story of how Raegar Breakbrow, $N, and some hunk o\' junk golem defeated the thane of Dun Argol!', 15595),
	(12154, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Raegar nods approvingly.>$B$BI can\'t stand to see explosives go to waste and it\'ll set our enemies back for sure.', 15595),
	(12155, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found this inside the Headless Horseman\'s jack-o-lantern?  It is an old symbol of the Light.  If must have been the Horseman\'s, before he was cursed and turned into the monster he is today.  Thank you, $N.  This symbol deserves to be with paladins.  I will make sure they get it.$B$BOh, and I almost forgot!  You have a secret admirer...$B$BOne of the children wanted you to have this.  She was too shy to give it to you herself.', 0),
	(12157, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As I crossed the bridge into Dragonblight a small group of Anub\'ar ambushed me! I was surrounded! Those monsters knew I was coming. I barely made it out of there with my flesh intact. This list I hold must be taken to Wintergarde Keep, but I am too badly injured to make the journey.', 0),
	(12158, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve come to help me, haven\'t you!', 15595),
	(12159, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rest in peace friends!  Do not worry -- I will tell everyone that we never gave up!', 15595),
	(12160, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Curse our luck.  We find the one functioning mine this side of the hills and it\'s full of Scourge.$B$BNo offense, friend.  But that survivor you found sounds like he\'s been a little traumatized due to losing his friends.  Arugal\'s been dead for years... I even saw his grave once.', 15595),
	(12161, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You seek knowledge beyond your reach so you\'ve come to me.  I must warn you, stranger, the answers I provide might not be to your liking.', 15595),
	(12164, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We got him good, $N.  But not good enough.$B$BOne thing\'s for sure... we won\'t be seeing him around these parts any longer.', 15595),
	(12165, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So Tormak\'s going to go ahead with the plan? I suppose he wouldn\'t have sent you if he didn\'t.$B$BOh, bother... Now how am I going to figure out how to put this together under all this pressure?', 15595),
	(12166, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have done what we can for the creatures of the land. Now we must take direct action against those that have caused this!', 0),
	(12167, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done.$B$BI will dispose of these filthy garments by cleansing them in the moonwell and destroying them through the power of the goddess!', 0),
	(12168, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, the leader of the cultists has revealed himself. We have a name.$B$BVanity and pride will be his downfall!', 0),
	(12169, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the high cultist destroyed, the rest of his forces can be mopped up and the land and its creatures will recover.$B$BThank you, $N. May the goddess illuminate your path.', 0),
	(12170, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N. Our control over the logging camp might not be complete yet, but thanks to you we\'re one step closer to smashing these Alliance worms.', 0),
	(12171, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Palena reads the note.>$B$BYou will take my fastest hippogryph, $r! This information must be delivered to High Commander Wyrmbane at once!', 0),
	(12172, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well. If you are ready, then so am I.', 0),
	(12173, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well. If you think you are ready, then let\'s not waste anymore of my time.', 0),
	(12174, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The High Commander reads the missive and then crumples it up.>$B$BDo you know where the people on this list are now? Take a look outside, near the front gate. They\'re the ones hanging from the arches.$B$BGhoul bait...', 0),
	(12175, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re a life saver, $Gbrother:sister;. If you\'re interested in more work, there\'s more where that came from.', 0),
	(12176, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m in your debt, mon.  Take this as payment.', 15595),
	(12177, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hope for the best, mon.', 15595),
	(12178, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just who do you take me for?  These hides smell of flour!$B$BThis is a complete insult to the Horde!', 15595),
	(12180, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Mountaineer Kilian listens as you relate what the captive prospectors told you.>$B$BThey mentioned Loken and a war against stone giants? You\'re certain?$B$BSo Raegar\'s instincts were right. We have to find a way to get in there and learn more about their plans.', 15595),
	(12181, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Uh, yea, you can go ahead and hold on to that vial, friend. I trust you.', 0),
	(12182, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh joyous day! And look, just beyond the mountain to the northeast creeps a whole field of Scourge for us to obliterate!', 0),
	(12183, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kilian takes the uniform from you.>$B$BThis should do. I won\'t have time to sew on a little patch with \'$N\' embroidered on it or anything, but anyone looking closely at you should be convinced that you\'re an overseer by the time we\'re done with you.', 15595),
	(12184, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, these should do. Now, to create a kit to pass you off as a convincing iron dwarf.', 15595),
	(12185, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Could it be that Loken isn\'t really exaggerating? The titans\' stone and iron sons fighting against each other for control of the ancient city of Ulduar. This is madness, $N and it could destroy our only chance to learn the true history of dwarvenkind!', 15595),
	(12188, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will do nicely, $N. Did those pathetic whelps put up a fight or did they just shower you with ghostly tears of sorrow?$B$BAh, they get so emotional...', 0),
	(12189, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We ran into a little - MINOR - problem. Everyone that tried handling the blight vaporized. We\'re working on adjusting the formula a tad so it doesn\'t instantly kill you for looking at it sideways. The good news is that I think I\'ve almost got it!', 0),
	(12190, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well now! Good ol\' Prigmon sent ya did he?$b$bThis should make fer some mighty fine eatin\'. Needs just a couple things...', 15595),
	(12191, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow...  S.T.O.U.T. didn\'t break... Hmm... Who would have guessed?$b$bI mean, hey, you did it!  Your aim is true, or at least true enough to help guard the camp.  I think you\'re ready now to take on the Dark Irons if they show up again.', 0),
	(12192, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you managed to stop the Dark Irons... While drunk too? That, $c, is truly the spirit of Brewfest! I guess in keeping with the spirit of Brewfest you want your prize tokens.$B$BThanks for your help, $N. Enjoy the rest of Brewfest.', 0),
	(12193, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aww, it\'s just a stein voucher... Maybe you\'re just playing hard to get. So here\'s this year\'s stein for you.$b$bBut I suspect I\'ll be seeing a lot more of you. After all, if you want any Brewfest tokens redeemed, I\'m your girl...$b$bOr maybe I\'m his girl...$b$bOooohhh... or his...', 0),
	(12194, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s this? A stein voucher? So you like drinking? Great! After I give you this stein, go have a few drinks! Then a few more. Maybe have a few more after that... Then, now this is important, come see me.$b$bLook, I know you\'ll be back eventually. If you want your Brewfest tokens redeemed you have to see me.$b$bAnyways, here\'s the stein, and remember to talk to me later.', 0),
	(12195, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These should serve. Now, let\'s see if it works.', 0),
	(12196, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Rokar wipes his forehead with the back of his hand.>$B$BOh, thank the Light. He was threatening not to feed me until you returned. Let\'s sort through this pile of parts and see what we can make.', 15595),
	(12197, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Rokar takes the batteries from you.>$B$BThese are low, but they\'ll be enough to start up the golem. He\'s nowhere near ready for battle, though.', 15595),
	(12198, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, now Tormak can\'t complain anymore. This baby\'s as ready as I can make it.$B$BAfter you tear your way through Dun Argol with it, that overgrown cow\'ll have to release me.', 15595),
	(12199, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So the prospector made good on his promises? Good. I was beginning to wonder if all of this scrounging for bits of metal and stealing building materials would amount to anything.$B$BIt\'s a shame he\'s of no further use to us.', 15595),
	(12200, 1, 1, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I do believe that the blight is now ready for a field test. Fortuitously, the dread citadel, Naxxramas, is laying siege to Wintergarde Keep. From beneath the very earth that Wintergarde was built upon rise the living dead, eager to do the bidding of Kel\'Thuzad.$B$BThe Alliance are, of course, outmanned and outgunned. The people laid to rest in the Wintergarde Mausoleum awaken, hungering for flesh!$B$BPerhaps we shall give them a taste of the blight, yes?', 15595),
	(12201, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This should work, but there\'s still the matter of the rest of your disguise. Even those dimwitted metal dwarves will recognize an impostor with a stolen suit.', 15595),
	(12202, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These should serve. By Garrosh, these creatures are ugly.', 15595),
	(12203, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So he means to foment civil war between the factions of the titans\' creation? Why does this titan city of Ulduar mean so much to him? I suppose this is what Kurun and his giants are hoping to prevent.$B$BWell, I doubt we\'re in a position to keep the giants from fighting each other, but we can find a way to use this to our advantage. I must inform our leaders at once.', 15595),
	(12204, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So he is the mastermind behind the iron dwarves? We must find out what he has been ordering the iron dwarves of Dun Argol to do.', 15595),
	(12205, 1, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well done, $r. I trust that you were cleverly vicious in your slaying?$B$BLet\'s see, how much I can offer you from the coffins... er, excuse me, coffers?', 15595),
	(12206, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'WHAT?! That\'s impossible! We\'ve perfected the blight. It has a one-hundred percent lethality.$B$B<The apothecary wrings her hands, concern crossing her unliving visage. Clearly frustrated, she continues in an angry tone.>$B$BThis is just really odd. Hand me that flask, $c. I\'m not going to be known as the apothecary that ruined everything!', 0),
	(12207, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This slime is foul with a darkness far more ancient than their worldly forms would indicate. The land itself has a memory of this evil for as long as it has existed.$B$BWe must find out more, $N.', 0),
	(12208, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here to get in on the bounty action, eh?', 0),
	(12209, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You do not smell so fresh now, new meat.$B$BVery well, all of this will do. By what name might I call you, $c?', 15595),
	(12210, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here to get in on the bounty action, eh?', 15595),
	(12211, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh good! For a moment I thought I was going to have to test the rats out on someone to make sure that they weren\'t defective.$B$BProgress, finally!', 15595),
	(12212, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are some choice pieces of meat!  ', 15595),
	(12213, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This orb... it has been tainted by... a purely evil force.$B$BWhatever else I might learn from studying this energy, one thing is certain. I must destroy this orb as soon as possible. Its corrupting force is just too strong.', 0),
	(12214, 1, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, nothing makes me happier than a job well done.$B$BYou\'ve done Venomspite a great service in acquiring these horses, $c.', 15595),
	(12215, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $c.$b$bThis should help ensure that the wildlife in these parts ends up where it should - roasting over our fires.', 15595),
	(12216, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Outstanding!$b$bOur stores are nearly replenished now. You\'ve done your part, $n.', 15595),
	(12217, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A somber task, I know. But we can rest easier now knowing the enemy\'s eyes are no longer upon us.', 15595),
	(12218, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As much as it irritates me that we may have assisted the Alliance, I declare the field test a success! Next stop: Agmar\'s Hammer!', 15595),
	(12219, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The slime is not natural, $N.  Its very nature is corrupt and... evil.$B$BWe must find out more.', 15595),
	(12220, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The energy in the orb is... overpowering...$B$BA dark force has tainted the ground near Vordrassil\'s remains.  We will need to investigate more.', 15595),
	(12221, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Doctor Malefious looks through the contents of the package.>$B$BGlorious! Exactly to specifications!$B$BHere is your payment, $N. Keep what you\'ve seen and done to yourself. This work is all classified - information is given out on a need to know basis.', 15595),
	(12222, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the talismans in hand, the drake will have no choice but to obey you. I can\'t wait to see the look on the thane\'s face when he realizes you\'ve commandeered his proto-drake.', 15595),
	(12223, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N. Now, we must follow through and press the advantage.', 15595),
	(12224, 66, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lok\'tar ogar! I have heard much about you, $N. Your battle scars run deep - a testament to your dedication and power!$B$BWith the flanking attacks of the Lich King crushed in both the west and east, only the forces at the gate remain. We gain ground each day, soon to break through this wall and into Icecrown!$B$BOnce we stop the skeletal dragons, Highlord Fordragon and I will take the field.', 15595),
	(12225, 5, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did what!!!$b$bThose were Amberseeds! And that was an entire harvest\'s worth!$b$bThose magical seeds may have been the answer to our food crisis. Believe me when I tell you, $n, you\'re going to make this right!', 15595),
	(12226, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These should do just fine...$b$b<Anderhol deftly twists the stalks, collecting their slick fluids in a tiny vial.>$b$bThere we go, now it\'s time to get down to business.', 15595),
	(12227, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, $n? Everything come out okay?$b$bHmm, looks like we caught \'em just in time....', 15595),
	(12229, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This blood carries the same taint as the slime you obtained earlier... this does not bode well, $N.', 0),
	(12230, 6, 1, 11, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<The deathguard rubs his hands together in anticipation.>$B$BExcellent. Their loss is my... our gain!$B$BYou didn\'t have trouble with any of these along the way? Some of them look rather unstable. I may be undead, but I value my existence!', 15595),
	(12231, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ursoc\'s children are wise. Their words explain much of what we\'ve seen so far.', 0),
	(12232, 4, 1, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh happy day!$B$BBy not using the time and resources of the apothecaries to get the job done, I\'m sure to attract the attention of the high executor!$B$BThinking outside the box, that\'s what I\'m all about. Yes, yes, you had a hand in helping too.$B$BHere, if I give you something will you promise to not mention your part in all of this?', 15595),
	(12234, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, what are you waiting for, $r? Hand them over!', 15595),
	(12235, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Urik points to a gryphon.>$B$BHave you ever ridden one of those? It\'s simple, friend. Just hop on and tell it where to go.\n', 0),
	(12236, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The druid looks pale and her eyes stare blankly past you.  She has left a package in anticipation of your return.>', 15595),
	(12237, 71, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Outstanding work, $N! We can get this keep back into working order now with the return of our citizens.', 13623),
	(12238, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We done a great thing, mon! And dis just be da beginning....$B$BSeek me out in Zul\'Drak when da time be right.$B$BDere be a war to be won, mon!', 0),
	(12239, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'You have word from the spy mistress?$B$B<The agent looks around to make sure that no one is watching as she puts down her shovel.>$B$BLet me see those plans.', 15595),
	(12240, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew my sister wouldn\'t let us down.$B$BWell done, $N. The Onslaught\'s lumbermill will be out of commission for a while, which means no new construction or ballistae.$B$BThanks for helping me to live up to the family name.', 15595),
	(12241, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t make any promises, $N.  But I will try my best to purify these.', 15595),
	(12242, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N.  I\'ll take those from you.$B$BThe corruptive power of these seeds is dangerous.  I must destroy them right away.', 15595),
	(12243, 11, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahhahahahahahahahaha!$B$BWithout their rutters, they\'ve got nowhere to run to now.$B$BLooks to me like the end of the Scarlet Onslaught, and just when they were getting started. How sad.$B$BHeh.', 15595),
	(12244, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Synipus whistles.>$b$bOh, she\'s a beauty! We\'ll fix her up nice.$b$bIf you\'re short on things to do, go talk to Gordun and get a ride down to Venture Bay. They\'re sure to need a hand.$b$bOh, and while you\'re there, use these keys on a Refurbished Shredder. Wait \'til ya see what these babies can do when they\'re cleaned up!', 15595),
	(12245, 6, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What? You were expecting us to have you rescue them?$B$BNow why would we do that when they have a proven track record of getting themselves captured in the first place?$B$BNorthrend is a cold place, young $N. I suggest that you adjust to it.', 15595),
	(12246, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The corruption present in this blood is identical to that of the slime.  I don\'t have a good feeling about this.', 15595),
	(12247, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ursoc\'s children are wise.  Their words explain much of what we\'ve seen so far.', 15595),
	(12248, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes!  Vordrassil\'s magic is still present in these ashes.  There might be hope for Ursoc yet.', 15595),
	(12249, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The druid looks pale and her eyes stare blankly past you. She has left a package in anticipation of your return.>', 0),
	(12250, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N.  I\'ll take those from you.$B$BThe corruptive power of these seeds is dangerous.  I must destroy them right away.', 15595),
	(12251, 66, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Halford salutes.>$B$BThe townsfolk are all back to work? Already? Outstanding, soldier! We\'ll get this town built back up and fortified in no time. Before long, reinforcements will be ready to join the fight with Lord Fordragon at the Wrathgate.$B$BI\'m getting ahead of myself, of course, as there is much left to do here before we can even think about sending you to the aid of Bolvar.\n', 13623),
	(12252, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'They knew all of that? And who the hell is this Grand Admiral Westwind that he spoke of?!$B$B<The high executor grumbles to himself about hating surprises.>$B$BBetter that we know than have to guess. I hope that you left your... er, my mark.', 15595),
	(12253, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Halford says a prayer for the deceased.>$B$BYou do the Light\'s work, $N.$B$BI fear that our work has only just begun.$B$B<Halford holds up a document.>', 13623),
	(12254, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'A newly scribed blessing at the back of the book you say?$B$B<The agent glances over your shoulder as you flip to the page at the end.>$B$BDamn it all! That\'s the high abbot\'s handwriting! I\'d stake your life on it.', 15595),
	(12255, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $N. I doubt any of the woodsmen would\'ve wanted to take a crack at the proto-drake, but we couldn\'t afford to let the Dragonflayers build a base of power in Grizzly Hills. If only the Horde was so easily dealt with...', 15595),
	(12256, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the power of the talismans, the drake has no choice but to obey your commands. The thane\'s fate is sealed.', 15595),
	(12257, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done exactly as I asked. We\'ve got the Dragonflayers on the defensive and it\'ll soon be time to deal with their leader.', 15595),
	(12258, 1, 1, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps now they will rest easy, their spirits free to ascend to the Light.$B$BMy thoughts and prayers now turn to Lord Fordragon and our forces at the Wrathgate. We must persevere here, if only to buy them enough time to defeat the Lich King. Wintergarde cannot fall.', 13623),
	(12259, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The few remaining Dragonflayers dare not challenge us after your battle with the thane. Show no mercy to our enemies - that is the way of the Horde.', 15595),
	(12260, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad, $c. Now that the priest\'s image is trapped within the mirror, I have something else that needs doing.', 15595),
	(12261, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. When they begin to flee in fear, the ward shall be there to wish them a fond farewell.', 15595),
	(12262, 11, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 0, 'Did they beg for their miserable lives? Weaklings.', 15595),
	(12263, 1, 0, 0, 0, 120, 0, 0, 0, 'We are the Black Dragonflight. We have rained destruction on the lands of Azeroth for thousands of years. The decrepit Cult of the Damned worships death and we shall be glad to oblige.', 15595),
	(12264, 6, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 0, 'Hearing their screams... watching the last life fade from their wretched bodies... it\'s invigorating, is it not?$B$BI relish it.', 15595),
	(12265, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. There is more to be done.', 15595),
	(12266, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, it\'s you.$B$BI had hoped Serinar would simply return himself once the task was done... I suppose he\'s distracted by something or another to kill. He\'s missing out on a gloriously messy battle!$B$BAre you still here? I\'m done with you.', 15595),
	(12267, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The bones of my brood have been spared this filth. You have served me well, and as such, you shall be awarded appropriately.', 15595),
	(12268, 273, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes indeed. These should do the trick...$b$bThere. One more shredder ready for the fight. Thanks, $n.', 15595),
	(12269, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Leoric takes the cards from you.>$B$BI will get these to our recorder and deliver the grim news to the families of the miners.$B$BThere is still much to be done if we are to succeed here and ultimately at the Wrathgate. Lord Fordragon is depending on us.', 13623),
	(12270, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, soldier!$B$BNow take this key and get yourself down to Venture Bay. It\'ll let you use one of the refurbished shredders to unleash chaos on our enemies.$B$BOh yes, and talk to Darrok if you want to take the shortcut!', 0),
	(12271, 6, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 'LeCraft had it you say? That makes sense.$B$BI recognize it from my youthful days as a torturer in the court of King Terenas of fallen Lordaeron. It\'s known as a rod of compulsion.$B$B<The high executor wrings his hands together in evil anticipation of what\'s to come.>$B$BI have an idea for how we can make good use of it!', 15595),
	(12272, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This might be the moment, the very second, that the tide turns against the Scourge. You have proven yourself as a hero of the Alliance, at least in my eyes, $N.$B$BNow if you would be so kind as to give me some space. I will require additional time to study this ore in order to isolate impurities and weakness.$B$BCarry on, ally. I will contact you once I have an update.', 13623),
	(12273, 4, 1, 25, 1, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<You think you see just the hint of a smile cross Wroth\'s face before quickly disappearing.>$B$BYou\'re now my favorite $c, $N. If you have a mind to, I\'d like you to think about joining up as an officer in the Hand of Vengeance.$B$BWe can start you out as a deathguard, and in a few decades I think you have what it takes to make junior executor!$B$BNo? Well don\'t be too hasty... take your time and mull it over.', 15595),
	(12274, 5, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 'What the hell is going on here?!$B$BHe jumped on his own? You\'re certain that you didn\'t push him?$B$B<The agent narrows her eyes at you.>$B$BFine. Clearly there\'s much more going on in this place than we first thought. ', 15595),
	(12275, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I feel terrible about this, friend. I fear that in my haste to recover the strange ore from Wintergarde Mine I may have doomed agent Slinkin.\n', 13623),
	(12276, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<There is a note in Slinkin\'s death grip.>$B$BChased into a dead end. Hidden for now, but they know I\'m here. It won\'t be long until they find me.$B$BThe miners work tirelessly to unearth the strange ore that fuels the Scourge war machines. There is much banter. The language of death confounds me, but I have been able to identify commonly uttered sounds and phrases. The word "Yogg-Saron" is said with great contempt and is usually followed by loud outbursts. They refer to the ore as "saronite." Meaning?', 13623),
	(12277, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'His death will not have been in vain, friend. The information that Slinkin died for will be instrumental in defeating the Lich King. I promise you that we will make this right.', 13623),
	(12278, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your paperwork looks to be in order. Welcome to the club, $N!$B$BYou can expect to get our mail at the start of every month. If you like what you got, stop by and we can sell you some more. This is the club that keeps on giving.', 0),
	(12279, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You! You\'re not Limpy Joe!', 15595),
	(12280, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks, $N. That should keep me going - at least until tomorrow....$B$BHere\'s the cash I promised.', 0),
	(12281, 1, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Halford opens the package and reads the analysis.>$B$BI am by no means a scientist, $N, so you\'ll have to forgive my plebian understanding of what has been written. Now, according to this analysis - assuming I have the brain power of at least an adolescent school boy - we still don\'t know jack squat about the Scourge war machine. The only thing we do know is that the Scourge uses this foul metal to craft its siege engines, armor and weaponry.$B$B<Halford lets loose a long sigh.>', 13623),
	(12282, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N. As fate foretold, you will be the one to carry us through these hard times. Now the long journey begins.', 13623),
	(12283, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Damn it all! Why couldn\'t you have come to me with good news?!', 15595),
	(12284, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fifteen down, eh? Good to hear it, $c.$B$BIf nothing else you\'ve bought us a bit of time - at least a day by my figuring.$B$BHere\'s your pay.', 0),
	(12285, 11, 1, 4, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Let\'s see them bring her back to life without her head!$B$B<The high executor\'s laugh draws a number of furtive glances.>$B$BI\'m a little concerned that you let this grand admiral get away, but you\'re still the $g hero : heroine; of the day, $N!$B$BTake your pick... you\'ve earned it!', 15595),
	(12286, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 0),
	(12287, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Zelig sent word, friend. We have been expecting you.$B$BI am Orik Trueheart, paladin of the Argent Crusade. The priestess standing across the campfire from me is Tilda Darathan. We are here on behalf of the Argent Crusade - sent to quell the unfortunate damned souls attempting to escape Wintergarde.', 13623),
	(12288, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, thank you, thank you.$B$BYou\'ve helped us to live another day. Perhaps there\'s hope yet.', 0),
	(12289, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n.$b$bYou\'ve bought us some time here, though likely no more than a day. Nevertheless, the Alliance is grateful for your efforts.', 15595),
	(12290, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Orik takes the murkweed and begins mixing an elixir.>$B$BIt won\'t be much longer, $N.', 13623),
	(12291, 1, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Orik\'s eyes fill with tears.>$B$BThey don\'t know. None of them know! They think Arthas to be some great hero, when in truth it was Arthas who ordered the ships to be burned. It was Arthas who left us all for dead in this frozen wasteland!$B$B<Orik weeps.>$B$BNot all of the soldiers from the Prince\'s fleet perished in the freezing winter. I was only a lad when I was given the chance to battle the Scourge... to save our home from certain destruction. I took that chance, $N.', 13623),
	(12292, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s locked, isn\'t it?  It looks pretty ordinary.$B$B<Lieutenant Dumont Shakes the chest, producing a rattling wooden sound.>$B$BNo matter, I suppose.  If this gets us the edge we need against the Horde, then I could care less if the cure for the Plague was in there. ', 15595),
	(12293, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it!  You recovered the Sc... you recovered the chest that the Horde stole from us.  We thank you, $N.', 15595),
	(12294, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent news, $N.  With the locals\' help we\'ll have the logistical support we need to outmaneuver the Horde in this region.$B$BI have further tasks for you if you\'re interested.', 15595),
	(12295, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to finally meet you, $N!  We\'d heard about you up here.  Welcome to Silverbrook.$B$BThese trappers are a great bunch of lads and lasses.  Hardy people, they know the lay of the land really well.  You\'ll find it\'s a great thing that we finally won them over to our side.', 15595),
	(12296, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful!$b$bThe Alliance shall live to see another day, in part due to your diligence.$b$bPlease accept my thanks, friend.', 15595),
	(12297, 5, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 0, '<Greer lifts his glasses onto the top of his head and reads the note, looking back up at you curiously when he\'s done.>$B$BYou will have my fastest gryphon! This information must be delivered to High Commander Wyrmbane at once!\n', 15595),
	(12298, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The High Commander reads the missive and then crumples it up.>$B$BDo you know where the people on this list are now? Take a look outside, near the front gate. They\'re the ones hanging from the arches.$B$BGhoul bait...\n', 0),
	(12299, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad, not bad.  You might not be as soft as some of the others.', 15595),
	(12300, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t do it, $N.  The people that sent you here.... you shouldn\'t trust them.', 15595),
	(12301, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Orik beams a smile at you.>$B$BYou did a good thing this day, $N. Hundreds of lost souls are now redeemed, thanks to you.', 13623),
	(12302, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Who\'s there?  Are you here to kill me?$B$BPlease!  You don\'t have to do this!', 15595),
	(12303, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The quartermaster gasps, but then his eyes narrow as he studies you for a moment.>$B$BI trust that you didn\'t stash any of this on the side for yourself? You wouldn\'t be that selfish when the fate of Venomspite is at stake?$B$BBesides, I\'m going to reward you with a percentage of the take. It\'s not much, but in times like this, we all have to make sacrifices.', 0),
	(12304, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Can\'t you just see it now, $c? It\'ll be the vacation spot of Northrend!$B$BWhat do you think of the name, "Hansen\'s Cove", or maybe "$N Bay"? Kind of catchy, don\'t you think?', 15595),
	(12305, 1, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Zelig smiles.>$B$BIt is I who owe you a debt of gratitude, hero. Orik is like a brother to me. You have changed his life and given renewed hope to countless others.', 13623),
	(12306, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you be joinin\' our ranks, $N? We treat ya nice here. You only get the best when you part of dis club!$B$BWe be sendin\' out brew to you at da start of every month. If you like what you got, and you be wantin\' more, head back over here. We make sure you get more of da brew you like.', 0),
	(12307, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Katja reels away from you nervously.>$B$BThank you, $N.  You didn\'t get any wolfsbane on you, did you?  I\'ve got these... allergies that act up once in a while.', 15595),
	(12308, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Worgen.  Blasted, Light-forsaken, filth-ridden worgen.$B$BIt\'s time we showed the locals what us civilized folk do with beasts like them.', 15595),
	(12309, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh brother, it\'s a mess down there! I barely made it out last time - which is what prompted my request to the High Commander.$B$B<Durkon looks you up and down.>$B$BYou got that crazy look in your eyes, $r. Thankfully, you\'re gonna need to be crazy to do what I\'m about to ask of you.', 13623),
	(12310, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s a shame those trappers turned out to be... afflicted.  We sure could\'ve used a few more fighting men.$B$BMay the poor souls rest in peace.', 15595),
	(12311, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now if we could stop the Scourge attacks coming from outside the keep we might be able to send help to Lord Fordragon at the Wrathgate.', 13623),
	(12312, 1, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Whatever information is held in this book must be of great importance! I could hear the howls and wails echoing through the crypt as you made your escape!$B$BThe High Commander must be notified!', 13623),
	(12314, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N! Without their leader, the Horde is weak and disorganized. I will order our men forward.', 0),
	(12315, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a true soldier of the Horde, $N. Your bravery will inspire my men to victory!', 0),
	(12316, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your bravery has inspired the men of the Westfall Brigade. Even now they fight with greater ferocity. The port will soon be ours.', 0),
	(12317, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The port will soon fall to us. You have done well this day, $N.', 0),
	(12318, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re from the Brewfest camp? Glory day! Brewfest may yet be saved.$B$B$N, Coren Direbrew must be stopped! We cannot let him sabotage our sacred holiday. Our brews must flow!', 0),
	(12319, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Halford\'s eyes widen.>$B$BThe fates smile down upon us on this day, $N. I know just the person to see about this tome.', 13623),
	(12320, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps, with proper motivation, Godfrey will tell us what he knows about the tome.$B$B<Hallard turns to Mayor Godfrey.>$B$BIsn\'t that right, mayor?', 13623),
	(12321, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We should have known about the damned mausoleum. This is preposterous! Duke August Foehammer and Ambo Cash will be dispatched to the front lines in preparation for our next assault.$B$BOnce you have cleared the mines I will send you to Foehammer so that we may begin our attack against the Scourge of Naxxramas!$B$BThe information you have garnered thus far will be sent to Lord Fordragon at the Wrathgate upon the wings of our most able gryphon!', 13623),
	(12323, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, soldier! Now the rest of the men can focus their efforts on the Horde.', 0),
	(12324, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The general will be pleased that you\'ve dealt with the Venture Company problem. Now, the men can focus on beating back the Alliance.', 0),
	(12325, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, the distinguished hero arrives. Welcome to ground zero, $N. Allow me to bring you up to speed!$B$BThel\'zan\'s most powerful forces have made their way into the Wintergarde Mausoleum. They plumb its depths in search of corpses and souls to send against Wintergarde while Naxxramas rains down terrible Scourge plague machines, set to hold us at bay!$B$BWe must strike now and hope that Lord Fordragon is able to hold out at the Wrathgate for just a little longer.\n', 13623),
	(12326, 274, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why I\'m not wearing any pants isn\'t important. Let\'s just say I took some Scourge shrapnel in the wrong place and leave it at that, ok?$B$BSo you wiped out those plague wagons up in the fields and got my soldiers here in one piece. Impressive. You\'re one of the first to make it this far, friend. Too bad you gotta go right back out into the Carrion Fields. Yep, we\'ve had a bit of a setback.\n', 13623),
	(12327, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you learn anything from your vision?  You mentioned Solstice Village during your trance -- which marks the second time someone has spoken the place\'s name today.', 15595),
	(12328, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good.  These will do just fine.$B$BI will have the potion ready for you in no time at all.', 15595),
	(12329, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was wondering when you\'d turn up.  Think you can give me a hand here?', 15595),
	(12330, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That... that was close.$B$BWe need to save Anya.  Now!', 15595),
