	(12411, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t want to be here anymore.  The worgen-men are mean.', 15595),
	(12412, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re back.  And you\'re alive.$B$BNow what\'s this nonsense about worgen?', 15595),
	(12413, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad, $N.  You might be slightly more useful than I initially thought.', 15595),
	(12414, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow! These sure are good horses! I think the Cap\'n will be real pleased with our work.', 15595),
	(12415, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Soulok nods in approval.>$B$BWell done, $N. We must not let the Alliance gain any kind of advantage.', 15595),
	(12416, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is a disgusting task, but I thank you dearly for doing it.$B$BThe Scourge cannot be permitted to push any further towards Wyrmrest or we are sure to lose it.', 0),
	(12417, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'In the earth, my brothers can grant life anew. You have saved them from a fate far worse than death.$B$BI don\'t know a word in your tongue that could express how much this means to my kind. Thank you, $r.', 0),
	(12418, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dahlia... they turned her?$B$BDahlia has been loyal to us for a very long time... if they can corrupt a being of her devotion, it does not bode well for the rest of the young races. Thank you for freeing her. I hope she has found some peace.$B$BYou have honored us with your selfless assistance today, $r. I will send word to the council of what your kind have accomplished here. Go with our blessing.', 0),
	(12419, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Dahlia was taken by the Scourge? This is a sad day for all of us.$B$BI will look to finding a new keeper once the shrine is retaken. Thank you for your efforts... the Ruby Dragonshrine is a sacred place to us, and the sacrifices your kind have made will not be easily forgotten.$B$BIt is good to know there are still heroes such as you - I will call upon you one day. Until that day comes, may your adventures be fruitful.', 15595),
	(12420, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your paperwork looks to be in order. Welcome to the club, $N!$B$BYou can expect to get our mail at the start of every month. If you like what you got, stop by and we can sell you some more. This is the club that keeps on giving.', 0),
	(12421, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you be joinin\' our ranks, $n?  We treat ya nice here.  You only get the best when you part of dis club!$b$bWe be sendin\' out brew to you at da start of every month.  If you like what you got, and you be wantin\' more, head back over here.  We make sure you get more of da brew you like.', 0),
	(12422, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re going to let me go... just like that?  Listen, I don\'t want any trouble with you... these monsters killed my father and took my sister.  I have other things on my mind right now.', 15595),
	(12423, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah!  Is this some sort of joke?$B$BI barely have any use for books I can actually understand.', 15595),
	(12424, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Could it be?  The man who wrote this journal feared for his daughters\' lives so he sent them away from Silverbrook.$B$BWe just captured an outcast in the outskirts of town about the same age as the eldest daughter.$B$BListen, $N.  There\'s more happening here than meets the eye... we can\'t just burn this diary.', 15595),
	(12425, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You seek knowledge beyond your reach so you\'ve come to me. I must warn you, stranger, the answers I provide might not be to your liking.', 0),
	(12427, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work, mon!  Here\'s your cut.', 15595),
	(12428, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those were some sharp moves, friend!  Lots of bets against you, which is good news cash-wise!', 15595),
	(12429, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My heart nearly skipped a beat there!  Thought that mound of metal was gonna get ya, mon!', 15595),
	(12430, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fancy footwork, fancy footwork.  You really made quick work of that crazy orc, friend.$B$BOdds were against you seven-to-one; made some nice coin on that one!', 15595),
	(12431, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What happened today... had to happen.  It doesn\'t mean I have to be happy about it.$B$BI\'ve freed my people from a tyrant, but I\'ve also lost a sister.  I thank you for your help, $N.  I wish to be alone now.', 15595),
	(12432, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha hah! What a ride, eh $c?$B$BIf we can\'t control the resources here, then no one can!$B$BWhen will those puny Alliance pests realize that they are no match for the might of the Horde?', 0),
	(12433, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh yes. That\'ll save me hours.$b$bTake this for your trouble, friend. And keep an eye out for more element 115. I\'ll take all you can find.', 15595),
	(12435, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You must be $N. The queen informed me that you would be coming.$B$BIf you are willing, we are in great need of your assistance.', 15595),
	(12436, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice job, $N. These will feed two or three grunts each. Not bad.', 0),
	(12437, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see that you survived that impact. Quite the explosion!$B$BWe can\'t afford for the Horde to make off with all that lumber.$B$BWell done, $c.', 0),
	(12438, 1, 1, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N. I will notify Illusia that a hero has heard her call for help and risen to meet the challenge! Here is your reward.', 0),
	(12439, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We definitely don\'t want another sundering, friend. I\'ll do all that I can to help you on your mission.', 13623),
	(12440, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Vas heard my distress call then, eh? Not a moment too soon, friend.', 13623),
	(12441, 4, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Outstanding work, $N! I will notify Drolfy that a hero did rise to meet his challenge and that the cruel Bloodpaw is no more!', 0),
	(12442, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At least for now the Scarlet Onslaught suffers a setback in their nefarious plans. You have done Wintergarde a great service, $N.\n', 0),
	(12443, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh yes. That\'ll save me hours.$b$bTake this for your trouble, friend. And keep an eye out for more element 115. I\'ll take all you can find.', 13623),
	(12444, 113, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work, $N.  We could use a few more folks like you up here.  We could really show the Horde not to mess with us.', 15595),
	(12447, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m trying to decide at which I\'m more surprised... that you actually came to the aid of a Black Dragon or that you\'re still in one piece after speaking with Nalice.$B$BHer words drip venom, but I suppose Wyrmrest can keep even our kind in check sometimes.$B$BOr perhaps it\'s just the armies of the red dragonflight that are massed around her.', 15595),
	(12448, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is a disgusting task, but I thank you for doing it.$B$BThe Scourge cannot be permitted to push any further out of the shrine lest all of these lands be overrun.', 15595),
	(12449, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'In the earth, my brothers can grant life anew. You have saved them from a fate far worse than death.$B$BI don\'t know a word in your tongue that could express how much this means to my kind. Thank you, $r.', 15595),
	(12450, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dahlia... they turned her?$B$BDahlia has been loyal to us for a very long time... if they can corrupt a being of her devotion, it does not bode well for the rest of the young races. Thank you for freeing her. I hope she has found some peace.$B$BYou have honored us with your selfless assistance today, $r. Perhaps not all of the Horde bear the black hearts of their ancestors.  I will send word to the council of what your kind have accomplished here.', 15595),
	(12451, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You offer a short introduction, explaining you were sent by Sergeant Nazgrim.>$B$BAh, so you\'re something in the way of reinforcements, then. Good.$B$BTormak and his men have need of your blade.', 0),
	(12453, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $N.  Your help is appreciated.', 15595),
	(12454, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do not regret the part that you played in the cycle of life. Birth, death, and rebirth are all part of the natural order.', 13623),
	(12455, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just in time! Some of my soldiers got a little overzealous and decided to wade into the crypts directly to the east and west of us. Needless to say, they were quickly overwhelmed by those mindless ghouls. We need to rescue the survivors!', 13623),
	(12456, 1, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do not weep for Alystros. He has dedicated his eternal life to the defense of the Emerald Dragonshrine and will be reborn.$B$BHopefully when he returns to us, he will not be gripped with the confusion of the Emerald Nightmare that seems to have taken hold of The Dreamer.', 0),
	(12457, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N, I haven\'t seen heroics like that since Silithus!$B$BI\'ll be sure that each and every one of those soldiers puts in a recommendation to Lord Fordragon that you be promoted!$B$BNow, on to more pressing matters. We\'ve gotten reports back from our scouts that Thel\'zan is close.\n', 13623),
	(12458, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Even now I can feel the pulse of nature from within these seeds.$B$BWe must put them to good use!', 13623),
	(12459, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. Just as I suspected all along. I shall have to attempt to contact Ysera and see if she approves.$B$BIf she can be coaxed from her nightmare, of course.$B$BThank you, $N. You have been indispensable.', 15595),
	(12460, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ambassador Lauriel sent you?$B$BIf you talk to her again, please let her know that we are very appreciative of her aid. We are fighting battles on far too many fronts.', 0),
	(12461, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ambassador Golluck sent you?$B$BIf you talk to him again, please let him know that we are very appreciative of his aid. We are fighting battles on far too many fronts.', 15595),
	(12462, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That oughta buy Ambo a little bit of time to get things situated. ', 13623),
	(12463, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You discover a journal on Plunderbeard\'s corpse.>$B$BEntry One:$B$BThey drag corpses through the tunnel to the embalming room for experimentation. There is an endless supply in this mausoleum. Whatever cannot be reanimated is turned into a bone construct of one kind or another.$B$BEntry Two:$B$BI fear that this lich, Thel\'zan, hides a dark secret. Who is he? Was he once... one of us?$B$BEntry Three: I have discovered the location of the lich\'s phylactery. It is...$B$B<The rest of the pages are torn out.>', 13623),
	(12464, 11, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An unfortunate, but necessary action that we had to take in dealing with Abbendis. In another lifetime, I think I could have imagined fighting side-by-side with her.$B$B<The commander\'s voice trails off as he reflects a moment before proceeding.>$B$BI\'m a little concerned about this grand admiral you describe. Barean Westwind you say? I can\'t believe that he\'s still alive. He must be ancient. We\'ll have to deal with him later, however.$B$BIn the meantime, I think you\'ve earned a reward and a little R & R.', 0),
	(12465, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ambo reads through the recovered journal pages.>$B$BThere\'s some good news and there\'s some bad news. Which do you want first?$B$BAh hell, why give you a choice? The good news is that if we can get Thel\'zan\'s phylactery, we can destroy him. The bad news is that the phylactery is on a rather large frostwyrm.', 13623),
	(12466, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now you know why they call this the Dragon Wastes. Bones of the beasts are strewn about as far as the eye can see.$B$BWe\'ve probably taken down a dozen or more frostwyrms and there\'s still no end in sight. The Scourge\'s got fuel for ten-thousand more what with all the bones laying about.$B$B<Tyralion clears his throat.>$B$BI don\'t mean to bore you with the details, hero. We\'ve got the wyrm you\'re looking for locked in our sights.', 13623),
	(12467, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve lost so many good soldiers to that monster, Thel\'zan. I wish I could be there to see you crush his phylactery in front of him and end his existence.', 13623),
	(12468, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So Krenna sent you to me? She must\'ve not liked you very much, but then again who does she like?$B$BCracking this vrykul outpost is going to be a tough, tough job.', 0),
	(12469, 6, 0, 0, 0, 30, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah! We lost another one, eh? Those harpies are becoming a real nuisance.$B$BNo matter! There\'s work to be done. Lend a hand around here, will ya?', 15050),
	(12470, 6, 4, 1, 1, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'You saw Nozdormu? That doesn\'t make any sense.$B$B<Chromie thinks a moment about what you\'ve said.>$B$BActually, that\'s great news! We had no idea of where or when the Lord of Time had gone to. We just knew that he had disappeared to deal with very important matters.$B$BSo, even though the leader of the Infinite Dragonflight wasn\'t revealed, you\'ve discovered that Nozdormu is alive and well, and fighting back against them!$B$BThank you, $N. I\'ll be seeing you soon!', 15595),
	(12471, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $N.  You\'ve shown a great deal of goodwill towards my clan.', 15595),
	(12472, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'When you\'re ready I\'ll place the phylactery out in front of the gateway and call forth Thel\'zan.', 13623),
	(12473, 4, 1, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wintergarde is saved because of you, $N. To think that one $g man:woman; could so swiftly turn the tides of battle is hard for most to comprehend; yet here we are - victorious! You have managed to restore the faith of these people and earned the respect of your commanding officers.$B$B<Halford salutes.> $B$BLord Fordragon has returned to Angrathar to prepare our forces for the destruction of the Wrathgate and has requested that you join him! I couldn\'t recommend a better soldier for the job, $N.\n', 13623),
	(12474, 1, 1, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This commendation is only given to those who have gone above and beyond the call of duty in the name of the Alliance. I could count the number of times I\'ve handed this one out on one hand, $N, and never has anyone been more deserving than you! Congratulations!$B$BNow, let us look upon the Wrathgate. Does it look familiar? It should. That strange ore you found at the Wintergarde Mine is exactly what the Wrathgate is made from. We will find its weakness and expose it for all to see! First, though...', 13623),
	(12475, 1, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A cave? Could it be? There can be no other correlation!', 13623),
	(12476, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hopefully the message is now clear to the Onslaught. I hope it was enough of a beating to make them doubt their affiliations.\n', 13623),
	(12477, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Halford reads the journal.>$B$BAbbendis has gone off the deep end. The Light speaks to her now?$B$BDespite the inane ramblings, this journal gives us a never before seen look into the mind of the Scarlet zealots. This was a great find, $N. Lord Fordragon will be pleased.', 13623),
	(12478, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Muradin lives? Could it be? I must notify King Bronzebeard at once!$B$BI need to consult the orb. There must be more information - somewhere!\n', 13623),
	(12481, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work.  That poor sap never saw it coming.', 15595),
	(12482, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $N.  When our forces from Vengeance Landing arrive, we\'ll be able to take care of any vrykul that are left.', 15595),
	(12483, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, mon - shimmercap stew! I can almost taste it already....', 15595),
	(12484, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nothin\' better than watchin\' them shcourge burn... <hic>.$b$bWrote a little shong about it. Wanna hear it? Here goes....', 15595),
	(12486, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The mystic knows? You say he felt that something horrible happened to Farseer Grimwalker?$B$BIt is as I feared!', 0),
	(12487, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Who are you?$B$BTell me why I shouldn\'t split you in two where you stand!', 0),
	(12488, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You were sent from Agmar\'s Hammer? It\'s about time!$B$BNo, the help is not for me. I simply have no one else to spare, but you\'ll do.', 0),
	(12489, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah! It\'s not often you run into a complete stranger in the middle of the jungle.$B$BYou one those druid lackeys sent to "stop me and my evil ways?" Yeah, good luck with that one!$B$B<Hemet lets out a hearty laugh and pats his gun.>$B$BDidn\'t think so! You\'re more than welcome to join us in the hunt, soon as we\'ve dealt with those Venture Company dogs. There\'ll be plenty to go around.', 0),
	(12491, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is the Coren Direbrew\'s drink? The brew he wanted more than anything to submit at Brewfest? Well, officially we can\'t recognize this submission, but out of respect for a fallen brewer, perhaps I\'ll have a taste...', 0),
	(12492, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, so Direbrew finally submitted his brew. What a pity he had to die to do it...$B$BOh, well. Bottoms up, eh?', 0),
	(12495, 1, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have come seeking my council, mortal. This I know, but do you know what it is that you face?$B$B<Alexstrasza points northward.>$B$BNorth of here are the dying grounds of Galakrond - progenitor of dragonkind. It is from Galakrond that the Titans created the Aspects. Imagine, then, the power of Galakrond. His size alone was greater than all of the Aspects combined! Now attempt to understand what the Scourge do in the Great Dragonblight.$B$BFrost wyrms, mortal, should be the least of your concerns.', 13623),
	(12496, 1, 6, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have come seeking my council, mortal. This I know, but do you know what it is that you face?$B$B<Alexstrasza points northward.>$B$BNorth of here are the dying grounds of Galakrond - progenitor of dragonkind. It is from Galakrond that the Titans created the Aspects. Imagine, then, the power of Galakrond. His size alone was greater than all of the Aspects combined! Now attempt to understand what the Scourge do in the Great Dragonblight.$B$BFrost wyrms, mortal, should be the least of your concerns.', 15595),
	(12497, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The bravery of mortals never fails to astound me. Death affixes its cold stare upon you and in return you rise to challenge its assertion! It is why your kind is so loved... and so hated.$B$BEven though the Red Dragonflight is entrenched in a war with Malygos, there is something that we can do to help.', 15595),
	(12498, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew that you would return, $N. You have served the Wyrmrest Accord and saved your people from certain death. Let it be known to all and let it be recorded for posterity!', 15595),
	(12499, 1, 1, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Know this: all that you have done has led to this moment. Without your efforts, we would have been finished! Now, stand guard as I take to the field and end this!', 13623),
	(12500, 1, 1, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My father was right about you, $N. Everything that he said has come to pass - only one final duty remains unfulfilled. I will now lead the Kor\'kron to the front line. The time to end this war is at hand. The Lich King\'s tyranny ends today!$B$BTake my post now, $N, and stand guard over our forces.', 15595),
	(12501, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, $N, at least you\'ve made it back in one piece. I suppose that\'s worth something....', 0),
	(12502, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, friend.$B$BAmazing what a little of one\'s colors do for a battleground.$B$BYou\'ll want to head on over to Captain Rupert next. He\'s stationed at the wall, just northeast of here.', 0),
	(12503, 2, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your assistance in this matter is greatly appreciated. Were it not for your efforts, we would have difficulty in holding the unliving back from our steps.', 15595),
	(12504, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alright then. We\'ll collect up the rest and head back to the stand.$B$BIt\'s a shame that we have to leave so soon. Doesn\'t quite feel like the job\'s done here, and quite frankly, I get the feeling that prophet in front of the altar is going to be big trouble!', 15595),
	(12505, 6, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 0, '<The dwarf sergeant warily eyes the orders in your hand.>$B$BAre those new orders for me, $g mister : miss;?', 15595),
	(12506, 6, 1, 5, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'Dead?$B$B<The hexxer\'s spirit is visibly lowered at the news you bring.>$B$BThey\'ve killed Sseratus and drunk deeply of his mojo; the prophet especially!$B$BWe must figure out a way to put an end to him before he drinks too much more!', 15595),
	(12507, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s the mojo of the wild gods, $c!$B$BThis is not good!', 0),
	(12508, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks, $c. I\'d have hated to leave without accomplishing what we came out here for in the first place.', 15595),
	(12509, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $c. And not a moment too soon. I\'ve received word that a counter-attack is imminent.$B$BYou should be on your way. The next post is to the northeast, near the coliseum. Captain Grondel should be waiting for you there.', 0),
	(12510, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. When combined with the mojo, these fluids will dilute the effectiveness of the mojo without completely eliminating it.$B$BNow, one more thing.', 15595),
	(12511, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You were almost shot down, eh? Savage monsters - those Horde.$B$BPayback will come for what they\'ve done. You can count on at least that much, $c.$B$BNow, it\'s time to put you to work.', 0),
	(12512, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Saved them all, did you? Outstanding!$b$bMaybe you\'d consider sticking around the post here? We could sure use someone like you....', 15595),
	(12513, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My... my hat! But... how did you...?$B$BWell... no matter. So, now you know my secret. I WAS beaten... once. Here: take this hat, in return for mine. You\'ve earned it.', 0),
	(12514, 25, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 0, '<The hexxer nods his approval.>$B$BHand that fungus over and I\'ll mix it up with the mojo and elemental lord fluids.', 15595),
	(12515, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My... my hat! But... how did you...?$b$bWell... no matter. So, now you know my secret. I WAS beaten... once. Here: take this hat, in return for mine. You\'ve earned it.', 0),
	(12516, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Amazing! You\'ve saved your people and the rest of Northrend from his madness.$B$BUnfortunately there\'s more of this insanity occurring up in the higher tiers of Zul\'Drak.', 15595),
	(12517, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The tarot cards are of great interest to the Darkmoon Faire, so do not hesitate to call upon us if you manage to collect more.  We are not without our own skilled tradesmen, so please allow us to offer something in return.', 15595),
	(12518, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your skill is most impressive! The tarot cards are of great interest to the Darkmoon Faire, so do not hesitate to call upon us if you manage to create more. We are not without our own skilled tradesmen, so please allow us to offer something in trade for the cards.', 0),
	(12519, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, now!$B$BYa saved me a fair bit o\' work there $Glad:lass;. I\'m grateful. I\'ll be sure ta make mention of ya in me report.$B$BOff with yeh now. Finklestein\'ll likely be waitin fer ya a bit west o\' here.', 0),
	(12520, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, well, well, it looks like you\'ve survived the rhinos, after all, and in pretty good shape if I do say so myself. But there\'s more to rhino hunting than just staring down the beast as it charges you and hoping your aim is true. No, you\'ll need more than that to take on the rhino patriarch that\'s rumored to dwell in the jungle.', 13623),
	(12521, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aye, Hemet\'s here. He\'s at the camp, just go northwest toward the river and you\'ll soon see it. And for the love of the Light, $g lad:lass;, have him send someone to cut me down!', 0),
	(12522, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There... just set it down there. Be careful! If you ruin this one, we\'re in big trouble. Now, let\'s see what I can do.', 0),
	(12523, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With a little work, these should suffice. My poor flying machine might end up looking more like a Venture Company shredder, though. Poor girl will have to wait until we get back to Dalaran to be restored to her rightful form.', 13623),
	(12524, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should hamper their operations, but I worry that the foreman will try to bring in more workers. We have to complete the job while we can.', 0),
	(12525, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a relief to hear that the Venture Company will trouble us no more. You have my thanks, and that of Hemet for dealing with this problem. A game hunter cannot, in good conscience, lift her weapon against another person.', 0),
	(12526, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What brings you to Rahm\'s shrine?', 13623),
	(12527, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, most excellent! Thank you. The crystals appear to be in fine condition!$B$BI have no doubt that Pestlepot put you up to doing his chores for him. Nevertheless, your assistance in this matter is greatly appreciated!', 15595),
	(12528, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You the new slave?$B$BGood. We running out.', 13623),
	(12529, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Goregek show silly $r slave how it done.', 13623),
	(12530, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Goregek take you to kill big mom of hardknuckles, eh? You lucky!$B$BDumb softknuckles squeal good!$B$B<Rakjak squeals loudly and breaks out laughing.>', 13623),
	(12531, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You kill Serfex? I bet you follow mighty wolvar that kill Serfex and take claw.$B$BMy claw now.', 13623),
	(12532, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good! I was worried about foodstuffs. I already pretty hungry.$B$BThank you, $r.', 13623),
	(12533, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We kill many many wasps.$B$BRakjak don\'t think they run out.', 13623),
	(12534, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You killed queen wasp! You stronger than Rakjak thought.$B$BMaybe wasps go away now and stop attacking Frenzyheart hunters.', 13623),
	(12535, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good $r! Okay, all ready.', 13623),
	(12536, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We here! Must work fast.$B$BWatch out for big-tongues.', 13623),
	(12537, 153, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It work so good!$B$BYou see lightning smash that oracle guy? So good!$B$B<Zepik rubs his hands together and chuckles maniacally.>', 13623),
	(12538, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 30, 0, 0, 'I stab those big-tongues good.$B$BYou did okay I guess.$B$BNo, I just kidding! You good hunter. I glad to hunt with you.', 13623),
	(12539, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Blown up by lightning?$B$B<Rakjak breaks out laughing for a moment.>$B$BYou good hunter. Rakjak like you. Maybe one day you can be honorary Frenzyheart!$B$BOnly maybe though!', 13623),
	(12540, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No kill me please! We was just looking for fish. We not want to die.', 13623),
	(12541, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it!$B$BThe intelligence gathered from that $r will undoubtedly be of great value. I\'ll be certain to make mention of your efforts in my report to the commander.$B$BThank you, $N.', 0),
	(12542, 1, 6, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mere footsteps from here lies the Drakkari empire.$B$B<Valus points east.>$B$BFor thousands of years the Drakkari remained isolated, preferring to keep within the boundaries of their sprawling temple cities and ziggurats. It was surprising then, to come upon this wreckage. Further up, beyond the foreboding stairs leading into Zul\'Drak, Drak\'Tharon Keep lies in ruin. The entire first tier of Zul\'Drak, destroyed...$B$BWhy has the Scourge waited until now to attack?  ', 15595),
	(12543, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The oracle inspects the fangs.>$B$BWe approve! Bones of Nozronn will speak to $N!', 13623),
	(12544, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Hemet listens as you describe what you learned.>$B$BWay to go, $g lad:lass;. No dead rhino tells Hemet Nesingwary where and what he can hunt. We\'ll show that heap o\' bones.', 13623),
	(12545, 1, 1, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As you can see, the Scourge war machine presses onward, yet the armies of the Horde and the Alliance remain divided, making for easy prey. It is for this reason that we must remain united.$B$B<Valus is lost in contemplation for a moment.>$B$BThe Argent Crusade has use for a $g man:woman; like you. Perhaps you would be interested in joining our cause? To battle and die at the side of the Ashbringer?', 15595),
	(12546, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am grateful for your help, $N. It is my duty to watch over these lands and all life that dwells on them.$B$BThanks to you, that life will continue to thrive while the forces of death wage in the bordering regions.$B$BYour actions will not be forgotten.', 0),
	(12547, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You hear the rumbling sound of stone grinding as The Etymidian\'s limbs come to life.>$B$BI am needed somewhere?', 0),
	(12548, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<As you read the engravings on this stone colossus, you realize that this is the weapon that Freya spoke of. This is the Etymidian.>', 0),
	(12549, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, you\'ve proven yourself a capable hunter, but how are you as a tracker?', 13623),
	(12550, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Buck listens as you recount your findings.>$B$BI think you may have found the proof we need for this Shango. And I think I have an idea as to where we can find him.', 13623),
	(12551, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Impressive, $c. Are you certain you\'re not a member of the expedition?$B$BNo, I\'m certain of it. There would\'ve been a crash joke in there somewhere.', 13623),
	(12552, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s not enough!$B$B<The sergeant\'s voice cracks as he mourns the corruption of his fallen comrades.>$B$BWe must do more to show respect for the memories of those men!', 15595),
	(12553, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those\'ll do!$B$BNow we\'re going to need some raw parts so that I can put the launching device together for you.', 15595),
	(12554, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'You\'re the $g hero : heroine; of the hour, $N.$B$B<Moonshard kicks the head away from him.>$B$BYou deserve our deepest respect, and something more I think.', 15595),
	(12555, 4, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yay! You\'re the best, $N!$B$BI wasn\'t looking forward to being sprayed with Scourge stuff, that\'s for sure! I guess it\'s going to be hard for those stupid nerubians to spread their evil now!$B$BHow about I give you a little something for saving my skin?', 15595),
	(12556, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Hemet examines the horn.>$B$BAn astounding trophy from an amazing animal! $N, I\'ve been hearing rumors of even bigger, more ferocious game in the northern reaches of the basin and I\'d like you to help us track it down.', 13623),
	(12557, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes, that\'s a good start.$b$bShould I call upon you to help me with an actual recipe, you\'ll need to locate ingredients in a timely manner.$b$bKeep that in mind, $c.$b$bFarewell.', 15595),
	(12558, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What an exquisite pelt from such a noble animal! It heartens me to see that the rumors about Shango were indeed true, $N. Your pursuit of the creature has been flawless. You are a true huntsman.', 13623),
	(12559, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re halfway there, $N. One more switch needs to be activated before we can retrieve the Etymidian.', 0),
	(12560, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Debaar accepts the sandfern fronds from you and starts bending them around your body.>$B$BYes, this should work. Stand still! We\'ll make a bush of you yet.', 13623),
	(12561, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well, $r. I am satisfied that you\'re not one of the Lich King\'s minions... perhaps there is something you can do for us after all.', 0),
	(12562, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $g sir : ma\'am;!$B$BI\'ll see to it that the commander is apprised of your mission results.', 15595),
	(12563, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, $N, at least you\'ve made it back in one piece. I suppose that\'s worth something....', 0),
	(12564, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine specimens, $n.$b$bOn behalf of my soldiers, I thank you for your efforts today.$b$bCaptain Rupert is likely the next stop on your patrol. He\'s stationed at the wall just east of here.', 0),
	(12565, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<If Zim\'Abwa could move his face, Zim\'Abwa would make a vicious grin.>', 15595),
	(12566, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, Nanik did find help then? Tell me, $N, how is it you made it here without him? None know this land better than the Taunka.', 15595),
	(12567, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You sense Zim\'Abwa\'s approval. Somehow you know that Zim\'Abwa wants more tribute!>', 0),
	(12568, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N.$B$BIt\'s not the most glorious job on the battlefield, but it must be done. I\'ll make note of your service in my report.$B$BCaptain Grondel is likely waiting for you to the northeast, just outside the amphitheater.', 0),
	(12569, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Debaar listens as you describe the failure of the disguise.>$B$BWhat do you mean, our plan didn\'t work as intended?$B$BWell, you did manage to get the kill, to your credit. Look at the size of this jaw! Hemet will be proud of our efforts. This crocolisk was truly a monster.', 13623),
	(12570, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You help us? You welcome then, dryskin.', 13623),
	(12571, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Snake gone?$B$BGood $r. We thank you.', 13623),
	(12572, 5, 0, 0, 0, 20, 0, 0, 0, 'Shinies for the Great Rain Stone! Good! Good!$B$BWe offer these right away. Lafoo thought of this, yes? He a very smart Rainspeaker.', 13623),
	(12573, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So mean! We only be nice and they only be mean.$B$BThey keep messing with great stones... maybe they not know great stones are sacred.', 13623),
	(12574, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We think we seen you before. You visit Mistwhisper village sometime already?$B$BSoo-say said you good. Soo-say smart, so we trust you too.$B$B<Mistcaller Soo-gan offers an awkwardly large smile.>', 13623),
	(12575, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it! You strong and nice! Good friend of Mistwhispers!$B$B<Mistcaller Soo-gan lets loose a big toothy grin.>', 13623),
	(12576, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You squash good. Thank you for help.', 13623),
	(12577, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You back so soon!$B$BWent good then, yeah?', 13623),
	(12578, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Before you say anything, do not assume me as foolish as most of the Oracles you\'ve met. I\'ve been into the world a bit, I\'ve learned your language, and I\'m not easily duped.$B$BI knew the Mosswalkers were dead before we ever came, though I didn\'t know that the undead were behind it.$B$BThey are not supposed to be able to enter this land... the destruction of the Lifeblood Pillar must have allowed them in somehow. We must see to it that they leave.', 13623),
	(12579, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We might be too late for the shards to make a difference, but our options are somewhat limited.', 13623),
	(12580, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m very glad there were some to be saved... with luck, they\'ll make it back to Rainspeaker Canopy safely.', 13623),
	(12581, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Inside Artruis\'s Phylactery you see what seems like an endless void... and you think you hear screaming in the distance from somewhere inside.>$B$B<As you\'re about to leave, you see an object floating in the void, just barely in reach.>', 13623),
	(12582, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I know you weren\'t traitor thing like others said. We hunt together... I know you better than all of them. Thank you for saving me.$B$BMay sound funny... I not a big fan of big-tongues... but even I feel little bad for big-tongue dying like that though...they fight good enough they deserve fair fight.$B$BYou want to be friends with Frenzyheart again? I think I can convince them that you save me and got the big-tongues good. I no want you to make me look dumb though, so you sure no more big-tongues for you?', 15595),
	(12583, 5, 1, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 0, '<The specialist steps back a bit when presented with the parts.>$B$BEw, those things are totally gross!$B$BOkay, okay, hand them over and I\'ll see what I can do. I probably should have had you take them to a priest first for purification.', 15595),
	(12584, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Can you not feel the pure evil of the stuff?$B$BWe must use the expertise and magics at our disposal, combined with the power of the Holy Light, to pierce the veil of iniquity surrounding this tainted ore. We must determine its origins.$B$BQuickly, hand the saronite to me!', 15595),
	(12585, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mighty kind of ya, $n. Mighty kind indeed.$b$bNow you\'ll be findin\' Cap\'n Arnath due west o\' here, just over the rise.', 0),
	(12587, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, $n, at least you\'ve made it back in one piece. I suppose that\'s worth something....', 0),
	(12588, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for looking into this for me, $n. I\'ll make mention of your service in my report.$b$bYou\'ll likely want to visit Captain Rupert next. He\'s stationed at the wall due east of here.', 0),
	(12589, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re not a bad shot, but you\'ll get better with practice. How would you like to make a little wager?', 13623),
	(12591, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re not out of the woods by any means, but your efforts have helped to slow the enemy down.$b$bCaptain Grondel up in Drak\'Agal will likely have need of you.$b$bFarewell, $n.', 0),
	(12592, 5, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, you\'ve come to concede already?$B$B<Drostan\'s jaw drops as you tell him you\'ve already made all your kills.>$B$BNo way! How in Azeroth did you do that? I just made my 58th. So close!$B$BBut fair\'s fair. I underestimated you, $N, but you\'ve earned this victory fair and square.', 13623),
	(12593, 1, 5, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have heard the call of the Lich King, death knight. Now is the time to answer your master.', 14480),
	(12594, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You sure about that, $r?$b$bSeems to me like there are more of them things out there now than when you started!', 0),
	(12595, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So old Hemet didn\'t forget about me, after all. I suppose he\'s going to want to participate in the hunt once we\'ve done all the hard work. Don\'t worry, there are plenty of drakes to go around. Hemet will get his wish.', 13623),
	(12596, 5, 1, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s about time you got your carcass back here! Thought we\'d lost ya to the Scourge - not that it would\'ve been a great loss....$b$bIf you\'re going to continue to serve the Crusade, you\'d best make a more impressive showing.$b$bTake note, $r! Your future patrols will be rewarded based on your timeliness.$b$bDismissed.', 15595),
	(12597, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine specimens, $n.$b$bOn behalf of my soldiers, I thank you for your efforts today.$b$bCaptain Rupert is likely the next stop on your patrol. He\'s stationed at the wall just east of here.', 15595),
	(12598, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re not out of the woods by any means, but your efforts have helped to slow the enemy down.$b$bCaptain Grondel up in Drak\'Agal will likely have need of you.$b$bFarewell, $n.', 15595),
	(12599, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mighty kind of ya, $n. Mighty kind indeed.$b$bNow you\'ll be findin\' ol\' Finklestein due west o\' here, just over the rise.', 15595),
	(12603, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can hear the confidence in your words. Good, the experience will come in handy when we face the queen of the drakes.', 13623),
	(12604, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You made excellent time on that patrol. It appears that you may be of use to us after all.$b$bAs promised, here\'s a little something extra for your efforts.$b$bKeep up the good work, $n.$b$bDismissed. ', 0),
	(12605, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, well done. Plenty of little hatchlings for Zootfizzle over there!', 13623),
	(12606, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These nerubians have taken a heavy toll, $c.$b$bNevertheless, I am grateful for your efforts.', 15595),
	(12607, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect! Now, all we need to do is get Hemet a stepladder...', 0),
	(12608, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The living... willingly serve the Lich King?$b$bAll this time I\'ve been searching for the wrong enemy, $r. Let us make haste and uproot these cultists from these lands.', 0),
	(12609, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These look to be excellent samples, $n.$b$bThank you for your assistance.', 15595),
	(12610, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n.$b$bI thank you for your assistance.', 15595),
	(12611, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You continue to prove yourself, $n. Perhaps I was too quick to judge you.$b$bI had assumed you were here with the poachers who were recently stranded in my lands, but perhaps you\'re ready to put that behind you.', 0),
	(12612, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The corpse is badly burnt. There appear to be the remains of several powder kegs in the vicinity.>', 0),
	(12613, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The waygate is active, $n. It is time!', 0),
	(12614, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, I had a whole speech prepared, but the old man himself has some words he wants to say to you.', 0),
	(12615, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Zim\'Torga\'s thoughts pervade your own. She senses the offerings you are about give to her and is pleased.>$B$B<She conveys that you will be appropriately rewarded.>', 15595),
	(12616, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The information you report is dire indeed if the orders you saw are legitimate. We can only hope that his mission was stopped early enough to prevent the enemy from knowing too much about our strengths.$b$bThank you, $n. May you remain safe in these dark times.', 0),
	(12617, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You speak the truth. The intruders at the camp were dealt with... but I\'m afraid it might have been too late.', 0),
	(12618, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Mother of Prosperity beams her approval down upon you.>', 0),
	(12619, 1, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N. You have successfully created your first runebladed weapon. With it you will sow the seeds of chaos and destruction! In your wake will be a bloodied field of battle, littered with the corpses of all that would dare oppose the Scourge.', 14480),
	(12620, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Impressive. I wasn\'t expecting a mere mortal to prove as worthy an ally as you.$b$bI fear our efforts have not been sufficient, however. The Scourge shows no signs of stopping.', 0),
	(12621, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is no turning back now. If you agree to help me, you will do so without hesitation.', 0),
	(12622, 11, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The scalper thinkin\' that you be his kind of $r!$B$BWhat\'s these candybars doin\' in here? What we do with this, mon?$B$BAhunae say that you can have them back!', 15595),
	(12623, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings to you, $c. I am glad to hear that Ubungo found someone that he could trust.$B$BWelcome to Zim\'Torga.', 15595),
	(12624, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it!  You actually found it!$B$BI don\'t know... I don\'t know how to thank you!', 13623),
	(12627, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, I can already feel the difference. Thank you.$B$BLet us see if we can make contact with the gods now.', 15595),
	(12628, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Listen closely, little $r. Time is of the essence.', 15595),
	(12629, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Stefan sifts through the foul components.>$b$bWell, it\'s far from perfect, but it\'ll have to do. Now brace yourself, $c. This is where it gets good....', 15595),
	(12630, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You know, you remind me an awful lot of my Nass.$b$bMaybe it\'s just the nose...', 15595),
	(12631, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am indeed familiar with items such as this.$b$b<Stefan looks you in the eye.>$b$bIt would seem, $n, that you have been... chosen.', 15595),
	(12632, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N. I will never forget what you have done.', 15595),
	(12633, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am indeed familiar with items such as this.$b$b<Stefan looks you in the eye.>$b$bIt would seem, $n, that you have been... chosen.', 0),
	(12634, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, that\'s a better assortment than I would\'ve expected from this place. Now, for the important question: can we distill it into anything drinkable? We\'d better get started.', 13623),
	(12635, 1, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aw, prime specimens!$B$BYou can see there the divergence from the root symbology. Quite extraordinary.$B$BWhat a pity that the ice trolls are determined to bring about their own demise.$B$BDid you know, for instance, that the Drakkari were exiled from the rest of the troll nations for their extremely violent ways?$B$BIt\'s true! How did you think trolls ended up in such a harsh climate as this?', 15595),
	(12636, 396, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The time to spill the blood of our enemies approaches. You must first learn what it is that you seek to destroy, before rushing headlong into battle. It is what separates a death knight from a mindless ghoul.$B$BI will grant you sight beyond sight, my champion. You will use the eye of Acherus to steal our enemies\' secrets. ', 14480),
	(12637, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now you\'ve observed the fate that was meant to befall you.$b$bAs I mentioned before, this was no coincidence. The creation of such a device is very involved, and the required resources would not be squandered on a random target.$b$bThe simple truth of the matter is this; You\'re wanted by the Scourge....', 15595),
	(12638, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now you\'ve observed the fate that was meant to befall you.$b$bAs I mentioned before, this was no random act. The creation of such a device is very involved. You\'ve somehow caught the attention of the Scourge leadership.$b$bThe question is not how, why, or even who... but what will we do about it?', 0),
	(12639, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. Those essences should be enough to fuel my casting for quite some time.', 15595),
	(12640, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahunae hopin\' that Dagoda got all of the defenders she wantin\'. With those rifts sealed, it\'s not likely she\'ll be gettin\' any more.', 15595),
	(12641, 396, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They prepare for battle - as expected - but there is something else. I sense an old enemy. An enemy that I destroyed long ago...$B$BIt matters not. We will send the full might of the Scourge against them before they have a chance to evacuate their homes and put in place their defenses.', 14480),
	(12642, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am barely hanging on. You must work quickly or all will be lost.', 15595),
	(12643, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Stefan sifts through the foul components.>$b$bWell, it\'s far from perfect, but it\'ll have to do.$b$bNow brace yourself, $c. This is where it gets good....', 0),
	(12644, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Grimbooze gives the cask a shake.>$B$BThere\'s something in here, but the million gold question is, can you drink it? Don\'t you go anywhere; you\'ll be responsible for overseeing the sampling of the product, too.', 13623),
	(12645, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Two out of three drinkers agree, eh? Not bad for a first try. Not bad at all. I suppose I\'ll have to whip up something else for Tamara by way of apology.$B$BNow... what should we call this creation?', 13623),
	(12646, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it.$B$BBut now there is one other thing that I need you to do.', 15595),
	(12647, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done what had to be done and honored me in the process.$B$BI give you my deepest thanks, $N. I only hope that you and Har\'koa will be able to help the others.', 15595),
	(12648, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So? How are you enjoying scourge life?$b$bBelieve me, it\'s not all it\'s cracked up to be....', 15595),
	(12649, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So? How are you enjoying Scourge life?$b$bBelieve me, it\'s not all it\'s cracked up to be....', 0),
	(12650, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'Let me look at those.$B$B<The chronicler examines the artifacts that you have recovered.>$B$BHmph, I\'d say that we\'re lucky you liberated these when you did, $c.$B$BHow very interesting. This artifact here depicts the events of the Sundering. There was a time when Northrend was the far northern portion of Kalimdor.$B$BBut after the Sundering, the land broke off, eventually becoming Northrend.$B$BThis, of course, is why we see Drakkari in the southern continents as well as here.', 15595),
	(12651, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, Hemet sent you? We were just about to let him know that we\'ve gotten things up and running here. Please forgive Marvin if he seems to be ignoring you, but he gets very absorbed in his work.', 0),
	(12652, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Num num!', 15595),
	(12653, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The cat goddess howls in pain.>$B$BMy spirit cries out in grief at the loss of another friend. But fear not, he will return and his spirit will live on forever.', 15595),
	(12654, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You got it! Now all I have to do is make a trophy out of it. That\'ll be the hard part -- finding a way to preserve it so that Hemet doesn\'t have a good laugh at my expense.', 0),
	(12655, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Zim\'Rhuk acknowledges the offerings you intend to place before him, though he knows that you took them from the corpses of others.>$B$B<If you give the offerings to him, he reluctantly agrees to grant you his blessing.>', 15595),
	(12656, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Zim\'Rhuk forces an image into your mind of one of his guardians squishing you beneath its foot. Perhaps you should attempt to appease Zim\'Rhuk with more offerings.>', 0),
	(12657, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The horns of war will soon echo across this land, waking the dead and calling forth the Scourge war machine. Woe unto those that would stand in our way!$B$BYou and your brethren will lead the charge, $N. When next I look upon the Scarlet lands, my sight will be obscured by the legions of Acherus. The march upon New Avalon begins now.', 14480),
	(12658, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, these are very nice! I\'ve gotten so tired of robotic squirrels and chickens for company. It\'ll be wonderful to have a pet whose joints won\'t require oiling!', 0),
	(12659, 11, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aw, me thinkin\' that too funny.$B$B$N is my kind of $r!$B$BYou still got my knife?', 15595),
	(12660, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $r. You\'re proving to be a worthy ally.', 0),
	(12661, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, now... I must admit I\'m more than a little surprised to see you, $n.$b$bTell me what you\'ve learned.', 15595),
	(12662, 4, 1, 1, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'You did it!$B$B<Dagoda gives you a big kiss on the cheek.>$B$BYou have no idea how much of a relief that is to me! Defending against trolls on all sides is really putting a strain on us. Not to mention his incessant yelling.$B$BPlease, $N, take your pick of what we have to offer.', 15595),
	(12663, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, now ya be seein\' what we be up against, mon.$b$bGo down, take some time ta learn da land, prepare some strategy. $b$bI\'ll be havin\' some tasks for ya soon.', 0),
	(12664, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, now ya be seein\' what we be up against, mon.$b$bI want ya ta go down, learn da land, mingle with yer bretheren. Prepare yourself...$b$bSoon, dere be much for ya to do. Don\'t ya be disappointin\' me!', 15595),
	(12665, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for bringing my kitten back safely.$B$BDeep down I knew it. I wanted to deny it, but your eyes have revealed the truth.$B$BNevertheless, I sense something else. All is not as it seems.', 15595),
	(12666, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The leopard goddess looks saddened at the collection of holy symbols that you have brought before her.>$B$BThere was a time when these meant something. Let\'s see if we can put them to better use.', 15595),
	(12667, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$R worm. Tell me why I should not annihilate you where you stand?', 15595),
	(12668, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Exquisite. Perhaps you will be of some use after all.', 15595),
	(12669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work, $n!$b$bDiluting those cauldrons will not only save lives, it will slow the growth of the Scourge in this region.$b$bNow come, tell me what you\'ve learned of Drakuru\'s strategy in Zul\'Drak.', 15595),
	(12670, 6, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you smell it?$B$B<Valanar sniffs at the air.>$B$BFresh meat... The scent of Scarlet Crusader wafts through the air.$B$B<Valanar salivates.>$B$BApologies, death knight, I\'m sure you\'re not interested in my choice of fine cuisine. You are here to work! To lead the charge! Yes... I know. The Lich King has told me all that I need to know about you, $N.$B$BThe time for bloodshed is now.\n', 14480),
	(12671, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You saved my life up there, buddy.  Nice flying!', 13623),
	(12672, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'ll do. Likely I won\'t even need them.$B$BBut it was fun watching you run around at my command.', 15595),
	(12673, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Da crystals be pilin\' up like never before!$b$bYou keep up da good work, $n. I got more tasks for ya real soon.', 15595),
	(12674, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The terrible spirit before you lets loose a blood-chilling cackle.>$B$BThey had it coming. And I\'ll give them more of the same again and again and again....', 15595),
	(12675, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A portion of my spirit?$B$B<The snow leopard goddess pauses a moment to consider.>$B$BThat\'s quite an expensive gift considering that this is for revenge and I\'m already greatly weakened by the actions of my subduers.$B$BStill, I may know a way.', 15595),
	(12676, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent!$b$bYour undercover work has truly paid off, $n.$b$bNow let\'s have a look at that scepter....', 15595),
	(12677, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fascinating!$b$bWe\'ll look into the properties of these crystals right away.$b$bNow tell me, $n, what is the latest with this Drakuru fellow?', 15595),
	(12678, 6, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you feel it, $N? That sensation is raw power coursing through your body. Such a thing cannot exist for mortals.$B$BThe front lines are now dismantled. The geist will finish the job and prepare the grounds for Razuvious. We turn our attention now to more tactical targets.\n', 14480),
	(12679, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, death knight! You feed the Scourge war machine with your deeds!$B$BAh yes, your reward - as promised.', 14480),
	(12680, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now for the true test. Can you show mastery over an unbound charger and brutally overtake the thing that you desire most?', 14480),
	(12681, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Colvin looks admiringly at the talons you\'ve brought back.>$b$bThese will more than suffice. The gorlocs have a saying that the more gnarled the talon, the more power it holds. I\'m sure the archmage will get his money\'s worth from this expedition.', 0),
	(12683, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! Here\'s your payment, as agreed. And, uh, a bit of advice: you might want to enjoy long, hot baths the next few days if that \'burning sensation\' persists.', 0),
	(12684, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well. Let us see if this works....', 15595),
	(12685, 1, 5, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 0, '<The witch doctor shakes his head in disbelief.>$B$BIt sounds like you barely escaped Quetz\'lun\'s underworld alive.$B$BI\'m glad that it\'s you out there. I don\'t know if I would have had the courage to deal with that situation!', 15595),
	(12686, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya done good, $n. You be learnin\' faster than I had hoped.$b$bGo now, get ya some rest. Soon I be givin\' ya an even greater test!', 15595),
	(12687, 1, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have succeeded where most initiates fail, $N. For that you will be rewarded handsomely.$B$B<Salanar bows.>', 14480),
	(12688, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for freeing Helice and seeing to her safe return. We all started to get worried when she didn\'t return from her crystal hunting trip.', 0),
	(12689, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hi! Really glad see you again!$b$bI knew we friends. I knew it! You good friend. Not just for us, but for all Oracles.$b$bI saw you bonk that puppy-man good! Undead thing said he your friend before? I not know that. You done with puppy-men though, yeah? Just Oracle friend now?$b$bI know you choose right! Thank you for saving us! Thank you, thank you!', 0),
	(12690, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We done it, mon!$b$bI got da chieftains all caged up and you led my abominations to victory over their armies.$b$bIt be time ta celebrate, mon!', 15595),
	(12691, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The huge stone key turns with a deep grunt as the coffer lid opens up to reveal hidden treasure inside.', 0),
	(12692, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It good to see you again. I knew you not a traitor, I glad Zepik prove me right.$B$BI hear you Lich Hunter now - that pretty good! You make Harkek proud.', 13623),
	(12695, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you again! We worried when you not come back right away.$b$bJaloot beat you back - lot of energy in Jaloot, he pretty fast. He told me how you save him from lich thing. Moodle told me how you save mosswalkers too. You really nice.$b$bI hope you stay with us for while. Always something need doing.', 0),
	(12696, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The professor sent you my way?  All right.', 13623),
	(12697, 15, 6, 274, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have fought hard to invade the realm of the harvester... Wait.$B$B<Gothik looks at his notes.>$B$BMy apologies, $r. Old habits die hard.$B$BValanar sent you, then? I trust you are somewhat competent.$B$BI do have a gift for the Scarlet dogs. One that is sure to speed up their work in the mines.', 14480),
	(12698, 1, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They now know that the mines are no longer safe. They will double their efforts in retreating, leaving their backs open to us!', 14480),
	(12699, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent!  ', 13623),
	(12700, 1, 1, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have served us well, death knight. Few of your brethren have survived our initial attack upon the Scarlet interlopers. You remain as one of the strongest.$B$B<Prince Valanar nods.>$B$BEast of us, past the Havenshire Mine, is the coast - called Light\'s Point by the Scarlet Crusade. A thousand soldiers stand between us and their ships. Insurmountable? Hardly the point...\n', 14480),
	(12701, 11, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The entire Scarlet fleet wiped out in a matter of minutes! I will receive a commendation from the Lich King for this! All that remains of the Scarlet Crusade now are the denizens of New Avalon.$B$BI\'ll set the fire starters and necromancers upon Havenshire immediately. You will carry my report to the Highlord!', 14480),
	(12702, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You good at this.$b$bMaybe someday we just dump Goregek in river so you not have to do this no more.', 0),
	(12703, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ritual went so easy for you!$b$bYou come back later for more killing someday, okay?', 0),
	(12704, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So many good shinies! You good at this.$b$bCome back for more again later, yes?', 0),
	(12705, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Soo-holu strong, huh? I very glad he accept you to share his body for fight.$b$bHe more trusting of people he met before, so maybe come back another time to help more, yes?', 0),
	(12706, 1, 1, 5, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Highlord Mograine reads over the report.>$B$BThe ENTIRE Scarlet fleet?$B$B<Highlord Mograine nods.>$B$BSuch power, $N... I have not seen such a display of domination in years... Since my father wielded...$B$B<Highlord Mograine shakes his head.>$B$BIt\'s not important...$B$BYes, your commendation, lest I forget.', 14480),
	(12707, 4, 94, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Score one for the victims, mon!', 15595),
	(12708, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'That should make them think twice about making more of those things. I shudder to think what it would be like to have to fight an army of those things.$B$B<The element-tamer is thoughtful for a moment.>$B$BI guess it would be just like fighting the endless waves of the Scourge.', 15595),
	(12709, 5, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just look at all of that!$B$BSee here, $N. This piece you recovered vividly illustrates that the Drakkari became aware of the weakening of the land that the Scourge caused by their presence.$B$BThe warlord felt compelled to take the opportunity this presented. He pushed the prophets to kill their gods in an effort to control the power and fight back against the Lich King\'s forces.$B$BEither way they were doomed. They inadvertently chose to be the instrument of their own destruction!', 15595),
	(12710, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, there ya have it, mon.$b$bWe be makin\' da ultimate scourge army ta serve da Lich King. He gunna be most pleased!$b$bYou keep da scepter, $n. You gunna be needin\' it ta command my army in battle....$b$bSoon!', 15595),
	(12711, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Atop the mailbox are several illegible letters and scrolls. Useless...$B$BPerhaps you should check inside?', 14480),
	(12712, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It might have been better if I hadn\'t asked you to bring it back here instead of heading directly to Gundrak.$B$BHowever, I think that it\'s best that you hear what else I have to say first.', 15595),
	(12713, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, it is done.$b$bWe still have much to do, but our work here will be much more manageable thanks to your efforts.$b$bPlease accept this as a token of our gratitude.', 15595),
	(12714, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Havenshire is ours! A thousand corpses litter the ground, patiently awaiting rebirth. We strike now at our enemy with the awakened strength of the Scourge!$B$BThe ghouls have already begun their assault upon New Avalon. Our forces have moved in behind them and taken the Crypt of Remembrance.', 14480),
	(12715, 2, 1, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hail, death knight. I am the blood lord, Keleseth, ruler of the southeastern reaches of Northrend. The Lich King has sought to utilize my talents in ending this mortal affront to the Scourge. As with all things the Lich King asks of me, I am happy to oblige. Of course, a sea of endless souls to sate my thirst certainly sweetened the deal, don\'t you think?\n', 14480),
	(12716, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect! Now give me a moment to get things set up.', 14480),
	(12717, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The plague cauldron jumps to life when the skulls are placed inside.$B$BAfter a few seconds some vials of dark liquid float to the top.', 14480),
	(12718, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The plague cauldron jumps to life when the skulls are placed inside.$B$BAfter a few seconds, the plague cauldron grants you the dark and frothy splendor of Noth\'s Special Brew.', 14480),
	(12719, 1, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The registry will tell us many things about the Scarlet insects.$B$B<Keleseth flips through the pages of the registry.>$B$BDeath rates, births, but most importantly, movement.$B$BLook here, $N, they have already sent three vessels abroad. Let me see here... Where are they headed?$B$B<Keleseth mutters something about latitude and longitude under his breath as he calculates the route.>$B$BWHAT? This is impossible. They sail to Northrend!$B$BBeside the coordinates are the words: "Crimson Dawn."', 14480),
	(12720, 6, 5, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An awakening? What nonsense do you speak, $g boy:girl;! What kind of fool would deliver their people into the very heart of the frozen wastes? Perhaps, though, this courier holds the answer.', 14480),
	(12721, 5, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No!$B$BAnother god destroyed, its power stolen. And now the prophet of Akali has threatened us directly.$B$BWhen he comes, he will come for Har\'koa. We cannot allow him to take her power too.$B$BWe must consult the gods once more, $N. They will tell us what must be done.', 15595),
	(12722, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are quite effective with that blade, $N. Perhaps, Lich King permitting, you would be interested in becoming one of my minions? Stratholme is looking for a new mayor.', 14480),
	(12723, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like we\'ll let anyone into the dark order these days. When I was given the gift, things were different. Much different!$B$BAs to this courier...', 14480),
	(12724, 1, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Orbaz flips through the schedule.>$B$BThese worthless cretins have been busy! Northern patrol routes, southern patrol routes, western patrol routes, eastern patrol routes, but nothing about their couriers\' routes. Wait a minute. What\'s this? It looks like a western patrol route, coming out of Western Plaguelands? This patrol will path through here today! I\'m going to need time to plan.', 14480),
	(12725, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You were foolish in coming after me. I failed. I should have been left for dead - now two of us might be killed.$B$B<Koltira shakes his head.>$B$BWe are death knights of the Scourge. This flies in the face of the dark brotherhood\'s covenants.$B$BThassarian, you blasted fool!', 14480),
	(12726, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $n. The great tempest will look upon us favorably thanks to you.', 0),
	(12727, 15, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll feed this monster\'s head to the ghouls!$B$B<Thassarian tosses the head into the back room.>$B$BDid Koltira make it out?$B$B<Thassarian pauses.>$B$BI\'m certain he did. Those walls can\'t hold him.$B$BTime for some payback.', 14480),
	(12728, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, this completes my report.$b$bI\'ll be sure to mention your kindness to the council, $n.', 0),
	(12729, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your bravery seems boundless, $N.$B$BPlease hand me the heart and the essence, and I will fashion them into that which will compel the prophet to appear before you.', 15595),
	(12730, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it! $N, you are the champion of Zul\'Drak!$B$BWe will never be able to repay the debt that we owe to you, but the Zandalari have given into my trust a number of objects they believe you might have an interest in.$B$BPlease, I want you to have a token of our appreciation, but hurry. I sense another issue of urgency!', 15595),
	(12732, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rejek thanks you. Rejek drink, grow strong, always remember mighty $n\'s gift.', 0),
	(12733, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'To the victor goes the glory, death knight! Well done! The Lich King looks favorably upon you on this day.\n', 14480),
	(12734, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rejek sees the stains of the blood of his enemies on the blade. Now Rejek has a mighty weapon for the mighty warrior he will be!', 0),
	(12735, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Waters... cleansed. Yes. All is well.$b$bYou understand our way, $n.', 0),
	(12736, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You see? I can tell you smarter already. And if not smarter... then... happier!', 0),
	(12737, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You learn fast, $n. You learn that song well. Maybe next time I teach you different song.', 0),
	(12738, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'re only flesh and bone - no match for the Scourge.$B$BWe didn\'t find any of our brothers, but we did stumble upon something special.', 14480),
	(12739, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $n. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever... ', 0),
	(12740, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re a good $g man : woman;, $N. We\'re fortunate that you happened to stop by.$B$BStick around a while. I\'m sure that we have much that a capable $c such as yourself can do.', 15595),
	(12741, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now Rejek show cowardly big-tongues how to really use elements!', 0),
	(12742, 6, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $N. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever... ', 0),
	(12743, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $n. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever... ', 0),
	(12744, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $n. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever... ', 0),
	(12745, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $n. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever... ', 0),
	(12746, 6, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $N. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever... ', 14480),
	(12747, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $n. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever... ', 0),
	(12748, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $n. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever... ', 0),
	(12749, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $n. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever... ', 0),
	(12750, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $n. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever... ', 0),
	(12751, 4, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another Scourge victory! These Scarlet dogs have nowhere left to run and hide. It\'s only a matter of time now...', 14480),
	(12752, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings, $gbrother:sister;. You may have come on behalf of the Argent Dawn, but that is not why you are here -- you are here to help your people earn the respect we so justly deserve. As any forsaken will agree, the end justifies the means, and our research into the zombie plague\'s cure is that proverb in practice...', 0),
	(12753, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$gBrother:Sister; $r, I am proud to stand with you during our days of need. Bless you, and may the alliance between $r and human last a thousand years.', 0),
	(12754, 1, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Orbaz reads the message.>$B$BThe armies of Hearthglen and Tirisfal will be marching into a massacre.$B$B<Orbaz smiles.>$B$BNow for the second part of the plan. You\'re going to deliver this message right into the hands of High General Abbendis. That\'s what the clothes are for...', 14480),
	(12755, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<High General Abbendis reads the message.>$B$BDamn it! The armies of Hearthglen and Tirisfal must not reach New Avalon! The Scourge will slaughter them all.', 14480),
	(12756, 1, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Orbaz flips through the journal.>$B$BWhat rubbish! This is the "Crimson Dawn?"$B$BThey sail to their deaths! Let us turn our focus to the encroaching armies.', 14480),
	(12757, 1, 1, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have become an instrument of doom, death knight! We will ravage these approaching armies and raise the dead as our own!', 14480),
	(12758, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rejek sees you were successful! Now Rejek try on new war helmet.', 0),
	(12759, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You almost as good with those traps as Zepik!', 0),
	(12760, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You a fierce fighter... come back for more battle soon. Never enough good battle!', 0),
	(12761, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, dryskin.$b$bI hold onto these crystals here to keep us safe. Maybe you come back soon and help us more.', 0),
	(12762, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So much energy in you... you full of the power of the Great Ones!$b$b I not lie, I little bit jealous.', 0),
	(12763, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Light shall prevail!', 0),
	(12766, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You must be $N. I was told you\'d be coming.$B$BI have something that I think you\'re uniquely qualified to take care of and by doing it, you\'ll be ingratiating yourself with the dragons here.', 0),
	(12767, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You must be $N. I was told you\'d be coming.$B$B<The ambassador grunts.>$B$BI have something that I want you to take care of. If you do, you\'ll prove yourself to the dragons here.', 15595),
	(12768, 6, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Back so soon, $N?$B$BCeristrasz sent word ahead of you. Thank you for what you did at the Ruby Dragonshrine.', 0),
	(12769, 6, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Back so soon, $N?$B$BVargastrasz sent word ahead of you. Thank you for what you did at the Ruby Dragonshrine.', 15595),
	(12770, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Light shall prevail!', 0),
	(12771, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By my beard! This holds a power to rival a fleet of our flying machines! I\'ll give it to my war priests and we\'ll devise a plan to send those vile necropolises scurrying back to Northrend... and we\'ll be right behind them!$b$bOh, Muradin my brother, you must live! By the honor of the Bronzebeards, I will find you!', 0),
	(12772, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n, honorable $r, welcome. May the Light shine upon you, and may your ancient wisdom ward our land in its time of need.', 0),
	(12773, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What is this? What a boon! They have captured such Light into this artifact, it shines nigh bright as the moon! Our priests will channel this power against our foes, and the Lich King\'s invasion will surely fail. Thank you, $n. Our world tree will be safe.$b$bWhat\'s more, we have sensed that perhaps another world tree grows far to the north, nestled hidden near the Lich King\'s own domain. Perhaps someday... we will shepherd both trees and herald a new era of peace.', 0),
	(12774, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, the holy folk in Shattrath created what they promised! In hindsight, diverting so many priests and paladins there, instead of sending them against the Scourge, was the right move. With this holy weapon, we can beat back that damned Lich King and his minions!$b$bI commend you, Lord $n.', 0),
	(12775, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$gBrother:Sister;, we are called again to fight against the Scourge. It is good you are here; with your strength, and the power of the Light, we may yet prevail.', 0),
	(12776, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, I can see the power of the Naaru shine through this thing, as if Light itself is housed here. Such good can be done with this implement; the necropolises sent from the frozen wastes of the north will surely fail.', 0),
	(12777, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My heart swells with Light to see you, a noble $r, come to our aid. Bless you, good $c!', 0),
	(12778, 396, 396, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have served me well, $N. The mark of the Scourge has been burned into these Scarlet lands. You have reaped death and destruction for as far as the eye can see and delivered to me the last of the Scarlet armies.$B$B<The Lich King points to the ruins of Havenshire and the burning city of New Avalon.>$B$BIt is now time to finish what you started.', 14480),
	(12779, 397, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kneel, champion. I place this helm upon your head to complete your terrifying visage. Any that dare look upon your dark countenance will know that death comes. Let none stand so boldly against your king so as to face your merciless wrath, $N.$B$BThere remains only one final task...$B$B<The Lich King looks west.>$B$BLight\'s Hope Chapel.', 15354),
	(12781, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We welcome you to the world of Azeroth, and offer you one of these unique gifts.', 0),
	(12782, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a fine specimen you are. We have many experiments to perform and our stable of volunteers is nearly bankrupt. So, elf, as your race\'s self-proclaimed name implies... Do you have blood to spare? Fresh blood is welcome blood indeed...', 0),
	(12783, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a fine, robust specimen you are. We have many experiments to perform and our stable of volunteers is nearly bankrupt. Fresh blood is welcome blood indeed, and the rage in your blood could fuel hours of research.', 0),
	(12784, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a fine, robust specimen you are. We have many experiments to perform and our stable of volunteers is nearly bankrupt. Fresh blood is welcome blood indeed, and I\'m sure someone of your stature has blood to spare...', 0),
	(12785, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, very good. The diseases this rotted head carries are deadly, but we must not shy from danger or from what we find distasteful. Some day, $n, you will learn that damnation is the path to salvation...', 0),
	(12786, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, very good. The diseases this rotted head carries are deadly, but we must not shy from danger or from what we find distasteful. Some day, $n, you will learn that damnation is the path to salvation...', 0),
	(12787, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, what a fine specimen you are. The disease, -- diseases -- dancing through your brain must offer you visions so sublime. We will spend long nights in conversation, you and I, and I will pick from you your thoughts as I slowly extract the meat from your skull.$b$bDo not fear, little one. The knowledge gained from your sacrifice will be awesome. You are a gift to the forsaken; you will herald a new age of respect for us among the peoples of this world. Your place in our history is assured...', 0),
	(12788, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, very good. The diseases this rotted head carries are deadly, but we must not shy from danger or from what we find distasteful. Some day, $n, you will learn that damnation is the path to salvation...', 0),
	(12789, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. Valus must have received my report.$b$bLet\'s get to work, $r.', 13623),
	(12790, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, $c. Now you know the way to get down to Crystalsong Forest and also how to return.', 15595),
	(12791, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Dalaran.$b$bI\'ll see to it that the ring is returned.', 0),
	(12792, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My report must have made it through to Kunz.$b$bIt is good to know that he is well.', 0),
	(12793, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Light shall prevail!', 0),
	(12794, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Dalaran.$B$BI\'ll see to it that the ring is returned.', 15595),
	(12795, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As it happens there is something you can do to be of assistance, $c.', 15595),
	(12796, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Dalaran.$b$bI\'ll see to it that the ring is returned.', 0),
	(12797, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well.$b$bWoe unto our enemies. Woe unto those who serve the Lich King and threaten the titans\' creations -- for the Etymidian is here.', 0),
	(12798, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your inscription ability has grown, scribe. The tarot cards are of great interest to the Darkmoon Faire, so do not hesitate to call upon us if you manage to create more. We are not without our own skilled tradesmen, so please allow us to offer something in trade for the cards.', 0),
	(12799, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c.$b$bThis should save my men some precious time.', 15595),
	(12800, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Highlord and the other death knights are preparing to strike! We will squeeze the last remnants of life out of this place.', 15354),
	(12801, 1, 1, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There will be no atonement for us, $N. We are forever damned to walk the earth as monsters. While the Lich King may have loosed his grip upon us, the specters of our past will forever haunt our memories.$B$BWe must make amends in the only way we know how: Death...$B$BI ask you now to join me in Acherus as a Knight of the Ebon Blade. Together we will destroy the Lich King and end the Scourge.', 15354),
	(12802, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Impressive, mon! Fate be kind in bringin\' us together.$b$bSoon I be avengin\' me bruddas by cleansin\' Drak\'Tharon, and you be awarded Drak\'Tharon\'s greatest treasure.', 15595),
	(12803, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are not of this land. But you also are not with the Scourge.$b$bWhat should I make of you?', 0),
	(12804, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that\'s a meal! If anything good came of the shipwreck, it\'s got to be that we\'ve been spared eating nothing but salt beef for the next month! Thank you again, $N.', 13623),
	(12805, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $n. It is a shame that the pillar has fallen, but we must salvage what we can.', 0),
	(12806, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s about damned time! No doubt that Baron Sliver took his sweet time in sending you to me.$B$BI should have that empty space above his shoulders removed!', 0),
	(12807, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'In their folly, the Argent Crusade has chosen to turn a blind eye upon the presence of the Scarlet Onslaught. We will not.$B$BWe do not care if they might assist in the battle against the Lich King. We do not believe them worthy of existence. We will be their end, once and for all!', 0),
	(12808, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$gBrother:Sister; $r, I am proud to stand with you during our days of need. Bless you, and may the clever eyes of your race help find a path to our salvation..', 0),
	(12809, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Inconceivably immaculate! This device stores Light energy at levels beyond those of any source yet known! Oh, the possible applications shiver my whiskers and curl my toes. Ho ho! The anti-nocturnal photo-dispersement geno-actuator I could build with this would turn dusk into dawn! The Scourge won\'t know what hit them. We\'ll destroy them all in one pull of a lever!', 0),
	(12810, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. Take a moment to let the saltwater dry from your skin before we continue.', 0),
	(12811, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a fine, robust specimen you are. We have many experiments to perform and our stable of volunteers is nearly bankrupt. Fresh blood is welcome blood indeed, and your primal blood could fuel hours of research.', 0),
	(12812, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, very good. The diseases this rotted head carries are deadly, but we must not shy from danger or from what we find distasteful. Some day, $n, you will learn that damnation is the path to salvation...', 0),
	(12813, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The draenei death knight fixes you with a cold stare, her eyes dead as the grave. A sly grin creeps across her features.>$b$bI\'ll have more of the tincture prepared tomorrow. Until then, be well.', 0),
	(12814, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh yeah this is gonna be good!$b$bStand back... I\'m gonna call down the wrath of the blood ritual!', 0),
	(12815, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s the spirit! And you know, I need this done everyday that we\'re here.$b$bI hope you\'ll come back again tomorrow. Your bone gryphon will be waitin\'.', 0),
	(12816, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm. From what you\'ve told me, the voices within the circles... they must be used for communication of some kind. I shudder to think what unnatural minds are contacted through such magic. Regardless, you seem to have emerged whole and sane. The Argent Dawn appreciates your service.', 0),
	(12817, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm. From what you\'ve told me, the voices within the circles... they must be used for communication of some kind. I shudder to think what unnatural minds are contacted through such magic. Regardless, you seem to have emerged whole and sane. The Argent Dawn appreciates your service.', 0),
	(12818, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 120, 0, 0, 'These will do nicely, thanks!$B$BDid you happen to see Dim out there? I sent him out a long while back and he never came back. I hope he\'s alright.$B$BSpeaking of which... I wonder where Janks is...', 15595),
	(12819, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Ha ha! These are them! Thank you kindly. I hope you didn\'t have too much trouble traversing the field.', 15595),
	(12820, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'So... here I sat, basking in the awesomeness that is me, and in the distance, I hear a pop! Then another! Then a dozen more! And a smile crept onto my face at the thought of all those magnataur and snobolds eagerly rushing to their own deaths.$B$BWas it glorious?', 15595),
	(12821, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent!$B$B<A fierce grin creeps onto Ricket\'s face.>$B$BLet the destruction begin!', 15595),
	(12822, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Haha! That\'ll teach those brutes to waste our time. From this day forth, green skin will strike fear into the hearts of all magnataur!', 15595),
	(12823, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The whole mountain shook! Was it gorgeous? I bet it was! How could it not be?$B$BAnd the Inventor\'s League tells me all of my inventions just blow up. Darn right they do! Hah!', 15595),
	(12824, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You blew the whole place up? Way to go! I bet Gino got a kick out of that.$B$BWe really appreciate all of the help you\'ve lent us, $n. How \'bout a souvenir for your troubles?', 15595),
	(12826, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, aren\'t these just the cutest little packets of destruction you\'ve ever seen?!', 15595),
	(12827, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope they weren\'t too hesitant to share the wealth. We\'ve been pretty forgiving with them picking through our leftovers thus far.', 15595),
	(12828, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And it\'s already well-done! I outdo myself sometimes.$B$BThanks much, friend!', 15595),
	(12829, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha ha! Good to see you\'re up for some dirty work.$B$BMuch appreciated there, pal!', 15595),
	(12830, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Woo! That\'s a ripe stench right there! You had to get hands-on with some of those snobolds, didn\'t ya?$B$BI do appreciate it though!', 15595),
	(12831, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should cut it... I hope Ricket can put something together for me. Ready to get out of there, then?', 15595),
	(12832, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for helping out our miner back there, $n! I should be able to put together an antidote no problem.$B$BIf you stumble into Tore again, tell her that she\'s a jerk for me, will ya?', 15595),
	(12833, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I like you. In fact, you rock!$b$bYay for you!', 0),
	(12836, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Groovy! You\'re my kind of $r.', 15595),
	(12838, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hand them over. I will sift through the useless ones and if there\'s anything actionable, I will call upon you.$b$bEither way, return tomorrow. It is well known that they change their plans on a daily basis.', 0),
	(12839, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A note written by Westwind? Why didn\'t you say so?$b$b<Arete tears the letter from your hand to read it.>$b$bThe fool! He\'s actually here?!$b$b<The lord-commander laughs.>$b$bThis is new information. I wonder how he imagines that he\'s going to conquer the world once he\'s taken down the Lich King? Not that he could accomplish either task in his wildest imaginings.', 0),
	(12840, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They resurrected Landgren? He\'s the one that will know where the grand admiral is then!', 0),
	(12841, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I wasn\'t sure you were coming back.  I dread to think what will happen to me if I stay here for much longer.', 15595),
	(12842, 25, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Remember these words, death knight: The Runeforge is a Scourge instrument. It exists only in Acherus, Naxxramas and the heart of Icecrown! You may only emblazon your weaponry at a Runeforge.$B$BReturn often and emblazon all of your weapons. A death knight must be prepared for all that would dare oppose $g him:her;!', 14480),
	(12843, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it!  Our boys are back!', 15595),
	(12844, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks, $N!  We\'ll see what we can do to salvage these parts!', 15595),
	(12846, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re definitely not with the Hyldnir... so what are you here for?  Ah... you must be looking for the new prisoner!', 15595),
	(12847, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hidden caves on the backside of the island. How very interesting.$b$bWell, at least now I know where all of my missing spies are.', 0),
	(12848, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As expected, my chosen knight has triumphed! You are ready, $N.', 14480),
	(12849, 1, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Within the Hall of Command you will find the schools of blood, frost and unholy. Each school has a trainer that can provide you with knowledge in the various dark arts.$B$BI, Lord Thorval, am the headmaster of the school of blood. Lady Alistra reigns over unholy and the arch-lich, Amal\'thazad, holds dominion over frost.$B$BYou must return here whenever you gain power and train!', 14480),
	(12850, 5, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The war has begun, death knight! I shall place you upon my finest gryphon and deliver you to Death\'s Breach. Chaos, death, destruction! You will herald in all of this and more!\n', 14480),
	(12851, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps you do have the heart of a warrior.$b$bTime will tell...', 15595),
	(12852, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'MAL\'GANIS?!!$b$b<The lord-commander laughs with abandon.>$b$bThe fools were taken in by the demons yet again and now they are destroyed!$b$bI trust that my favorite $c will stick around long enough to help us finish off the rest of them? Perhaps one of these would convince you?', 0),
	(12853, 3, 1, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Welcome to K3!$B$BWe came here to make our way into those peaks and get our fair share of some of those amazing titan machines. Progress on that end has been somewhat minimal, though. Gnolls, snobolds, magnataur... there\'s no shortage of trouble to go around... not to mention, we can\'t seem to keep any fliers in the air without their motors freezing.$B$BThere\'s plenty of work to be done though - lend a hand, eh?', 15595),
	(12854, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Archaeologist Andorin looks at you expectantly.>$B$BYou were supposed to come back with Brann, not a piece of paper. What\'s going on here?', 0),
	(12855, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You... you\'re not a member of the Explorers\' League, at least not one I remember. But, if you recovered the communicator, they must\'ve sent you. Good, that\'s almost what I was hoping for.$B$B', 13623),
	(12856, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your efforts appear to have been successful, sister.$b$bYou have brought glory to the Brunnhildar!', 15595),
	(12857, 7, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Chief Rageclaw cries.>$B$BHad Ragemane since pup. Sad day for Rageclaw. First troll attack Rageclaw, then troll make Ragemane bad. Rageclaw never trade with troll again!', 15595),
	(12858, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! Now that we have the disk, you must use it to open the Inventor\'s vault!', 13623),
	(12859, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It strange because I know you put fire out, but fire still burning. Maybe this thing not so good after all, eh? Still, Moky pay you for what you do! Hopefully troll burn too!', 15595),
	(12860, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Brann looks at the disk as you hold it up.>$B$BI can\'t tell if there\'s anything stored there or not! You have to tell me what happened.$B$B<You describe the data retrieval process.>$B$BSo it worked? At least we can count on Mimir to be systematic. Can\'t say that for the rest of these Keepers from what I\'ve been hearing... ', 13623),
	(12861, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rageclaw thank you, $N. Though Rageclaw Den probably lost forever and troll-Rageclaw friendship also lost forever... and also now I think of it, Ragemane lost forever too. Also brother-in-law. He gone. Hrm, have you seen Chief\'s mate? I think she gone too.$B$BMaybe you go now. Chief a little depressed.', 15595),
	(12862, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ow! That looked painful. It was a pretty grand entrance though, lad!$b$bWelcome to Frosthold! Are ya here to help us find a path into Icecrown?', 0),
	(12863, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Medical supplies? Thank you! Not exactly sure what to do with them to be honest, but I\'m sure they\'ll be useful.$B$BIt\'s good to meet you... there\'s such a colorful variety among your peoples. We\'re not used to having visitors up this way very often - it\'s good to have some fresh company.', 0),
	(12864, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'When a scout doesn\'t come back for this long... that\'s about the expected result. The harpies then?$B$BKing Stormheart has us train hard year round... he\'s turned us into amazing fighters. At times like this, I understand why it\'s necessary. He\'s the wisest and strongest leader I\'ve yet seen among our people... don\'t let his peachy skin fool ya.', 0),
	(12865, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, kindly... and I\'m sure they\'re quite appreciative too. They make powerful allies; you\'ll be well off being on this side of their graces.', 0),
	(12866, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s dirty work, I know, but we appreciate it. Now what was the name the scout mentioned... Sirana?', 0),
	(12867, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good stuff, $G lad:lass;. You\'re making fast friends.$B$BIf you stop back by soon, I\'m sure we can find one that will let you ride... they should know that you\'re trustworthy now.', 0),
	(12868, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s done then. Thank you.$B$BI\'ve spoken with Fjorlin - he said that his men will take charge of keeping the harpies down a bit. As long as we don\'t let up again, they won\'t find the courage to think they can attack our people.$B$BI know this wasn\'t the most tasteful work - take this as a token of my appreciation.', 0),
	(12869, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t see the drakes being dissuaded so easily. Stop back by tomorrow if you think you can spare more time to help.', 13623),
	(12870, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Beaut! Yer a good one you are.$B$BTilt one back wi\' me! Let us celebrae\' this glorious find!', 0),
	(12871, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By Muradin\'s beard! Is that what I think it is?! Brann\'s really outdone himself this time... and you too for that matter! The boys back home are never going to believe this.', 13623),
	(12872, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s it! That\'s the first half of Norgannon\'s keystone. Well done, $N. When I get back to Ironforge, I\'m going to have you inducted as an honorary member in the Explorers\' League!', 13623),
	(12873, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Norgannon\'s Core? Never heard of it. I might well know someone that has though.', 13623),
	(12874, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha! Grand tale $G lad:lass;... perhaps ye have a bit of frostborn blood in ye, eh? Yer not just talk anyway, and that\'s what I needed to hear.', 13623),
	(12875, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Drom coughs up a bit of blood.>$B$BNorgannon\'s Core, eh? I\'ve spent a fair number of days trying to find anything I could about it myself, but it seems to be one of the relics that\'s still guarded. With reason I suppose.$B$BIf King Stormheart sent you, he surely must see something noble in ye... and I\'m not one to refuse my king.', 13623),
	(12876, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Grim news, $G lad:lass;. Those iron dwarves seem to be increasing in numbers... we\'ve been seeing them all over the mountains. I smell war coming.$B$BThank you for dealing with this bunch... a little more time bought.', 13623),
	(12877, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Drom\'s ring? I am to assume Drom is not well if he did not introduce you directly. I am sorry to hear of that. Drom is a noble dwarf, if an inquisitive one.$B$BOn what business have you come then?', 13623),
	(12878, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<As the chest opens, air rushes out into the chamber, carrying with it the musty smell of something that has been here for countless years. Norgannon\'s Core rests in the bottom of the chest, undisturbed by the ages.>', 13623),
	(12879, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Someone is using the Forge of Wills to create this army... Ulduar is no longer safe.$B$B$R, I am pleased that you were able to reach the core before these abominations were.', 13623),
	(12880, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re brilliant, $G lad:lass;! Brilliant! This will be a glorious day indeed.$B$BQuickly, hand me the core before those iron dwarves make their way down here.', 13623),
	(12882, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will do nicely! I am much obliged. Perhaps a drink for your troubles?', 15595),
	(12883, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If this is the same Drakuru from Drak\'Tharon Keep we are going to need... outside assistance.$B$BDeath knights of Acherus are stationed nearby, undoubtedly following the same trail of Scourge destruction that lead the Argent Crusade here. As half of our army is tied up at the Argent Stand, battling crazed Drakkari trolls, we will have to join forces with the Knights of the Ebon Blade.$B$B<Lantinga mutters under his breath.>$B$BI was hoping I\'d never have to see those scoundrels again after Light\'s Hope...', 15595),
	(12884, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Stefan reads the missive, then crumples it up and tosses it into the fire.>$B$BOld news. The Argent Crusade is - once again - late to the party. We\'ve been tracking Drakuru since Grizzly Hills. He is slated for eradication.', 15595),
	(12885, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you know Brann Bronzebeard, then? He is our closest ally among those of the flesh. We are as brothers in the struggle against Loken and his followers, in the struggle for Ulduar.', 0),
	(12886, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sif... is that you?', 15595),
	(12887, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps now we can really get something done. Don\'t be fooled though, the Lich King can still \'see\' through his Scourge minions.$b$bThat\'s why you\'re here.', 0),
	(12888, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You begin performing the repairs indicated by the access card. When the repairs are complete, you close the access panel and throw the power switch.>', 0),
	(12889, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You examine the display on the repaired prototype console. At least one of Mimir\'s schematics seems to have survived the long period between maintenance cycles. From the diagrams and instructions displayed in the schematic\'s file, you could easily construct the mechagnome shown.', 0),
	(12891, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Quickly, hand them to me and stay out of sight!$B$BThe rod, the hook, and the rope are all very self-evident in their usage when combined. I just need to infuse the result with the essences and we\'ll be ready to proceed.$B$BIt\'s all very mundane in its composition, but extraordinary in its application!', 0),
	(12892, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps now we can really get something done. Don\'t be fooled though, the Lich King can still \'see\' through his Scourge minions.$B$BThat\'s why you\'re here.', 0),
	(12893, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We will put those three to good use once we finally take the vault.$B$BSpeaking of which....', 0),
	(12894, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Everything was fine until the Scourge attacked. They took off with Dargath, Gerk and Burr and they also destroyed our ride. Guess who led that attack?$B$B<MacKellar nods.>$B$BNavarius...$B$BSeems this whole area is some type of factory for Scourge. We\'re in the middle of a damned undead mine field!', 15595),
	(12895, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Of course, with our luck, I probably could\'ve predicted this. Well, we\'re not going to let him get away that easily. Let\'s see what that note says.', 15595),
	(12896, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'General Lightsbane and his forces are defeated? The Shadow Vault is taken?', 0),
	(12897, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'General Lightsbane and his forces are defeated? The Shadow Vault is taken?', 0),
	(12898, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good of you to return. As you can see, we have our hands full here.', 0),
	(12899, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good of you to return. As you can see, we have our hands full here.', 0),
	(12900, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will do nicely.  I\'ll have the harness ready for you in no time.', 15595),
	(12901, 273, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What is this junk! Ah, damn it all! It\'s useless. Scourge metal isn\'t gonna do the trick. What are we going to do?', 15595),
	(12902, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is a scroll floating in the air above the strange altar. This must be what Crusader Lord Lantinga is looking for!', 15595),
	(12903, 1, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It was a great sacrifice that those three made and it won\'t soon be forgotten. Their passing will not be in vain. We will be victorious!', 15595),
	(12904, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Gerk is dying.>$B$BTh... They say these Vargul are the... the ones that weren\'t found worthy by the Lich King. Can... Can you im... imagine it? Just th... think how powerful the... the... worthy must be...$B$BI\'ll say a prayer for you in the hereafter, hero... May you never have to face them in number.', 15595),
	(12905, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was expecting a replacement for one of my overseers.  It\'s about time you showed up.$B$BLet\'s put you to work.', 15595),
	(12906, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad for a new overseer.  I\'ve another task for you if you\'re feeling brave today.', 15595),
	(12907, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If I had any reservations regarding your commitment when you first arrived, I no longer have any.  With just a little more effort you could be a permanent member of my operation.', 15595),
	(12908, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew you\'d be back!  Get me out of these shackles and I\'ll help you find the goblin.', 15595),
	(12909, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So Boktar has volunteered Frostbite for an errand, eh? Well, this had better be important. He knows better than to try to separate a hunter from her pet!', 15595),
	(12910, 25, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<An image of a dwarf appears as you activate the communicator. It can only be Brann Bronzebeard.>$B$B<From the look on his face, Brann seems shocked to see you and begins gesturing furiously.>', 15595),
	(12912, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A... A storm giant? I don\'t know about this, $N. That sounds risky. On the other hand, I don\'t think we have too many other options.$B$BIf I do this you have to promise me that you will get your giant friend to help us deal with Navarius and his cronies.', 15595),
	(12913, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Boktar will not be happy that you didn\'t find Brann, but at least you didn\'t come back empty-handed. Now, let\'s see what we can do about this babbling dwarf.', 15595),
	(12914, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thankfully we weren\'t in short supply of explosives. Putting together the jumbo seaforium charge should be no problem with the materials you brought me.', 15595),
	(12915, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, it is done then.$b$bLet us hope it is enough.', 15595),
	(12916, 53, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'FREEDOM!$B$BDo not be afraid, little one. Gymer is an honorable giant. Like you and your people, I too wish to see the Scourge driven away from this land and the Lich King destroyed. I will help you, as promised, to the best of my ability.', 15595),
	(12917, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You should be able to communicate with the dwarf now. Ask Boktar what he requires of you. There is little time to lose.', 15595),
	(12918, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are perfect for replenishing my stock.  Not only will I teach you the art of gemcutting perfection, but I cut one of them gems into its perfect form which you may have as a reward.', 0),
	(12919, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Unbelievable! This will be a story for the ages, $N! One $g man:woman; rode upon the head of the king of storm giants and decimated an entire Scourge army!$B$BAnd I was there to see it all happen...', 15595),
	(12920, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Boktar listens as you describe your conversation with Brann.>$B$BThere\'s truth to the dwarf\'s words. Vor\'takh\'s plan is not the way of the Horde. If Brann Bronzebeard knows of a way to stop these iron dwarves and their patron, it serves us to help him.', 15595),
	(12921, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re here -- good.  I think I know where your goblin is.', 15595),
	(12922, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You place the metal on the anvil and immediately upon adding the sparks they work the ore furiously.$b$bWhen at last they burn out, you are left with a large piece of metal that gleams with a light of its own.', 15595),
	(12924, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It would seem that I have refined my technique considerably. That, or the legends surrounding this anvil are true.$b$bThis suit of armor is superior to the last, and took less material to create.$b$bWith the excess, I was able to fashion you a little something as payment for your assistance.', 15595),
	(12925, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have our thanks, sister.  We cannot allow our valiant traditions to be corrupted.', 15595),
	(12926, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was quick! Now that we have the disk, we have to find out how to use it to unlock the first half of the archive key.', 15595),
	(12927, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Brann looks at the disk as you hold it up.>$B$BI can\'t tell if there\'s anything stored there or not, $g lad:lass;. You\'ll have to tell me what happened.$B$B<You describe the data retrieval process.>$B$BSo it worked? At least we can count on Keeper Mimir to be systematic.', 15595),
	(12928, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s it! That\'s the first half of Norgannon\'s keystone. Well done, $N. I\'ve had Archaeologist Andorin on the lookout for clues to the shell\'s whereabouts for a long time. He\'s never going to believe me when I tell him it was an intrepid $r who found it instead.', 15595),
	(12929, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you know Brann Bronzebeard, then? He is our closest ally among those of the flesh. We are as brothers in the struggle against Loken and his followers, in the struggle for Ulduar.', 0),
	(12930, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will allow us to patch up more of the fallen. Thank you, $N, on behalf of all who defend the refuge.', 15595),
	(12931, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve given the defenders something to cheer about. Seeing the enemy fall by your hand has reinvigorated them and bolstered their courage.', 15595),
	(12932, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad, friend. You might make some gold out here - if you manage to stay alive.', 0),
	(12933, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow! When I first saw Stinkbeard, I thought you were done for! Nice work!', 0),
	(12934, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Unbelievable! I thought this whole place was going to explode when it first appeared! You really dominated that round!', 0),
	(12935, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was worried for a while there, $N. When he busted out the seals and penguins... Well, I didn\'t know what to think to be honest. It looked pretty damn ridiculous.', 0),
	(12936, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Damn, I remember Korrak from way back in my younger days when I used to work for the Frostwolf Clan. He would never shut up! I think you just did the world a great service, $N.', 0),
	(12937, 396, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The warriors that you\'ve healed will aid us in holding the line even longer. If we are to truly be free of the iron threat, we must find a way to strike at them behind the lines.', 15595),
	(12938, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s a pleasure to finally meet you, $n. We owe you a great deal, but we\'re not done with you yet.$b$bThere is a vrykul city just over the mountains to the west, a place called Jotunheim.$b$bThe vrykul there are in a constant state of challenge to \'ascend\'. The winners go to Ymirheim to serve as the Lich King\'s elite warrior caste, the Ymirjar, and the losers are reduced to Scourged Vargul.$b$bYou are going to be my instrument to see to it that more Vargul than Ymirjar emerge.', 0),
	(12939, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Already I\'m hearing reports of the prowess you displayed on the Savage Ledge. Excellent, $n... excellent!$b$b$b$bAnd now I think it\'s time to issue a decree to the thane of those vrykul that you so easily defeated.', 0),
	(12940, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 0),
	(12941, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 0),
	(12942, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The val\'kyr are nothing but the Lich King\'s lapdogs.  They will be put down like the scum they are.  They\'ve made their choice, now they have to live with the consequences.', 15595),
	(12943, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Duke Lankral nods his approval at your report of success.>$b$bWe face a foe that dwarfs us, not only in stature, but also numerically. If we are to win the battle for Icecrown, we must outthink them!$b$bWith Ufrang dead, that gives us an advantage in Jotunheim. Let us see if we can capitalize on it.', 0),
	(12944, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 0),
	(12945, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 0),
	(12946, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 0),
	(12947, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 0),
	(12948, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it, $N! That was the most exciting fight yet! What are you going to do with your winnings? Me? I\'m going to Dalaran and blowing it all in the Underbelly. Lot of hot action going on down there!', 0),
	(12949, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $r. Just hand me the key, I\'ll take care of it myself.', 0),
	(12950, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 0),
	(12951, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What?! We can ill-afford to lose one death knight, let alone an entire contingent!!!', 0),
	(12952, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will have to do. I can teach you the art of gemcutting perfection, and give you proof of my skills as well.', 0),
	(12953, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that is what I call dedication!  Those traitors might have a new master now, but they\'ll never forget their sisters\' parting gift.', 15595),
	(12954, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey! I know you. Your victory at the Ring of Blood was talked about for months! Too bad you forfeited the championship when you failed to show up to defend your title! Easy come, easy go, eh? At least you\'re still alive.', 0),
	(12955, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was important, $n. By driving them off, you\'re keeping them from interfering with whatever we need you to do over there.', 0),
	(12956, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You notice Thorim\'s stern countenance brighten with recognition as you present the ore.', 15595),
	(12957, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I had hoped that more of the captives would choose to join us, but I do not blame them. Willing allies are few and far between, and we are thankful that you have lent your blade to our cause.', 15595),
	(12958, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here is your Dalaran Jewelcrafter\'s Token as promised. Come back tomorrow and I am sure I will have another item I need from you!', 0),
	(12959, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here is your Dalaran Jewelcrafter\'s Token as promised. Come back tomorrow and I am sure I will have another item I need from you!', 0),
	(12960, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here is your Dalaran Jewelcrafter\'s Token as promised. Come back tomorrow and I am sure I will have another item I need from you!', 0),
	(12961, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here is your Dalaran Jewelcrafter\'s Token as promised.  Come back tomorrow and I am sure I will have another item I need from you!', 0),
	(12962, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here is your Dalaran Jewelcrafter\'s Token as promised. Come back tomorrow and I am sure I will have another item I need from you!', 0),
	(12963, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here is your Dalaran Jewelcrafter\'s Token as promised. Come back tomorrow and I am sure I will have another item I need from you!', 0),
	(12964, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Bouldercrag reaches out to take the ore, but then recoils.>$B$BThat ore... I can\'t touch it. It seethes with unnatural energy. No creature of stone can handle it. What do they mean to do with this?', 15595),
	(12965, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Bouldercrag nods grimly.>$B$BYou\'ve weakened the stormforged considerably, but they\'ll keep fighting. Their casualties matter nothing to them, while our defenders continue to fall. Even if it costs them a hundred or a thousand iron corpses, they\'ll keep fighting until we\'ve been pounded to gravel.', 15595),
	(12966, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Reforging Thorim\'s armor? It can be done.$b$bFirst though, there\'s the matter of the anvil...', 15595),
	(12967, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An honorable performance, $r. I shall inform the king of your assistance.$b$bThe anvil is nearly cool enough. I shall see you in Dun Niffelem soon.', 15595),
	(12968, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yulda had it coming.  No one gets away with insulting the Hyldsmeet.  Not even one of our own.', 15595),
	(12969, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, young one.  It looks like our deal has been satisfied on both our ends.', 15595),
	(12970, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s settled then.  You will compete in the Hyldsmeet and with my help you\'ll restore great Thorim to his rightful place.', 15595),
	(12971, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it, $N.  You\'ve bested some of the fiercest fighters the Hyldnir race has to offer.', 15595),
	(12972, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Think we\'ll give you your own bear just like that?  You\'ll have to prove yourself before you get anything from us.$B$BDo not think too highly of yourself just because you bested a few challengers in the Hyldsmeet.', 15595),
	(12973, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'King Stormheart sends his most sincere thanks for reuniting him with his brothers. It seems he\'s off to settle a score now - perhaps you\'ll meet with him again on Arthas\'s doorstep.', 13623),
	(12974, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Shifty sent you, eh?', 0),
	(12975, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another good deed you have done on Thorim\'s behalf, $c.$b$bThis will help to soften the hearts of my people towards him.', 15595),
	(12976, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Njormeld\'s eyes become noticeably moist as he pours the contents of the bag onto the anvil.>$b$bThe Horn of Hodir....$b$bThis was a sacred gift to our people from Hodir himself, $r. It is a relic of great importance to us.$b$bWhen you next return to our stronghold you shall see the fruits of your labor.$b$bFarewell.', 15595),
	(12977, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are filled with a sense of peace and contentment knowing that the once tormented souls of Thunderfall are now resting peacefully.', 15595),
	(12978, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There may be hope for victory, $N. We have never been able to sustain an attack on the stormforged, but with your efforts, Valduran may yet fall!', 15595),
	(12979, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Careful, now. Keep that plate as far away from me as you can. Even being in its presence is enough to inflict pain.$B$BBut you\'re right, $N, these are gigantic armor plates for a war golem of normal size. What would the stormforged be doing with them? There\'s only one way to find out.', 15595),
	(12980, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Bruor listens as you describe what you learned in the workshop.>$B$BSo Valduran\'s master has given him this sinister metal to construct a giant weapon? That must be what he intends to use for the final strike against us! We need to stop him before he\'s able to complete it and unleash this weapon.', 15595),
	(12981, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You feel a sense of accomplishment as you realize that your efforts continue to strengthen the renewed bonds between Thorim and the Sons of Hodir.', 15595),
	(12982, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. With the death knights that you freed, we\'ll be able to hold the line... for now.', 0),
	(12983, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m impressed.  I never thought I would see an icemaw matriarch again.  Especially not one this size.', 15595),
	(12984, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At last, Valduran is dead, and the stormforged are weakened, but if his boasting is true, we must continue fighting the stormforged in his absence. This weapon they\'re building could be the end of us.', 15595),
	(12985, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is nearly done.$b$bWith this artifact in place, Dun Niffelem shall be warned of impending dangers before they are upon us.', 15595),
	(12986, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The news you bear forth is grave indeed. I do not know the fate of the remaining watchers, but their absence spells dark times for all of the lands of Azeroth.$B$BI shall examine the knowledge contained in the databank that you have returned and attempt to fully assess the situation. I believe I am in possession of knowledge that you deem more pertinent at this moment however, so I shall allow you to partake in said wisdom first.', 13623),
	(12987, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Njormeld gazes up at Hodir\'s Helm, visibly moved.>$b$bThat will do, little $r.$b$bThat will do....', 15595),
	(12988, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work! Oh, it won\'t stop the iron dwarves, but it\'ll take them valuable time to rebuild those forges. I daresay we\'ve gained the advantage.', 15595),
	(12989, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The jormungar are vile creatures.  You did well in destroying them.', 15595),
	(12991, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There were days when I could never ask someone to do what you did, but my experience with the iron dwarves has extinguished those feelings. We have bought time against the enemy\'s advance.', 15595),
	(12992, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N is my bestest little $r!', 0),
	(12993, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Bouldercrag begins to look over the documents, his eyes wide.>$B$BI had no idea the irons were capable of this! Our men will have no chance against this behemoth if it\'s completed. Fortunately, it looks like they\'re still lacking a key part.', 15595),
	(12994, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As you slide the chain back around the denmother\'s neck she licks your face approvingly.', 15595),
	(12995, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N. Let them see the desecrated corpses of their fallen comrades and think twice about striking at us!$B$BIf you come back tomorrow, I will make certain to have more banners prepared for you.', 0),
	(12996, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad.  I was hoping Kirgaraak would snap your neck so I could keep your bear.$B$BJust joking, sister.  Well... half-joking.  That\'s a really nice bear you\'ve got.', 15595),
	(12997, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You really did it!  You made it out with your health.  Wish we could say the same for your bear.$B$BIt\'s going to take a while for her to recover.  Fortunately you won\'t need her for a while.', 15595),
	(12998, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the heart in the hands of Narvir, the colossus will achieve its full power! We\'ll have no choice but to fight it.', 15595),
	(12999, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n, you came.$b$bAlready I have heard of your activities on the Savage Ledge. This is good. I am glad that you seem willing to help with undermining the vrykul here at Jotunheim.$b$b$b$bYou and I are going to have a great deal of fun with them!', 0),
	(13000, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These furs are rather... large.  I\'d hate to see the worgs you had to face off with.$B$BWe\'re all very thankful.  The temperature is starting to drop already.', 15595),
	(13001, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Stand back, $r, and behold the fulfilling of a prophecy!', 15595),
	(13002, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dey be perfect mon\'.  Here is the art of gemcutting perfection for ya.', 0),
	(13003, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done.$b$bYou have stared certain death in the face and emerged victorious.$b$bBy single-handedly defeating such a mighty beast, you have brought great honor to Dun Niffelem!', 0),
	(13004, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you.  I shall teach you of gemcutting perfection and in addition give you a perfect gem that I have cut.', 0),
	(13005, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s a good start.  But my brother\'s forces will not take long to regroup.  We must make our victory a decisive one.', 15595),
	(13006, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As you coat the helm with a thin layer of oil, the frost falls away and the surface gleams.', 15595),
	(13007, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve done it, we\'ve really done it! The refuge is spared and the stormforged are defeated! We must warn Brann before Loken gets it in his mind to try to rebuild his forces. The only way to secure the victory you have won today is to go into Ulduar and defeat Loken for all time!', 15595),
	(13008, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There are still many Argent Crusade soldiers out on that field and in Scourgeholme, $N. While your help is appreciated, there is still much left to be done.', 15595),
	(13009, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<As you present Thorim with the reforged suit of armor, he is visibly stricken by its splendor.>$b$bYou have done well, $r, but there remains much to be done.', 15595),
	(13010, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Words cannot express my gratitude, $c.$b$bYou have served me honorably. Please accept this token of my gratitude.', 15595),
	(13011, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So it is done.$b$bWe have heard the screams of Jormuttar as they echoed from across the valley.$b$bYou have done our people a service this day, little $r.', 15595),
	(13012, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to know the people of this land still pay homage to the olden races.  I bid you well, $N, and offer you this token...', 15050),
	(13013, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to know the people of this land still pay homage to the olden races.  I bid you well, $N, and offer you this token...', 15050),
