	(13501, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 0),
	(13502, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! And here, please... keep the basket!$B$BRemember, you can always return with more Noblegarden Chocolates to trade for additional items.', 0),
	(13503, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! And here, please... keep the basket!$B$BRemember, you can always return with more Noblegarden Chocolates to trade for additional items.', 15354),
	(13518, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. Some of them surely would not have made it without you.$B$BWe\'ll be taking the wounded to the main building once we have them all safely back in town. Perhaps you can meet us there later?', 15050),
	(13538, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I heard the explosion from here! Excellent job - we\'ve already begun rerouting the power into the Titan relic to super-charge our own forces.', 0),
	(13539, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now in order to kill the enemy, our men must be roused to anger; that there may be advantage from defeating the enemy, they must have their rewards. I hope that these are sufficient for your service to the Horde.', 0),
	(13542, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I cannot thank you enough, $N. Now we\'ll have a fighting chance to retake the ruins as soon as we are in better health.', 15050),
	(13543, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Without those three coaxing them, perhaps the flow of elementals into the Ruins of Auberdine will be stemmed.$B$BThank you, $N.', 15050),
	(13547, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So much death and pain. Can there be any doubt that there is more yet to come?$B$BAll I wish to do is move onward into the Goddess\'s embrace as do these others.$B$BBut first, let us see if we can keep even more misery and destruction from being spread.', 15050),
	(13548, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 0),
	(13549, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very fine specimens indeed, $N! These are sure to provide many hours of curious speculation amongst my colleagues back home.', 15595),
	(13556, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'One, two, three,... hehe, that be a good number o\' them, mon! Now we be safe for quite some time!', 0),
	(13558, 6, 2, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'Yalda? The spirits of others from the Ruins of Auberdine?$B$B<The druid ponders what you\'ve conveyed about your adventure in the ruins.>$B$BI remember them all. They will be dearly missed, but they have moved on into the Goddess\'s embrace and that is for the best.$B$BAnde\'thoras-ethil, may your troubles be diminished, $N!', 15050),
	(13559, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Sons of Hodir accept your tribute, small one.  You continue to prove your worth as an ally in more ways than one.', 15595),
	(13571, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Above the stale, unwashed stench, you catch a whiff of a familiar smell!  It appears as if this once-mighty adventurer has a real love for kungaloosh.$b$bPeeking through the bars, you can barely make out the recipe written on his arm....', 15354),
	(13573, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is no time to waste, $c.  It is taking every ounce of my power to keep Darkshore\'s entire landmass from being shattered and swept into the ocean... you must listen to me very carefully.', 15050),
	(13575, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have much respect for the great Malfurion Stormrage.  I cannot, however, leave my people in their time of need.  Maybe there is a way we can both help each other.', 15050),
	(13576, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The element of fire is unique in that attacking it indiscriminately can often lead it to spreading further... succeeding only in agitating its flames.$B$BWe are wiser than that, $N.  We are going to dispose of it properly.', 15050),
	(13577, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A terrible sadness surrounds the creature.  Its eyes stare beyond you as you approach it.', 15050),
	(13579, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If the great Malfurion requires my presence, it is my duty to heed his call.  It is also my duty to protect these ruins, however.$B$BPerhaps you\'ll help me fulfill both my obligations, $N?', 15050),
	(13580, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are in your debt, $N.  Perhaps now, with Malfurion\'s help, we can save the rest of Darkshore.', 15050),
	(13581, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is fortunate news, $N.  The furbolg may seem little more than a savage race, but their ties to the land are ancient and their shamans are second to none.', 15050),
	(13583, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The wildkin were once the guardians of the land.  It is good to hear they haven\'t all forgotten their old ways.', 15050),
	(13584, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s become clear, $N.  The elements won\'t be calm until Malfurion succeeds in returning balance to the land.  Aiding him is, in a way, also fulfilling my task.', 15050),
	(13585, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent job, $N!  Selenn\'s help in holding back the vortex will be invaluable.', 15050),
	(13586, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Malfurion calls?  Yes... I can hear his voice through the dream...', 15050),
	(13587, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $N.  You\'ve given me my freedom.  Let\'s see what we can do for your world now.', 15050),
	(13588, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are turning the tides, $N.  We should be able to contain further damage.$B$BMuch work still remains to be done.', 15050),
	(13592, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome back from your exercises, $N. Even while we practice for the competition, it\'s good to remind ourselves that the Scourge is still out there.', 0),
	(13593, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are proud that you have agreed to train with us and compete on our behalf.', 0),
	(13594, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The sentinel eyes you appreciatively for a moment.>$B$BA job well done, $c. If you\'re any indication of the quality of the $r adventurers we\'re going to be seeing more of, we should have this war against the orcs and their Horde taken care of faster than expected.', 15595),
	(13595, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have helped me to return to the ground, $N.$B$BNow my hair will cease to sprout for these creatures. Better yet, I will be regrown all the sooner.', 15595),
	(13600, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The marshal accepts the Blade of Drak\'Mar from you.>$B$BA fine weapon, and perfectly balanced. It will serve me well in the next match.', 0),
	(13602, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well done, $N. Your actions in the Zoram Strand against the naga are commendable.$B$BI know your feat was not easily accomplished, for the strength and guile of the naga is well known to the night elves. We know this, for we share a history with them.$B$BThe naga are cursed Highborne night elves. Ten thousand years ago, Queen Azshara made a pact of desperation with the Old Gods to save her surviving people from a watery grave.$B$BThe naga are the result of that pact.', 15595),
	(13603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So the tales were true? This is a fine blade and I have no doubt that it will serve me well in the tournament. You have my thanks, $N.', 0),
	(13604, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The platinum disc fits perfectly inside the console.  It begins to spin as its contents are scanned by white beams of light.', 15595),
	(13605, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aye, you\'re the fine $g lad : lass; who saved my Hollee!$B$BWell, I\'ve got a fitting reward for you here, I\'m sure. We really can\'t thank you enough for bringing her to safety, $N.', 15050),
	(13606, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent job, $N. We\'re one step closer to saving Azeroth!', 0),
	(13607, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s locked?  Figures!$B$BLet\'s see what information this junk heap can give us...', 15595),
	(13609, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ye did it! I don\'t know how, but ye did!', 0),
	(13610, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ye never cease to impress, $N.$b$bYe and me are having a pint together after all this is done, ye hear me?', 0),
	(13611, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve got to hand it to you, $N. Our odds might not be the best, but I feel a lot better with you lending a hand.', 0),
	(13614, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Stand by for verification.$b$bAccess to the Celestial Planetarium granted. Please retrieve your key.', 0),
	(13616, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The blade is as fine as the stories say. It would seem there\'s little reason to complete the repairs on my customary blade. Winter\'s Edge is far superior and I will continue to carry it. You have my thanks, $N.', 0),
	(13617, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello, $c.$B$BWhat\'s that? You say that Shyela sent you?$B$B<The night elf briskly rubs his nimble hands together.>$B$BVery well, let\'s get started.', 15595),
	(13623, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, Evenar was succesful. Actually, more to the point, YOU were successful.$B$BI cannot thank you enough, $c, but there is more that must be done to the leaves before they will serve as a curative for what ails the child, Relara.', 15595),
	(13624, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'d received a report about you from some of my scouts out in the forest but I had no idea how capable you are!$B$BThank you, $N. With what you\'ve accomplished the tide is turned. I\'ve no doubt now that we\'ll rout them by the end of the day!', 15595),
	(13625, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N. Mounted combat is often hard to pick up for those accustomed to fighting on foot. I have no doubt that you\'ll continue to improve with practice, which is more than I can say for some warriors.', 0),
	(13626, 274, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I do not look forward to writing the letter to the Argent Dawn embassy in Darnassus. At least we\'ll be able to send their most prized possessions back for their loved ones.$B$BI cannot thank you enough for your courage, $N. Please accept this on behalf of the post.', 15595),
	(13627, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All excellent planks, and the price is right, too! Even better, those Argent Crusade sticks-in-the-mud will never know. They\'ll get their precious coliseum and I\'ll get my early completion bonus. Now that\'s a win-win if I ever saw one.', 0),
	(13630, 2, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N.$B$BWith the moonstones of Ordil\'Aran deactivated, we should not need to worry about any further incursions of furbolg here.$B$BHowever, my scouts have returned with disturbing news from the furbolg village. There is an imminent danger massing there.$B$BI wonder, might I entice you to carry a warning to Astranaar for me?', 15595),
	(13631, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re here.  Let us hope this works.  For all our sakes.', 15595),
	(13632, 2, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are in your debt, $c. If I know anything about the furbolg, they do not like their noses bloodied.$B$BIt won\'t be long now before they tuck tail and return to their village.', 15595),
	(13633, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you\'re saying this knight\'s story is a sham? Most suspicious. Dishonorable at the least, and murderous at the worst. Still, we can\'t confront him until we know for certain whether he was involved in these murders.$B$BDo nothing to arouse his suspicions, $N. Discretion will serve us well as we continue to investigate.', 0),
	(13634, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you\'re saying this knight\'s story is a sham? Most suspicious. Dishonorable at the least, and murderous at the worst. Still, we can\'t confront him until we know for certain whether he was involved in these murders.$B$BDo nothing to arouse his suspicions, $N. Discretion will serve us well as we continue to investigate.', 15595),
	(13639, 5, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmph, it\'ll take more than a Dark Iron ambush to stop the deliveries!$b$bBut Saean... I would never have suspected him to be one of their sympathizers. We\'ve been working with him for almost a year now... maybe I missed the signs.$b$bWell, I\'ll consider that later.', 15354),
	(13641, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This one will do nicely. All that remains is to imbue it with the power of the Light, giving it the ability to find truth amid deception.', 15595),
	(13642, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the concoction blessed by the Light of Elune, it should be ready for delivery to Astranaar.$B$BThere is no time to waste, $N!', 15595),
	(13643, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you say Lorien Sunblaze was done in by poison and Sir Wendell was burnt alive? Dreadful ways to die, both of them. Only Conall was killed by cold steel, and from your description, it was a coward\'s strike, not honorable combat that laid him in his grave.$B$BAll three sparred with and were scheduled to fight the Black Knight. This cannot be a coincidence. Now, we must find a way to prove it was the Black Knight\'s work.', 15595),
	(13644, 33, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the death of the harbinger, I can begin to cleanse the lake.$B$BYou have my deepest thanks, $N. I mourn the loss of your friend, but know that his remains will fuel the reclamation of the forest hereabouts.', 15595),
	(13645, 18, 6, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'Teronis is dead?$B$B<The lady weeps softly for the loss of her friend and then composes herself after a moment.>$B$BWe must see to it that his sacrifice was not in vain. Are you willing to see this through, $c?$B$BVery well, allow me some time to think about how we should proceed. I will know shortly.', 15595),
	(13646, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Avana is alive?! I feared that she might be dead when we heard about the attack on Maestra\'s Post!$B$BAs you can see, we have our hands full with the Horde here as well.$B$BYou have given me the greatest gift by letting me know she is well. Any time that you wish to ride one of my nightsabers back to Maestra\'s Post, it is yours.', 15595),
	(13647, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello there, $G laddy:lass;! The mountaineers sent you over, eh? I do suspect we might have just the sort of work you\'re looking for. Welcome to the Farstrider Lodge!', 15354),
	(13648, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You brought that damned spy to justice! This is good news. We can all rest a little bit easier, not worrying about that one.', 15354),
	(13650, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Woo! I\'m relieved... I was worried they\'d all be destroyed by now. Thank you for checking in on them.', 15354),
	(13654, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Crusader Rhydalla examines the bag\'s contents with a look of disgust on her face.>$B$BIt\'s all here, $N: the poison that killed Lorien, a collection of knives, torches, and oil. No man has cause to possess these things here and no squire would do so without orders from his knightly master. We\'ve found our murderer, $N, but who is he working for?', 15595),
	(13655, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well look at that. You found one of our stolen documents!$B$BWe\'re much obliged for its return. Hopefully a bit of gold will suit your fancy for the finder\'s fee?', 15354),
	(13656, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello, $G sonny:lass;! You seem to have found one of our stolen documents, eh?$B$BThank you kindly for bringing it back to us. We\'ll gladly lend some coin as thanks for its return.', 15354),
	(13662, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Keep the residue pouring in!', 15595),
	(13663, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Crusader Rhydalla\'s face pales as she reads the orders.>$B$BThis can only mean one thing, $N. The Black Knight is a member of the Cult of the Damned and has been sent by Arthas to disrupt the tournament!$B$BThe Black Knight has proven himself a fearsome combatant, and you will need to be every bit as good if you wish to face him. When you are a champion, return to me and we\'ll find a way to ensure his defeat.', 15595),
	(13664, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the death of the Black Knight, the tournament may once again serve its purpose. The champions of the Horde and Alliance may demonstrate their skill at arms and train for the day when Arthas and his minions will no longer threaten us.$B$BYou have the thanks of the Argent Crusade, $N, and that of all who have answered our call.', 15595),
	(13665, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. Training against the other valiants is one of the best ways to prepare yourself for tournament competition. I know you\'ll make Stormwind proud, $N.', 0),
	(13666, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So there is some truth to those old tales? It seems they did not lie about the quality of the blade. Well done, $N. The champion who wields it will be a lucky man, indeed.', 0),
	(13667, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have entered your name in the rolls, $N. As an aspirant you will train with others who wish to compete in the tournament and hone your mounted combat skills. Once you have proven yourself, you will be allowed to enter the lowest rank of competition on behalf of your capital city.', 0),
	(13668, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have entered your name in the rolls, $n. As an aspirant you will train with others who wish to compete in the tournament and hone your mounted combat skills. Once you have proven yourself, you will be allowed to enter the lowest rank of competition on behalf of your capital city.', 0),
	(13669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'s no doubt that this is a blade of exquisite quality and balance. Now I understand why these weapons are so coveted among the champions of the Alliance.', 0),
	(13670, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The blade is as fine as the squire said it would be, but where did he find out about it? No matter; it will serve its new owner well. Perhaps it\'s only fair that Ironforge\'s grand champion be the one to wield it.', 0),
	(13671, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have shown yourself a capable combatant, $N and you will serve as an example to the rest of the aspirants who clamor to compete on behalf of the Alliance.', 0),
	(13672, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well, I will make the arrangements.', 0),
	(13673, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So there is some truth to those old tales? It seems they did not lie about the quality of the blade. Well done, $N. The champion who wields it will be a lucky man, indeed.', 15595),
	(13674, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'s no doubt that this is a blade of exquisite quality and balance. Now I understand why these weapons are so coveted among the champions of the Alliance.', 15595),
	(13675, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The blade is as fine as the valiant said it would be, but where did he find out about it? No matter; it will serve its new owner well. Perhaps it\'s only fair that Orgrimmar\'s grand champion be the one to wield it.', 0),
	(13676, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have shown yourself a capable combatant, $N and you will serve as an example to the rest of the aspirants who clamor to compete on behalf of the Horde.', 15595),
	(13677, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N. Mounted combat is often hard to pick up for those accustomed to fighting on foot. I have no doubt that you\'ll continue to improve with practice, which is more than I can say for some warriors.', 15595),
	(13678, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well, I will make the arrangements.', 15595),
	(13679, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Congratulations are in order, $N. You have bested your challenger and earned the right to advance to the rank of valiant.', 0),
	(13680, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Congratulations are in order, $N. You have bested your challenger and earned the right to advance to the rank of valiant.', 15595),
	(13681, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These should do. Just don\'t go around blabbing to those crusaders about where you got them from. I\'m sure they\'ll get upset. But, hey, it\'s not like the titans have come back for them. They\'re fair game, I say. Good work, $n.', 0),
	(13682, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N, you and your allies have spared the tournament from a devastating attack. Though our skytalon riders are brave, they  have their hands full keeping the peace on the tournament grounds and would be hard-pressed to defend the skies against the cult\'s attack. You have the thanks of the Argent Crusade and all who have gathered here to compete.', 0),
	(13683, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are in your debt, $c.$B$BUnable to complete their nefarious rituals, the satyr are now fighting a losing battle where they are unable to replenish their numbers.', 0),
	(13684, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome aboard then, Valiant $N. The Stormwind delegation is proud to count you among its members.', 0),
	(13685, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to meet you, valiant. Ironforge needs competitors like you to prevail in the tournament.', 0),
	(13688, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome aboard then, Valiant $n. The Gnomeregan delegation is proud to count you among its members.', 0),
	(13689, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to the Darnassus tournament delegation, $n. It will be a pleasure to train and compete alongside you.', 0),
	(13690, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome aboard then, Valiant $n. The Exodar\'s delegation is proud to count you among its members.', 0),
	(13691, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you want to compete for Orgrimmar? Just because you\'ve beaten up a few dummies doesn\'t mean you\'ll win, but you\'ll be training with the best from now on.', 0),
	(13693, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You think you have what it takes to compete for Sen\'jin? I think we\'ll be finding out.', 0),
	(13694, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'On behalf of Thunder Bluff and its warriors, I welcome you, $n. Always fight honorably and bravely beneath our banner.', 0),
