	(14088, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, shall we begin your Apprentice Riding training?', 0),
	(14089, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, shall we begin your Apprentice Riding training?', 0),
	(14090, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The sooner we get these stinking things out of my sight and into their cage, the faster my mood will improve. I wish the Argent Crusade had given the Sunreavers the care of this creature. They\'re enough alike that they ought to be able to understand each other.', 0),
	(14091, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s you again.  Looks like you\'re not one to hide in the face of danger.  Very well, then.', 15595),
	(14092, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll let the crusaders know that you\'ve just returned with a fresh load of food while the Silver Covenant was sitting on its heels.', 15595),
	(14093, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s no use, $N!  They\'re not letting up.', 15595),
	(14094, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent!  I\'ll make sure these get taken to a safe place.', 15595),
	(14095, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew that Kraken was not a match for the likes of you.  Without that Kraken disrupting those boats, those Kvaldir will have no choice but to retreat.  Great job, Champion!', 15595),
	(14096, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks to you, Kul and the aspirants will live fight the Scourge again. That\'s far from the first time someone\'s had to save Kul from himself. My only hope is that the crusaders can find a better outlet for his enthusiasm than allowing him to impart all of his bad habits to impressionable young aspirants.', 0),
	(14098, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good job, $N.  Thanks to you, many Gilneans will live to see another day.', 15595),
	(14099, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re all fine here.  A little shaken... but alive.', 15595),
	(14100, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, you\'ve mastered the four totems. You should be proud of your accomplishments so far, young $r, but this is only the beginning of your journey.$b$bHere, accept this gift from the Earthen Ring. Carry this relic with you and you will have the power of all four elements at your command.$b$bContinue your training, friend. Grave challenges are ahead for this world - I can hear it in the wind and feel it in the rumblings of the earth. We must be prepared for the worst.', 0),
	(14101, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The defeat of the drottinn will set the kvaldir to fighting amongst themselves, buying us time to use our advantage. The crusade and the tournament are in your debt, champion.', 15595),
	(14102, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have bought us valuable time to move against the Kvaldir and free the seas of these pests. Once again, the Argent Crusade is in your debt.', 15595),
	(14104, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ornolf\'s crew will want to avenge their leader, but without him, they will be easier to defeat. We must live to carry out our mission, to see Icecrown rid of the Scourge and other evils.', 15595),
	(14105, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are truly an example to all who have gathered beneath our banner, $N. Together, we will show the Scourge that we will not be defeated.', 15595),
	(14107, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done our fallen brethren a great service and spared us the need to face them again on the field of battle. As our campaign against the Scourge progresses, I find myself thinking about my own fate.$B$BShould I fall, $N, I would want someone like you to do for me what you have done for the spirits of the fallen this day. I could not bear the thought of forcing my own brothers to slay me again and again.', 15595),
	(14108, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Crusader, you may have bought those sailors just enough time to escape,  Maybe next time, those Silver Covenant and Sunreavers will listen before running head first at the enemy.', 15595),
	(14109, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, you are going to look so fine, but not as gorgeous as me! You\'re going to replace the Trade Prince any day now at the rate you\'re going!$B$BI can\'t wait to not have to work anymore! You\'re going to buy me everything that I want, right babe?$B$BLet me have all that stuff and I\'ll help you get into it right before the party.', 15595),
	(14110, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh yeah, you\'re going to look hot! You\'re going to replace the Trade Prince any day now at the rate you\'re going!$B$BI can\'t wait to be a kept man!$B$BLet me have all that stuff and I\'ll help you get into it right before the party.', 15595),
	(14111, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see you\'ve mastered use of the four totems. You are on your way to becoming one with the elemental spirits, but this is only the beginning of your journey.$b$bHere, accept this gift from the Earthen Ring. Carry this relic with you and you will have the power of all four elements at your command.$b$bYour training must continue! I sense a great many trials lie ahead for this world, and we will need the power of the elements behind us if we are to prevail.', 0),
	(14112, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad we\'ve gotten that done. It\'s not the most glorious task in the world, but when we partnered with the Argent Crusade, we promised to do all they asked of us without complaint. Of course, the same cannot be said of the Sunreavers.', 0),
	(14113, 4, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very nicely done, $g sir : ma\'am;. The party appears to have been a smashing success!$B$BEr... what\'s that?', 15595),
	(14115, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Phew, that was close, boss. Unfortunately, I\'m the bearer of more bad news.$B$BPlease don\'t shoot me....', 15595),
	(14116, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, well, well, if it isn\'t my wayward protege, $g Mr. : Ms.; $N.$B$BI\'m hurt and disappointed. You didn\'t send me an invitation to your little party out there. Sorry about the crashers... you know how pirates can be.$B$BSo, shall we get down to business?', 15595),
	(14120, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A bazillion macaroons?!?! Where are we going to get that kind of moolah?$B$B<Sassy thinks a moment.>$B$BUm... did the Trade Prince say anything about letting me escape with you on his yacht?', 15595),
	(14121, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow, you really did it?! Well, they had it coming, I guess.$B$BThat\'s an awful lot of loot. Do you think it\'s enough to get you a spot on the Trade Prince\'s yacht?$B$BAre you going to be able to bring anyone with you? I don\'t make too much working in marketing.', 15595),
	(14122, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey, you have been saving! I\'m so proud of you!$B$B<Sassy counts all of your macaroons.>$B$BUm, boss... this isn\'t nearly enough.', 15595),
	(14123, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, wow! These are worth a fortune.$B$B<Slinky eyes everything with a practiced, greed-filled eye.>$B$BI just hope that the Trade Prince doesn\'t notice them when you hand them over with the rest of your wealth....', 15595),
	(14124, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nicely done, $g sir : ma\'am;, nicely done! That\'s a fortune you have there in your bags.$B$BWith all of that, I bet the Trade Prince will let all of us come along on his yacht!', 15595),
	(14125, 5, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is nothing. You should see Bilgewater Port... the whole thing is going up in flames!$B$BFine, fine, I don\'t have time to inspect this place. Here\'s the moolah from the Bilgewater Cartel\'s insurance policy.$B$BI\'ve got to find a way off the island! Good luck, $N!', 15595),
	(14126, 1, 5, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Congratulations, you just made it. I see that you\'ve brought me all that I asked for, including your hot rod.$B$B<The Trade Prince flashes an evil grin.>$B$BA bazillion macaroons couldn\'t have been easy to come by. I\'m now the wealthiest, most powerful, goblin on all of Azeroth!$B$BTOO BAD FOR YOU THAT I\'M CHANGING THE TERMS OF OUR DEAL!$B$BYou\'re now my slave. Get below deck and take a turn shoveling coal. Next stop, Azshara!$B$BMuahahahahahahahaha!', 15595),
	(14136, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great job, Champion.  The fight continues, but now the Kvaldir know that we do not tolerate such attacks.', 15595),
	(14138, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A gift from Sassy? I hope it\'s a bonus!', 15595),
	(14140, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your actions have shown that we Sunreavers are far better allies to the Argent Crusade than the Silver Covenant and it is we who will be triumphant.', 15595),
	(14141, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The sooner we get these stinking things out of my sight and into their cage, the faster my mood will improve. I wish the Argent Crusade had given the Silver Covenant the care of this creature. They\'re going to have to get their hands dirty when the battle for Icecrown Citadel starts and I have a feeling they\'ll prove fragile and fussy allies.', 15595),
	(14142, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kul will live to embarrass himself again. That\'s far from the first time someone\'s had to save Kul from himself. With examples like him, it\'s no wonder most of the aspirants are taking up the habits of the Silver Covenant.', 15595),
	(14143, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These look a little worse for wear, but they\'re still edible. The crusaders will be glad to hear that we\'ve had some success. Maybe we can give the half-eaten ones to the Silver Covenant. That would make my day.', 0),
	(14144, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Girana accepts the prayer book from you.>$b$bThank you. We don\'t always see eye-to-eye with the crusaders, but I\'ve learned a lot from Confessor Paletress in my time here.', 0),
	(14145, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad we\'ve gotten that done. It\'s not the most glorious task in the world, but when we partnered with the Argent Crusade, we promised to do all they asked of us without complaint. Of course, the same cannot be said of the Silver Covenant.', 15595),
	(14152, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems things are worse than we initially thought.  You still made a valiant effort and saved many of The Wavecrest\'s crew\'s lives.', 0),
	(14153, 4, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very nicely done, $g sir : ma\'am;. The party appears to have been a smashing success!$B$BEr... what\'s that?', 15595),
	(14154, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did it, $N.  Thanks to you a good man has survived.', 15595),
	(14157, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greymane wants to save Crowley?  Has he gone mad?', 15595),
	(14159, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t look at me!  Leave me alone!', 15595),
	(14160, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is a fine list of deeds, $n! You are to be rewarded handsomely for your accomplishments.', 0),
	(14163, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Horde will never be a match for our forces as long as we have people like you on our side, $n.', 0),
	(14164, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nothing will stand between us and total victory. For the Horde!', 0),
	(14178, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent news,$c! If our tactical deployments continue to be this successful, the Horde will be in full retreat before long.', 0),
	(14179, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve come one step closer to achieving total victory over the Horde. We cannot allow the enemy to obtain a foothold in this world or any other.', 0),
	(14180, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n. The integrity of our borders must be preserved at all costs!', 0),
	(14181, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve brought great honor to the Horde, $n. Your victory today will ensure a thousand victories tomorrow!', 0),
	(14182, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You bring honor to us all, $n. We must show the enemy that we will fight them wherever we find them.', 0),
	(14183, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Horde is in your debt, $n. You\'ve made your people proud with your courage in defending our lands.', 0),
	(14184, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What!?\n\nFurien!! My brother is no more?\n\nThey must pay! All of them!', 0),
	(14188, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Furien\'s passing is... regrettable.\n\nI shall do all that I can to assist you in avenging his death.', 0),
	(14189, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Comparing the characters on the ancient tablet to those in Furien\'s journal, it is clear that there is a distinct correlation.', 0),
	(14191, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is clear to you now that these ruins are those that Furien recorded in his journal.\n\nAfter examining the engravings upon the ruins themselves, you feel that you are able to decipher more of Furien\'s writings.', 0),
	(14193, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'After filling it with liquid from the melons, you proceed to wash your eyes from the ancient font.$b$bUpon opening your eyes, you are able to see the spirits of ancient elves, still faithfully carrying out rituals to their goddess.', 15595),
	(14195, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is clear to you now why you were guided here.\n\nYou recognize this ancient runestone from Furien\'s final journal entry:\n\n"The ancients revered the gems created by this mystical object, claiming that they were gifts from the goddess herself. It was believed that they were weapons capable of delivering them from any enemy."', 0),
	(14196, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done! Furien\'s exhaustive research was not in vain.\n\nThe raging Vortex is ready to be unleashed upon your enemies at last!', 0),
	(14198, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very impressive, $c.\n\nYou completed Furien\'s work and rained vengeance down upon his killers.\n\nYou have brought peace to my brother\'s soul, and to my mind. Please accept this gift for your diligence.', 0),
	(14199, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to see that you have emerged victorious from the trial. Truly, you are a champion, not only of the Argent Crusade, but indeed of the Kirin Tor as well.$b$bOne can only hope that you have dealt the final blow to that dark villain and that\'s the last that we will see of him.', 0),
	(14203, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is quite a find, <name>. I can\'t have you selling this to anyone else, so I\'m willing to offer generously.', 0),
	(14204, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent.  I\'ll start rounding up some help to get these cannons positioned.', 15595),
	(14212, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brace yourself, $N.$B$BHere they come.', 15595),
	(14213, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The divine brazier indiscriminately endows you with a blessing.', 0),
	(14214, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew Crowley would come through.  His weapons will be more than useful to us.', 15595),
	(14217, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The divine brazier indiscriminately endows you with a blessing.', 0),
	(14218, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, $N.  You\'ve done more than could be asked of any Gilnean.$B$BWe\'re running low on ammunition.  It\'s time to regroup inside now.', 15595),
	(14219, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the ritual completed, you are awarded a divine gift.\n\nYou can\'t help but wonder what Elune would think of someone such as you receiving one of her boons.', 0),
	(14221, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve given them everything we have... yet still they come.  Do not worry, $N.  We\'ll slay many more before today is over.', 15595),
	(14222, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They... they\'ve stopped coming.$B$BNo, $N.  That\'s not a good thing.', 15595),
	(14223, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done.\n\nSorrem should be able to sleep in peace now that Kohor\'s threats have been silenced.', 0),
	(14225, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is most fortunate that you took the time to search for this.\n\nNo one would have expected the Burning Blade to be in possession of something so powerful!', 0),
	(14227, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You diverted what would have been a serious crisis, $c.\n\nIf that summoning was delayed just a bit longer, the demon would have become far too powerful for our small forces here to contend with.\n\nPlease accept this gift as our thanks for your service.', 0),
	(14232, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ears of the Burning Blade?\n\n<Sorrem smiles.>\n\nWell done, $c. This is just a shadow of what will soon become of that vile cult!', 0),
	(14233, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Orcs?! They were sunk and stranded too?  And now the Alliance are on the island? Do you think they\'re going to kill us?$B$B<Sassy looks thoughtful.>$B$BI think it\'s time for a little sitdown with these orcs.', 15595),
	(14234, 1, 274, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<The orc makes a move to grab the field journal from you, but then stops herself, exhaling deeply.>$B$BI apologize. It has been a very rough couple of days for all of us.$B$BI am Aggra. All of us here are what remains of the crew of the Draka\'s Fury.$B$BPerhaps we can work together. We have a common enemy in the Alliance. Their SI:7 assassins are all over this island and they\'re not going to stop until we\'re all dead.', 15595),
	(14235, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Goblin, can you fight?$B$BFor your sake, I hope so. Otherwise, there may be no breaking through this hell of killer plants.', 15595),
	(14236, 5, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I saw it with my own eyes, and still I do not believe it!$B$BYou have our thanks and the debt of our lives, little goblin. I hope that soon we can repay you the honor.$B$BMay I ask a small favor of you while my scouts and I move on?', 15595),
	(14237, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Throm-Ka, $N. We have a problem.', 15595),
	(14238, 4, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N, well done. We\'ll make an orc of you yet!$B$BTime to move on. We\'d better hurry.', 15595),
	(14239, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s up to you now. Are you going to come back to life and be the $g hero : heroine; that your fellow survivors need you to be, or are you going to rest for eternity here?$B$BOnly you can decide.$B$BDon\'t go into the Light, $N!', 15595),
	(14240, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello, little goblin. Bastia is fast, no?$B$BWe have something very important that needs doing. Can you help us?', 15595),
	(14241, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm, where the heck is the ignition?$B$BIt\'ll be a wonder if it flies without doing something weird, like turning into a chicken or shrinking down to the size of an ant.$B$BHey look, someone left their loose change in the ashtray! What else is in there?', 15595),
	(14242, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If not for you, I would surely be on my way back to Stormwind to be paraded as a trophy and a slave.$B$BThe Alliance dogs found me unconscious on the shore and put me in this magical cage. It was keeping me from connecting with the elements.$B$BNo longer!', 15595),
	(14243, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done what few others could have, $N. Our world owes you a debt larger than you can possibly understand.', 15595),
	(14244, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N, I sure am glad you survived the trip... not everyone did!', 15595),
	(14245, 5, 6, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<cough, cough!>$B$BHey! Where\'s the dock?! Someone stole the dock and the oil refinery from our town-in-a-box!$B$BWho would do such a thing?$B$BWhere\'s the Trade Prince?', 15595),
	(14246, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, $c.\n\nThis land is in your debt.', 0),
	(14247, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You look around, scanning the horizon for what might be responsible for placing this stone here...', 0),
	(14248, 5, 6, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'Boss! Er, well, I guess you\'re not the boss anymore, but still, good to see you!$B$BCan you believe it? We\'ve got a cave full of intelligent killer monkeys mining kaja\'mite!', 15595),
	(14251, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is how I got my start, you know.\n\nSlingin\' poison to the rogues in Orgrimmar. Ahh, those were the days...', 0),
	(14252, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'ll do, $c.\n\nA few more friends like you and I\'ll be back on my feet in no time!', 0),
	(14253, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well now, that\'s quite a load of feathers, $c.\n\nThey\'ll make for a good pillow \'til I get \'em to market!', 0),
	(14254, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s this?\n\n<Bizby examines the ore.>\n\nWahoo! I know someone who will be most interested in acquiring these samples.\n\nMost generous in payment for them as well, I\'ll wager.\n\nHere, $c. Take this as your finder\'s fee.', 0),
	(14255, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good that you have come.\n\nThere is grave danger looming here.', 0),
	(14256, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So now you see. These are not a simple band of displaced naga, but a well organized army, capable of great devastation.\n\nDo you agree to assist me in my investigation?', 0),
	(14257, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, $c. But I\'m afraid that your work here is just beginning.', 0),
	(14260, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t just stand around, when there is so much to be done!\n\nMust I instruct everyone on each detail?', 0),
	(14264, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The enemy\'s ranks are thinning, little minnow.\n\nPerhaps you are worthy of assisting in our search...', 0),
	(14265, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N!  Where have you been?$B$BAnyway... it\'s great to see you in one piece.', 15595),
	(14266, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work!', 15595),
	(14268, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes! You\'ve found it!\n\nNeptulon\'s engravings... there can be no mistake!', 0),
	(14277, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A disciple of the arcane always finds a way forward.  I\'m glad to see you, $N.', 14333),
	(14280, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have been blessed today!  You are alive and well!', 15595),
	(14281, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve learned with such speed and ease.  Soon you\'ll be the one doing the teaching.', 14333),
	(14282, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The vision was true!\n\nYou have singlehandedly succeeded where others have failed.\n\nThe Circle will be have no choice but to pay attention to these findings.', 0),
	(14283, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad at all.  Perhaps there is still hope for the old ways.', 15595),
	(14284, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The priestess is no more...', 0),
	(14286, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well in coming here.  If we Gilneans stick together we might yet defeat this terrible enemy.', 15595),
	(14288, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well in coming here.  If we Gilneans stick together we might yet defeat this terrible enemy.', 14333),
	(14291, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well in coming here.  If we Gilneans stick together we might yet defeat this terrible enemy.', 15595),
	(14292, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have witnessed your actions here, $r.\n\nYour presence here is both welcome and timely.', 0),
	(14293, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N.  We\'ll make sure Krennan makes it out of the city alive.', 15595),
	(14294, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re left with very few choices, $N.  What we do next will be a critical decision.', 15595),
	(14301, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Please accept this reward for your heroic accomplishments, $N.\n\nYou have bought us precious time!', 0),
	(14302, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Karnum opens and reads Korrah\'s Report.>\n\nThis is alarming news, indeeed, $r - something we have no shortage of here.\n\nI shall call a council regarding the issue. You will be summoned if you are needed.', 0),
	(14303, 1, 273, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<Aggra gives you the eye as if she doesn\'t quite believe what you are telling her.>$B$BI am not easily impressed, but if what you are telling me is true, then I have never before heard of such a thing.$B$BYou have my thanks, $N.', 15595),
	(14304, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This should be enough.\n\nThank you, $c.', 0),
	(14305, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are fine specimens, $r.\n\nI shall commence my studies immediately.', 0),
	(14306, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'On behalf of Desolace herself, I thank you, $r.\n\nPlease accept our deepest gratitude.', 0),
	(14307, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, $c.\n\nWe will doubtlessly call upon you for assistance with more significant matters in the future.', 0),
	(14308, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work, $N! Now, we need to decouple the reaction core matrix from the fuel sumps, or that whole place is gonna blow itself to Outland...', 15354),
	(14309, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! Karnum will be so pleased!\n\nPlease, accept this as my thanks.', 0),
	(14310, 21, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Whew, the sample is secure. And it\'s still steaming! Thank you, $N.$B$BAzsharite is a complex mystery wrapped in a velvety enigma of danger. Grapplehammer insists that we learn more about this strange substance.', 15354),
	(14311, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The rejuvenation is so invigorating! Don\'t you think?', 0),
	(14312, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Be not afraid, $r. I mean you no harm.', 0),
	(14313, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It worked!  By the Light, it worked!', 15595),
	(14314, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $r.\n\nOur tribe may not have survived without your aid.', 0),
	(14316, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As we suspected, the Magram have been stealing our supplies.\n\nWe shall guard them more closely.', 0),
	(14318, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why is it that you meddle in centaur affairs, $r?', 0),
	(14320, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The crate has been smashed and the vials inside of it appear to have been broken.', 15595),
	(14321, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Forsaken!  Quick, $N!  We must mount a defense.', 15595),
	(14325, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good, $r.\n\nThis will sustain us for now.', 0),
	(14326, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My mission is too critical to let these meddlers continue to dog us. It\'s up to you and I to put an end to this once and for all!', 15595),
	(14327, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, $c.\n\nNow we must convince the Gelkis...', 0),
	(14328, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My sons all slain... my clan in ruins...\n\nWere I in my youth, I would tear you limb from limb!\n\nGo now... kill me or leave me to mourn alone, $r.', 0),
	(14329, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As you slaughter their enemy, the Gelkis clan cannot help but to acknowledge your prowess.', 0),
	(14330, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Is it safe for me to leave, $r?', 0),
	(14332, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, $r.\n\nAnd not a moment too soon...', 0),
	(14333, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The destruction of those defiled relics will ease the minds of the Gelkis, and will strengthen their resolve.\n\nYou have done well.', 0),
	(14334, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oy, mon! Ya did it!\n\nWe soon be havin\' fish to eat, thanks be to you.', 0),
	(14335, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'On behalf of us all at Shadowprey Village, I thank you, $r.', 0),
	(14336, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N!!!  You ARE alive!$B$BI thought I was having dreams about the old days when I heard your voice...', 15595),
	(14337, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Shadowprey Village, $r.\n\nI was not sure the Cenarion Circle would send anyone.', 0),
	(14338, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings, $c.\n\nIt is good that you have finally arrived...', 0),
	(14339, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes.\n\nThese will do nicely...', 0),
	(14341, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, my harnesses!\n\nThanks, friend!', 0),
	(14342, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $r!\n\nThe danger persists, but you have bought us some time.', 0),
	(14343, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hate to use such unnatural measures, but I fear we simply have no choice...', 0),
	(14344, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You should be proud of how you manipulated the enemy\'s power and used it against them.\n\nYou\'ve dealt the demons of Mannoroc a severe blow...', 0),
	(14346, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your deeds continue to impress me, $N.\n\nPlease accept this gift on behalf of the Cenarion Circle.', 0),
	(14347, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, $N!  Just like old times...$B$BI\'m going to have to work hard at not shooting you, but Krennan explained everything to us.', 15595),
	(14348, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You and me, $N.  We make a great team...$B$BIt\'s good to have you back.', 15595),
	(14354, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The relics are intact! Well, indeed, that is something.$b$bYou have put my mind at ease, $r. Please accept this as my gift to you.', 15595),
	(14356, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, $C. You\'ve done well. I\'ll keep these safe from prying eyes; the last thing we need is a strong Shadow Council rising up again.$B$BCheck back with me in the future; there\'s always something that needs doing around here, apparently, and I might need another able body.', 0),
	(14357, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the ritual completed, you are awarded a divine gift.$b$bYou can\'t help but to feel a great sense of honor as you receive one of Elune\'s boons.', 15595),
	(14358, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The divine brazier graciously endows you with a blessing.', 15595),
	(14359, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The divine brazier graciously endows you with a blessing.', 15595),
	(14360, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'After filling it with liquid from the melons, you proceed to wash your eyes from the ancient font.\n\nUpon opening your eyes, you are able to see the spirits of ancient elves, still faithfully carrying out rituals to their goddess.\n\nYou ponder the significance of this revelation and determine to study Furien\'s research for more clues...', 0),
	(14361, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done.\n\nCaptain Pentigast should be able to sleep in peace now that Kohor\'s threats have been silenced.', 0),
	(14362, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ears of the Burning Blade?\n\n<Captain Pentigast smiles.>\n\nWell done, $c. This is just a shadow of what will soon become of that vile cult!', 0),
	(14363, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is most fortunate that you took the time to search for this.\n\nNo one would have expected the Burning Blade to be in possession of something so powerful!', 0),
	(14364, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You diverted what would have been a serious crisis, $c.\n\nIf that summoning was delayed just a bit longer, the demon would have become far too powerful for our small forces here to contend with.\n\nPlease accept this gift as our thanks for your service.', 0),
	(14365, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good that you have come.\n\nThere is grave danger looming here.', 0),
	(14366, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great news, $N.  I\'ve sent the remaining militia to the shore to meet the Forsaken force head on.', 15595),
	(14367, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Forsaken are here in full strength, $N.  We barely have enough men to hold them back.', 15595),
	(14368, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My children are safe!  You\'ve done a wonderful thing, $N.  I don\'t know how to thank you!', 15595),
	(14369, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad, $N.  It\'s a good thing you\'re on our side.', 15595),
	(14370, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, excellent. Some of these samples look fresh. I\'m going to be up to my neck in this stuff trying to solve this mystery!', 15354),
	(14371, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Phew! The stench! Well, hopefully that massive heap of carcasses smells more appetizing to a giant.', 15354),
	(14372, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Demons?\n\nOh, there be lots I can tell yeh \'bout demons!', 0),
	(14373, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, lad!\n\nDon\'t hesitate to knock a few more down for good measure!', 0),
	(14374, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aye, that\'ll buy us some time, $c.\n\nThank yeh.', 0),
	(14375, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I need you to pull through, $N.  This dosage is strong enough to kill a horse.$B$BBut I know you.  I know what you\'re made of.  You will be fine.$B$BTrust me.  I know what you\'re going through.$B$BNow drink up and close your eyes.', 15595),
	(14376, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You should be proud of how you manipulated the enemy\'s power and used it against them.\n\nYou\'ve dealt the demons of Mannoroc a severe blow...', 0),
	(14377, 5, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Speak slower - what are you saying? Am I hearing you right? Those formations of azsharite are actually where the giants have - oh my. Groady!! Let\'s not tell Dr. Grapplehammer, he\'s made this stuff his life\'s work.$B$BWell, at least now we know where azsharite comes from, and why it\'s so rare. We\'ve got to figure out a way to speed up, uh, "production!" ', 15354),
	(14378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Justice is done!\n\nNow let\'s have a peek at what\'s left of my goods...', 0),
	(14379, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ohhh, these will do nicely!\n\nThargad will be so surprised!', 0),
	(14380, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Karnum examines the concoction.>\n\nYes, $c. Not only do I know what this is, I know just how you should use it...', 0),
	(14381, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your deeds continue to impress me, $N.\n\nPlease accept this gift on behalf of the Cenarion Circle.', 0),
	(14382, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N.  You might be a bloody beast, but you\'re our beast.', 15595),
	(14383, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh - marvelous. Tell me more. And that precocious young Gadgetspring? Dead as well? Ah, wonderful. My work here is important but at times I do miss the carnage of demolishing my enemies on a more personal level. Here, perhaps you can make use of some of my discarded equipment.', 15354),
	(14384, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Nijel\'s Point, $r.$b$bNow, let\'s see about getting you briefed on our situation here.', 15595),
	(14385, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So it was a no-go? Literally? Well, Grapplehammer won\'t take no for an answer. We\'ll have to try something else.$B$BMaybe I\'ll have my interns smuggle this laxative into the night elf encampment. That\'ll be good for a laugh, at least.', 15354),
	(14386, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it, $N.  That should take the wind out of their sails.', 15595),
	(14387, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A pleasure to meet you, $c.', 15595),
	(14393, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N!\n\nLet us finish this!', 0),
	(14394, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Agogridon is no more.\n\nThe demons shall never again take hold in our lands!', 0),
	(14395, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did what you could, $N.  With any luck a few others will find their way to shore.', 15595),
	(14396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The ocean, $N.  It swallowed everything... the land... the Forsaken... our men!', 15595),
	(14397, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Liam is right.  We must get everyone to higher ground.$B$BYou must help me spread the word while I manage the logistics of the evacuation.', 15595),
	(14398, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A visitor!  Are you staying for tea, sweetheart?', 15595),
	(14399, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why thank you, $N.  I hope you didn\'t peek!$B$BWhere are your manners, dear?', 15595),
	(14400, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re a peach, $N.  Thanks!', 15595),
	(14401, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There he is!  Grandma\'s special boy!$B$BThank you so much for finding him.  I hope it wasn\'t too much trouble.$B$BMy... what manner of dirt found its way underneath my fingernails!', 15595),
	(14402, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did the impossible, $N.  You convinced Grandma Wahl to leave her home.$B$BYou are something else, let me tell you.', 14333),
	(14403, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You here to give us a hand?', 15595),
	(14404, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is great, $N.  I should be able to finish the repairs in no time.', 15595),
	(14405, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s just as well, $N.  Maybe the Haywards will fare better than us.', 15595),
	(14406, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Stay back! Don\'t make me...$B$BIs it you?  By the Light!  It\'s you, $N!', 15595),
	(14409, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, the writings of Daros. He always was meticulous about tracking progress. His words may aid in explaining how far we\'ve come.$b$bYou have my thanks for bringing this to me, $r. Perhaps we will see more of each other once it is understood we mean no harm.', 0),
	(14412, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent!  I\'m almost done here.', 15595),
	(14416, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve got the horses, I\'ll make sure Duskhaven gets them.', 15595),
	(14434, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Are you ready to set sail, $N?  Your people have been granted shelter in the lands of the kaldorei.$B$BDo not worry, $r.  Your people will get a chance to fight for Gilneas again.  This time, with the full strength of the Alliance.', 15595),
	(14438, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N, it is good you\'ve taken the task seriously. Respect of the land and its creatures is important. Death and life are a circle... a necessity. One cannot exist without the other. Take time to ponder this and do well to never forget it.', 15595),
	(14445, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow, oh wow! Is that who I think it is?$B$BYou rescued Thrall, Warchief of the Horde?!!!$B$B<Sassy $g gives you an appraising look : looks envious of you;.>$B$BWell, let\'s see about getting over to that larger island. I sure as heck don\'t want to swim the strait with all of those sharks down there.', 15595),
	(14449, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to your first true test as a tauren.', 15595),
	(14452, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve fought well, $n. We may yet be saved.', 15595),
	(14455, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the corruptors slain, the Earth Mother will mend her own wounds in due time.  The roots are not meant to thrive here, and will wither.  Balance will return.', 15595),
	(14456, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n. Respect your prey, and the danger it carries, but never fear it. In fear, you become prey yourself.', 15595),
	(14458, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'More trials lay ahead, $n. I hope you\'re prepared.', 15595),
	(14459, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $n.  Those beasts could have been a greater threat than the quilboar themselves, if we had not taken action now.', 15595),
	(14460, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Chief Hawkwind holds the mane of Thornmantle over his head.>$B$BThe Chief of the Bristleback is slain. Greatmother Hawkwind\'s spirit has been avenged!', 15595),
	(14461, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve not only wiped the boar pens clean, but put a stop to a horrible desecration.  Well done.', 15595),
	(14463, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $N.  I think I speak for everyone when I say the sooner we get out of here, the better.', 15595),
	(14465, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N.  I\'ve heard much about you.$B$BI understand you were crucial in my family\'s survival during the outbreak in Gilneas City.', 15595),
	(14466, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There you are, $N.  I\'ve been expecting you.$B$BI got word of your recovery and... wait -- do you feel that?', 15595),
	(14467, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look, $N!  Look at what\'s become of Duskhaven!$B$BLook at what\'s become of the last safe place in Gilneas!', 15595),
	(14473, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s just hope we don\'t have to deal with their mommy later. That would be very bad.', 15595),
	(14474, 4, 6, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'Oh, thank heavens that you survived, $N! I thought for sure that you\'d drowned when I saw you go over the side!$B$B<Sassy\'s eyes fill up with tears as she hugs you.>$B$BLook at all of these folks you saved!', 15595),
	(14482, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not exactly the battle you had anticipated, I\'ll wager. But a battle nonetheless, as you shall soon see....', 15595),
	(14483, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'ve you got there?$B$BOh hey, this is big. Real big. Most of the crazy details in one little package. Thanks - you really helped us reel this all in. Good working with ya.', 0),
	(14491, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The land is clearly still in great upheaval if it took such effort to calm.$B$BRemember this, $n.  Do not forget seeing the fate of those who would scar the Earth Mother.', 15595),
	(20439, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work. Now that this is in our hands, we must get it to Caladis Brightspear as soon as possible. We can\'t risk the book falling back into Sunreaver hands.$BI\'ll ensure that Shandy Glossgleam gets his tabard back without incident, along with a healthy reward for his help', 0),
	(20440, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, $N.  I will take these and bind their power into a totem of cleansing.', 15595),
	(20441, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Be not afraid, $N. You have successfully passed the Rite of Vision.', 0),
	(23733, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If you are prepared to leave Camp Narache behind, I will help call the spirits to guide you onwards.', 15595),
	(24215, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Bloodhoof Village, hero.  I am glad the spirits have guided you safely here.', 15595),
	(24220, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent news, $c!  If our tactical deployments continue to be this successful, the Horde will be in full retreat before long.', 0),
	(24428, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What? How did you get this? Isn\'t she... Never mind the details, I suppose. You\'ll be wanting one of these baubles as recompense, no doubt.', 0),
	(24429, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 60, 60, 0, 'You\'ve brought me the head of someone who is... No, best not to think about it too hard. You\'ll be wanting recompense for your heroic deeds, no doubt.', 15595),
	(24431, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is quite a find, $N.  I can\'t have you selling this to anyone else, so I\'m willing to offer generously.', 15354),
	(24432, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here you are, $c. With this you should find maneuvering in the sea to be nearly effortless. $b$bNow we must get to work. There is much to be done in little time.', 15595),
	(24438, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for stopping, $N.  Our carriage got hit pretty bad.$B$BThe one in front of us got it worse.', 15595),
	(24440, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'The Grimtotem...$B$B<Mull scowls.>$B$BI\'d hoped to see the end of my days before Tauren attacked other Tauren senselessly on the very plains of Mulgore.  But be proud, $N.  You have done a great thing for the land, and for our people.', 15595),
	(24441, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N.  The purity with which these beasts hunt is vital in the creation of the next cleansing totem.$B$BThe Thunderhorn Well is a symbol of my own tribe, and to know it is being desecrated by our own kind raises a fury in me I haven\'t felt for years.', 15595),
	(24442, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Mariel accepts the orders and the captured seeing crystal and examines both.>$B$BGood work, $N, and quick thinking. I\'m sure the theft of this trinket won\'t slow them down for long, but I think you\'ve bought us time to warn the leaders of the Horde and Alliance about the impending attacks.', 0),
	(24451, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work. Now that this is in our hands, we must get it to Myralion Sunblaze as soon as possible. We can\'t risk the Silver Covenant taking the book from us again.$B$BI\'ll get that tabard back to Shandy and see that he\'s well compensated for his assistance. Once the book is in Myralion\'s hands, the Silver Covenant won\'t be a threat anymore.', 15354),
	(24456, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done great honor for both me and my ancestors today.  Please, take this with my gratitude.', 0),
	(24457, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I sensed you would be coming to me, $c. I can always recognize one who is trying to pass the Rites of the Earthmother.', 0),
	(24459, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well met. If Ahmo has already explained the minor quibbles of what kind of goblin we\'ll be driving from our lands, let\'s get to work.', 0),
	(24461, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have remade the blade of Quel\'Delar, although Blood-Queen Lana\'thel proclaimed we could not! The blade must still be tempered, but she and her master will not stand in our way!', 15595),
	(24468, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it again, $N.  You have my thanks.', 15595),
	(24469, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Impressive work, $g laddie: lassie;.  We can hold the perimeter from here on out.$b$bHere, take this for yer troubles.  It might come in handy, as I\'ve got something more important to ask of ye...', 15595),
	(24470, 6, 113, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm... they blame us for destroying their home, ye say?  Well, that wasn\'t us, that was the horrible earthquake we had earlier today.  Are they that dense that they can\'t see we nearly lost our camp too?$b$bCan\'t blame a trogg for fightin\' for his home, though.', 15595),
	(24471, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Many of those that y\'saved have already made it back to camp.  The wounds\'re well-dressed!  Ye might have a future in first aid, if ye\'re into that sorta thing.', 15595),
	(24472, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You definitely got the ettin angry, $N.   I heard him myself.$B$BLet\'s hope this works.', 15595),
	(24473, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Achh.. and what do YOU want?  Can\'t ye see I\'m busy in here!  Go an\' bother someone else, I haven\'t the time.$b$bWait, what\'s that ye say?  Joren sent you to help?  Well why didn\'t ye say so?', 15595),
	(24474, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Jona drinks deeply from the Gnomenbrau.>$b$bAhh... that hits the spot.  Now we can get some work done around here.', 15595),
	(24475, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This\'ll have to do for now.  We\'ve a lot of people to feed here, but we\'ve got to make do with what we\'ve got.  With any luck, King Bronzebeard in Ironforge will send us some help shortly.', 15595),
	(24476, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I... I don\'t understand. Tempering the sword should\'ve restored the blade to its original condition. What has happened here?', 15595),
	(24477, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful!  Look at this one... it must be over 200 years old!$b$bNow, onto other matters...', 15595),
	(24480, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I had not thought it possible for evil to take hold in such a sword, but I suppose it was naive of me. If the greatest of dragonkind\'s creations could be corrupted and turned against them, why not a mere sword?$B$BUther\'s advice is wise, $N, and I would urge you to heed it quickly.', 15595),
	(24483, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to see you made it, $N.  It looks like most everybody did.$B$BWe\'re not doing too bad so far for an emergency evacuation.', 15595),
	(24484, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, $N.  The spiders are everywhere, however, and I\'m afraid we\'ve barely put a dent in their numbers.', 15595),
	(24486, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well would you look at this!  An axe blade, a couple of arrowheads, and what appears to be some sort of rudimentary spoon.  This is indeed fascinating.$b$bThanks again for your help, $n.  I\'ve much studying to keep myself occupied while Joren\'s got us under lockdown.', 15595),
	(24487, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, $c.  Are you ready to get to work?', 15595),
	(24488, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s my $g boy : girl;! Now to get one of these useless hunks of metal in working order and you into the game!', 15595),
	(24489, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm... interesting.  From what you\'re saying, it sounds like a fire elemental might have snuck in from Searing Gorge.  Or, the earthquake opened up a crack to the elemental plane...$b$b<Soren laughs uncomfortably.>$b$bEither way, this is bad news.  You should probably report this information to Grelin.', 15595),
	(24490, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'To Ironforge?  Well first, you\'ll need to go through Kharanos, and before that, you\'ll have to go through this tunnel.', 15595),
	(24491, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Milo Geartwinge, reporting for duty.  You sent up a distress signal?', 15595),
	(24492, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Took you long enough.  Hold on tight, and take a good hard look!  Chances are you won\'t be coming back here for quite some time.', 15595),
	(24493, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Coldridge Valley?  I\'ve got my own problems here!  What, they can\'t deal with a couple of troggs?  And trolls?  And incursions from the elemental plane?$b$bActually, on second thought, that\'s kind of a lot.  I\'m surprised they\'re doing as well as they are.  I\'ll see what I can do.', 15595),
	(24495, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N.  It will take some time, but I\'ll try to make sense of what we have.', 15595),
	(24498, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well this day. With many of the slaves freed and now with access to the forges, it will not be long before I have a strong force to aid in delivering us from Scourgelord Tyrannus and this foul pit.', 0),
	(24500, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Jaina is still catching her breath.>$B$BI can barely believe we\'re still alive. It was foolish of me to follow him. I\'ve made that mistake too many times.  And you... it was reckless of you to come after me instead of escaping with the information! But... well... thank you. You truly are a hero.$B$BWith Uther\'s guidance, we may stand a chance at defeating Arthas. All the lives lost today were not in vain.', 0),
	(24501, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great job, $N.  We\'ve heard rumors of survivors further in the mountains.  Now we\'ll be able to send scouts there.', 15595),
	(24502, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it, kid! Now all we need to do is score a goal and the title is ours!', 15595),
	(24503, 5, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, 'Uh... you did it, kid. You REALLY did it! We won the game and....$B$BDID YOU SEE THAT DRAGON?!!!', 15595),
	(24504, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Patrolling the high road is grave business, but it must be done. These narrow mountain trails are, for the time being, one of our only lifelines into Stonetalon. They must be preserved.$B$BThank you.', 15354),
	(24505, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So the Alliance is probing the twists and turns of the high road?$B$BEven if they were to map it out, they couldn\'t attack these hills in numbers. This is our land, $N. And they will pay dearly for presuming otherwise.', 15354),
	(24506, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Good. $n, I know of you. You\'ll be perfect for these tasks.$B$BWe\'ve been afforded a rare chance to delve into Icecrown Citadel, but we must move quickly if we\'re to avoid Arthas\' notice.', 15050),
	(24507, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well this day.$B$BWith many of the slaves freed and now with access to the forges, it will not be long before I have a strong force to aid in delivering us from Scourgelord Tyrannus and this foul pit.', 15595),
	(24511, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 60, 60, 0, 'The Pit of Saron lies ahead, and if our scouts are correct, past that will be the Halls of Reflection.$B$BIt is there that Arthas lets his guard down, and it is there that we hope to find a clue to his weakness... and a route to vengeance long overdue.', 15595),
	(24512, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'From up here I got the perfect view of the havoc you just caused, $N. Our lost brothers reclaimed some of their dignity, and the Alliance dogs were sent scrambling. Sharp work, my friend!$B$BIf the Alliance sleeps comfortably at night, we are not doing our job.$B$BWe will never let up.$B$BWe will never give in.', 15354),
	(24513, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have them? I\'ll take your word for it. Hearing Peake scream like one of his victims is reward enough for me.$B$BNow leave me be, $N. I do not wish to be a burden to my clan.', 15354),
	(24514, 273, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Onatay looks over the fresh hides, nodding her head slowly.>$B$BYes $N, I can work with these. You work fast!$B$BThese hides will help us hold out for reinforcements longer. Thank you.', 15354),
	(24515, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So my sister recognized the old signals? Her hunter\'s eyes are as sharp as ever.$B$B$N, when we first set up this camp we were at the edge of this jungle. Now look at it!$B$BSomething is amiss.', 15354),
	(24517, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, $N. It will be some time before we can assault the hold proper, but until then, we must teach them to fear the Barrens.', 15354),
	(24518, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kilrok pages through the plans you discovered.>$B$BThis explains much, $N. No wonder our foes are so hellbent on taking the southern Barrens. It\'s at the center of their plans for the continent!$B$BBut they didn\'t account for us, did they $c? ', 15354),
	(24519, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, good. We\'ve got to keep Honor\'s Stand isolated.$B$BAlone ... afraid ... $N, if we keep up the pressure, maybe someday they\'ll simply surrender the pass.', 15354),
	(24520, 5, 273, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'You\'re kidding, right?! DEATHWING?!!!$B$B<Sassy looks panicked for a moment.>$B$BOkay, this\'ll work out just fine. We\'ll throw your party and by the time it\'s over, I\'m sure that the dragon will be long gone and the ground will stop shaking.$B$BIf not, we can always charter a ship off of the island.', 15595),
	(24523, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good, $N.  I can feel the sacrifice of the land in this offering, and my spirit swells with sadness, and pride.', 0),
	(24524, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it.  You have cleaned the wells, and healed our land.  Bloodhoof village is grateful, $N.\n\nMay the wind whisper your deeds for a hundred seasons, and may the waters of Mulgore remain clean forever.', 0),
	(24525, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So it is done.$B$BNormally these scavengers are part of the Earthmother\'s cycle of life. But on the heels of the devastation wracked by both the Alliance and the cataclysm, their numbers grow overwhelming. It is good to thin them out.', 15354),
	(24529, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s bad enough to have one\'s village sacked... but to spend the following night in a quilboar cage? I\'m glad you were there to help, $N.', 15354),
	(24530, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that ye\'ve got a new hunter trick under yer belt, and now that I\'ve got some of yer money, go out there an\' track some beasts!  Come back sometime in the future, an\' we\'ll talk again.', 15595),
	(24534, 6, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What? He attacked you with a dozen boars? I guess quilboar have their own ideas of what "single combat" means.$B$BStill, the Bristleback will be left reeling after the blow you delivered. It will not be long before a new champion rises amongst them to stir up trouble... but at least this buys us some time to get these refugees relocated safely.$B$BThank you, $N. The survivors owe you a great debt.', 15354),
	(24535, 25, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I confess that I did not expect Thalorien\'s spirit to recognize you as the heir to Quel\'Delar, but I defer to his judgment. You may enter the Sunwell, but I remind you that you are a guest in our most sacred of precincts, and you should act accordingly.', 15595),
	(24536, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey, thanks, kid. Give it over, let\'s take a look.$B$B<He takes the device from you and fiddles with it.>$B$BOh, that ain\'t good.', 0),
	(24539, 273, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N. But now on to the larger question:$B$BWhere is this overgrowth coming from? And why is it raging out of control?', 15354),
	(24540, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome back, $N.\n\n\n\nWhat was done was not for revenge, or pride. It was simply to protect Thunder Bluff, and all our people, from torment and fear. Today, Mulgore is safe once more.\n\nThe Earth Mother thanks you for all your brave deeds, $N, as do I. You have earned your reward, hero. May you be welcome in Thunder Bluff always.', 0),
	(24541, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You got it, huh? Good job, kid. Top notch. Let\'s see what we got here.\n\n<He cracks open the crate and rummages around inside.>', 13623),
	(24542, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, samples from different parts of the overgrowth? These will be immensely helpful, yes. Thank you, $c.', 15354),
	(24543, 68, 30, 1, 0, 0, 3000, 0, 0, '<Kirge listens intently and then falls to one knee.>$B$BAlive! My boy still lives! Praise to the earthmother, I still have a son.$B$B<Kirge composes himself.>$B$B$C, my boy\'s mother didn\'t make it out of Taurajo alive. I will avenge her death, even if it means my son grows up without either of his parents. ', 15354),
	(24546, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you held your ground! With tenacity like yours we may yet drive the Alliance from our lands.', 15354),
	(24550, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Thunder Bluff, $N. You\'ve done great things for our people.\n\nTell me of your journey.', 0),
	(24551, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Bloodhilt looks at the badges, then allows them to spill from his hands onto the sands below. His lips curl open into a toothy grin.>$B$BNow THIS is what I like to see, $c! What is your name again?$B$BYou will go far here.', 15354),
	(24552, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah yes... I see a cunning in your eyes that was not present before. Well done, $c.', 15354),
	(24555, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must recover that book from the Silver Covenant. Without that book from Krasus, we stand little chance of solving the mystery of the sword in Icecrown or unlocking its power.', 15354),
	(24556, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew Shandy would find a way to make it work. Let me get this enchanted and ready for you to use. With any luck, the tabard\'s owner won\'t even know it\'s missing and Shandy will cover the rest of our tracks.', 15354),
	(24557, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Magister Hathorel reads the captured orders.>$B$BThe agent you intercepted was supposed to deliver the Wyrmrest tome to Icecrown, after meeting with one Arcanist Tybalin inside the Silver Enclave. We have to reclaim that book, $N, and we only have one chance before it leaves the city. We have to work quickly.', 15354),
	(24558, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Myralion accepts the heavy book and begins leafing through it.>$B$BThose symbols on the blade seemed familiar and now there\'s little wonder why. This is certainly a dragon blade, gifted to one of the mortal races, but which blade is this, and how did it come to rest in Icecrown?', 15354),
	(24559, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have remade the blade of Quel\'Delar in defiance of that Blood-Queen Lana\'thel\'s pronouncement! Now, the blade must be tempered before we can show her the folly of her words.', 15354),
	(24560, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tempering the sword should\'ve restored the blade. Why hasn\'t it worked?', 15354),
	(24561, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How can evil take root in such a sword? I would not have thought it possible if the evidence wasn\'t here before my eyes. If the greatest of dragonkind\'s creations could be corrupted and turned against them, why not a mere sword?$B$BI believe Uther is right. You must heed his advice quickly, $N.', 15354),
	(24562, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope you understand that I can\'t just admit you to the Sunwell, $N. This is the most sacred place known to the sin\'dorei and we have only recently regained control over it.$B$BYou would raise the hopes of our people with tales of Quel\'Delar? Without proof of the truth of your claims, I see no reason to take you at your word.', 15354),
	(24563, 25, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You truly do carry Quel\'Delar. This is a great day for all of Quel\'Thalas and the sin\'dorei. You have my leave to enter the Sunwell and finish the sword\'s restoration. Keep your head high, $N. The children of Silvermoon have dreamt of this day for years.', 15354),
	(24565, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. I\'m pleased to see you return intact; the viciousness I\'ve been seeing among these creatures is startling.', 15354),
	(24566, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh dear. It seems the forces at work here are a bit difficult to control...$B$BPlease, don\'t bother Naralex with this. It will only upset him.', 15354),
	(24567, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There you are, my $g boy : girl;! Quick, there\'s no time to waste! We need to get one of these shredders back in working order.$B$BI\'m bringing you off the bench... you\'re going to win the game and the title for us!', 15595),
	(24569, 15, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good. Now, should they storm the gates, they will have to do so with infantry.$B$BDo you think they have the stomach for that?', 15354),
	(24570, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will do perfectly. Bright colors like these don\'t occur naturally in the barrens, but they haven\'t developed any other mutations so far.', 15354),
	(24571, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m concerned by how...active these are. Nevertheless, it simply means we must continue to act quickly before the corruption here becomes worse.', 15354),
	(24572, 1, 5, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. I\'ll have their bodies strung up along the gold road as a message to the Alliance.', 15354),
	(24573, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Winnoa bows her head.>$B$BThank you.', 15354),
	(24574, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Naralex slowly takes the squirming heart from you, visibly disturbed.>$B$BI\'ve been a fool. The one truth I did not want to accept has been staring me in the face this entire time...this foul thing is proof of that.$B$BYou and I have much work to do.', 15354),
	(24575, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it again, $N.  The freed villagers are eager to help us against the Forsaken in any way they can.', 15595),
	(24576, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You got his ledger? Really? That\'s great, $n. There\'s probably loads of good information in here.', 13623),
	(24577, 274, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Gar\'dul breaks into a sweat.>$B$BLook - ah - let\'s not discuss this here, in front of the men...', 15354),
	(24578, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve been expecting you, $N.  Do not be alarmed.$B$BMy name is Belysra.  I am a priestess of the moon... a night elf.$B$BYou might not know my people, but the destinies of our two races have been linked since the Curse befell you.', 15595),
	(24579, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 0),
	(24581, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s one less thorn in our side. With Noth destroyed, Scourge research into refining the means of creating the undead will grind to a halt.', 0),
	(24584, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With Malygos defeated, the Nexus War should come to a swift conclusion. You have the gratitude of the Kirin Tor, $N.', 0),
	(24585, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I never cease to be amazed by the horrors that can be created through the use of technology.', 0),
	(24586, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now Veranus can finally rest in peace.', 15595),
	(24587, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I trust that you did not have to face too many of his iron construct assistants?', 0),
	(24589, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All of Azeroth is fortunate that Timear foresaw the Eredar lord\'s arrival and that you were there in time to slay him.', 0),
	(24591, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve just learned a little something about the inner workings of Horde high command.$B$BWarlord Bloodhilt is in charge of Desolation Hold now. He may have more for you to do in the courtyard below. ', 15354),
	(24592, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I wish it could\'ve been avoided, $N.  Let us ensure this is resolved without further bloodshed.', 15595),
	(24593, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done then, $N.  You are one of us now.', 15595),
	(24598, 1, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Am I truly laying my eyes upon the weapon of Thalorien Dawnseeker? This is a wondrous day for the Sunreavers and for all sin\'dorei!', 15354),
	(24601, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve done it! The nightmare\'s connection to this place has been severed. The rest of the land is safe from this intrusion now, and in time, the abberations here will be subsumed by the balance of nature.$B$BI cannot thank you enough, $n. By helping to restore order here, you\'ve let me make amends for my foolish actions.', 15354),
	(24602, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N.  Let us hope this works.', 15595),
	(24603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Take your reward; this is only a prelude.', 15354),
	(24604, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mahka sent you?$B$B<Mankrik\'s fury quells for a moment.>$B$BIt is a small comfort. But nothing can console me until I am done here.', 15354),
	(24606, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are blood shards. They used to be found all over the Barrens.$B$BIt\'s said they were formed from the blood of Agamaggan, the great demigod that the quilboar sprang from. I knew the quilboar prized them, but nobody would think they\'d take the time and care to carve them like this one...$B$BThere may be more to learn here.', 15354),
	(24607, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Anotha newblood, eh?$B$BYa actually look ta be in shape though. Steady hands. Fierce eyes. I may be able ta turn ya into a real $c.$B$BLets not waste anymore time \'den.', 15595),
	(24608, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good.  Good! They will all die!  Their chieftains, and their women, and their children, and their foul pets!', 15354),
	(24612, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My "thanks" for this Lovely Charm Bracelet.', 13623),
	(24614, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My thanks for this Lovely Charm Bracelet.', 13623),
	(24616, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N.  The scout never had a chance.', 15595),
	(24617, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re all right, $N!  I\'ve been waiting for this day for a long time, it truly is great to see you friend.$B$BI\'ve heard of what you\'ve done and I\'m thankful... especially for Lorna -- she\'s all I\'ve left.  I will send for her right away.', 15595),
	(24618, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! You\'re my kind of $c, $N.$B$BWith your help, we will throw these invaders back into the sea.', 15354),
	(24619, 1, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Calder peers into the sack of extremities and licks his lips with a dry, black tongue.>$B$BOh my. This is exciting.$B$B Aren\'t you excited, $N?', 15354),
	(24620, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Calder grasps the gigantic heart in both hands, squeezing it and listening to the valves slurp and squish.>$B$B<His pale mask of a face splits open into an enormous, childlike grin.>$B$BIt is so very important to love one\'s work, wouldn\'t you agree, $N?$B$B<Calder chucks the heart over his shoulder into a waist-high pile of entrails.>', 15354),
	(24621, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Calder holds the brains in an outstretched hand while withdrawing a gore-caked multi-tool from his belt.>$B$BWonderful work! Now the secret here is to leave the reptilian nervous systems intact while removing the higher cognitive functions. We can\'t have our new friend developing a conscience or remembering he\'s Alliance...$B$B<Calder digs and snips at the brain, removing large chunks.>$B$BAnd... we\'re finished! How lovely.', 15354),
	(24622, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice ta see new faces \'round here, mon. It\'s easy ta get ta feelin\' isolated since we left Orgrimmar.', 15595),
	(24623, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank ya so much! They can be vicious when provoked, but most of da time dey don\'t know betta.', 15595),
	(24624, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c.$B$BIt will be takin\' brave and determined people like you ta drive da Darkspear up again. I hope dere are more people even half as dedicated to come.', 15595),
	(24625, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n! Dis naga has set us back quite some time, but nothin\' will be holdin\' us down foreva.$B$BIt\'s good ta be havin\' ya wit us, $n. Ya have a fierce heart within ya.', 15595),
	(24626, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Swiftclaw! Kijara was tellin\' me about him and he sounded like he\'d be a handful. I don\'t mind da challenge - it\'s da spirited ones like dat that be makin\' da bravest and truest companions when real times of need be comin\'.$B$BTank ya, hon. Ya\'ve been very helpful.', 15595),
	(24627, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are as good as I remember, $N.  It is good to have you back.', 15595),
	(24628, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These simple leaves grow by Elune\'s grace.  They will help your mind understand the need for balance and your soul will permanently earn mastery over the beast.', 15595),
	(24629, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great work, $N! People will come running to buy Crown perfumes now that they\'ve had a chance to sample their wonders.$B$BHere\'s a little something for helping us out.', 0),
	(24631, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Tomusa snorts as he takes back his hook.>$B$BVengeance feels hollow. Still. I could not allow them to go unpunished.', 15354),
	(24632, 25, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Gann looks you up and down.>$B$BWe could use your help, $c. But this is not a skirmish. We fight here to strike a killing blow... or die trying.', 15354),
	(24633, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N.', 0),
	(24634, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah! The fool didn\'t destroy these orders.$B$BLet\'s see what we can learn...', 15354),
	(24635, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work, $N! People will be buying Crown colognes by the crate-load now that they\'ve had a chance to try them.$B$BHere\'s a little something for helping us out.', 0),
	(24636, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lovely work, $N! People will be tripping over one another to get Crown chocolates now that they\'ve had a chance to taste those sweet, romantic treats.$B$BHere\'s a little something for helping us out.', 13623),
	(24637, 11, 15, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Upon hearing the news, Bloodhilt snorts. His eyes gleam. He tips his head back and bellows a wet, cackling laugher that echoes between the blackened walls of Desolation hold and reverberates throughout the hills beyond.>$B$BSo it is done! The Butcher of Taurajo is felled at last. Cut down in the streets like a dog. Fitting.$B$BYou have done well, $N. You\'ve sowed fear into our enemies, and soon we will reap the harvest!', 15354),
	(24638, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good job, kid. You deserve a little somethin\'. And hey, come back tomorrow if you get the time; I might have a job for ya.', 0),
