	(24864, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, they\'re so cute! I wish that we could turn them into little plush toys and sell them for a gazillion macaroons!', 15595),
	(24868, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A faceless of the deep? What\'s that? That does NOT sound like a naga!$B$BWell, you killed it, whatever it was. It doesn\'t matter now. We have other fish to fry....', 15595),
	(24871, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The giant is dead? Praise the Light!$B$BThe way onward and upward is clear. Take some of these spoils of the battle as a token of our gratitude, and we will drink together in celebration once the Frozen Throne has been ground to dust!', 0),
	(24873, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At last, we have live specimens to study! You have helped to save countless lives this day, $N.$B$BPlease, take this as a token of thanks for this great deed.', 0),
	(24897, 5, 18, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, '$N? We\'re saved!$B$BWho am I kidding? We\'re all going to die!!!', 15595),
	(24901, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Okay, I think that\'s good enough for now, but they took a bunch of the townsfolk captive.$B$BWe\'re going to have to take the fight to them!', 15595),
	(24902, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Plague?  Something so heinous that not even the orcs condone its use?  I\'d say this warrants notifying King Greymane.', 15595),
	(24903, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You present me with the most difficult choice of my life, $N.', 15595),
	(24904, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve driven the Forsaken back.  We hold three out of the four districts.$B$BBut at what cost...', 15595),
	(24915, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Impossible...$B$BFather, is it you?!$B$BYou have done me a great service, hero. I offer you the reins of my faithful steed. Do with it as you please, but do not forget those that assisted you in this monumental feat.', 0),
	(24916, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What... how did you manage to come by this!?$B$BYou have done me a great service, hero. My heart could not bear to keep this locket, but I will place an enchantment upon it that you may find useful. Do with it as you please, but do not forget those that assisted you in this monumental feat.', 0),
	(24917, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aye. I know this blade... and I will treasure it always - a moment of time that will be lost forever.$B$BYou have done me a great service, hero. I offer you a gift from the Frostborn dwarves. Do with it as you please, but do not forget those that assisted you in this monumental feat.', 0),
	(24918, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sylvanas silently reflects for a moment before returning her gaze to you.>$B$BYou have done me a great service, hero. I offer you the boon of the Banshee Queen. Do with it as you please, but do not forget those that assisted you in this monumental feat.', 0),
	(24919, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Uther stares at the medal, speechless for a moment.>$B$BArthas\' medal.$B$BI remember well the day I presented it to him...$B$BYou have done me a great service, hero. My soul may now rest in peace. I offer you a memory lost in time. Do with it as you please, but do not forget those that assisted you in this monumental feat.', 0),
	(24920, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, $N.  Almost everybody managed to make it through.  ', 15595),
	(24924, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N? What are you doing wearing that pygmy helm? Looks like it\'s about to fall apart.$B$BI\'m glad that they sent you up here. I thought for sure they were going to send that jerk, Grapplehammer and his ego-enabling assistant.', 15595),
	(24925, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great job, but that\'s not even half of the hostages that they took from town.$B$BDarn it all! They must have taken the rest of the captives to their other villages up in the volcano!', 15595),
	(24929, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work, $g bud : girlfriend;! Hope he wasn\'t too tough.', 15595),
	(24930, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If I hadn\'t seen you kill a few of the mangy things with my own eyes, I\'d think you did not complete the task I asked of you.$B$BIt looks like we\'re hardly putting a dent in their numbers.', 15595),
	(24931, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, perfect! Just what I need...full of potent focusing energies...$B$B...ahem! I mean, perfect for my collection! Narain Soothfancy is in no need of artificial enhancement of any kind!$B$BNow take your pay and be off!', 15595),
	(24932, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This isn\'t goin\' fast enough. There\'s gotta be a faster way...', 15595),
	(24933, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Man, this stuff looks delicious. I\'m half tempted to just fry some up myself.$B$BNo! We\'ve gotta focus on gettin\' out of here.$B$BMaybe just one piece...', 15595),
	(24937, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They turned some of our people into zombies? Tell me something I don\'t know....', 15595),
	(24938, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aubrey sent you? Good! I take it you know your way around a cannon?', 0),
	(24939, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ho ho! The beach is ours!\n\nWe just might keep a foothold on this miserable dustball of a continent after all.', 0),
	(24940, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My star player has arrived!', 15595),
	(24941, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Horde is massing at the base of the hill. Breathlessly, you stuff the debris you collected into the muzzle of the cannon, step back, cover one ear, and tug on the igniter cord...', 0),
	(24942, 71, 16, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'You did it! No more zombies to worry about. Let\'s pause a moment in silence for the stinky departed.$B$BOkay, done.', 15595),
	(24943, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great work! We\'ve knocked them on their heels, maybe long enough to shore up our defenses.\n\nProvided we find a way to take out their artillery...', 0),
	(24944, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A steady stream of the walking wounded have come up the hill to see me, $N. I trust that was your work? Well done!', 0),
	(24945, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I gotta tell you, that\'s a load off of my mind. That is, I won\'t have to worry about no new zombies coming after my brains!', 15595),
	(24946, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will do. In fact, it\'s more than we need. I devised an ingenious idea for a weapon that the boots will be turned into once you get them to Hobart.$B$BHand the powder over and I\'ll load it into the Super Booster Rocket Boots.', 15595),
	(24948, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good! Without heavy equipment, the Horde will have to pull back to regroup. We\'ve bought ourselves some time to re-secure the fortress. Well done!', 0),
	(24951, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at the size of it! It\'s glorious. This ugly sucker\'s gonna help us bring down the whole hive.', 15595),
	(24952, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'s no time to waste, $G boy : girl;!$B$BWhat\'s wrong with the actuator on the left boot?!', 15595),
	(24953, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh man, that was awesome! You should\'ve seen the flames coming out of the hive!$B$BHere\'s your reward, for entertaining me as much as for clearing the hive!', 15595),
	(24954, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, 'Careful with those glands, $N, careful!$B$B<Grapplehammer\'s eyes light up at the sight of the fiery organs.>$B$BAnd now to load them into the refashioned shredder boot. I\'m certain that you\'ll be surprised and amazed by my genius invention.', 15595),
	(24956, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Tolliver grasps the helmet reverently with quivering hands.>\n\nRageroar\'s battleships intercepted our vessel as we fled from Gilneas. We were to be carried here as trophies to the Warchief. As we neared the shore, some of us fought back. Rageroar - he began killing indiscriminately - howling with laughter. Our ship capsized and he ordered his men to fire at us as we drowned. Few of us made it to land.\n\nAfterwards, I learned that he wore my brother\'s scalp as... as a trophy.\n\n<He closes his eyes.>', 0),
	(24958, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I managed to get everyone else safely back to town.$B$BJump in, we gotta get out of here before the volcano blows for good!!!', 15595),
	(24959, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello there.  You must be... $N?', 15595),
	(24960, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, $c.  As you can see, not all of us have resigned to our fates.  I\'m glad to see that you\'re at least willing to work.$b$bValdred will be a valuable asset to the Forsaken.  As for the other two... there is not much we can do.  We cannot force them to join us.', 15595),
	(24961, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You say she ran away?  What a shame.$b$bVery well.  As long as she\'s maintained her free will, there\'s still hope.', 15595),
	(24962, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will be here to train you as you grow in experience... find me as often as you like. I charge a minimal fee, but you\'ll find everything I can teach you to be worthwhile.$B$BGo now and test your skill. Many more things will become known to you as you gain experience, some of which I am unable to discuss with you here. Just know that Sylvanas will need hunters with your type of cunning in the future.$b$bYou will be the backbone of our salvation. Do not forget it.', 15595),
	(24964, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You seem to be somewhat of a natural, $n.  This is good.  I can\'t teach you everything myself.$b$bGo, practice what we\'ve discussed today.  Return when you\'re stronger, and we\'ll cover some more tricks and abilities.', 15595),
	(24965, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve got to admit, the spell I just taught you probably won\'t increase your intellect severalfold.  That was a lie to get you to buy my services.  But it will still be a helpful spell for you and your allies.$b$bNo hard feelings!', 15595),
	(24970, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N.  You made it.$b$bYou see those tents up there?  That\'s where we\'re headed.  The battle\'s probably already started.', 15595),
	(24971, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Being born again under the power of a val\'kyr is a strenuous process.  Many don\'t survive the shock, turning into zombies or ghouls.$b$bOthers retain just enough humanity to seem normal on the outside... but they\'re sick inside.  We should have slain those rotbrains the day they were raised.$b$bAs for you... you\'re a strong $c, $n.  I knew you\'d do well.  You\'ll be headed out of Deathknell soon.', 15595),
	(24972, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, this is very good. You\'ve done well in obtaining this information, $n. Hmm... names of the Scarlet Crusade officers in the Tirisfal Glades...$b$bImagine the blow we could deal to the morale of those bloody zealots if we were to kill their leaders in one swift strike.  I will pass this information forward.', 15595),
	(24973, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, it\'s a start.  It\'ll take a few weeks or months to fully clean out the infestation.  After that, we\'ll have to get down there with some torches to burn away the webbing.$b$bYou\'ve done your duty well, $n.', 15595),
	(24974, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, look at him!  Isn\'t he the most adorable thing you\'ve ever seen?  Thank you, $n.  I feel more energetic already.', 15595),
	(24975, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have performed your bidding well, young $c.  You are proving yourself to be quite an asset to the Dark Lady\'s army.', 15595),
	(24976, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $N.  Now comes the fun part.', 15595),
	(24977, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By the Light!  Finally some food!  Sweet, sweet pumpkin....', 15595),
	(24978, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve the makings of a mighty $c, $r.  I heard the cries of those humans from all the way over here.  Perhaps soon we will be rid of this human blight.', 15595),
	(24979, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Scarlet Crusade takes no prisoners.  That they would do so with this young woman... curious.$b$bThe powers that you describe are even more curious.  She passed through the bars of her prison and killed her captor?  Why hadn\'t she done that in the first place?', 15595),
	(24980, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Most excellent, $c.  Your skill in the art of combat is undeniable.', 15595),
	(24981, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It sounds like we\'ll have to keep our eyes out for this Voss character.  I don\'t expect any Forsaken to receive a reward if we capture her... I\'m just worried she\'ll eventually turn against us.', 15595),
	(24982, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, I\'m Brill\'s local magistrate, reporting directly to the Dark Lady.  Impress me, and you may end up meeting the Banshee Queen herself.  Now, onto your first task...', 15595),
	(24983, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Magistrate Sevren wants a report?  Very well: the defenders at The Bulwark are holding the majority of the Scourge at bay, but some do slip through on occasion.$B$BWe have seen sporadic Scourge activity east of this station, with a concentration around the Balnir Farmstead.', 15595),
	(24988, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I appreciate your efforts, $N.  May Sylvanas recognize your bravery one day. . . .', 15595),
	(24989, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is troubling to hear of the Scourge slipping past the Bulwark.  Even now, they are ceaseless in their assaults.$B$BBut we will not give in.  The Lich King is dead; we will not be taken again!', 15595),
	(24990, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, $N and I thank you for your efforts.', 15595),
	(24991, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Holland?  He\'s an amateur.  You don\'t need a fancy two-story apothecarium to make plague... you need love.  And maybe some good assistants.$b$bLet me show you how plague is REALLY made.', 15595),
	(24994, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, my doom weed. Excellent!$B$B<Apothecary Jerrod rubs his hands together greedily.>$B$BThese will come in quite handy. You\'ve done me, uh, the Lady, a fine service today, $N. As promised, here is the reward that you deserve.', 15595),
	(24995, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The scales are perfect, $N. Exactly what I needed for this concoction.', 15595),
	(24996, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, a drink at last.  What matter of ale is this?  I\'m sure it\'s no Rhapsody Malt but I\'ll take anything to wet the old whistle at this point.', 15595),
	(24997, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Expertly done, $N.  The Scourge are mistaken if they think they can use those corpses against us, and the fluid you gathered from the Rot Hide slaves will be studied by my master.  It may have secrets we can use against them.', 15595),
	(24998, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work!  Now if only I can convince Jerrod to let us move our operation into that shack...', 15595),
	(24999, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did they run from you, $N?  Good.  This is better than killing them... if they live to tell the tale, then future generations of murlocs will learn to fear us.', 15595),
	(25000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey, you\'re tougher than you look. These terrortooth hides reflect arrows and turn axe-blades - they don\'t go down easy, but their hides are worth their weight in silver in these light-forsaken Barrens. Nice work.', 0),
	(25002, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My supplies! Well, that showed some real initiative, $c. Those rap-saws or whatever they\'re called have torn lesser men to ribbons. Thank you!', 0),
	(25003, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your actions struck a telling blow against the Scourge.  And your victory will not go unnoticed - not by the Forsaken, nor by our enemies.$B$BContinue the struggle as we all do, $N, and one day the Forsaken will have the dominion over Azeroth that they are owed!', 15595),
	(25004, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your efforts are appreciated, $N.  I will not thank you for doing what is necessary, but I will remember your name.', 15595),
	(25005, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Devlin Agamand?  Is that him you carry in your sack there?  Ha!$b$bYes, I know what Coleman wants to try, and I want to try it too.  I hope you\'re prepared, $N.', 15595),
	(25006, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, how unfortunate.  Perhaps the Scourge\'s dominion over Devlin\'s mind remained too strong.  Or perhaps our methods are simply not strong enough.  It\'s also possible that Devlin was too simple-minded to comprehend what we were asking him.', 15595),
	(25007, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The High Executor sizes you up.>$b$bNot much of a $c, are you?  Well, you will be when I\'m done with you.', 15595),
	(25008, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ooooo-oooh aye! The best Hecklefangs are the dead ones.', 0),
	(25009, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your actions will slow down the Scarlet Crusade\'s advancement in Tirisfal quite a bit... hopefully for good.  But other threats loom.', 15595),
	(25010, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As you look over the ruins of the camp, you hear a whisper behind you.$b$b<"I could kill you right now if I wanted to.  You\'d better watch your step, $r.">', 15595),
	(25011, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sure, I\'ll give you a ride.  If High Executor Derrington asks for it, then technically I have to.', 15595),
	(25012, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome back, $N.  I\'ve heard stories from the east.  Who would have thought that a young $r $c like you would have been the one to wipe out the last whimpering remnants of the Scarlet Crusade?', 15595),
	(25013, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, this venom will do perfectly, $N.  Everything else has been added to my concoction and boiled down.  Thank you, $c!', 15595),
	(25015, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Corporal Teegan nods as you deliver your report, then grasps the Bramblestaff with both hands.>\n\nSo, this is what the quilboar are using against us? Do you think they used these to create this jungle?', 0),
	(25021, 7, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Mazoga gathers the pile of blood in his hands and raises it to his mouth. It liquifies and pours gorily down his throat.>$B$BDey drink de blood, dey get de power. I drink dere blood...$B$B<Mazoga gives you a wide, blood-smeared grin.>', 15595),
	(25022, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work. Gaines passed through here not long ago on his way to Northwatch and a warm bath.\n\nThe mission wasn\'t a total loss, though. We\'ve learned a good deal about these quilboar and their leadership structure.\n\nNow we can handle things ... MY way.', 0),
	(25023, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I told you we would meet again, $N.$B$B<The Warchief gives you an appraising look.>$B$BUnfortunate that it\'s under such dire circumstances.', 15595),
	(25024, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve not seen a finer display of $c prowess.', 15595),
	(25025, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Mazoga grins as he takes the sword from you in both hands.>$B$BDidn\'t like ya much, eh? More in this world craves blood than just trolls, mon.$B$BLet\'s find the other blade...', 15595),
	(25026, 7, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Mazoga tilts his head back and inhales the clumps of mysterious material. His eyes flash.>$B$BPowerful stuff, mon... ah, if ya could see what I see now... mebbe you go try it yaself sometime.$B$BThe spirits call...', 15595),
	(25027, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '...Torn limb from limb!? Well, I\'d almost feel bad but the burning hatred gets in the way. She got what she deserved.\n\n<Corporal Teegan takes the Bramblestaff and snaps it over his knee.>', 0),
	(25028, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, samples from different parts of the overgrowth? These will be immensely helpful, yes. Thank you, $c.', 0),
	(25029, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Revenge has a sweet taste, don\'t you think?  When you destroyed the Agamands, did you catch any hint of free will within them?  I hope so.  I hope they knew fear before they were smashed into oblivion.$B$BIt is a foolish hope, I know.  But it is a hope I foster nonetheless.', 15595),
	(25031, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Argh!  Get back!  Oh, you\'re not Scourge, are you?$b$bThank the Banshee Queen that you\'re here.  I\'ve greatly underestimated how bad it\'s gotten up here.', 15595),
	(25032, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mazoga? He\'s taken the sword? That filthy...$B$B<Trenton glowers for a moment.>$B$BAt least you escaped with your life. The Lasher\'s bite is a vicious one.', 15595),
	(25034, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, $N! I\'ve been talking you up to the General here. Thank you again for saving my life.', 0),
	(25035, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to have ya, $G brotha:sista;.$B$BVol\'jin makes us all proud in dese moments. It feels good ta be tacklin\' threats head on.', 15595),
	(25036, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, Paxton says there\'s no jungle in the Barrens? What do you call THIS!?\n\nI\'ve got a pile of supplies to move to the interior and my camp has been overrun by a forest that - I swear - grows by the hour!', 0),
	(25037, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oi! Tasty, mon. Thank ya for your great kindness, young one. Da spirits shall surely be regardin\' ya with great favor.', 15595),
	(25038, 6, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s this? Gloom weed?! I\'ve no need for gloom weed! That mindless mass of flesh is out there picking daisies and convincing the Lady knows how many dupes like you into doing the same. No offense.$b$bWe\'ll deal with the gloom weed later.  For now, we\'ve got other matters to discuss.', 15595),
	(25041, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work! How was it? Did you enjoy the hunt?\n\nDid you run through tall grasses, the scent of your prey urging you forward, until you leapt at its throat, adrenaline surging as your slavering fangs... Well, something like that.', 0),
	(25042, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sam\'s eyes bug out of his head as you slam the huge slabs of meat before him.>\n\nOh yeah... oh ... YES! I\'ll have mine raw. I suppose I can grill some up for the others... How would you like yours?', 0),
	(25043, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good. We may never drive the Horde completely from these lands, but with a strong presence we can undermine their will to fight.', 0),
	(25044, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A "Boarpocalypse," you say? These animals certainly have a unique idea of "Single combat!"\n\nNo matter, you\'ve done well. With the quilboar in chaos I should have no trouble convincing the field commanders to execute any strays they find scurrying about. The General need not know we\'ve stepped up the campaign... it\'s for the better.', 0),
	(25045, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your report, $c?\n\n\n\nIncredible, $N! You\'re a real asset to the Alliance. I\'ll see to it that my men follow your example!', 0),
	(25046, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'From birth to grave to undeath, we all have our own path to follow.  Some are easier than others.  It sounds like this Voss girl has had a rough path so far.$b$bHopefully she ultimately chooses to join us and follow the Dark Lady.  With power like hers, we could do incredible things.$b$bBy the way, $N... excellent work out there.  If you\'re ever ready and willing, I may have some more work for you in the Plaguelands.', 15595),
	(25048, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Most of this looks just fine! How lucky!$B$BThe Steamwheedle goblins will be so happy to see their cargo back safe and sound. And here\'s a reward for your good deeds, of course!$B$BWe\'ve got lots of other stuff to do though! Busy busy!', 15595),
	(25049, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, it\'s going to be so much nicer around here now that they\'re gone!$B$BAt least until more show up. But thank you!', 15595),
	(25050, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was great! It looks like most of the goblins we helped made it back here and didn\'t blow up. We really showed that goblin girl!$B$BHere\'s a special reward for you, $gmister:miss;.', 15595),
	(25052, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good job! We\'re really cleaning up around here!', 15595),
	(25053, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Isn\'t that just so pretty to watch?', 15595),
	(25054, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fantastic! Gosh, this will make enough wire for an entire army.$B$BLucky us!', 15595),
	(25056, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dithers, you\'ve done it again!  These are perfect.', 15595),
	(25057, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N. Several of the looters have already crawled back, requesting clemency. I\'ll let them stew for a bit in the Northwatch brig.\n\nThank you for helping maintain discipline in the ranks. It is important for our army to be perceived as soldiers, not common bandits.', 0),
	(25058, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Score one for the goblins! Stupid dwarves and gnomes.', 15595),
	(25059, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What have you dug up for me? Hmm. Interesting. This notice from Orgrimmar indicates a change in Horde leadership is underway - I guess heads are going to roll after what we did to Taurajo.\n\nWhat\'s this? A death warrant for the General here! This is good to know... Very good to know...', 0),
	(25061, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m amazed that Soothfancy was capable of following a simple set of instructions. And ones that required him to keep his foolish mouth silenced as well.$B$BIn addition, it is honestly good to see you again, $n. Now that I\'ve dropped the charade, you\'ll get to see how gnomes get things done around here.', 15595),
	(25064, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey there, hon. Vol\'jin sent you? So sweet of him to be thinkin\' of me.$B$BI surely could use da help, but ya have a bit more walkin\' ahead of ya.', 15595),
	(25066, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'YES!', 15595),
	(25072, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for the help, this was really killin\' things here. Once you start losing men, you start losing manpower. And morale. And weapons. And the magazines you loaned to that one guy.$B$BYou know how it is.', 15595),
	(25073, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, young $r.$B$BYa come highly recommended, mon. It\'s nice ta finally be meetin\' ya in person.', 15595),
	(25074, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you heard? The General never made it!\n\nKilled in the field, like some kind of dog!', 0),
	(25075, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oohh look! A mostly complete exhaust manifold, a reciprocating junction box, a working counterweight slip differential ... you sure know your junk, $N.', 0),
	(25079, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great! Set the keg down right here. I\'ll measure out some charges once I\'ve donned my full-body protective gear.', 0),
	(25080, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The gizard shocks Mizzy as you hand it over, blasting her to the ground.>\n\nOh, OH! That\'s nasty! I love it!', 0),
	(25081, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Incredible work, $N! My men report a breakthrough. Their stronghold won\'t survive much longer...', 0),
	(25082, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That oughta take care of our bug problem for a while - they\'ll be hard-pressed to tunnel their way outta that!', 0),
	(25084, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve my thanks, if not that of the entire Earthen Ring.\n\nMaybe someday we\'ll find a way to talk it out with these pigs, but we can\'t heal the land if we\'re dead in our sleep.', 0),
	(25085, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a relief. Maybe the rest of \'em will keep to their own devices now. The less fighting around here, the better.', 0),
	(25086, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What? Little Logan thinks I might need protection?\n\nIt\'s me doing the protectin\'!\n\nThe quilboar here are poised to rampage. They\'ve choked off the entire south, and we\'re the only thing standing in their way.', 0),
	(25087, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The General reads over the report, nodding in approval as he reads about the Battlescar.>\n\nQuite a name you\'re earning for yourself here in the Barrens, $N. But Roberts isn\'t going far enough. What we need is a decisive victory...', 0),
	(25089, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those val\'kyr have been really busy resurrecting you newbies lately.  I\'ve already seen a couple dozen new bodies run down that hill since this morning.$b$bYou, however, are the most promising $c I\'ve seen today.', 15595),
	(25090, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done.  I enjoyed watching you smash those undead into rotting pulp!', 15595),
	(25091, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Marin sent you? I\'m appreciative of his help.$B$BI\'m here to seek out Sul\'thraze. If you wish to help, speak with Mazoga...he\'s been cooperative so far.', 15595),
	(25093, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N. The spirits of the fallen can now be put to rest.', 15595),
	(25098, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Once again you have helped us to overcome our mutual enemy, the Alliance.$B$BNow it is time for us to help you.', 15595),
	(25099, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Of course you can borrow Bastia. That is, if she\'ll take you.$B$B<Kilag winks.>', 15595),
	(25100, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N?! Nice kitty.$B$BLook we don\'t have much time here. You might have noticed that the volcano is blowing?!', 15595),
	(25102, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thought you might be responsible for them clouds of dust I saw to the east. Nice work! Them bulls ain\'t sissies.', 0),
	(25104, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Father sent you? He worries too much. There\'s nothing here I can\'t handle...\n\nBut I\'d still appreciate the help.', 0),
	(25106, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My father would be proud of you, $N.\n\nNow, to get this flying machine up and about again...', 0),
	(25108, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Marley nods grimly.>\n\nAye, it\'s for the best I suppose.', 0),
	(25109, 6, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<The assistant looks confused.>$B$BHuh... what? Who?', 15595),
	(25110, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Assistant Greely spots the Kaja\'Cola Zero-One in your hand and her eyes seem to come to life.>', 15595),
	(25111, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alchemists pay through the nose for these things. Sure, maybe I tell some of them they\'re dragon parts, but that ain\'t my problem, right?', 15595),
	(25112, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice going, kid. Didn\'t lose any fingers? Good, we can get some more work for you then.', 15595),
	(25115, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Beautiful! We\'ll have these puppies shined up and ready to sell in no time.', 15595),
	(25118, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll rest easier knowing one of those lumbering things won\'t be wandering into my bedroom at night... again.  Thanks much.', 15354),
	(25120, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The battered dwarf hangs limply from the cockpit. As you approach the burning wreckage, his eyes flutter open.>\n\n<Marley Twinbraid is still alive!>', 0),
	(25121, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hi there! The fun\'s already started!', 15595),
	(25122, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hate the Trade Prince, but you can\'t argue with the results of his methods. Kaja\'Cola Zero-One is a huge improvement over regular old Kaja\'Cola at half the calories and twice the ideas!', 15595),
	(25123, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your soulstone has expired, Blastshadow!', 15595),
	(25125, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks a little rickety....', 15595),
	(25151, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Marley\'s eyes sparkle as you rush toward him with the ale. He grasps the mug in both of his shaking hands and upends it, white foam spilling out over his blood-caked beard.>\n\nAh... that\'s the stuff. Ol\' Barkerstout... Thank you, friend.\n\nThat\'ll make this... a little easier.\n\n<Coughing one final time, he slumps over the shattered control console, the half-empty mug crashing to the ground and spilling its contents into the sand. His eyes glaze over.>\n\n<Marley Twinbraid is dead.>', 0),
	(25152, 6, 1, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another one of Kaltunk\'s recruits, hm?$b$bA sorry state of affairs we find ourselves in if this is the best the Horde can produce. No matter. By the time we think you\'re ready to leave the Valley, you\'ll be a proud warrior of the Horde.', 15595),
	(25153, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re a legend, $N.\n\nThe other survivors and I will be telling the story of your deeds for years to come.', 0),
	(25163, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<One smoldering corpse stands out amidst the carnage. The dead goblin clutches the schematics of the fortress in his lifeless hand...>\n\n<The Bilgewater Cartel goblins. They did this!>', 0),
	(25164, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad you were here, mon.$B$BToshe be lookin\' like he wants to chase dem down. You should go help\'em.', 15595),
	(25165, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is it!  The scorpid juju Bom\'bay been waitin\' for!  Now we gonna fix you right up, $c.$b$bYou come back to Bom\'bay when you be needin\' a pickup.  Bom\'bay got the spells to fix ya!', 14333),
	(25166, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He was controlling a sea giant? Fascinating. If we\'d managed to investigate further...$B$BOh, I mean, wow, that\'s totally crazy! But thank goodness he\'s gone, hooray! Mister Noggenfogger will be so pleased.$B$BHere\'s a nice big reward, you!', 15595),
	(25167, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, we\'ve stymied their efforts for now, but they\'re still here.  We\'ll have to press on, $n.', 15595),
	(25168, 274, 1, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'A battle well-fought, $c, but I still have my doubts about our effectiveness.  These humans don\'t seem to be going anywhere.$b$bYou, however, have done more than could reasonably be asked of any loyal member of the Horde.  Thank you.', 15595),
	(25169, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, hero.  You done good for Sen\'jin today.  No... you done good for all of Durotar.', 15595),
	(25170, 94, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya mon, that\'s tha stuff.  Now we get the other jujus.', 15595),
	(25171, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That troll wants us to send help?  Bah, he can forget it.  I\'ve got my own human problems to worry about, and even those are the least of my worries right now.$b$bSen\'jin Village is right next to Echo Isles and the Valley of Trials.  Old Gadrin should find plenty of youngbloods to help him with his human infestation.', 15595),
	(25173, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Word of your bravery travels fast, $c. Tales of your victory at Tiragarde Keep will be heralded in Orgrimmar.', 15595),
	(25174, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What... WHAT!?\n\nBael\'dun in ruins? Corpses everywhere - no. No!\n\n<You describe the evidence you found at the scene.>\n\nThe Bilgewater goblins, was it? They want a fight do they? We\'ll show \'em what it means to be a part of the Horde, we will. I\'ll fill the Battlescar with their corpses. I\'ll redden the dirt with their blood.\n\n<Twinbraid grabs you by the collar.>\n\nGoblins. Are going. To die!', 0),
	(25175, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<General Twinbraid hurls his axeblade into the dirt, his voice quiet but his body quivering with disbelief and rage.>\n\nThat was my boy, $N. My only boy.\n\nThey\'ve made it personal, $c. Personal.', 0),
	(25176, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$G You brought me my treasure!  What a sweetheart!: About time you showed up.  Don\'t even think about stealing that treasure... it\'s worthless here in Kalimdor, anyhow.;', 15595),
	(25177, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The scent of the sea hangs about you, $N.  Your efforts may have purchased another day for Razor Hill.$b$bI will pass word of your deeds up my chain of command.  You have our gratitude.', 15595),
	(25178, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$g You really know how to treat a girl, you know that?  If you ever need anything...: Well, I suppose you\'re not completely useless.  Now stay away from my men!;', 15595),
	(25179, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve already spoken with several orcs that have returned from the beach.  All of them told me that you were the one who saved them.$b$bYou\'ve done a noble task today, $N.  Lok\'tar ogar!  For the Horde!', 15595),
	(25182, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dead? Good.\n\nLet word of this deed spread, and with it, terror.\n\nThe Horde will feel the consequences of their attack on Bael\'dun, and they\'ll rue the day they ever crossed us, $N.', 0),
	(25183, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The explosives are armed and ready!>', 0),
	(25184, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As we would say in the Tinker\'s Union, out of the heat-applied metallic cooking container and into the oxydizing, energetic mixture of reacting gases and solids!', 15595),
	(25185, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Twinbraid nods as you describe the destruction of the mine, but his eyes still burn with rage.>\n\nVery nice work, $N. I suppose there\'s some strategic value in depriving the Horde of those minerals, but I\'d have done it anyway just to crush those little green monstrosities.', 0),
	(25186, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So our supplies aren\'t getting through? Hmmm. Honor\'s Stand just gets more and more isolated.\n\nStill, the defeat of Thunderwalk should send a signal to our foes that we mean to stay. Thank you, $N.', 0),
	(25187, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see... so the trick is that you need to put the LITTLE end of the spyglass up to your eye.  I\'ll remember that piece of information.', 15595),
	(25188, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I used that trick you taught me with the spyglass, and I watched you running around down there.  Quite impressive!$b$bHow\'d you make the old woman fly, by the way?', 15595),
	(25189, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My grandmother was a powerful shaman in her day.  I thought she had lost most of her powers in her old age, but I suppose some things stay with you forever.', 15595),
	(25190, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Raggaran appears to have calmed down a bit since your last encounter.>$b$bGood, good.  One step closer to eliminating those beady-eyed, basket-wearing, hog-nosed, two-toed...$b$b<Raggaran\'s anger is clearly rising again.>$b$b...hunchbacked, squealing, prickly... no-good... gnome-loving... GREEEAAAAGH!  Quilboar!', 15595),
	(25192, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Again, Raggaran appears calmer.>$b$bYou\'ve done well, stranger.$b$bI\'m sorry you had to see me like that.  Thank you for killing the quilboar, but maybe you should leave before I fly into another one of my rages.', 15595),
	(25193, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $r.  I will get to work on the necklace right away.$b$bBefore Kron died, I had made this for him to wear.  I have no use for it now, but perhaps you might.', 15595),
	(25194, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I love all the little animals, mon.  I love the big ones, too.  I just hate to see you hurt them like that... but it\'s for the best.', 15595),
	(25195, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Something happened to Screamslash when the cataclysm hit, Zen\'Taji thinks.  He wasn\'t always so violent and irrational.$b$bThank you for your help, $N.  Zen\'Taji gonna get back to his studying now.', 15595),
	(25196, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re the one who handled the Burning Blade to the south?  I\'ve got ears in all kinds of places, $g boy: my girl;, and word travels fast.', 15595),
	(25200, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t say that I was ever much of a footbomb fan, but you\'re giving me an appreciation for the game!', 15595),
	(25201, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yeah, these will do nicely. You did good, kid. I\'ll see to it that you get the best footbomb uniform ever made.$B$BIn the meantime, you\'ve got other bombs to drop on the Trade Prince\'s lackeys.', 15595),
	(25202, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He got just what he deserved. There, there, don\'t cry. You\'ll find someone else that\'ll treat you right.$B$BHere, let me take that... we wouldn\'t want people to think that you\'re crazy.', 15595),
	(25203, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'s no two ways about it... he got exactly what he deserved.', 15595),
	(25204, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All of the lights and indicators on the control panel are going crazy!', 15595),
	(25205, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The moral of the story: hasty, lazy actions have ruinous results.  We mustn\'t take shortcuts... we must work for our rewards.  I\'ve been trying to tell this story to the "Enforcer", but I fear his Hellscream-worshipping skull is a little bit too thick.', 15595),
	(25206, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'See?  The shaman\'s tales are nothing but that... a youngling\'s bedtime stories.  The new Horde takes what it wants, and doesn\'t waste time with such frivolity.$b$bIf you get a chance, I recommend you tell Shin... and those like him... not to waste any more of your time.', 15595),
	(25207, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I felt the heat from the explosions all the way over here!', 15595),
	(25208, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re back. What did Estulan say?', 15050),
	(25213, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was wondering where you were!$B$BDon\'t worry, Hobart will get that footbomb uniform converted into the most Ultimate Footbomb Uniform ever!', 15595),
	(25214, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oops. Well, what goes up must eventually come down.', 15595),
	(25215, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It shouldn\'t take long to cleanse the water. Thank you for your help.', 15595),
	(25216, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another fan of the Great Sambino! Come all this way for an autograph perhaps? I\'m far too busy to be signing anything... move along now.', 15595),
	(25217, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another sample. Brilliant! The rocky riches of the sea shall soon be mine!', 15595),
	(25218, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya know, I should have given you a weight belt so that you wouldn\'t just float away, air balloon and all. Lucky for me you came down here with armor and all! Hah!', 15595),
	(25219, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. Seriously. If I would have had to endure another shipwreckee laughing at me, I swear I would have gored someone.$B$BI\'ll let you know if I come up with anything.', 15595),
	(25220, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. There are still much bigger predators we\'ll have to keep an eye out for, but this will at least give us a bit of peace of mind around the cave.', 15595),
	(25221, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Swift work. Very impressive.$B$BThat Fathom-Lord got away... I don\'t see him anywhere. He\'s most certainly the key to finding our captured friends.$B$BI will hunt him down. He cannot stay hidden for long.', 15595),
	(25222, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A friendly face! Welcome!$B$BVery kind of you to come check on us. We\'re fine. A naga scouting force did find us, but I\'m pretty sure none escaped. We should be safe for now.', 15595),
	(25223, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I suppose your abilities are... suitable.  Color me impressed.', 15595),
	(25224, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you managed to pass this part of the test without getting yourself eaten by Smolderos or being incinerated by the fire elementals?$B$BI suppose I should congratulate you on ascending the lowest rung of our ladder.$B$BWell... congratulations, recruit!', 15595),
	(25227, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gail sent you?  Did... did she say anything about me?', 15595),
	(25232, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is quite interesting.  These rites aren\'t all that different from the spells which are taught to Horde warlocks.  This merits further investigation!', 15595),
	(25233, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! The chaos we sow back here will be felt up and down the chain of command.', 15595),
	(25234, 1, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Jadi kicks open one of the crates and picks up a curved dagger within. She immediately winces in pain.>$B$BAugh! Cursed - this metal is cursed - it bites!$B$B<When the dagger falls to the ground, it shatters, as if made of brittle glass.>$B$BWhat demented workmanship is this? $N, I\'ve never fought any foe like this before.', 15595),
	(25236, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The electricity was only one of the dangers.  If those carcasses rot too long under the water, that entire source becomes undrinkable.$b$bWell done, $c.', 15595),
	(25243, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m sure she deserved it, $N. She should never have betrayed you like that.$B$BIt gives me the shivers to think that she might have kissed that monster, the Trade Prince!', 15595),
	(25244, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Serves her right for stealing your man in the first place.', 15595),
	(25246, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May you find what you\'re looking for, $gbrother:sister;.', 0),
	(25247, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May you find what you\'re looking for, $gbrother:sister;.', 0),
	(25248, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May you find what you\'re looking for, $gbrother:sister;.', 0),
	(25249, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May you find what you\'re looking for, $gbrother:sister;.', 0),
	(25251, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it! You did it!$B$BWe\'re saved, $N!', 15595),
	(25255, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N. I worry that our actions here may be too little, too late, but nature always has a way of rebuilding itself that never ceases to amaze.', 15595),
	(25256, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Vek\'nag sent you?  Without telling you that I need wagon wheels, nails, and rations?  That idiot.', 15595),
	(25257, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I watched you fight out there.  How long you been a $c?$b$bYou\'re alright, kid.', 15595),
	(25258, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m at a crossroads now, $N... you defeated him easily in combat, but then again, I did get him for free, and he\'s pretty cheap to feed.  Maybe we\'ll keep him around for a bit.', 15595),
	(25259, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine, here\'s the money... but you\'d better make yourself scarce before I reconsider my policy on keeping Horde slaves.', 15595),
	(25260, 1, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I ask for an orb, and you bring half of the goblin\'s arm with you?  I like the way you work.$b$bTell you what... you\'ve already given me a hand.  Allow me to return the favor.', 15595),
	(25261, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, $N.  Word reached me of your coming, and of your exploits in Durotar.$B$BYou are a $c of growing skill and renown.$B$BStay on the pure path, and your future will be great indeed.', 15595),
	(25262, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good.  Hiding within these collars is the secret behind the Burning Blade.  And I will uncover that secret...', 15595),
	(25263, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, and where did you get this?  Good Margoz sent you to me, did he?$B$BWell, let me take a closer look...', 15595),
	(25264, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is not news to me.  While I appreciate your efforts, the Burning Blade will have to wait.  We have other matters to which we must attend.', 15595),
	(25265, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lok\'tar! Victory, $N!', 15595),
	(25266, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<The orc continues on in hushed tones.>$B$BI know who sent you. Did he give you something to deliver to me?', 15595),
	(25267, 5, 1, 397, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Thrall had you deliver this?$B$B<The Warchief takes a step back, visibly shaken.>$B$BI understand the meaning of this all too well, goblin.$B$B<Garrosh points to Gobber.>$B$BThis smelly thing was caught unattended in the city and seems to recognize you.$B$BI have already put others of your kind to work in Azshara. Take it with you when you leave.$B$BFrom this day forward, you and your Bilgewater Cartel will serve the Horde!', 15595),
	(25268, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re here to rescue me, $c? Thank you!$B$BNo, no, don\'t worry about the cage for now. My life isn\'t important. We\'ve got to save the shrine, first.', 15595),
	(25269, 15, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lok\'tar, $c! Don\'t worry about this cage - these animals will come to fear me before long.$B$BMy first priority is to clear this filth away from my beloved shrine.', 15595),
	(25270, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Takrik examines the incense.>$B$BDisgusting. This is like the incense we burn when we wish to commune with the spirits... but it\'s... befouled.', 15595),
	(25271, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ian examines the incense.>$B$BAs I suspected. These reagents bear the marks of the Twilight\'s Hammer. And here, the name "Lycanthoth." I believe these are used in a summoning ritual...', 15595),
	(25272, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You were brave to face down Lycanthoth, $N. Like myself, he was a primal force of nature... but his origins were from a darker place.$B$BThose who birthed that beast reached deep into the blackness, channeling powers never intended for this world.$B$BCome, $c. Climb onto my back, and let us show these beasts the true face of ferocity!', 15595),
	(25273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You were brave to face down Lycanthoth, $N. Like myself, he was a primal force of nature... but his origins were from a darker place.$B$BThose who birthed that beast reached deep into the blackness, channeling powers never intended for this world.$B$BCome, $c. Climb onto my back, and let us show these beasts the true face of ferocity!', 15595),
	(25274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent.  I\'ll do my best to alter these documents.', 15595),
	(25275, 5, 25, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N? The $N?!$B$B<The labor captain eyes you up and down.>$B$BThe rumors are already flying about you. I don\'t know if I should be thankful or frightened that you\'re here. At least we don\'t have any volcanoes in Azshara!$B$BHonestly, I can\'t believe you\'re showing your face here... Trade Prince Gallywix has setup shop atop the mountain!', 15595),
	(25276, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$Ndamus?  Let us hope your parents brought you into this world with more than just a ridiculous name.', 15595),
	(25277, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah! So you really sent some heads rolling, did you?$B$BIt was said during the War of the Ancients that Lo\'Gosh fought demons for ten days solid. Hopefully you weren\'t fighting that long...', 15595),
	(25278, 1, 4, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You really cleared that place out, didn\'t you? Well done!$B$BThe night elves once told me a story about how Goldrinn fought and killed a dreadlord, even as three others clung to his flanks, burning his flesh. I wonder if you or I will ever have the strength to do the same?', 15595),
	(25279, 4, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N, it was incredible! For a fleeting moment I saw Lo\'Gosh through the trees - a creature of both fury and light. My cage collapsed and the vandals melted like wax under the kiss of his claws, their screams and howls echoing through the valley... Was that your work?', 15595),
	(25280, 4, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N, it was astounding! Goldrinn himself appeared to free us, his white fur bright like the summer moon. Our cages collapsed and the vandals melted like wax under the kiss of his claws. He was beautiful, $N. Beautiful!', 15595),
	(25281, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'While you were away, I was able to revive some of the fallen soldiers.$b$bWe\'ll need every hand if we are to survive here.', 15595),
	(25284, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, good. It\'ll take them many sleepless nights to figure out where we came from and where we disappeared to after the kills...', 15354),
	(25286, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Toby is all done with the speech? Let me see...$b<Reads the speech> Pumping pistons! What a fantastic speech! I knew Toby was a good writer, but this is perhaps the best he\'s ever written.$bI think it\'s time to get you out to the battle.', 0),
	(25291, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You think you\'re ready for the next step then, $Ndamus?$B$BLet\'s see what you\'re capable of.', 15595),
	(25294, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent.  This little pup will grow to be strong and merciless like his father.', 15595),
	(25296, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent job, $N.  Or should I say: "$N"damus?$B$BGive me a minute to read these.', 15595),
	(25297, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You dump out the current contents of the cauldron, instantly killing the surrounding plant life.>$B$B<The draught you brew in its place boils chunky and reeks of rotted cabbage. You turn your head aside and bottle it up.>', 15595),
	(25298, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! Let\'s hope the damage wasn\'t permanent.$B$BJudging by the poor victims still in camp here, the Twilight\'s Hammer really messed with their heads.', 15595),
	(25299, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve succeeded, $Ndamus.  You\'re ready for the next step.', 15595),
	(25300, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You approach the Eye of Twilight. As your fingertips graze its luminescent surface, you are aware of a malignant presence peering back at you, searching your soul.>$B$B<Instinctively, you draw back.>', 15595),
	(25301, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<A heavy tome, bound in flesh, lies open on the table.>$B$B<The language - pictographic and scrawled in rust-colored ink - is undecipherable, but notes and translations are tucked within several pages. This must be what you\'re looking for.>', 15595),
	(25303, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Flush with the energies of the captured elementals, you stand before the Twilight Apocrypha. The pages turn of their own accord.>$B$B<Suddenly, you see what the Eye sees. It is yours to command!>', 15595),
	(25304, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These foul things will be driven back into the sea. I hope you\'re ready.', 15050),
	(25308, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent job, $N!  You\'ve outdone yourself this time.', 15595),
	(25309, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re on the fast-track to success.  Let us hope you don\'t ruin your track record with such silly notions as compassion and humaneness.$B$BCome, then.  Let us discuss your future.', 15595),
	(25310, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $Ndamus.  We must show all would-be competitors that we are not ones to give up easily.', 15595),
	(25311, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sharp as always.  You do not disappoint me.', 15595),
	(25312, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello, yes? What? You? Oh, you\'re one of the ones I sent after the Eye of Twilight, aren\'t you?$B$BGood work, very good. I suppose that\'s a valuable lesson:$B$BNever to take orders from a big purple ball.', 15595),
	(25314, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $N.  Our plan\'s almost come together.', 15595),
	(25315, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You.  You\'re clearly not with them.$B$BAn ally then?', 15595),
	(25316, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ysera appears to be in some sort of trance.>', 15595),
	(25317, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve arrived just in time, $N.', 15595),
	(25319, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, $N.  But I fear the battle is far from over.', 15595),
	(25320, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Help has arrived at last!', 15595),
	(25321, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am thankful, $N.  I will deliver my findings to our people.', 15595),
	(25323, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N.  This will help us turn the tide against the enemy.', 15595),
	(25324, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The dragon might be right.  The Twilight\'s Hammer has breached our security and this is our most dangerous prisoner.', 15595),
	(25325, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did well, $N.  I will take Fandral to Moonglade myself.$B$BHis prison will be far enough from the battlefront there.', 15595),
	(25328, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kristoff reaches down to snatch the key.>$B$BIt\'s about time!$B$B<He squirms in his bonds, trying to reach the padlock behind his back.>$B$B...Can I get a little help here?', 15595),
	(25330, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $Ndamus.  I\'m having the servants you chose for me briefed on their new duties.', 15595),
	(25332, 6, 374, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kristoff, Kristoff... Oh yes, I remember now. I recall sending him on what amounted to a suicide mission.$B$BHe survived? I suppose that means he failed.$B$BStill, you deserve at least some coin for the trouble.', 15595),
	(25333, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome back from the battle! The Twilight\'s Hammer have been disgraced in the eyes of the Gordunni, and driven from Feralas.$B$BWe\'ve shown the glory of the Alliance in full force today! Be proud!', 15050),
	(25334, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'d all suspected da naga, but I knew nothin\' of the Twilight Cult bein\' beneath the waves. Somehow dey are corruptin\' and pervertin\' the elements, makin\' demselves into dese horrors.$B$BWe goin\' ta have to be fightin\' both of dese threats to stand a chance of bringin\' peace ta Vashj\'ir. We don\'t have da men ta do that yet.$B$BCome, $c, we got much ta do.', 15595),
	(25352, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You should\'ve seen the battle from here! Bodies were falling off of the cliff! Spectacular!', 15595),
	(25353, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, it is true! You indeed carry lightning in your hands.$B$BYou are the chosen one, $N. You will be my champion, and carry my vengeance to realms where I cannot tread...', 15595),
	(25354, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Impressive, $N. Very impressive.$B$BYou embody all of the strength of the wolf ancient, and possess the wisdom to use your powers well. I salute you.', 15595),
	(25355, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, it is true! You indeed carry lightning in your hands.$B$BYou are the chosen one, $N. You will be my champion, and carry my vengeance to realms where I cannot tread...', 15595),
	(25357, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s hope your efforts prove to be enough of a diversion...', 13623),
	(25358, 30, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I trust we both know what\'s been going on inside these crates...$b$bThat\'s right... ferrrmenntation! Here y\'are. My personal secret recipe.$b$bYou wouldn\'t get this from any other guy!', 15595),
	(25359, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I remember you. You were there when they attacked us back in the cave.$B$BGood to have you with me, $c. Ready for a little vengeance?', 15595),
	(25360, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Does everything down here only come in jumbo size? Oooh! That\'s a thought. Maybe there are some hunky sea goblins around here somewhere.$B$BThanks, by the way.', 15595),
	(25364, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done as I have asked, and for that I salute you.  Take this small reward as compensation for your efforts, $n.$B$BWith their numbers thinned and their leaders slain, the gnolls will think twice about storming the camp.  This doesn\'t conclude the issue at hand, however...$B$BThere must be some reason why the gnolls have been whipped into such a frenzied state.  Before they have a chance to regroup, I want to find out what is causing it.', 15354),
	(25366, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, this is exactly what we needed.  While I am not so skilled at ciphering what most of the scrawling on this map is, I\'ve seen enough battle plans in my day to understand what is happening with the gnolls.  It looks like they are currently fighting a two front war.  One is with us... but it seems that their main energy has been against a foe to their south.$B$BThere\'s more at hand here than meets the eye.  Perhaps it is time to figure out who this other foe they face really is.', 15354),
	(25367, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $c.  Though the extensiveness of the Zukk\'ash presence will not be thwarted with anything less than a full-scale invasion, you have bought us some time so we can devise a proper strategy.$B$BI will be sure to have these carapaces analyzed; we\'ll need to learn everything about them before we deal with what has unfortunately turned into a much larger issue than we had anticipated.', 15354),
	(25369, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Impressive, $c... most impressive!  If Stinglasher is indeed one of their strongest creatures, the study of the beast will prove to be quite valuable in time.  It\'s now my charge to make sure we defend ourselves long enough to take advantage of it.$B$BPlease accept this coin bounty as a token of the entire camp\'s thanks, $N.  Well done.', 15354),
	(25370, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, $N.  We cannot allow the Twilight\'s Hammer spies this close to the world tree!', 15595),
	(25371, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Amazing! You look exhausted. She must have really made you work for it.$B$BLife should be a lot easier down here going forward with a mount that swift at your beckoning. Congratulations, $n!', 15595),
	(25372, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is the key, $N! With the seedlings you collected for me earlier, the animals you\'ve saved from around Hyjal, and the Heart of the Forest you\'ve just discovered, we can rejuvenate this land right from under the feet of Twilight\'s Hammer. Imagine their astonishment to see their work undone, as life triumphs over chaos...$B$BI will begin the ceremony at once!', 15595),
	(25374, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will be able to rest easy now, $n. You\'ve saved our camp from a terrible menace.', 15354),
	(25375, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, good. Let\'s hope the ogres are at least smart enough to realize we\'re sending a message!', 15354),
	(25377, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve discovered lost treasure!$b$bYour mind reels at the thought of what else might be hidden in the depths of the sea.', 13623),
	(25378, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve come.$B$BI am ashamed to ask this of you, $c, but I\'ve ran from him long enough. Taerar must be stopped.', 15354),
	(25379, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done.$B$BThis land that has suffered so much can rest now.', 15354),
	(25381, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N. You\'ve given us the opportunity to try to reclaim the upper hand.', 15595),
	(25382, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dead? Good!$B$BBut it seems there\'s still so much to be done... fires to quench... and the soil to heal...$B$BI hope you\'ll stay close and help us reclaim Hyjal!', 15595),
	(25383, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are truly blessed by the Earth Mother, $n, to have the honor of fighting with the guardians of nature, and to also survive it.$B$BKnow that you have kept safe every living soul in this camp, and possibly this entire forest. Take these gifts with my deepest thanks.', 15354),
	(25385, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Squueeeee!$B$BDid the nice $gMr.:Mrs.; $c pull you from the flames, little friend? You\'re safe now!$B$BHooray!', 15595),
	(25388, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why, $n! What a surprise!$b$bIf anyone ever calls your character into question you be sure to send them my way.$b$bI\'ll tell anyone who\'ll listen that in my moment of need, you gave me a case of crabs...', 15595),
	(25389, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, my!$b$bThat\'s some of the biggest, juiciest tail I\'ve ever seen!', 15595),
	(25390, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, you\'ve found them! I was sure they were lost forever...$b$bHere you are, $n. I hope this is ample payment.', 15595),
	(25392, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh yay! Happy little deer!$B$BNow they can grow up and have ADVENTURES.$B$BYou\'re swell.', 15595),
	(25394, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This development worries me greatly. This has happened before...', 15050),
	(25396, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The mountain giants are precious allies of our race. We must stop this corruption before it claims any more creatures of the forest.', 15050),
	(25397, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The spirits of these guardians will return in time, $n. You\'ve freed them to move on in nature\'s cycle.$B$BNow it falls to us to make sure that cycle is free of corruption and needless suffering.', 15050),
	(25398, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your bravery has seen us through! The Emerald Nightmare has been shut out from this land.$B$BThe fate of the dragon Taerar worries me...but there is much work still to be done. I cannot afford to dwell on it.', 15050),
	(25399, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your valor was mentioned in my briefings, $n. I commend you.', 15050),
	(25400, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It sounds like there were more than we thought! Thank you for your brave work, $n.', 15050),
	(25401, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Is that it? Let me see here...', 15050),
	(25402, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, the orb I mentioned before. A decent reason to disturb me.', 15050),
	(25403, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, you\'ve brought him. Now I merely have to suffer the fate of speaking to him.', 15050),
	(25404, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well, $r. I will help you mortals, even from within my bonds.$B$BBut don\'t sicken me by claiming it\'s my redemption. I do this for my own ends.$B$B<Blackhorn\'s sudden grin is unsettling.>', 15595),
	(25405, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hear you, $r.$b$bI understand the urgency, but these men are in no condition to fight.', 15595),
	(25406, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! Everything\'s going according to plan. Lady Shandris will be pleased.', 15050),
	(25407, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wisps have always lived in harmony with night elves, and we depend on them for many things. These little guys you sent back, for example, will be helping us with some new construction and repairs.$B$BReady for more?', 15050),
	(25408, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good. Please crush the berries into a pulpy liquid. That\'s quite an aroma isn\'t it?$B$BNow now, don\'t gag. It\'s beneath you.', 15595),
	(25409, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A properly trained squadron of hippogryph riders can take on nearly any opposing force. Feathermoon Stronghold will be much safer with these noble beasts on our side.', 15050),
	(25410, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They may not look it, but some treants grow to be ancient protectors. We could use a few more of those around here...', 15050),
	(25411, 2, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The wretched creature before you speaks in a wavering voice, its body broken but briefly animated by Blackhorn\'s vile potion.>$B$BYes, master?', 15595),
	(25412, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes! Show me the runes you discovered.$B$B"Vol\'talo Thol\'embaar." That\'s the name of your real enemy.$B$BPresumably you\'re dealing with one of Ragnaros\'s generals, sent here to scorch the mountainside and pave the way for his conquest.$B$BI will show you how to crush him.', 15595),
	(25419, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This treasure was obviously crafted by the local water-goblins for a female they regarded highly.', 15595),
	(25424, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This development is troubling, $N.  We must act swiftly.', 15595),
	(25426, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n. I didn\'t think those gnolls would give you much trouble.', 15050),
	(25427, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect. Any gnolls left will be simple prey, lost in the woods.$B$BHeh...here, soldier, take your reward before I get distracted. We\'ve got other threats to deal with.', 15050),
	(25428, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There it is! Such a trophy! Born in the fires of another plane...$B$BGo ahead, $r. Crush it. Crush his charcoal heart in your hands and let the winds scatter the ashes... yes, yes.', 15595),
	(25429, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are silithid after all...I wasn\'t sure, having never seen one in person. Gilneas had its problems, but at least we didn\'t have these monstrosities running around!', 15050),
	(25430, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My duties are here, viewing the enemy\'s movement from above, commanding our armies where they\'re needed.$B$BYour aid would be most welcome.', 15595),
	(25431, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n! You\'re proving very valuable to securing this area for the Alliance.', 15050),
	(25432, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to see you back. We\'ve learned more about the ogre situation.', 15050),
	(25433, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done once again, $n. Yet another threat removed from Feralas.', 15050),
	(25434, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, and good riddance. I hope we never have to see another ogre here again!', 15050),
	(25436, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I didn\'t want to scare you, but this is a grave situation. If the portal at Dream Bough was sealed, and the corruption is still spreading...', 15050),
	(25437, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve come.$B$BI am ashamed to ask this of you, $c, but I\'ve ran from him long enough. Taerar must be stopped.', 15050),
	(25438, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'To be drawn into a fight between dragons...I don\'t know if you\'re blessed or cursed.$B$BLady Shandris has heard of all you\'ve done, and has personally sent this reward for your bravery. I\'m glad you came back in one piece to receive it.', 15050),
	(25439, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to have a real warrior at my side. Too often, my shaman brethren can\'t seem to stomach the work.', 15595),
	(25440, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And with this, hopefully their attacks on us will calm for a while.', 15595),
	(25441, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Too often, we are mistaken for druidic types. Perhaps that\'s true for some shaman, but do not let yourself be plagued by the ignorant belief that we are always peaceful.$B$BNothing about what I do is harmonious. I command the elements to my will. There is nothing offered in return. I would have it no other way.', 15595),
	(25442, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What is this? A pearl? Much more I think.$B$BThis is exactly what I was looking for, thank you for bringing it to me.', 15595),
	(25444, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These be enough for me purposes. Now comes de hard part.', 0),
	(25445, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n, you\'d be a mighty warrior and a fierce commrade to da Darkspear trolls.  De Echo Isles are OURS now and we couldn\'ta done it wit\'out ya.$B$BTake dis cloak. Wear it wit pride.  You\'d be a member of da tribe now!$B$BIn no time, da trolls will have a home again and we have you to thank for dat.', 0),
	(25446, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m already beginnin\' to see what de frogs are seein\'. Ya done it perfectly, $N. Now Vol\'jin and I will see what Zalazane be plannin\'.', 0),
	(25447, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At the very least, these creatures\' suffering has ended. Let us hope their sacrifice will bring a stop to further pain.', 15050),
	(25448, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. That\'s one less distraction for me.', 15050),
	(25449, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you stop and examine the texture of these hides?  Properly treated, these hides could very well be stronger than iron.  Not many people know about these hides, and that in combination with the vast treating solutions I know will allow me to potentially make items with a true mark of quality... thanks to you, of course!$B$BAnd now, please choose from what I am able to offer you for your service!', 15050),
	(25450, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, excellent!  These are going to work out incredibly well - I can already tell that they\'re going to be much harder when properly cured.$B$BThanks again for your help $N.  Here - please take one of my latest creations.', 15050),
	(25456, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sam\'s in one piece then? And his poor assistant Felice? Good to hear.$B$BI hope that one day he\'ll learn to respect the elements as more than just a tool.', 15595),
	(25458, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good riddance to foul creatures. May the naga slither back into the sea and never return.$B$BYou\'ve proven yourself on the battlefield, $n. I would ask more assistance of you in defending our lands here.', 15050),
	(25459, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well that\'s a load off my mind.$b$bThank you again, $c.', 15595),
	(25460, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $N.  Your fighting prowess is admirable.  You will be crucial to putting a halt to the elemental onslaught.', 15595),
	(25461, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya found some good ones. I be trainin\' them hard and we won\'t stop until we\'ve driven Zalazane from our islands.', 0),
	(25462, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $N. Those little bears are shaken up but they\'ll survive.$B$BAt least the ones that hit the mat.', 15595),
	(25463, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you here. Estulan is being...difficult. We\'re going to have to deal with these ogres for Lady Shandris on our own until he decides to deal with us.', 15050),
	(25464, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N.  We cannot afford to lose any further ground in Hyjal.$B$BBy stopping Baron Geddon we will have dealt a huge blow to the enemy.', 15595),
	(25465, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Splendifimous!  Not only am I glad to see that you\'ve returned with the residue, but also with all your major appendages intact!  That is, well, there was never any danger in using the Ultra-Shrinker, now was there!$B$BI do appreciate your effort on my behalf, $N.  Truly, you are a friend to goblins everywhere.  Accept this as a token of my appreciation!', 15050),
	(25466, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Scrumdillyriffic!  These cores will keep me working for some time.  Add to that the benefit of there now being fewer elementals along the coast, and I might no longer cry myself to sleep at the prospect of having set up shop in perhaps the worst place imaginable!$B$BThank you, $N, for your efforts on my behalf.  While it certainly straps me financially to do this, allow me to show you some gratitude you may understand and appreciate... loot!', 15050),
	(25467, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The satisfying sound of a chest unlocking is followed by the sight of once-hidden treasure.', 13623),
	(25468, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aren\'t they adorable? The babies are even cuter.', 15050),
	(25469, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent!$B$B$n, you\'ve helped bolster our forces here, and you\'ve saved many of these forest creatures from the Horde as well. With our army now ready, Feathermoon will stand against all threats, Horde or otherwise!$B$BOn behalf of Lady Feathermoon, I\'d like to award you with this weapon, fit for a Sentinel.', 15050),
	(25470, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Vanira\'s frogs be tellin\' de truth, den? Dis tiger be a druid and an ally? We couldn\'t be hopin\' for a better outcome. Dis be a good omen for de coming battle.', 0),
	(25471, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ello, mon! You look a bit more capable then most of dem coming through here.$B$BCome rest a bit. Make yaself at home.', 15595),
	(25472, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, $N.  This will be a great weapon against the enemy forces.', 15595),
	(25473, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Just so you know, you\'ll find Kaja\'Cola all over town. It\'s the Bilgewater Cartel\'s best-selling product of all time!$B$BJust remember, image is everything if we\'re going to get you promoted to Trade $g Prince : Princess;! No, wait, profits are everything! Explosions are a close second! Then, image!', 15595),
	(25475, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You place the egg... distress beacon... inside the chicken... homing robot.$B$BHums and whirs are heard from inside the robot as it struggles to stand up.  After the robot comes to life, Oglethorpe\'s voice is heard once more, but now from inside the robot:$B$B"OOX-22/FE is working at least, but it needs major repairs!  It is much too heavy for you to carry it... but I think I have an idea.  Are you up for watching over it some more?"', 15050),
	(25477, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How unfortunate...$b$bWell, all things considered, it is good to see that you made it back unharmed.', 15595),
	(25480, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will take de spirits\' advice to heart. Wit\' dem behind us and de power of de ancient loas of de Darkspear Tribe, we be ready to reclaim what\'s ours!', 0),
	(25481, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Falfindel Waywarder sent you? Good! We need your help, now!', 15050),
	(25486, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A boat? Yes, you can have this last one.', 15050),
	(25490, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good. The Twilight\'s Hammer must be sent the message that we will never give up.', 15595),
	(25491, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Arch Druid inspects the seedlings.>$B$BThese seedlings have survived an apocalypse. Even a handful hold great power. Life always replenishes itself, often stronger than before.$B$BOnce the way is clear, we will use these to perform a miracle on this mountain, $N. You will see.', 15595),
	(25492, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $N. There\'s a chance the forest will recover from this yet.$B$BNow, there\'s something else I need you to take care of for me...', 15595),
	(25493, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good. We will need these to act as bait while they are still warm.$B$BHere is my plan...', 15595),
	(25494, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent!  Our pup is ready for a fight.', 15595),
	(25495, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At last, everythin\' be ready. Now, we show Zalazane what happen to dose who defy de Darkspears!', 0),
	(25496, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s how it\'s done!', 15595),
	(25499, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh.  You\'re still alive.$B$BNot bad.', 15595),
	(25500, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is the speech from Toby? Fantastic!$bRecruit, you\'ve done all we could possibly ask for and the Gnomeregan Army thanks you!$bWe\'ve got a strike team heading to Gnomeregan now and that wouldn\'t have been possible without your assistance. For all of your help, we\'d like you to join the Gnomeregan Reserves!$bIt doesn\'t pay very well, but you do get this snazzy helmet. Hang on to that, you might need it someday!', 0),
	(25502, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s good! Between your work and the work of a few others, that valley is secure from a counter-attack.$B$BI\'ve done all I can. It\'s all up to you and the Arch Druid now.', 15595),
	(25507, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Arch Druid takes the shell from you with surprising reverence.>$B$BNemesis is an instrument of evil, but he was forged from a shell fragment of the true ancient.$B$BWe will exploit this connection.', 15595),
	(25509, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well.  You\'re at least competent enough to figure out which way the pointy end of the pick goes.', 15595),
	(25510, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$R.$B$BThis tongue. Is not yours.$B$BWhat do you want ... tormentor?', 15595),
	(25514, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Tortolla quivers and shakes debris free from his great back.>$B$BYou...$BAre not like the others.$B$BI am free once again.$B$BThe others...$BWill pay.', 15595),
	(25519, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$R.$BYou are not like the others.$B$BBraver. Stronger.$BA part of this world...$B    and not the shadow that came before.$B$BThank you.', 15595),
	(25520, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N!$B$BYou were able to earn the ancient\'s trust?$B$BWonderful! We are one step closer to taking back this mountain...', 15595),
	(25521, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh thank you, thank you! I know a bit of alchemy, I\'m not totally useless. Here goes...', 15595),
	(25522, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t believe it! You\'re amazing! Here, please, take your reward, take anything you want! I\'ve gotta save Chelsea!', 15595),
	(25523, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! How does it feel?$B$BIt is challenging to master flight in this burning wasteland, but it is the only way.$B$BI hope you\'re ready for battle, $N...', 15595),
	(25525, 66, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Spectacular flying, $N! Their screeches of anguish echoed about this light-forsaken cavern.$B$BBut our work is not yet finished...', 15595),
	(25531, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my thanks, $N.', 15595),
	(25535, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'More help! Superb! We can certainly use it, I\'ll tell you that much.', 13623),
	(25536, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for stepping up to take care of this, $c. I know there are a lot of concerns swarming us right now, but maintaining the safety of the survivors is paramount.', 13623),
	(25537, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Superb! Chemicals abound!$B$BMy instantaneous chemical synthesizer is already pre-tested and prepared. Your deployment compound shall be ready in the blink of an eye!', 13623),
	(25538, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done my odorific associate. You are both swift and assiduous, if I do say so myself. May your future travels be rampant with inspiration and opulence.', 13623),
	(25539, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, indeed. This is an entirely unshameful amount of clams to have gathered. The survivors back at the cave will surely be grateful.', 13623),
	(25540, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is wonderful. I will begin cooking them immediately. It is good to know that of our many fears, starvation shall no longer need to be one of them.$B$BI imagine the Admiral will have much work for you. Let me trouble you no further for a while.', 13623),
	(25544, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By the wings of Aviana - you were born to fly, $N!$B$BQuickly, let\'s get back out there and hit them again...', 15595),
	(25545, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $c!$b$bThanks to you, my men will be ready to confront the enemy when they attack.', 13623),
	(25546, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This should help relieve our exhaustion.$b$bAgain, we thank you.', 13623),
	(25547, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No time to address the troops now.$b$bJust as well. They know what must be done.', 13623),
	(25548, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did well, $N.  I\'ve a new target for you.', 15595),
	(25549, 1, 6, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You continue to prove your prowess, $N.  At this rate Hyjal might survive this ordeal after all.', 15595),
	(25550, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $N.  We shall soon claim victory in Hyjal.$B$BIt has been an honor to fight along your side.', 15595),
	(25551, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hyjal has been saved, $N.  And it\'s all thanks to you.', 15595),
	(25552, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, $N.  We will use this to draw out the Twilight matriarch.', 15595),
	(25553, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That went... better than expected.', 15595),
	(25554, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These foul books should not be allowed to exist.  Yet the information inside them is of vital importance.', 15595),
	(25555, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done.  Only the final step in your mission remains.', 15595),
	(25558, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Earthen Ring has received my distress message and sent help - just in time it would seem.$b$bHopefully more can be sent soon. We are but few against a great many.', 13623),
	(25560, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A decisive blow! ', 15595),
	(25564, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Everything here seems to be in working order.', 13623),
	(25574, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, $N.  That should put a stop to the attacks once we finish these elementals off.', 15595),
	(25575, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, good. I like nothing more than to see the works of our enemy destroyed.', 15595),
	(25576, 11, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dead? Good. They sealed their fate when they threw their lot in with Ragnaros and his kingdom of flame.$B$BLeave their bodies down here to crumble into ash.', 15595),
	(25577, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great work!$B$BThere was a time when adventurers would collect these cores in order to craft mediocre fire-resistant equipment. But for now, I\'m glad just to destroy these fiends once and for all.', 15595),
	(25578, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alysra\'s decision might not have been the wisest, $N.  Yet there is little time to worry about that now.$B$BI bring important discoveries from the Emerald Dream.', 15595),
	(25579, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $c.$B$BI will get some of our own patrols out to make sure that no more naga get within sight of this cave. We should have the area secured within the hour.', 13623),
	(25580, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n, and just in time too. The Admiral just started sending more men out. Strong sword arms to be sure, but I doubt they possess quite the same awareness and finesse that you do.$B$BWe were lucky to have you here when things went south. I suspect you will have a large role to play in things to come as well.', 13623),
	(25581, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you so much for taking this seriously.$B$BThis is some of the first definitive proof of other members of the Vashj family. Very interesting. And I\'d never even heard of either of the other two figures you mentioned until now.$B$BSo much of our history was lost during the sundering - it\'s exciting to have a chance at reclaiming some of it.', 13623),
	(25582, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is good intel. You have a sharp eye, $c.$B$BIt sounds like the building tucked under the terrace at the far end of the ruins will make a suitable forward post. I will send some men immediately to start defensive preparations and we will reposition there as soon as possible.', 13623),
	(25583, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Interesting indeed.$B$BThe remains you describe sound much like the sea vrykul we encountered in Northrend. I highly doubt we will be striking any alliances with their sort, no matter the cause. Still, this information may prove useful in the future.$B$BI will think on it further if time permits. Thank you for bringing it to my attention.', 13623),
	(25584, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ysera sent you? Good! We need all the help we can get.$B$BWe\'ll never be able to recover the shrines to the ancients so long as Twilight\'s Hammer controls the roads. Somehow we\'ve got to stem the flood.', 15595),
	(25587, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'I cannot thank you enough, $r.$b$bI just hope this whole nightmare has a happy ending.', 15595),
	(25592, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You know what it is to carry yourself with honor, $c. You do Hellscream proud.', 15595),
	(25593, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. You\'ve proven very useful.', 15595),
	(25594, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Glad you know a quick buck when you see one. Pleasure doing business with you, $g buddy:gorgeous;.', 15595),
	(25595, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now to hold up my end of the bargain. I\'ll get this cooked and passed out immediately.$B$BYou and I will have to have a talk later. I\'m going to need help that these soldiers just can\'t offer.', 15595),
	(25597, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey there.  I\'m glad to see they sent someone of your caliber for this operation.$B$BThis here\'s going to call for some subtlety.  We can\'t risk Commander Shadowsong getting killed.', 15595),
	(25598, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where would we be without you, $r!$b$bI don\'t want to even imagine!', 15595),
	(25599, 6, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is the tome we\'ve heard about?$B$B<Jordan hefts the stone slab into his arms and looks it over.>$B$BI see... I guess it\'s good that I can read some of the elemental script. I\'ll work on translating this. Meanwhile, there\'s one final problem to take care of.', 15595),
	(25600, 4, 5, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done! We\'ll seal this fiery hole up behind us and let the minions of the Twilight\'s Hammer discover the corpses we left behind. We couldn\'t have done it without you, $N!', 15595),
	(25601, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There you are, $Ndamus.  I\'ve been meaning to talk to you about something.$B$BI heard about the unfortunate incident that befell our poor friend, Okrog.$B$B<Mylva looks to her left, then her right.  She finally nods and shoots a sly wink in your direction.>$B$BYou might be a better pupil than I had thought.', 15595),
	(25602, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Outstanding!$b$bLet\'s see if this does the trick....$b$bStand back, $n!', 15595),
	(25607, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Ah, ze junk haz arrived! Zit is ze last piece of ze puzzle! Now to zet it up! Standby, $N!', 15595),
	(25608, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $N.  We might win this one yet.', 15595),
	(25611, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'re moving supplies to Hyjal straight from the elemental planes? That explains so much.$B$BYou\'ve made Goldrinn proud by sealing that flamegate, $N, but there may be more portals to seal. You should check with the other shrines!', 15595),
	(25612, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'re moving supplies to Hyjal straight from the elemental planes? Devious.$B$BYou\'ve made Lo\'Gosh proud by sealing that flamegate, $N, but there may be more portals to seal. You should check with the other shrines!', 15595),
	(25613, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kalen sighs.>$B$BWe use guns just fine, friend. CANNONS, on the other hand, I take issue with...', 15595),
	(25614, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $N. The gnome technology, while somewhat obnoxious, is highly effective. We should now have a clear path to Windshear Hold.', 15595),
	(25615, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the airways clear our hippogryphs will be able to move into Stonetalon freely. Well done, $N!$B$BNow on to more pressing matters. $B$BWhat you witnessed at Trueshot Point was a small sampling of the decimation left in the wake of Hellscream\'s legacy. As Warchief of the Horde, Hellscream has declared Kalimdor as the Horde\'s sovereign territory. All that would oppose the Horde are destroyed.$B$BWe are Kalimdor\'s last line of defense. Should we fall, Kalimdor will also fall. The Horde must be stopped!', 15595),
	(25616, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the Krom\'gar incinerators dealt with, the forest may be allowed to regrow. Only time can heal the wounds left by the Horde.', 15595),
	(25617, 2, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, you are the champion Lo\'Gosh promised! Your eyes don\'t deceive you: you have entered the Firelands, an elemental plane of molten stone and fire. We\'ve got our work cut out for us here.$B$BPut aside your differences with the Alliance, there\'s plenty of danger to go around.$B$BAnd take this: the Fang of Lo\'Gosh will allow you to channel the ancient\'s power here within the Firelands. Use it well!', 15595),
	(25618, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, you are the champion Goldrinn promised! Your eyes don\'t deceive you: you have entered the Firelands, an elemental plane of molten stone and fire. We\'ve got our work cut out for us here.$B$BPut aside your differences with the Horde, there\'s plenty of danger to go around.$B$BAnd take this: the Fang of Goldrinn will allow you to channel the ancient\'s power here within the Firelands. Use it well!', 15595),
	(25619, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah! It seems you were right. That broken trident is serving you just fine. I suppose I don\'t get to see you claw anything to death today after all.', 15595),
	(25620, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, my battlemaiden, you\'ve come to me. The warrior caste whispers of nothing but your victories on the battlefield, and we\'ve only just begun our assault to take the city.$B$BYou have served me proud thus far. May the Queen favor you that you might continue to do more of the same.', 15595),
	(25621, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Gnomecorder crackles and pops with static electricity.>$B$BCome in, $N. Can you hear me? Zis iz Professor Xakxak!$B$B*POP*$B$B*CRACKLE*$B$BPERFECT! Viz ze Gnomecorder I vill be able to direct you about Stonetalon vile staying out of harmz vay!$B$BNow, onto our next order of buziness!', 15595),
	(25622, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Gnomecorder buzzes loudly.>$B$BVonderful! As promised, VOILA, your reward!$B$BNow, I have a bit of news that you might find interesting.', 15595),
	(25626, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Minions of the Old God? Two very potent foes have joined forces then. Their hope to defeat the Tidehunter may not be so foolish after all.$B$B$n, we can\'t let that happen. If Azshara defeats the Tidehunter and takes his power for herself, I\'m not sure any number of us could ever hope to oppose her on the seas.$B$BThe first step is clear at least - we need to hunt down the fiend that destroyed our ships. The navy was confident enough to bring in a new fleet, perhaps they have a plan.', 13623),
	(25629, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, Battlemaiden.$B$BI will attend to the eastern bridge. I need you to attend to the temple itself. The ritual must not be interrupted.', 15354),
	(25630, 274, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Can this wait, $c? The battle is not going well.$B$BOh, you\'re here to help. I hope you don\'t mind a little heat...', 15595),
	(25637, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good of you to join me, Battlemaiden. The echoes of your combat graced your approach. It was a beautiful sound to behold.', 15595),
	(25638, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If he still lives, I may be able to locate this poor soul.', 15595),
	(25640, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you again, $N. Thanks for the rescue in Ashenvale. Damn shame about all the gnomes we lost.$B$BYou ready to get down to business?$B$B<Boog points to "The Bomb.">', 15595),
	(25642, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not too much trouble, I hope. With these samples we should be able to figure out what they plan to do with the ore and the big bomb.', 15595),
	(25644, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You were right to come to me with this, $N.  This represents a great threat to us if we do not act swiftly and boldly.', 15595),
	(25646, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice job, I could hear their shrill screams from out here. You\'ve turned the whole place on its head!$B$BDid you happen to find any other information about the mining operation?', 15595),
	(25647, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Boog takes the letter from you and begins to examine it.>$B$BInteresting.$B$B<Boog smells the parchment.>$B$BHrm... Troubling...$B$B<Boog folds the paper in half and looks at you.>$B$BCan\'t understand a damn thing written here - if that is writing. Could just be toilet paper. Sure smells like it.', 15595),
	(25649, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Minx takes the letter from you and begins to read it.>$B$BUh oh...$B$B<Minx smells the parchment.>$B$BDisgusting!$B$B<Minx folds the paper in half and looks at you.>$B$BThe good news is that this isn\'t toilet paper. The bad news is that the ink on this paper is a mixture of kodo poop and blood. That\'s not the worst of it, though...', 15595),
	(25650, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Beads of sweat roll down Boog\'s overly large forehead as he reads the translated letter.>$B$BThis is bad. Really, really bad. You have to warn Lord Fallowmere at Windshear Hold.$B$BWhat in the... It\'s MOVING! The goblin balloon is taking off! We\'re too late!', 15595),
	(25651, 5, 5, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'My gunpowder!$b$bYou found it! I\'m not crazy after all!', 15595),
	(25652, 5, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Amazing story, $g lad:lass;. I\'d have never believed you had I not seen it with my own eyes. You did enough damage to that balloon to make those fiends pull back! Alas, the threat is far from over. We have only delayed the attack. There is much work to do if we are to stop the Horde from destroying Stonetalon!', 15595),
	(25653, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By relieving Tortolla of his final burdens you have acquired for us a formidable ally... and the final piece of the puzzle.$B$BSteel yourself, $N. The most difficult part of our journey is to begin.$B$BWe will bring the fight to their stronghold.', 15595),
	(25654, 2, 0, 0, 0, 400, 0, 0, 0, 'These lands will finally be free of the foulness of the harpies. I cannot thank you enough.', 15050),
	(25655, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Thisalee nods, contentedly, her eyes sparkling.>$B$BFeels great to be off the leash, doesn\'t it?', 15595),
	(25656, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, that\'s a start.$B$BThe birds who laid these eggs will never accept them again, so we\'ll have to raise these birds as orphans in the shrine here. Were Aviana here, she never would\'ve let this travesty happen.$B$BBut, on to business...', 15595),
	(25657, 5, 5, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Amazing!$b$bYou watch the great white beast swim off into the depths and wonder to yourself if anything could ever take him down...', 15595),
	(25658, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Nar\'shola Wards are performing perfectly. I will inform the Mistress of the Tides of your aid immediately.$B$BThank you for your assistance, my lady. ', 15595),
	(25659, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Kvaldir General crumples to the ground, defeated.>$B$B<With this, the ruins of Vashj\'ir have been claimed for Lady Naz\'jar. Her ultimate goals remain uncertain, but it is clear that the naga came here with purpose.>$B$B<If only you could continue, you are sure that the answers to defeating the naga lie within this vision, but the Wavespeaker\'s magics are waning, and you are losing your connection with the Battlemaiden.>', 15595),
	(25662, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We don\'t have much time. To get me out of here you are going to have to take out Warlord Roktrog. He holds the key to this prison.', 15595),
	(25663, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<A whispered plea rings within your head.>$B$BTo be born again, but in darkness...$B$BI have been stolen away.$B$B<The spirit appears frantic, but falls silent as her image fades.>', 15595),
	(25664, 273, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was nasty work, $N, but it had to be done.$B$BAnd if Aviana is truly to be resurrected, then perhaps your actions have enabled Blaithe to someday come back as well?$B$BNow let\'s see if we can contact our long lost guardian...', 15595),
	(25665, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Slow down, $c! You look as though you\'ve seen a ghost...', 15595),
	(25667, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that you\'ve dealt with the wendigos, we should be able to focus our efforts on the Frostmane trolls to the east.', 15595),
	(25668, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N. The mountaineers will be glad to hear that half-rations are at an end. They\'ll need all their strength to continue fighting the Frostmanes.', 15595),
	(25669, 6, 25, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A hero thwarted their plans to destroy Windshear Hold, eh? That hero was you, $N. You are the pride of the Alliance!$B$BIt seems that you have bought us a little bit of time. I must plan for the battle that lies ahead of us. Seek out the other inhabitants of Windshear Hold and lend them your assistance. I will call for you when I am ready to initiate our defensive strategy.', 15595),
	(25670, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This really ain\'t as bad as it looks...', 15595),
	(25673, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Alice claps excitedly.>$B$BMr. P you\'re gonna be ok! Hooray!$B$B<Alice expertly places all of the parts you collected into Big Papa.>$B$BOh, Mr. P! I knew it!', 15595),
	(25721, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well I\'ll be. There\'s someone around here that isn\'t a disgrace to Magni, bless his poor gravelly heart.$B$BJust for that, you get first crack at the ale, $glad:lass;. But don\'t let it get to your bloody head! We\'ve got more gorram work to do, and I won\'t tolerate you lettin\' up early!', 15354),
	(25722, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, well. The good news is, these will do perfectly. The bad news is I can tell they\'re the wrong color for topsoil here, even drunk as I am.$B$BThat means things aren\'t looking good for the area, $n. But we\'ve got more tests to run before we hang up the towel.', 15354),
	(25723, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lovely. These\'ll fry up nice, and the camp\'ll be spared a week of mushroom biscuits.', 15354),
	(25724, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We should be able to focus our efforts on the rest of the trolls to the east, but there\'s still the matter of the wendigos in the Grizzled Den.', 15595),
	(25725, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These\'ll do nicely. I\'ll have the lads back on their feet as soon as I make these somewhat edible.', 15354),
	(25726, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh good, it\'s undamaged! Thanks a lot.$B$BYou ah, you might want to wipe yourself off a bit there.', 15354),
	(25727, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good riddance to bad rubbish! I\'ll burn the foul thing later so it doesn\'t stink up the camp.', 15354),
	(25728, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lord Fallowmere coughs.>$B$BThis is awkward...$B$BGood job out there with the robot. You caught me a little off guard. I didn\'t realize the little girl was so...$B$B<Lord Fallowmere points to his temple and twirls his finger around.>$B$BSpecial...$B$BWell, whatever gets the job done, right? Am I right?$B$BProbably.$B$BHave some ice cream.', 15595),
	(25729, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Gnomecorder buzzes loudly.>$B$BVonderful! That\'s von more name I can scratch off of my list!$B$BI vill be in touch.$B$BXakxak, out!', 15595),
	(25730, 5, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well I\'ll be a monkey\'s uncle. You actually got the beast, eh? Well, a deal\'s a deal! Here\'s your reward!', 15595),
	(25731, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So the harpies are tools of some sort of dragon - "Sethria."$B$BBut what are the dragons doing to those eggs? And what\'s this \'special\' egg that Sethria wanted so badly?$B$BThis is beyond me, $N. I\'ve given a report to Skylord Omnuron - he\'ll know what to do next.', 15595),
	(25732, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is it?$b$bHow is this gunna remove - wait a minute...', 15595),
	(25733, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good job. I wouldn\'t be surprised if the horrid things had eggs in there somewhere, but it\'ll do for now.', 15354),
	(25734, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful, $glad:lass;. This should be all we need. Let\'s have a look.', 15354),
	(25735, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Glorious! Beautiful stuff, this ore.$B$BGood on you for not droppin\' your pick. Last person I sent out let the butt end hit the floor, and that part\'s not sparkproof.', 15354),
	(25736, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The thing\'s still got some fight in it! Amazing!$B$BYou\'re a tough one, $n. It\'s much appreciated. I\'d say a reward is in order before you head out.$B$BKeep doin\' your best for Ironforge, you hear? And if you ever see my sister, say hello for me.', 15354),
	(25739, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Captain Kosak forces a smile at you.>$B$BDon\'t worry about me. Should be ok now that big hero killed the spider queen.$B$BCan get reinforcements through safely now.', 15595),
	(25740, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, $N! I was hoping to see you out here.$B$BWhat, Omnuron calls this a \'fact-finding mission?\' Bah! Facts are best found on corpses.$B$BLet\'s do some damage.', 15595),
	(25741, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will keep us stocked on anti-venom for the foreseeable future. Thank you, $N!', 15595),
	(25743, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, what might have been...', 15595),
	(25746, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re good at this.$B$BI like you.', 15595),
	(25747, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you again, $c. I almost thought we\'d lost you to the Wavespeaker\'s fool errand.$B$BDid anything come of it?', 13623),
	(25748, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'More naga are amassing to the south than reported too it seems. We shall have to move quickly then.', 13623),
	(25749, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are perhaps the most dependable person I\'ve ever met. I wish I could have more men half as thorough as you.', 13623),
	(25751, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are brave indeed! I\'ve seen you battling all manner of murloc, naga, and pointy-toothed fish, but that was nothing! The way you just sling those kelp bulbs under your arm like that is a whole new kind of fearless. BOOM! You could blow up at any second.$B$BYou\'re my kind of $r.', 13623),
	(25752, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did great up there! You devastated their ranks, but there were far more than we accounted for, and most of our men went down out there in the masses of naga.$B$BWe\'ll need to hold this position as long as possible to buy them time. Hopefully some of them will still make it to the rendezvous.', 13623),
	(25753, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. Truly.$B$BWe need to get these men moving as soon as possible. I\'ll meet you back at the forward post soon, I\'m sure.', 13623),
	(25754, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Still so many? They must want something very important here to come in such numbers.$B$BI will be honest with you, $n, because you deserve at least that: I don\'t know how much hope there is. We will retreat shortly, but we won\'t be able to defend ourselves when they strike back. We don\'t have anywhere to run... we\'re running out of options.$B$BI\'m sorry, I should keep such thoughts to myself. Do me a favor and don\'t mention any of that to the men. I\'ll figure something out.', 13623),
	(25755, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re finished! Just in time. I don\'t think we could have held them much longer.$B$BAn artifact? Could this be something we can use against the naga? I suppose that would require finding it.$B$BWe may have to attend to more pressing matters first, until an opportunity to pursue this further presents itself.', 13623),
	(25758, 1, 5, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at these things. Ugh, the runes make my eyes hurt. This one here is meant to sear flesh? Seriously? Ouch! Wait a minute...$B$BThese plates are designed to be riveted directly into flesh. The pain must be unbearable!', 15595),
	(25760, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A Battlemaiden? I never heard of such a thing.$B$BThe way you explain it, it sounds like the naga forces are far greater in scope than the Admiral could possibly have realized. We might be able to learn more through the blade if we can find other locations where this Battlemaiden was present, but the information you gave me makes me fear for the admiral and his soldiers. We must warn them.', 13623),
	(25761, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was some fancy bladework, $N!$B$BThere\'s one less threat for us to worry about in Hyjal.', 15595),
	(25763, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'re doing what?$B$BThey\'re cloaking something? Of course - so our aerial scouts can\'t see anything with our eagle-eyes!', 15595),
	(25764, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did it, $N! Aviana\'s Egg should soon be tucked safely in the boughs of her shrine.$B$BDo you think this means she\'ll really return to us?', 15595),
	(25765, 6, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kosak sent you, eh? Surprising. I thought for sure that he\'d be dead by now.$B$BWell if you made it past the blockade then you definitely have something that we can use.$B$BNow, do you have any news of the Horde? What are they doing? Where are they going? Tell me everything.', 15595),
	(25766, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I assure you, simpleton, the spirits you captured are at rest. Do not let their protests move you.', 15595),
	(25767, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! Arcanist Valdurian will be most pleased.', 15595),
	(25768, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m assuming you saw the Krom\'gar hot air balloon on your way here. If not, get your eyes checked. It\'s hovering directly over the oil platform.', 15595),
	(25769, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you again, $N. I have some news from Mirkfallon Lake.', 15595),
	(25776, 4, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sethria is slain! I knew it was worth the risk.$B$BI\'ll stay here to look for survivors, but I imagine they\'ll want to see you back at the shrine.', 15595),
	(25777, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s take a look here.$B$BOh, this is just lovely. "Significant geological instabilities"? "Threat of sudden, massive topological destabilization"?$B$BNice to hear that somethin\' bad might happen around here. I guess we\'ll just pick up our flooded town and fly it off somewhere safe!$B$BBah!', 15354),
	(25780, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He\'s dead! Thank the Makers...$B$BI don\'t like the looks of them, lad. The Dark Iron I\'ve tussled with were never this crazy. Something\'s getting to these sods...', 15354),
	(25792, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Finally, some good news from the Frostmane Front. I\'ll have the mountaineers press their attack immediately. Now, we must signal our gnomish allies at Steelgrill to start their advance.', 15595),
	(25793, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Seal it off? That\'s gonna take some work, friend.', 15595),
	(25794, 5, 396, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'We must make haste!$b$bAs you can surely see, his time is not long.', 15595),
	(25795, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N! Is it true you led an assault against a twilight dragon?$B$BYou are truly a herald of the ancients!', 15595),
	(25800, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A hearty seafood dinner will lift everyone\'s spirits and help us get the town back in shape again. Thanks for the help, $n.', 15354),
	(25801, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, well done $N.$B$BAccept this as payment for fulfillment of your contract with the Merchant Marines.', 15354),
	(25802, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This crate is covered with clawed scratches, and the marks of water damage.  Prying it open reveals soggy and rotted straw, as if something of value was stored in the crate.  You search through the straw...$B$B...and find an armload of red-colored bottles.', 15354),
	(25803, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This barrel is largely untouched.  Prying it open...$B$B...you are assaulted by the pungent odor of cheese.  It\'s a little wet, but still tasty!', 15354),
	(25804, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This barrel is halfway buried amidst the mud and grass ...', 15354),
	(25805, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The captain of the Blind Princess will be relieved to hear this precious cargo has been recovered.  You\'ve well earned this payment for services rendered.$B$BIt\'s good to see dependable folk like you, especially in trying times such as these.', 15354),
	(25806, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Gnomecorder buzzes and whirs.>$B$BHey, this thing on?$B$B<You hear a tapping sound.>$B$BAnybody there?', 15595),
	(25807, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I ... live.$B$BThose that tried to corrupt me and kidnap my children will soon feel the rake of my talons, $c. Believe it.$B$BContinue to push forward across Hyjal. I will collect myself and assemble with the other ancients.', 15595),
	(25808, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nicely done, $N! You worked the mines like a pro. Now how about returning my goggles.', 15595),
	(25809, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank the Light! You truly are a righteous instrument of power! The Alliance is lucky to you have, $N.', 15595),
	(25810, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So it\'s true - Aviana has returned, with you as her herald.$B$BThere\'s much to be done here. We are deep in the heart of the Firelands. Sethria smuggled stolen eggs from Mount Hyjal here to hatch her own hideous creations - birds of prey, trained for war.$B$BI hope you\'re ready to fight back!', 15595),
	(25811, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here goes nothin\'!', 15595),
	(25812, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A... a $r? Here?$b$bI must be mad...', 13623),
	(25815, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah!  That hits the spot, and loosens the tongue.  Thanks, mate!', 15354),
	(25820, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, bless your heart, to do such a thing for a married woman like me. You\'re too kind.', 15354),
	(25821, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew that you\'d be a special snowflake when I first set my eyes upon you, $N. So special, in fact, that I\'d trust no one else here with what I\'m about to ask of you.', 15595),
	(25822, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This should be enough to supply a hundred Grimtotem! Now to present the weaponry to their chieftain.', 15595),
	(25823, 1, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will call for the infantry to move in and clear up whatever might be left over. If only we had ten-thousand more like you, $N!', 15595),
	(25824, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, it\'s not encouraging, but it\'s something...', 13623),
	(25830, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I ... have not yet ... perished.', 15595),
	(25832, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Aviana\'s face is immobile as you tell her about what happened within the hatchery.>$B$BThey stole my eggs, $c. They took them to that foul place. Corrupted them.$B$BMy children stolen, tormented, killed in a vat of flame... Yes, we will make Twilight\'s Hammer pay.$B$BBut I confess, part of me wants to fly up and simply watch this whole... world... burn.', 15595),
	(25834, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The name be "Cookie," $g lad:lass;: greatest cook \'cross Azeroth. Now the Commander\'s told me what we be needin\' to do. To gain audience with the Grimtotem chief we\'re gonna have to cook up the finest of tauren cuisine.$B$BYe get me the ingredients and I\'ll put together an offerin\' no tauren could refuse. Not even a grim tauren or whatever them things be.', 15595),
	(25837, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Stand back, $N, there\'s about to be a flavor explosion and I wouldn\'t want ya gettin\' hurt.', 15595),
	(25838, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, you must be the $r that Captain Tharran said he\'d be sending. I\'ve already used the deploy-a-tron to get most of the covert ops team into position at Frostmane Retreat. They\'re just waiting on your arrival.', 15595),
	(25839, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t worry, the feeling of being zapped won\'t stay with you for more than a few minutes. All in all, it\'s not a bad way to get where you\'re going. That parachute system needs some work, though. Very late deployment, indeed. Sometimes, too late. Anyway, we have a mission to carry out.', 15595),
	(25840, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent job, $N. With Battok dead, I\'ll send the signal to Captain Tharran. This should be the end of the Frostmane threat.', 15595),
	(25841, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Both you and the air wing performed admirably. There\'s no way that the Frostmanes will remain here now. All that remains is to begin mopping up the survivors.', 15595),
	(25842, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $r.$B$BI am ready now.$B$BAll that I am, and all that this forest once was... it is now yours.', 15595),
	(25843, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$R.$B$BI remember you. Savior of my children.$B$BThe time has come. For vengeance.', 15595),
	(25844, 1, 397, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ton and his bodyguards scarf down the meaty offering.>$B$BThis... this is the greatest thing I have ever tasted. You may prove to be a valuable ally, but before the Grimtotem agree to work with the Alliance, you must agree to our terms. I will now give to you those terms as told to me by my leader. Take them back to your commander and see if he accepts.', 15595),
	(25845, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Weapons, eh?$B$B<Force Commander Valen sighs.>$B$BI\'m about to make an executive decision here, $N. Let\'s hope this pays off, else King Wrynn will have my head!', 15595),
	(25846, 15, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are fine weapons! Powerful steel! My warriors will be unstoppable armed with such weaponry. Magatha smiles down upon you, $N.$B$BThere is but one thing I ask of you, perhaps two.', 15595),
	(25847, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The fight is far from over, $N. The Horde generals still live...', 15595),
	(25848, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Grundig crushes the insignia in his massive fist.>$B$BYes, ally, you have done it! It will take Hellscream weeks to recover from this blow. Southern Stonetalon belongs to the Grimtotem... and the Alliance, of course.', 15595),
	(25851, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Outstanding work, $N! Now our forces only need to worry about the Horde as they enter Stonetalon. ', 15595),
	(25858, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Reinforcements have begun to circle the waters around the ledge, preparing for the attack. They await only your lead.', 15595),
	(25859, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not one slipped through to the bridge. Not one.$B$BIt was very boring. I\'d appreciate it if you shared a little next time.', 15595),
	(25860, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Azjentus is to be taken at his word. Lady Naz\'jar\'s Honor Guard should be sufficient to see the rest of the ritual through.', 15354),
	(25861, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My scythe is sated. Thank you, my lady.', 15595),
	(25862, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The crucible looks far too heavy to carry on your own, but more than enough naga forces remain to prepare it for transport.', 15595),
	(25863, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, my Battlemaiden.$B$BThis crucible will serve as a font of power for our summoning ritual. With it, Sira\'kess will beckon our allies from the depths to bolster our already swelling forces.', 15595),
	(25875, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Get in here and hug a wall! I can\'t risk blowing my cover!', 15595),
	(25876, 5, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'OH NO! They plan to "test" the bomb at Thal\'darah Grove! That\'s the school for young druids located in the heart of Battlescar Valley. You\'ve got to return to Barus with this information! Master Thal\'darah must be warned!', 15595),
	(25877, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Blasted Horde! I\'ve got friends at that grove. Hopefully you know how to ride a hippogryph. We\'ve got to get you to Master Thal\'darah at the overlook immediately!', 15595),
	(25878, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I could see the explosions from here, $N! The Horde won\'t be refueling from Mirkfallon anymore, thanks to you!', 15595),
	(25879, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Slowly, but surely, we pick away at the Horde\'s numbers. They won\'t have a leg to stand on when this war really opens up.', 15595),
	(25880, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are dire times, indeed, $N. Our outpost in Stonetalon Peak has been overrun by fiendish creatures from the depths and the Horde seeks to destroy us. We need a hero, $N; a soldier of the Alliance strong enough to guide us through these trying times.', 15595),
	(25881, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve assembled the survivors? Good, good. And the rest of the mountain - healed?$B$BHaha, strike me down! We\'re on the front lines again!', 15595),
	(25882, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you\'re the one who\'s been helping Captain Tharran beat back the Frostmane trolls? I\'ve seen your name in the reports. It\'s good to finally meet you. You might be just the $c we need to help secure the ranch.', 15595),
	(25883, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re confident that your assault on the naga armaments has made an impact on their effectiveness.', 15595),
	(25884, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The waters surrounding the Holding Pens are red with the blood of the naga.$b$bRendel would be proud!', 15595),
	(25885, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes. This is the stuff.$b$bMaybe I can gradually eat less of it and avoid that side-effect.$b$bThank you, $n.', 13623),
	(25886, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Terrific! Twilight\'s Hammer will no doubt try to re-take the mountain, but they\'ll have to do so without the leadership of those fat-for-brains thugs.', 15595),
	(25887, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is as it should be.$b$bNow the way is clear to deal these naga a crippling blow.', 15595),
	(25888, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us hope for the safety of those released prisoners.$b$bIn return for your noble efforts, please accept this gift.', 13623),
	(25889, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Praise you, $N. The hero we have been searching for has finally arrived, and not a moment too soon.', 15595),
	(25890, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Erunak trusts this task to me?  Very well, let\'s see what we can learn from the ancient one.', 15595),
	(25891, 6, 1, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you know why the Horde destroys? The Horde destroys because they cannot comprehend beauty. They fear it and that which they fear they must destroy. Why else would they destroy Thal\'darah Grove?$B$BTogether, we will make them understand. They will know that what they do comes at a great cost.', 15595),
	(25892, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You made it! After the attack at the forward post, I thought we might be the only ones left. I\'m very glad to see you.', 13623),
	(25893, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Impeccable timing. Like clockwork! Trouble comes. You come. Save the day.  Clockwork!$B$BWe\'ve devised our brilliant plan. Gloriously simple, barring the hostility of local life. Simpler yet with a you available! ', 13623),
	(25894, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Less gill goblins is good!$B$BI\'m glad that they\'re so primitive. I don\'t think I\'d want to be dealing with a race of aquatic tech-freaks right now. Not at all.', 13623),
	(25895, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let me see, let me see... flare gun... balloon... no rope. Never any rope. Terribly impractical if you do ask me. Rope should be mandatory.', 13623),
	(25896, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Kvaldir have proved a greater threat than we anticipated, but our plans are not hindered in the least. As our allies arrive, we will have a force more than sufficient to usurp the Tidehunter.$B$BAll that remains is to ensure that the ritual of summoning is completed.', 15354),
	(25897, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is great! I love it. It should work per... ewww! Is this stuff braided with hair?$B$BDoesn\'t matter. Almost done. This thing will be ready in the twist of a rope.', 13623),
	(25898, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect! There\'s no way they missed that, fighting or not.', 13623),
	(25899, 6, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You killed how many? Well, well. Quite a show. I guess my men don\'t have any more excuses.', 15595),
	(25900, 274, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That didn\'t go well.  For some reason, the beast won\'t speak back to me.$b$b<Duarn is clearly frustrated.>$b$bIf only Erunak had not left us!  He would know what to do.', 15595),
	(25901, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! Still sharp. A little blood on the fletching, but they\'ll fly true.$B$BThank you, $N. Our defense of Hyjal can continue.', 15595),
	(25904, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This power is ancient.$BPrimitive.$BEasy.$B$BWe will use it against them.', 15595),
	(25905, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The rams you rescued have made their way back into the pen. I\'ve got members of the family on a day and night watch now. Those trolls won\'t take us by surprise again!', 15595),
	(25906, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You were sent by the turtle god? Bless his almighty shell! I thought I was trapped down here forever.', 15595),
	(25907, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $N... although I\'m afraid I haven\'t been nearly as productive as you have.', 15595),
	(25908, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Can you sense it?  If you have an ounce of shaman\'s blood in you, you must feel the sense of relief in the air.$b$bNespirah is pleased.  Perhaps she will finally speak with us.', 15595),
	(25909, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Duarn looks at the crab and disguises a frown.>$b$bIt doesn\'t look very impressive, does it?', 13623),
	(25910, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So it is done.$B$BKnowing that Twilight\'s Hammer is in league with creatures of malice such as these... it really curdles the blood.', 15595),
	(25911, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That is the best news I\'ve heard in what seems like an eternity. We\'ll get the survivors moving over there to the surface as soon as possible. Perhaps we can forget that this whole nightmare ever happened.$B$BThank you, $n. I\'m not sure there\'s anything I can do to repay you for everything you\'ve managed to accomplish in this ocean, but I will try to find a way.$B$BYou should consider meeting us at the ships later, when you finish saying your goodbyes to the naga.', 13623),
	(25912, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve found it! Elune bless you, child! Perhaps this book will give me the strength to carry on.', 15595),
	(25913, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N. Each glaive has the name of the sentinel it belonged to imprinted upon its blade. We can now send word to their families and put their souls to rest.', 15595),
	(25914, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m afraid that the death of Harbinger Aph\'lass has not ceased the tendril attacks. You\'ve done all that you can, $N, and for that I thank you.', 15595),
	(25915, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah yes, yes... the secret strength of Nemesis, unearthed here in these caverns.$B$BWe know all that we need to know, $N. It is time to finish this.', 15595),
	(25916, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I had assumed that the naga were only here for those pearls.  No, this makes much more sense.  If they had Nespirah\'s power under their control, the amount of damage the naga could do would be catastrophic!$b$bSomething must be done.', 13623),
	(25917, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N... is that you?', 13623),
	(25918, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2, 0, 0, 0, '<Admiral Dvorek admires the polearms you present him.>$b$bOh, I\'m sorry.  I was just imagining what these will look like with little bits of naga stuck to the ends of them.  Thank you, $N.  We\'ll put these to good use.', 13623),
	(25919, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hopefully we made some progress.  I\'m not sure how we\'ll know when the creature wakes up, but something tells me that it will be pretty obvious when it does.', 13623),
	(25920, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brilliant work!$b$b<Valoren tucks the pearls away beneath her armor.>$b$bNow I just need you and Captain Taylor to get me safely out of here.  I can handle the studies from there on.', 13623),
	(25921, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'No need to bring me up to speed... Nespirah has been narrating your adventures as they happened, and Captain Taylor filled me in on the rest.$b$b<Duarn closes his eyes and nods.>$b$bNespirah says that she is quite grateful, and that she has a small surprise ready for the naga.', 13623),
	(25922, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It appears that I owe you my life, yet again.  Thank the Light that you found me before you and your shaman activated those bio-defenses.', 13623),
	(25923, 1, 5, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The usurper has perished!$B$BTwilight\'s Hammer dreamed of creating their own pantheon of twisted ancients to rule over the land, sea, and air. With your help, they\'ve all been executed.$B$BWe must tell Tortolla at once!', 15595),
	(25924, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not exactly the battle you had anticipated, I\'ll wager. But a battle nonetheless, as you shall soon see....', 15595),
	(25925, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We witnessed the detonation of the bomb. Terrible, terrible destruction... Farwatcher Glen, for better or for worse, is still intact. Unfortunately we\'ve nowhere to run.', 15595),
	(25928, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve been to the firelands?$B$BNemesis is dead?$B$BSo it is finished.$B$BThank you.', 15595),
	(25929, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here you are, $c. With this you should find maneuvering in the sea to be nearly effortless. $b$bNow we must get to work. There is much to be done in little time.', 15595),
	(25930, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Gnomecorder crackles with energy.>$B$BI say, are you there, $N? It would appear that you are in the center of a dragon\'s lair.', 15595),
	(25931, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A smashing success! Perhaps only a minor victory against the brood of Deathwing, but a victory nonetheless!', 15595),
	(25932, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With your help, we\'ve managed to weaken the raiders considerably. They haven\'t suffered such losses since the raids began. Now is the time to press our advantage.', 15595),
	(25933, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sergeant Flinthammer? I\'m not familiar with the name, but, aye, there is a Flinthammer among the miners. He\'s one of the ones lucky enough to make it out of the mine, but most of my men are still trapped down there.', 15595),
	(25934, 5, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. This will allow me to finish my last task and hopefully gain the form of the wolf!$B$B<Salsbury howls.>', 15595),
	(25935, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. The dogs will be well fed and ready to defend our outpost for weeks!', 15595),
	(25936, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'While you were away, I was able to revive some of the fallen warriors.$b$bWe\'ll need every hand if we are to survive here.', 15595),
	(25937, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for recovering these artifacts. I will see to it that they are displayed in the Ironforge museum along with the story of those who died to recover them.', 15595),
	(25938, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hold there, stranger!', 15595),
	(25940, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The forest is being devoured!', 15595),
	(25941, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hear you, $r.$b$bI understand the urgency, but these men are in no condition to fight.', 15595),
	(25947, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done!$b$bNow, more than ever, we are prepared to face the naga!', 15595),
	(25948, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No time to address the Vanguard.$b$bJust as well...', 15595),
	(25949, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Earthen Ring has received my distress message and sent help - just in time it would seem.$b$bHopefully more can be sent soon. We are but few against a great many.', 15595),
	(25950, 4, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Chicken and rice, $N! That will show those sorry and sad snakes who\'s the ol\' pitch and toss!$B$BNow it\'s bird lime for that tiddlywink. Finger and thumb or plink plonk?', 13623),
	(25951, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I could ask for no more proficient a Battlemaiden than you. You have done yourself a great honor this day.', 15354),
	(25952, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $c.$B$BI will get some patrols out of our own to make sure that no more naga get within sight of this cave. We should have the area secured within the hour.', 15595),
	(25953, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n, and just in time too. The Captain just started sending more men out. Strong axe arms, but I doubt they possess quite the same awareness and finesse that you do.$B$BWe were lucky to have you here when things went south. I suspect you will have a large role to play in things to come as well.', 15595),
	(25954, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you so much for taking this seriously.$B$BThis is some of the first definitive proof of other members of the Vashj family. Very interesting. And I\'d never even heard of either of the other two figures you mentioned until now.$B$BSo much of our history was lost during the sundering - it\'s exciting to have a chance at reclaiming some of it.', 15595),
	(25955, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is good intel. You have a sharp eye, $c.$B$BIt sounds like the building north of the gardens will make a suitable forward post. I will send some men immediately to start defensive preparations and we will reposition there as soon as possible.', 15595),
	(25956, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'A shard of metal?$B$BThe remains you describe sound much like the sea vrykul we encountered in Northrend. We\'ll not be striking any alliances with their sort, no matter the cause. Still, this information may prove useful in the future.$B$BI will think on it further if time permits. Thank you for bringing it to my attention.', 15595),
	(25957, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A Battlemaiden? I never heard of such a thing.$B$BThe way you explain it, it sounds like the naga forces are far greater in scope than the Captain could possibly have realized. We might be able to learn more through the blade if we can find other locations where this Battlemaiden was present, but the information you gave me makes me fear for the captain and his soldiers. We must warn them.', 15595),
	(25958, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you again, $c. I almost thought we\'d lost you to the Wavespeaker\'s fool errand.$B$BDid anything come of it?', 15595),
	(25959, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'More naga are amassing to the south than reported too it seems. We shall have to move quickly then.', 15595),
	(25960, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are perhaps the most dependable $r I\'ve ever met. I wish I could have more men that showed half as much pride as you do.', 15595),
	(25962, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are brave indeed! I\'ve seen you battling all manner of murloc, naga, and pointy-toothed fish, but that was nothing! The way you just sling those kelp bulbs under your arm like that is a whole new kind of fearless. BOOM! You could blow up at any second.$B$BYou\'re my kind of $r.', 15595),
	(25963, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did great up there, soldier! You devastated their ranks, but there were far more than we accounted for, and most of my men went down out there in the masses of naga.$B$BWe\'ll need to hold this position as long as possible to buy them time. Hopefully some of them will still make it to the rendezvous.', 15595),
	(25964, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. Truly.$B$BWe need to get these men moving as soon as possible. I\'ll meet you back at the forward post soon, I\'m sure.', 15595),
	(25965, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Still so many? They must want something very important here to come in such numbers.$B$BI will be honest with you, $n, because you deserve at least that: I don\'t know how much hope there is. We will retreat shortly, but we won\'t be able to defend ourselves when they strike back. We don\'t have anywhere to run... we\'re running out of options.$B$BI\'m sorry, I should keep such thoughts to myself. Do me a favor and don\'t mention any of that to the men. I\'ll figure something out.', 15595),
	(25966, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re finished! Just in time. I don\'t think we could have held them much longer.$B$BAn artifact? Could this be something we can use against the naga? I suppose that would require finding it.$B$BWe may have to attend to more pressing matters first, until an opportunity to pursue this further presents itself.', 15595),
	(25967, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You made it! After the attack at the forward post, I thought we might be the only ones left. It\'s good to see you in one piece, $c.', 15595),
	(25968, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at you, a regular aquatic hero! Trouble comes. You come. Save the day.  You must be proud of yourself!$B$BWe\'ve devised our brilliant plan. Gloriously simple, barring the hostility of local life. Simpler yet with a you available! ', 15354),
	(25969, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Less gilblins is good.$B$BI\'m glad that they\'re so primitive. I don\'t think I\'d want to be dealing with a race of aquatic tech-freaks right now.', 15354),
	(25970, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let me see, let me see... flare gun... balloon... no rope. Never any rope. Terribly impractical if you do ask me. Rope should be mandatory.', 15354),
	(25971, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is great! I love it. It should work per... ewww! Is this stuff braided with hair?$B$BDoesn\'t matter. Almost done. This thing will be ready in the twist of a rope.', 15354),
	(25972, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect! There\'s no way they missed that, fighting or not.', 15354),
	(25973, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That is the best news I\'ve ever heard. We\'ll get the survivors moving over there to the surface as soon as possible. Perhaps we can forget that this whole nightmare ever happened.$B$BThank you, $n. You\'ve shown your worth down here. There will be a glorious spot in the Horde for you.$B$BYou should consider meeting us at the ships later, when you finish saying your goodbyes to the naga.', 15354),
	(25974, 4, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice, $N! That will show those naga who\'s the boss!$B$BNow it\'s time for that drink. You want rum or wine?', 15595),
	(25975, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should be enough for now. We know where there\'s more should the need arise.', 13623),
	(25976, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a lot! And we know where there\'s more should the need arise.', 15595),
	(25977, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice Uncle Bob of pokin\' their general.$B$B<The lieutenant shakes her head and grins.>', 13623),
	(25978, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it! The mountaineers are returning to camp and our medics will have their hands full. We are all in your debt, $N.', 15595),
	(25979, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is never easy to countenance violence against the very elements whose powers I wield, but sometimes there is no other solution. Our duty to the people of Dun Morogh comes first.', 15595),
	(25980, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Stuck him right through, did you? I would have loved to have seen that!', 15595),
	(25981, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, they\'re ugly, but they mostly look harmless. Smelly though.$B$BHere, let me clean the gilblin stuff out of these. I\'ve got an idea....', 13623),
	(25982, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, they\'re ugly, but they mostly look harmless. Mostly. They\'re almost cute in a way.$B$BHere, let me clean the gilblin stuff out of these. I\'ve got an idea....', 15595),
	(25983, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s very disturbing news, but I believe our Earthen Ring friends here have a plan.$B$BAnd now that you\'re here....', 13623),
	(25984, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If it weren\'t you saying it, I wouldn\'t believe what that troublesome goblin has to say. This is troubling indeed, but I think our Earthen Ring friends have a few ideas.$B$BAnd now that you\'re here....', 15595),
	(25985, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, you were sent here by Tiala? A wonderful student, she\'ll do many great things.$B$BAlthough I sense even greater potential from you.$B$BPlease, stay a while in our shrine. There\'s much to do, but you can\'t accomplish anything with a troubled mind.', 14333),
	(25986, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s a good thing the Senator didn\'t come out here on his own. It\'s dangerous, and we\'re going to need all the help we can get to get the situation under control.', 15595),
	(25987, 5, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What happened? That thing wasn\'t completely dead! Maybe I should stick to mechanical stuff.$B$BIt gave you a vision? Of killing all of us?! That doesn\'t sound good.$B$BWell, in any case, that Earthen Ring fellow, Erunak Stonespeaker, wants these specimens all taken out to him. I\'ll make sure he gets them. I don\'t want them anywhere near me.', 13623),
	(25988, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My bad. My name is Fiasco for a reason. I should have known that thing wasn\'t completely dead when it wiggled a little.$B$BYou say it gave you a vision? Of killing all of us?! That doesn\'t sound good.$B$BHrm, well that Earthen Ring fellow, Erunak Stonespeaker, wants these specimens all taken out to him. I\'ll make sure they get out there. It\'s not like I want them stinking up the place around here.', 15595),
	(25989, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Duarn looks at the crab and disguises a frown.>$b$bIt doesn\'t look very impressive, does it?', 15595),
	(25990, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I had assumed that the naga were only here for those pearls.  No, this makes much more sense.  If they had Nespirah\'s power under their control, the amount of damage the naga could do would be catastrophic!$b$bSomething must be done.', 15595),
	(25991, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N... is that you?', 15595),
	(25992, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2, 0, 0, 0, '<Captain Vilethorn admires the polearms you present him.>$b$bOh, I\'m sorry.  I was just imagining what these will look like with little bits of naga stuck to the ends of them.  Thank you, $N.  We\'ll put these to good use.', 15595),
	(25993, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hopefully we made some progress.  I\'m not sure how we\'ll know when the creature wakes up, but something tells me that it will be pretty obvious when it does.', 15595),
	(25994, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brilliant work!$b$b<Tulra tucks the pearls away beneath her armor.>$b$bNow I just need you and Legionnaire Nazgrim to get me safely out of here.  I can handle the studies from there on.', 15595),
	(25995, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'No need to bring me up to speed... Nespirah has been narrating your adventures as they happened, and Legionnaire Nazgrim filled me in on the rest.$b$b<Duarn closes his eyes and nods.>$b$bNespirah says that she is quite grateful, and that she has a small surprise ready for the naga.', 15595),
	(25996, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It appears that I owe you my life, yet again.  Thank Hellscream that you found me before you and your shaman activated those bio-defenses.', 15595),
	(25997, 1, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew they weren\'t here to see the sights.$B$B<The sergeant examines the plans you captured, his eyes wide.>$B$BThis is more serious than we thought! This is no mere raid. The Dark Irons intend to cripple the defense of Ironforge itself!', 15595),
	(26000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '...$r? Here?$b$bI must be mad...', 15595),
	(26005, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You made it out! Good to see you, $n.$B$BIt\'s good to be out of the water for a bit, and to have some resources at our disposal again. I\'m sure many of the boys would give anything to turn around and head home after what we\'ve been through, but we still have a grim task ahead.$B$BWhat about you? Want to stick it through to the end with us? I wouldn\'t blame you if you\'ve had your fill.', 13623),
	(26006, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like you make it out in one piece, $c!$B$BIt\'s good to be out of that foul pit of water for a moment, and to have some resources at our disposal again. Don\'t get too comfortable though, we still have a grim task ahead.$B$BWhat about you? Had enough honor for one day, or do you want to get back in there and make Hellscream proud?', 15354),
	(26007, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, it\'s not encouraging, but it\'s something...', 15595),
	(26008, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us hope for the safety of those released prisoners.$b$bIn return for your noble efforts, please accept this gift.', 15595),
	(26012, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for heeding Rhonin\'s call, brave adventurer.$B$BLet me share with you what we know regarding recent events, and any assistance you might offer would be greatly appreciated.', 15595),
	(26013, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you again, $C, for rescuing me from Baltharus\'s clutches!$B$BThere is still much work to be done, however....', 15354),
	(26014, 18, 18, 18, 0, 0, 3000, 5000, 0, 'Of course we haven\'t returned yet!  We\'ve had our fair share of setbacks... not the least of which was the passing of my dear brother Oskar.$b$b<Humphrey sniffles loudly.>$b$bHe lost his grip and floated away, the poor lad!  He thought he\'d grab some fish to bring back to the captain, but he floated off, and was eaten by one o\' those... those great-eels!  Bwaaaah ha ha haaaah!', 13623),
	(26015, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Humphrey grabs the phosphora from you and attaches it to an unusual device.>$b$bThere ya go.  It\'s beautiful!  Oskar would be proud.', 13623),
	(26017, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya did good, $N!  Ya did real good!', 13623),
	(26018, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Humphrey listens as you recount your fights with the Coldlight murlocs.>$b$bHmm... they sound like regular ol\' murlocs... just underwater.  That\'ll make Cap\'n Glovaal happy.', 13623),
	(26019, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Whaaa... an egg?  An EEL egg?$b$b<Even upside-down, you can see the gears in Humphrey\'s head turning.>$b$bWe can definitely do something with this!  Get ready kid, \'cause it\'s time for some good ol\'-fashioned Digsong revenge!', 13623),
	(26021, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oskar\'s alive?  Wait... what did ya say?  Ya let him FLOAT AWAY AGAIN?!$b$bWell... ya held up your end of the bargain, and I appreciate everything ya\'ve done, $N.$b$bHere... take this.  I\'ve only been hanging onto it as ballast, but it doesn\'t seem to be doing much good.', 13623),
	(26040, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes. This is the stuff.$b$bMaybe I can wean off of it and avoid the side-effect.$b$bThank you, $n.', 15595),
	(26056, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I sure am glad you\'re here!', 13623),
	(26057, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I sure am glad you\'re here!', 15595),
	(26065, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N.$B$BThese nightmarish creatures that rise from below give me pause. I fear that our efforts will be for nothing.', 15595),
	(26070, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good enough for me.$B$BDon\'t get too complacent, $N. The hard part\'s about to come.', 13623),
	(26071, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done.$B$BDon\'t get too full of yourself, $N. The hard part\'s about to come.', 15595),
	(26072, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, $r, can you feel them seething with a desire to break free and destroy us?$B$BThis is good! They will be the perfect lure for their leader.', 15595),
	(26080, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see.  Yes, I am rememberink now... Humphrey and Oskar vere not the strongest svimmers.$b$bThe reconnaissance is helpful, and the extra fish look very tasty.  If you are seeink Mister Digsong before he returns, please send him my thanks.', 13623),
	(26086, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gah!  These fish are impossible to hit!$b$b<Orako looks at you.>$b$bMy wolf got eaten by a fish, and I\'m not going back until I find her.', 15595),
	(26087, 1, 18, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey, look at how glowy it is!$b$b<Orako looks wistfully off into the distance.>$b$bMy wolf loved things that were glowy...', 15595),
	(26088, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm... you got a lot of fish, but none of these are the ones that ate my wolf.  I think it was probably a bigger fish.', 15595),
	(26089, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I know, murlocs aren\'t fish.  I thought that killing them would make me feel better, but I still feel sad about my wolf.$b$b<Orako sighs.>', 15595),
	(26090, 397, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That is a big egg.$b$b<Orako sniffs it.>$b$bIt is big, and it smells like fish.  Maybe the big fish that made this egg is the big fish that ate my wolf!', 15595),
	(26091, 4, 4, 4, 4, 0, 1000, 1500, 2000, '<Orako is busy playing with Wolf.>$b$bOh, thank you, $N!  I knew Wolf was alive!$b$bHere, take one of these.  I don\'t need them anymore.', 15595),
	(26092, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is his report?!  That idiot...$b$bI suppose we can use the food.  Thanks, $N.  You\'ve done as well as can be expected.', 15595),
	(26096, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will use the mushrooms as a reagent to treat the corpses. We will have one ready for you soon.', 15595),
	(26103, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Engineer Hexascrub sticks a finger into each sample and sniffs it.>$b$bYes, I think this will do.', 13623),
	(26105, 273, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did well, $N.  We need to be especially wary of Horde attacks right now.  The Pincer X2 has plenty of firepower at sea, but in the back of this cave, she is exceptionally vulnerable.', 13623),
	(26106, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you considered a career in science, $N?  If you ever get tired of this $c nonsense, come see me!  I could use an assistant with your devotion to experimentation and the scientific method.', 13623),
	(26111, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And now we will see if we can get you into L\'ghorek to speak with it before it dies.', 15595),
	(26122, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Fiasco sticks a finger into each sample and sniffs it.>$b$bYes, I think this will do.', 15595),
	(26125, 273, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did well, $N.  We need to be especially wary of Alliance attacks right now.  The Verne\'s got plenty of firepower out at sea, but in the back of this cave, she\'s far too vulnerable.', 15595),
	(26126, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s it.  Starting today, I\'m shifting the Verne over to bio-fuel.  I\'ll send some men up to harvest more oil.$b$bThink of all the sea creatures that we\'ve saved today, $N!', 15595),
	(26129, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rebel arsenals?  In my own city?$B$BWhat in the bloody hell was Crowley up to?', 15595),
	(26130, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that you have unplugged L\'ghorek, we must attempt to make contact with it. I can sense that the ancient yet lives, but only barely.', 15595),
	(26132, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The last thing we needed was a bunch of summoned creatures swarming our forces during the final assault.', 13623),
	(26133, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s one less thing we need to think about during the final assault.', 15595),
	(26135, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Minions of the Old God? Two very potent foes have joined forces then. Their hope to defeat the Tidehunter may not be so foolish after all.$B$B$n, we can\'t let that happen. If Azshara defeats the Tidehunter and takes his power for herself, I\'m not sure any number of us could ever hope to oppose her on the seas.$B$BThe first step is clear at least - we need to hunt down the fiend that destroyed our ships. The navy was confident enough to bring in a new fleet, perhaps they have a plan.', 15354),
	(26140, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'WISE OF... YOUR ERUNAK TO... HAVE... YOU USE... THE FACELESS\' BRAIN. I SEE... YOU NOW.$B$BI WILL DIE. THERE IS NO... STOPPING... THE INEVITABLE.$B$BBUT... YOU WILL HELP... ME DEAL WITH... THESE PARASITES FIRST.', 15595),
	(26141, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'WE WILL USE... THESE... RUNESTONES TO ALLOW... YOU TO POSSESS... ONE OF... THE WATER ELEMENTALS.', 15595),
	(26142, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'THEY SHALL ASCEND... NO MORE!', 15595),
	(26143, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'YOU HAVE DONE... MYSELF AND... THE TIDEHUNTER GREAT... SERVICE.', 15595),
	(26144, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A job well done. Now you don\'t need to worry about what would have happened to them if you hadn\'t been around.$B$BThe last one was even appreciative enough to give you a reward they\'d kept hidden on their person.', 13623),
	(26149, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A job well done. Now you don\'t need to worry about what would have happened to them if you hadn\'t been around.$B$BThe last one was even appreciative enough to give you a reward they\'d kept hidden on their person.', 15595),
	(26150, 1, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'William sent you? Bless his soul. I... I\'m ok... It\'s just... Well...', 14333),
	(26152, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And justice is served!', 14333),
	(26154, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'THEIR DEVOTIONS ARE... SILENCED.$B$BNOW THAT... YOU HAVE... THEIR POWER... YOU MUST DESTROY... THEIR LEADER.', 15595),
	(26177, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These crabs look great!  I will clean these up and make sure that the King hears about your contribution.  Thanks!', 13623),
	(26179, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t think there could be too much misinterpreting or ignoring of that signal, hm? The Venture Co. will know not to take the $r lightly, or to be so arrogant as to believe we would allow them to steal the natural resources around us without protest.', 0),
	(26180, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My anger is somewhat lessened at the news that the villain Fizsprocket is dead. I will go through his personal effects and see if there is any additional information about what the Venture Co. has planned for the future. Thank you for your efforts, $N.', 0),
	(26181, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello again, $c.$B$BI felt L\'ghorek die. A shame that such a magnificent being is gone.$B$BIf we do not assist Neptulon, we will all meet the same fate.', 13623),
	(26182, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello again, $c.$B$BI felt L\'ghorek die. A shame that such a magnificent being is gone.$B$BIf we do not assist Neptulon, we will all meet the same fate.', 15595),
	(26188, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, thank you, $N. Using the items you brought me, I will be able to create the remedy I need to stop the spread of the infection and, eventually, cure it completely. I owe you my life in thanks.\n\nBut I\'ll never forget that screeching call when Mazzranache came upon me, the blaze of color as its beak descended...\n\nBe wary on your travels.', 0),
	(26190, 1, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N.  I will get to work scaling these for the King right away.  ', 13623),
	(26191, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With every day, more warriors arrive at Azshara\'s command. Soon, Neptulon the Tidehunter will hear of our preparations, but too late to stop what we have set in motion. Our numbers will be too great and our allies too powerful. Victory is only a matter of time.$B$BIn Azshara\'s name.', 15595),
	(26192, 1, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These sacks look like just enough, $N.  Can\'t wait to see the smiles on the orphans\' faces.', 14333),
	(26193, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'NO!$b$bThis is NOT over!', 13623),
	(26194, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They may think they\'ve won, but my axe and I have something to say about that!', 15354),
	(26203, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'For a gnome who has spent so much time inside Gnomeregan, you look positively fit and healthy, $n. That\'s good. Before we can complete what Operation: Gnomeregan began, we\'re going to need more warriors like you.', 0),
	(26204, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, mon! Dis stuff come easy to ya.', 0),
	(26205, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow, I never expected it to work on the first trial!$B$BUh, I mean, we\'ve succeeded! I wonder what other uses I we can find for this handy little guy.', 0),
	(26208, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Even now, only the S.A.F.E. teams dare to venture far into the city to search for survivors. Meanwhile, Thermaplugg has sent one of his followers, Crushcog, to distract us and buy time for him to dig in.', 0),
	(26209, 6, 5, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gnolls and murlocs? Horse poopy, $g pal:lady;! Gnolls and murlocs didn\'t kill these people. I\'ve seen what gnolls and murlocs do to people that they kill and this... isn\'t it. Too pretty. Too... perfect.$B$BFurthermore, the Furlbrow\'s had been squatting on this farm for 5 years. No, whoever wiped them out had a reason. This is murder, plain and simple and we\'re gonna get to the bottom of it...', 15595),
	(26210, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'MON! This is fantastic! With my best lure and the snapjaw population down, the fish will pile up.', 0),
	(26211, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, mon! I can\'t thank you enough! Hopefully this here fishing pole will be reward enough for the job.', 0),
	(26212, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lard takes the huge haunch of meat from you and stuffs it in his face.>\n\nDis hit da spot! Tanks little one.\n\nLard make you special picnic basket for help Lard.', 0),
	(26213, 6, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Is this supposed to be some kind of joke, because I\'m not laughing. Bits and pieces of red cloth? What the hell is this supposed to mean?', 15595),
	(26214, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice find, rookie. I think I have a stack of these on my desk back at the station. We\'re basically back to square one. What do we know? Someone that likes to write fiction about the past sent the Furlbrows a letter.$B$BLooks like we got ourselves a real history... mystery.', 15595),
	(26215, 274, 1, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look, we ain\'t got no room for no more...$B$BHoratio sent you? Right then... um, how can I help you?$B$BHe\'s not here is he? Heh, he knows I wasn\'t hidin\' from him, right? Was just tryin\' to lay low and all that, ya know?', 15595),
	(26219, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Vell done, Private $n.$B$BThe cavern is ours, but the beast escaped. Should it raise its ugly head again, ve vill make with blastink it out of the vater.', 13623),
	(26220, 1, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $N.  These will do nicely.', 15595),
	(26221, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $c.$B$BThat slippery beast got away! I\'ll be making a few upgrades. It won\'t be so lucky next time.', 15595),
	(26222, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are fantastic! Let\'s see what we can put together. Would you be interested in testing out the prototype once I\'m done?', 0),
	(26223, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A job well done, $r. The Revantusk thank you for your contribution.', 0),
	(26224, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have proven a worthy ally to the Revantusk, $N. Well done.', 0),
	(26225, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect! I don\'t know where I\'d get this stuff if it wasn\'t for drunk humans repeatedly crashing their ships.\n\nNormally I\'d settle down and get ready to haggle with you for an hour, but you\'re in luck; I\'m too eager to crack these open. Cheers!', 0),
	(26226, 1, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ugh, I never liked cooking these slimy things.  Thanks for the help $N.', 15595),
	(26227, 1, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let me see your hands... Aha!  You\'re not any better at collecting these wretched things than I am!', 15595),
	(26228, 274, 1, 5, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lou puts his hands to his ears and starts talking loudly.>$B$BSTOP! STOP! STOP! I don\'t wanna hear it! I don\'t wanna know and I don\'t care! That kind of information is liable to get you killed \'round these parts.$B$BI got one more bit of information for you and then we\'re done!', 15595),
	(26229, 4, 5, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh SWEET justice! Killin\' those kobolds won\'t make me walk like a normal person and it sure won\'t get me a job, but damn does it feel good.$B$B<Jimb reaches into a crusty old sack.>$B$BHere, I think I got somethin\' for you from my kobold huntin\' days. Maybe you can put it to good use.', 15595),
	(26230, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just smellin\' you comin\' got my stomach rumblin\'! We\'re gonna eat like kings tonight!', 15595),
	(26232, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re dealing with an organization here, rookie. You don\'t just off the richest bum in Westfall in broad daylight and leave no witnesses. Someone with a lot of power is behind these murders. What have you learned so far?', 15595),
	(26233, 1, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see you are a skilled thief as well, $N.  Don\'t worry, we will return the rice once we are done... or not.', 15595),
	(26235, 1, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work $N!  I will see that these rations are returned to the troops immediately.', 15595),
	(26236, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Horatio Laine? That man is a scumbag. Dirty as my underwear.$B$BListen, friend, I don\'t often give out advice like this, but you seem like a good $g man:woman;. GET OUT OF WESTFALL. You\'re already in way over your head. All you\'re doing now is putting your neck on the chopping block.', 15595),
	(26237, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $g brother:sister;. You\'ve done Salma and I a great service and I promise that it won\'t soon be forgotten. I don\'t have much money, but you\'re welcome to what I do have.', 15595),
	(26238, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That will show the Wildhammer to stay away from our lands!\n\nCrazy dwarves should\'ve stayed in the mountains...', 0),
	(26240, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Makes all the difference, doesn\'t it? That\'ll teach those dwarves a lesson.', 0),
	(26241, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Bless your heart, dear. These poor orphans haven\'t had a hot meal in days.$B$BIt looks like we will have enough left over to help feed many more of the homeless of Westfall.', 15595),
	(26244, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did what was necessary, $N.  I can tell you\'re the sort of $c I\'ll get along with well.', 15595),
	(26245, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The clues point to an obvious conclusion.  Too obvious perhaps.', 15595),
	(26246, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why would the Alliance attack the Horde just as they\'re about to deliver a fragment of the World Pillar to us?', 15595),
	(26247, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oi, $N!  I was told I\'d have company soon.', 15595),
	(26248, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We were bound to run into the Twilight\'s Hammer sooner or later, $N.  If they\'re behind this, it\'s quite likely that the World Pillar fragment is in their possession.', 15595),
	(26249, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This ship is filled with rats...', 15595),
	(26250, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oi, this was a heavy one!  He nearly broke me gryphon\'s back!$B$BAre you ready to interrogate the ogre, $N?', 15595),
	(26251, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N.  The Twilight\'s Hammer is an evil that we must fight anywhere we find them.', 15595),
	(26252, 25, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Is that... Is that the heart of one of the watchers? I\'ve heard stories about using one of these to power up a watcher for personal use. Of course I\'m really in no shape to try such things myself.', 15595),
	(26254, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have our answers, $N.  Let\'s report back.', 15595),
	(26255, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must investigate your findings further, but we must not lose track of the fragment.', 15595),
	(26256, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'re keeping slaves here?  We ought to free them regardless, but perhaps they might also aid us in finding the forgemaster.', 15595),
	(26257, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It actually worked? That\'s incredible, $N. Hopefully that takes care of the harvest golem problem here in Westfall.', 15595),
	(26258, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This must be where the world pillar fragment was brought.  Let\'s have a closer look.', 15595),
	(26259, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is still great power present in his blood, $N.  I can sense it even now.$B$BYet there is also much corruption.  I am not sure we can salvage the Earthwarder\'s essence from this.', 15595),
	(26260, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is an entry for an upcoming meeting at the Upper Silvermarsh.$B$BThis must be where the Forgemaster is.', 15595),
	(26261, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us find this journal.  We\'re getting close to the World Pillar fragment, I can sense it.', 15595),
	(26263, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, mon. A fine hero of the Horde you are.', 0),
	(26264, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t wait to give this new technology a try! We\'ve lost more gnomes to radiation than we can count. It\'s time to turn that around!', 0),
	(26265, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a relief! Thank you for your help. I hope that gadget Engineer Grindspark was working on helps get the airfield cleaned up permanently.', 0),
	(26266, 5, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I smell Westfall stew! Mother sent you!?', 15595),
	(26267, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to see you back... and not missing any limbs, either.', 0),
	(26268, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'re still intact! There\'s a lot of memories in these crate. Let\'s see what we\'ve got in the first one...\n\nHey, banana bread! And it\'s still fresh!\n\nHere, mon, I\'ll take this and you can pick something else.', 0),
	(26270, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Of course, dear. Our little girl works at Sentinel Hill and is very close with the homeless of Westfall. Perhaps she has overheard something. Before you go, let me wrap up the Westfall Stew and tell you a little bit about our dear little girl.', 15595),
	(26271, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have a kind heart, $N. You have done a good thing, today, and that act will reflect back upon you when judgment day comes.', 15595),
	(26272, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Anotha newblood, eh?$B$BYa actually have a sly look about ya though. Fierce eyes. You might have the makings of a real $c.$B$BLets not waste anymore time \'den.', 0),
	(26273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad, mon. Ya have a natural flow to ya swings - you may have a talent for dis.$B$BSome rough edges ta be sure, but we\'ll get dose ironed out here and I\'ll teach ya a few new tings as we go.', 0),
	(26274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, mon! Dis stuff come easy to ya.', 0),
	(26275, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dese are some fine pelts, $G boy:girl;. We could make some hefty cloaks outta dese.', 0),
	(26276, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya handle yerself quite well. Ya gonna be quite powerful some day.', 0),
	(26277, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya tha new recruit everyone\'s talkin\' about, eh? Welcome ta tha Darkspear.', 0),
	(26283, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fascinating... How large did you say it was? I wonder if others could be found intact...\n\nThis sample is excellent. I\'ll be sharing it with my fellow researchers.', 0),
	(26284, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have me own thanks and th\' thanks of th\' men you rescued. I\'ve already had th\' boys start setting up the gear down inside the cave. It should be ready to go soon.', 0),
	(26285, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, now, that\'s more like it. We may get around to blowin\' up somethin\' after all.', 0),
	(26286, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Helix? I\'ve heard that name before. Recently as a matter of fact, but who is this admiral?', 15595),
	(26287, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N. You have provided us a temporary reprieve from the onslaught of gnolls, but there is more work to be done.', 15595),
	(26288, 4, 396, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $N. It will take the Riverpaw weeks to recover from the blow you just dealt. Please take an item of your choosing as a reward for what you have done.', 15595),
	(26289, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Helix is the one responsible for the gnoll attacks?$B$B<Kearnen nods at the tower.>$B$BHe\'s inside. He\'s been there for days. I\'ve just been waiting for an excuse to bust him.', 15595),
	(26290, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What could possibly be going on in Moonbrook? I don\'t like this one bit, $N.', 15595),
	(26291, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Who IS this Shadowy Figure? We have to get to Moonbrook.', 15595),
	(26292, 396, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The natives are restless, $N. I don\'t know what\'s going on, but homeless activity in this area has quadrupled in the past two days. If I didn\'t know any better I\'d say they were planning something...', 15595),
	(26293, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Busy now. Go away.$B$BWait, what? Hellscream sent you? What - uh - what can I do for you? Him? Us?', 15595),
	(26294, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Garrosh laughs.>$B$BInstilled a little discipline in them, did you? Good, good!$B$BEveryone pulls their weight in my Horde, from the smallest peon to the proudest warrior. I tolerate nothing less.$B$BOur preparations for the invasion are almost complete.', 15595),
	(26295, 6, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'V? The only V I know is VanCleef, but he died many years ago.', 15595),
	(26296, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I haven\'t seen a red bandana in five years. Could this shadowy figure be attempting to reform the Defias Brotherhood?', 15595),
	(26297, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I could hear the cheers from here. It seems as if we\'ve got a huge problem on our hands, $N.  We have to discover the identity of this shadowy menace before we enlist the aid of Stormwind. Perhaps there is another way...', 15595),
	(26306, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N! Let the Vilebranch flee in terror from the sight of you!', 0),
	(26307, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It won\'t be long until we\'re the only trolls left breathing on these walls.', 0),
	(26308, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There are none left to oppose the Revantusk! Any stragglers will be quickly taken care of.\n\nYou\'ve done my people a great honor, $N.', 0),
	(26309, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'First the spiders and now this. I can smell the venom in this blood... it\'s the same as the skitterlings, but stronger.\n\nThe Vilebranch and spiders... there\'s some potential here.', 0),
	(26310, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh yes... I was wise to ask you to get these. How fascinating.\n\nCome here, my pretties. Into the bag you go.', 0),
	(26311, 6, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sauranok seems uninterested in the map as you relate your story.>$B$BTwilight Assassins followed you to the bar? Here, in Orgrimmar?$B$BThe Warchief won\'t be happy about this.$B$BContinue your preparations for the invasion and I will investigate.', 15595),
	(26312, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. Many Earthen Ring owe dere lives to ya dis day.', 15354),
	(26313, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dese are in surprisingly good condition - good work, mon.', 15354),
	(26314, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dat will slow their assault a bit while Norsala be findin\' a way to calm\'m. We\'ve no desire ta be remainin\' enemies of Therazane the Stonemother.', 15354),
	(26315, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yeah, mon... dat\'s about the reaction we were expectin\'.$B$BHe mentioned Diamant though? If da two don\'t get along, perhaps this Diamant be a bit less brash den Boden. At least it\'s somethin\'.$B$BLet me see if I can get da earth to tell me where we might be findin\' dis Diamant.', 15354),
	(26316, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It won\'t be tough to collapse th\' tunnel, but I\'m goin\' to need my team an\' my equipment \'afore I can get to th\' task.', 0),
	(26318, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I could feel th\' explosion way up here! My boys did a fine job riggin\' up that blast, but it wouldn\'t have happened without your help. It\'s only fair that I split my contract payment with you for helpin\' me finish th\' job.', 0),
	(26319, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm, yes, perhaps I could be of some assistance. When I was in Northrend I helped the people of Valgarde uncover some of the mysteries of the vrykul by delving into the spirit world. Perhaps the same could be done here.', 15595),
	(26320, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'WHAT? VanCleef had a daughter?', 15595),
	(26322, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will deploy a battalion of soldiers to Westfall at once! With the Defias Brotherhood reborn, an old threat to the kingdom is renewed.', 13623),
	(26324, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What, another message from Hellscream? His patience is thinner than calf\'s hide.$B$BHave you ever worked with goblins before? Everywhere is another hidden cost! Our ships lie half-assembled and the air fleet is scattered to the winds.$B$BIf this invasion is going to happen, I\'m going to need your help.', 15595),
	(26326, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey, mon! Thank ya for comin\'.$B$BWe weren\'t ready for dis kind of attack. We been expectin\' da Twilight Cult, but not elementals... we\'ve got no idea what upset dem so much that dey would turn on us like dis.$B$BYou haven\'t been out dere killin\' them, have you?', 15354),
	(26327, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well met! If you\'ve got a weapon on you, I\'ll take any help I can get clearing out these crazed fools!', 13623),
	(26328, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah... you must be the $r that I was expecting.$B$BYou have come on behalf of the Earthen Ring then?', 15354),
	(26329, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The high tinker reads Jessup\'s report.>$B$BSplendid news! With the troggs taken care of, we should be able to turn our attention to Crushcog\'s troublemaking.', 0),
	(26331, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should set back Crushcog\'s plans a bit, but we can\'t rest until he is defeated and Chill Breeze Valley is secure.', 0),
	(26333, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mekkatorque will be pleased to hear that you\'ve ruined Crushcog\'s plans to use our old weapons for his followers. Without the mechano-tanks under his command, he\'ll be weak and vulnerable.', 0),
	(26335, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Here, in excruciating detail, are the blueprints for the Foebreaker.>$B$B<You twist the documents every which way, trying to make sense of the incomprehensible scribbles, notes, and corrections.>', 15595),
	(26337, 5, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So they were trying to skimp on production costs? Unacceptable!$B$BI\'m glad you knocked some sense into them. If that foreman makes good on his word, our fleet will be ship-shape in time for the invasion.', 15595),
	(26339, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, yes, Kelsey told me to expect you. There\'s still much to do before we can take on Crushcog.', 0),
	(26342, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve given us just the opening we\'ll need to get the drop on Crushcog. Excellent work, $n.', 0),
	(26347, 396, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Praise you, brave $C.  The rocks of the Westfall Coast shall be lit thanks to your hard work.  Many lives will be spared so long as the torch is kept lit.$b$bI died needlessly on this very shore.  My afterlife plight is to see that no others follow my destiny.', 15595),
	(26348, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N.  You have quite a knack for combat.  Thanks to you the Coast of Westfall is a safer place.', 15595),
	(26349, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So the foul heathen, Murk-Eye is dead.  Well done, $N.  By your hands one life was laid to rest but perhaps many more were saved.  The Great Sea, wrought with danger as it is, shall be a wee bit safer this night thanks to your heroics.', 15595),
	(26353, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The footlocker slowly creaks open.  Sand and water seem to be its only contents. But wait!  A small crab scurries out with a clue to the treasure in his claws!', 15595),
	(26354, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, treasure hunter!', 15595),
	(26355, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re on your way to the jackpot, treasure seeker!', 15595),
	(26356, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The hinges on the old chest are rusty but they still work.  You force the chest open and take the booty.$b$bCongratulations!', 15595),
	(26357, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Such a pretty site ta see the enemy\'s hopes burnin\'...', 0),
	(26358, 5, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Fleep wipes her face, plastering an enormous grease smear across her cheek.>$B$BWhat? The Captain said WHAT?$B$B<She shakes her pipe wrench threateningly.>$B$BIt\'s HIS fault this big beast of an engine is delayed.', 15595),
	(26361, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! I should have this here engine samophlanginated within the hour.', 15595),
	(26363, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dead? All of them, around the altar? And you found these spider idols on them...\n\nA mass sacrifice. They threw their lives to Shadra.', 0),
	(26364, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re finally free of Razlo Crushcog and his interference! With the defeat of Crushcog and his forces, Thermaplugg can\'t afford to send any more of his followers to the surface. I can\'t wait for the day when we defeat him for good!', 0),
	(26365, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Heard Westfall was in some deep doody.$B$B<Parker doesn\'t even turn to face you.>$B$BWell, we got our own set of problems here. See them gnolls out there? Looks like they\'re actin\' up again. I don\'t like it. Don\'t like it one bit.', 13623),
	(26366, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The look of fear and confusion on his face... this is what he deserved! Let\'s make sure all the Vilebranch wear the same look.', 0),
	(26367, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I wish I could have been there to see it, $N! I\'ll have to hear the story from Ongo\'longo himself when this is over.', 0),
	(26368, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mmm, yes... that old nostalgic smell.\n\nYou\'ve done well for the Forsaken, and the Horde.', 0),
	(26369, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The parts scattered, the keepers separated... I see.\n\nThis is a ritual to summon Shadra. They must not have gotten far. It should be destroyed...', 0),
	(26370, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Five years of work burned to the ground in five minutes. Damn the Defias!$B$BAnd this is only the beginning, $N! We have a long, hard road ahead of us.', 13623),
	(26371, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aye... I used to be flesh and blood, just like you, $g lad:missy;. That is, until that fateful day when the murlocs attacked the lighthouse...', 15595),
	(26372, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My airship has engines? At last!$B$BNow we can rip the heavens a new one!$B$BOnce the ground and naval forces are ready, we\'re going to light up the skies over the Twilight Highlands.', 15595),
	(26374, 273, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N! Most of my soldiers have already reported for duty, some a little worse for the wear.$B$BOne night in Bilgewater makes a hard orc humble.$B$BStill, fresh fighting in the Twilight Highlands should restore discipline.', 15595),
	(26375, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a generous $r. You give back to the earth that offers you so much. You have my respect. You shall surely have the respect of the Stone Lords with time.', 15354),
	(26376, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have observed you, $r.$B$BYou do not fear shedding Twilight blood.$B$BIn this, I am willing to extend you some degree of trust.$B$BIt is a start.$B$BAll things in time.', 15354),
	(26377, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Time brings respect to all.$B$BThe smallest pebble.$B$BThe largest mountain.$B$BThe most stubborn cultist.', 15354),
	(26378, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Murder, rookie. That\'s what you\'re looking at on the ground in front of us.', 15595),
	(26380, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These look promising. I\'ve heard great things about the Short and Stout Brewery, but I haven\'t had the chance to try their ale until now.$B$BWhile you\'re here, relax a little. If you need a spare hearthstone or wish to make Kharanos your home, just speak to me and I\'ll be happy to help.', 15595),
	(26381, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m pleased, $N. That was quicker than I expected.', 0),
	(26382, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, good. Just put them over there, I\'ve got my hands full.', 0),
	(26384, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, what have we here...\n\nFascinating. Quite fascinating.', 0),
	(26385, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our allies have come to our aid? Thank Elune. Tyrande was wise to extend open arms to your people.$B$BWe need help.  We need everyone we can get.', 15595),
	(26387, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now we\'ve got a win-win situation. The spiders are going to either starve off, or find some dwarves and elves to replenish their larder, since my colleagues and I would make a poor meal.', 0),
	(26388, 5, 6, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is a disaster, $N!$B$BOur air fleet was decimated. And reports are coming in that our navy was attacked - unprovoked - by the Alliance in open water.$B$BAnd what of Hellscream? Is the Warchief dead?', 15595),
	(26389, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Blackrock orcs will surely fall now that their main force has been defeated! Only one task remains.', 15595),
	(26390, 396, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With Kurtok slain we are safe once again from the orcish hordes. I will send peasants to the pass in an attempt to seal the passage so that no more orcs may come through into our territory.$B$BYou have the thanks of Stormwind and of the Alliance, hero!', 15595),
	(26391, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Bless your heart, $N. You truly are a hero of the Alliance! Though the land is completely incinerated and there is nothing left of the vineyard but ash and debris, I still might be able to recover. Right? How bad can it be?', 15595),
	(26393, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have to get this note to Stormwind?  That\'s not a problem, you can take one of my gryphons!', 15595),
	(26394, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, a note from Smith Argus?  I\'m not surprised he needs more gear.  There are so many new recruits these days.$B$BWell thank you, $N.  Here\'s some money to cover your travel costs.', 15595),
	(26395, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A crate for Goldshire, eh?  People sure are getting lazy. Have you been to Goldshire before?  If so, then it\'s no problem, my friend.  I have plenty of gryphons trained to fly that route!', 14333),
	(26396, 4, 2, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Great, you brought the armor!  We\'ll get this divvied to those who need it immediately.$B$BThank you, $N.  Your efforts have been a great help to us.  And now that you\'re no stranger to gryphons, I hope you\'ll come and lend your aid to Goldshire often!', 14333),
	(26402, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Telaron has already sent word of you, $n. I\'m interested in seeing if you\'re half as skilled as he claims.$B$BI am fighting a war on multiple fronts, while keeping our currently held areas properly defended, as well as overseeing the instruction of our youngest sentinels. If you\'re a decent fighter, there will be plenty for you to do.', 15050),
	(26406, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There it is... only one left.', 0),
	(26409, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hiya! Lend a hand, would ya, $g bub : toots;?', 15595),
	(26410, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good thing that I just happen to be a grand master of all things explosively alchemical.$B$BThis won\'t ignite on its own, though.', 15595),
	(26411, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like that did it. He should come to any moment now.$B$BI told you I was a grand master of alchemy!$B$BI\'ve got some extra resin leftover. I can make it into all kinds of explosively wonderful stuff. What do you want?', 15595),
	(26413, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are honored by Flint Oremantle\'s presence. I am given to understand that the Stonefather is in possession of a fragment of the World Pillar.$B$BIt is imperative that we recover all of the fragments. The instability between worlds is increasing. Soon it may become too great even for mighty Thrall to hold at bay.', 15595),
	(26418, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes... it\'s finally time. Shadra will be ours!', 0),
	(26419, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellently done. You have served the Dark Lady well today, $N.\n\nThis virulent blood will supply our armies with all manner of powerful weapons against the disgusting Alliance. We will wipe them from these lands.\n\nFor the Horde, of course... and all thanks to you.', 0),
	(26420, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those look like some nice bass, $N.  Let\'s fry em\' up and see how they taste!', 14333),
	(26425, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to meet you, $n. You\'ve probably heard others speaking of Operation: Gnomeregan. Let me tell you a bit about what happened and why we left the dwarven city of Ironforge.', 0),
	(26426, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The ground rumbles slightly as you approach the cave. This looks to be the entrance that Diamant and Felsen spoke of.>', 15354),
	(26427, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All right, help me get tied to the wheel.$B$B<Moody sips from the bottle.>', 15595),
	(26430, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Revantusk, $c. I hope fighting the Witherbark hasn\'t exhausted you; the Vilebranch are even worse.', 0),
	(26432, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, $c. We\'re gonna make the Vilebranch regret ever crossin\' us.', 0),
	(26436, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Diamant says you are to be trusted. Diamant is patient and wise, so I shall allow you to prove yourself.$B$BAs it happens, I could use hands that are more... mobile.', 15354),
	(26437, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh... invigorating. Thank you, fleshling.', 15354),
	(26438, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve proven useful, $r.', 15354),
	(26439, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $r.', 15354),
	(26440, 33, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The stones in Pebble\'s body bounce up and down happily. He seems very appreciative.>', 15354),
	(26441, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve made a friend, have you?$B$BAre you certain you want to feed him? He might become attached.', 15354),
	(26442, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like the traps are working!  Thanks $N!', 13623),
	(26443, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By the Seven Crystals of Ata\'mal, this cannot be! They plan to attack Forest Song?!$B$BNot on my watch!$B$B<Vindicator Vedaar crumples the demon-scrawled plans in his fist.>$B$BNo. We will not allow this to happen!', 0),
	(26444, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my respect and thanks, $c. Perhaps we\'ll be able to create a new home here without having to worry about the Burning Legion yet again.', 0),
	(26445, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Never again will the Burning Legion threaten Ashenvale! You have delivered us from a fight we very likely would have lost, $c.$B$BI give you thanks, $N, and the deepest gratitude of the Hand of Argus. It honors me to have you at our side!', 0),
	(26446, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Though it may take a great deal of your years for the seedlings to grow into ancients, in the fullness of time they will aid us in our fight against all of the enemies of Ashenvale.', 0),
	(26452, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $r!  I look forward to seeing you fight again soon.', 15595),
	(26453, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to see another new arrival here at Forest Song.$B$BVindicator Palanaar is sending as much help as she can muster and each set of hands is appreciated.$B$BTake a look around, $c. It may not be much now, but with time and help from our night elf allies, we\'ll build a settlement worthy of calling home. There is much to be done here and any help you can provide would be welcome.', 15595),
	(26454, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wood warped by foul demonic magic is of no use to the draenei at Forest Song. Nothing sound can be built with it, but I shall purify it and return it in good time to Architect Nemos and his people for their use.$B$BSome good will come from this tragedy, after all.', 0),
	(26455, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $N. There is certainly a latent power here, one that not even constant exposure to the corruption of the satyr can dim.$B$BDo you see how it still shines, after all these years?', 0),
	(26456, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for delivering this report, $c. From what Sentinel Melyria writes, it seems our worst fears have come to pass. With each advance we make, the Horde appears more determined to do as much damage as possible.$B$BWe can\'t afford to back down; the fate of our ancestral lands hangs in the balance. With more people like you on the frontlines, I\'m certain we could triumph.$B$BWill you join our fight? A new front has just opened in Warsong Gulch to the south.', 15595),
	(26457, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At last we have sent a message that the orcs won\'t dare ignore. Any overseer or foreman who sets foot within the camp to replace Gorthak will feel my wrath!$B$BWe must press our advantage, $N, and never rest until the Warsong Lumber Camp is a distant memory and a glade of trees stands upon that ground.$B$BNow what was this about explosives...?', 0),
	(26462, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad for a city-dwellin\' $r. Good show, aye!', 0),
	(26463, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Teronis\' body lies broken atop the small rise next to the Keeper.$B$BDeep slashes crisscross his corpse.', 15595),
	(26464, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is terrible, $N. Teronis is dead?!$B$BThe time for mourning will come, but for now we must focus our efforts. I will send some of the Sentinels to recover Teronis\' body and to assist the keeper.$B$BYou have the gem that Teronis was seeking? It must be delivered to Astranaar.', 15595),
	(26465, 5, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s quite a few that you have found! Thank you, $N!$B$BThe old city of Zoram holds many secrets, and these statuettes may be the key to many of them.', 15595),
	(26466, 4, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found the ring! Thank you, $N.$B$BPlease take this as payment, and know that your deeds today will remain forever in my memory.', 15595),
	(26467, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Judging by the gaping wound in her side, Anilia is on the verge of death.', 0),
	(26468, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Anilia died? No... that can\'t be! It was just yesterday that we were running and playing together in the woods.$b$bI guess those days are over...', 0),
	(26469, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, kind $r. My sister\'s spirit is gladdened by your efforts.', 0),
	(26470, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N! With the befouled elemental numbers thinned and Tideress put back into the lake, we should be able to launch a counter-offensive on Silverwind Refuge.$B$B<The sentinel frowns a bit, concern washing over her face.>$B$BJust as soon as we\'re done with defending the spire....', 15595),
	(26472, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rest in peace, my friends.$B$B<You can see the sorrow in the druid cat\'s eyes.>$B$BI felt the anguish of the Dor\'danil Barrows lessen, and knew that you had completed your task.$B$BIt was grim work that you did, $N, for the spirits you destroyed were merely victims of the Horde\'s evil. But with their destruction, let us hope the maddened spirits will finally find peace.', 0),
	(26473, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'Ah, you have the hair! This is a good first step. There are other ingredients that we will need, but the hair of the fallen Ancient could well be the most important.$B$BI only hope that whatever the Forsaken are devising from the plant will not be turned into a weapon. We simply do not have the numbers to remove them right now, especially with Maestra\'s Post under attack!', 15595),
	(26474, 6, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is from Orendil?$B$BHis skill with herbs and healing is great! This cure gives me hope, when before I had little....', 15595),
	(26475, 5, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, you found it! Odd... it looks tarnished somehow. I will place the tear in a stew, and pray that it will cure her.$B$BThank you! Thank you, $N!', 15595),
	(26476, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, Raene sent you? It must be serious indeed.$B$BWhat can I help you with?', 15595),
	(26477, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m pleased to see you\'re back, $N.', 15595),
	(26478, 6, 21, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You got it? Wonderful for you... and for Raene!$B$BI guess we\'ll have to see about reassembling it, won\'t we?', 15595),
	(26479, 6, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve recreated the rod Teronis had set out to find? That\'s wonderful to hear.$B$BShael\'dryn has been indispensible in her assistance. Teronis would be proud to see his quest is continuing even after his tragic passing.$B$B<Raene looks over the reconstructed rod with a look of approval and thoughts racing behind her eyes.>$B$BNow it is time for us to make use of its power to eliminate the enemies of Ashenvale!', 15595),
	(26480, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes... you appear as one of my kind, but I care not what you truly are if you can help the furbolg.$B$BThe night elves and now the orcs have visited many atrocities upon my people.$B$BCorruption runs through our veins, corruption brought down upon us by the prideful night elves and the warlike orcs. They are the ones who did this to our people... They are the ones I blame for being cast out of my tribe.$B$BAt night I can still see the campfires burning in the darkness.', 0),
	(26481, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, my friend.$B$BNow quickly, hand me Ran\'s skull. While his essence yet taints it, we shall fashion it upon Dartol\'s Rod giving you the power to influence my brethren and deliver them from evil!', 0),
	(26482, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, you used the skull of the furbolg king to modify the power of Dartol\'s Rod? You then used that power to convince the captured furbolg to rise up and attack the Horde at Silverwind Refuge?$B$BI am more than pleased and impressed with your abilities, $N. The Sentinels cannot thank you enough. It should be a simple matter for us to sweep away the orcs and retake the refuge now!$B$BTeronis would be proud. You have my deepest respect.', 0),
	(26483, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that\'s what I like to hear! Good on ya.', 0),
	(26484, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Stonefather\'s son, Flint, sent you? No time to talk.$B$BWe must prevent a second front from opening up on the war!', 14333),
	(26485, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, nice an\' fresh. I\'ll get those going while you fetch me some more goods then...', 0),
	(26486, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s the stuff! Wouldn\'t want any trolls or goblins gettin\' pleasure out of these, now would we!\n\nMaybe I can work a bit of this into my next brew...', 0),
	(26490, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at it! That\'ll put some oomph into the mix!', 0),
	(26491, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to see you back... and not missing any limbs, either.', 0),
	(26492, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like it\'s still good inside! Huh... is that banana bread? Still fresh!\n\nHere, lad, take your share of goods.', 0),
	(26496, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well met, $N! We\'ve got a lot of trolls to kill and only so many hands to do it with!', 0),
	(26497, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aye, we\'ll have these trolls cleared out yet.', 0),
	(26498, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It won\'t be long until we\'re the only dwarves left breathing on these walls.', 0),
	(26499, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my thanks, $N. You\'ve made all the difference, and the fate of these cowardly stone trogg ambushers is set in stone.$B$BNow we must get about the business of retaking Stonehearth.', 14333),
	(26500, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not a bad start, though you\'ll have to destroy more of them than that if you\'re going to rescue the Stonefather.$B$BA lot more.', 14333),
	(26501, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is good. We no longer need to worry about stone trogg attacks from the rear.$B$BLet\'s see what you can do for us on the front.', 14333),
	(26502, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<Clay grumbles to himself.>$B$BThose\'ll do. Just put them down over there.$B$B<The Earthen looks you up and down with one eye and then spits dust onto the ground.>$B$BI\'m going to have something for you to do in a moment. Maybe.', 14333),
	(26503, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew it! Looks like Yowler is behind this uprising - which is incredible, because we keep killing gnolls named Yowler. I don\'t know how many sons the original Yowler had, but it\'s got to be close to a hundred.$B$BWell, looks like we got ourselves another Yowler to kill.$B$BMagistrate Solomon must be notified.', 13623),
	(26504, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A job well done deserves a reward, wouldn\'t you say?$B$BDon\'t spend this all in one place, $c. Better to spread it around, if you catch my drift.', 13623),
	(26505, 1, 1, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Magistrate Solomon puts on his monocle.>$B$BOh, you\'re not Conacher. What have you got there?$B$B<Magistrate Solomon takes Parker\'s report from you.>$B$BOh for pity\'s sake. Yowler? AGAIN?', 13623),
	(26506, 4, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'PERFECT! I\'ll put these in the pot right away. Dinner should be ready in a few hours.$B$BThank you, darling!', 13623),
	(26507, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Pebble leaps upon the pile of petrified bats and rolls around in them, seeming to forget that you exist entirely. Perhaps for the best, if Kor\'s warnings are to be trusted.>', 15354),
	(26508, 4, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for finding my necklace $G mister : miss; $c... you are very kind!  My kitty thanks you too - isn\'t that right Effsee?', 13623),
	(26509, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Finally the menace is laid to rest!  Thank you, $n, you have done me a great service.  The garden shall be in full bloom this season!', 13623),
	(26510, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! Let me make a few adjustments here and we should be good to go.', 13623),
	(26511, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That ought to teach those murlocs a lesson. Hopefully the next time they decide to raid our town they\'ll think twice.$B$BWe both know that won\'t happen.', 13623),
	(26512, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The gnomecorder crackles and pops.>$B$BCan you hear me, $N? Is this thing on? Ah, yes, I see you there now.$B$BLet\'s get to work!', 13623),
	(26513, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, citizen. Without you, we would have starved or worse, been forced to go out and get food for ourselves.', 13623),
	(26514, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The gnomecorder crackles and pops.>$B$BGood work, $N. I\'ve just been handed some important information. It would appear that our most hated enemy, the Blackrock orcs, have wised up...$B$B<The gnomecorder whirs as a compartment opens up.>$B$BI\'ve transferred a few silver over to you for the gnome, erm, gnoll kills.', 13623),
	(26515, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ain\'t that a hoot! Wish I could\'ve seen it myself.', 0),
	(26516, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve cleared straight through \'em! Jintha\'Alor is as good as wiped out!', 0),
	(26517, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dead? All of them, around the altar? And you found these spider idols on them...\n\nIt\'s Shadra. The Spider Loa! They\'re trying to tap her power!', 0),
	(26518, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s one ugly mug. Maybe he was takin\' other heads tryin\' to find a prettier one!', 0),
	(26519, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The orb hisses as you touch it.>', 13623),
	(26520, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You used an ettin to remove the boulder that was crushing Foreman Oslow? Incredible work, $N! Oslow will be grateful once he regains his composure.', 13623),
	(26521, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The elements dance, and fire consumes. Let the flame show \'em the cost of their wickedness!', 0),
	(26523, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By Kurdan\'s beard... these don\'t look like any spiders I\'ve seen before. Dark magic\'s at work here.', 0),
	(26524, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This isn\'t just blood... it\'s venom!\n\nSpiders... venom... I hope I\'m wrong about my hunches here, $N.', 0),
	(26525, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good riddance. May those horrid things never walk these lands again.', 0),
	(26526, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A tablet! If I can read this... this is a ritual to summon Shadra herself into this world, and a list of the idols needed.\n\nYou\'ve done a good job slaying the keeper and getting ahold of this, $N.', 0),
	(26528, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N. We\'ll be knockin\' on this bug\'s door in no time.', 0),
	(26529, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There it is... only one left, lad.', 0),
	(26530, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is it, lad! We\'re ready!', 0),
	(26531, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Talonaxe and the boys are right behind. Let\'s do this!', 0),
	(26532, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done a great thing for the Wildhammer today, $N. I wish Falstad could\'ve been here for that.\n\nOn behalf of the whole clan, I\'d like to repay you for keeping these lands free from that foul shadow. You\'ve earned this reward.', 0),
	(26536, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These perch look great $N.  Why don\'t you join us for a fish fry tonight?', 13623),
	(26537, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a good dent, but it\'s clear to me that we\'re going to have to handle this a slightly different way.', 14333),
	(26538, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Gregor bows respectfully to Zaela.>$B$BIf it is Zaela\'s wish, then you shall have your supplies. Just don\'t tell the Dragonmaw Warchief...', 15595),
	(26539, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad you\'re here, $c. Perhaps a seasoned veteran of the Horde\'s campaigns in Northrend and elsewhere can talk some sense into the Dragonmaw leadership...', 15595),
	(26540, 5, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dragon\'s Blood!? We best not tell our red dragon allies that we\'ve used these.$B$BStill, it\'s powerful magic... We\'ll have our fighting force back in no time.', 15595),
	(26542, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Aerie Peak, $N. On behalf of High Thane Falstad, I thank ye for comin\' to help us.', 0),
	(26543, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like you found the clams, $N.  These will do nicely.', 15354),
	(26544, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The gnomecorder buzzes and whirs.>$B$BJust put the missive in the little compartment and I\'ll read it. I am fluent in orcish.$B$B<You hear a distraught yell in the background.>$B$BIt looks like these orcs are here under the direct command of Yowler. That means Yowler must have the orc invasion plan.', 13623),
	(26545, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Magistrate Solomon takes the plans from you and begins reading.>$B$BShadowhide army!? Damn those orcs to hell! These invasion plans speak of a massive build up of orcish and gnoll forces in the east. Looks like Gath\'Ilzogg, the Blackrock general, is preparing to march his armies across Lakeshire and attack Stormwind directly!', 13623),
	(26546, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Treat them with respect, and they\'ll treat you with it as well.\n\nGive \'em guff and you\'ll be out an eye!', 0),
	(26547, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Much appreciated, $N.', 0),
	(26548, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you out here! Let\'s get to it.', 0),
	(26549, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wake up, $N! We don\'t have much time.$B$BI rescued your gear for you.$B$BAt least now you\'ve seen the foolishness of our leader first-hand. His blood is contaminated, his rage is unquenchable -- and he\'ll destroy us all trying to defeat the Horde!', 15595),
	(26556, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work $N.  These samples will help us figure out what is going on in that toxic soup over there.', 15354),
	(26557, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Outstanding!  Those sandy carp are picky eaters aren\'t they?', 15354),
	(26558, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Marnal draws close... and Shadra even closer. Prepare for bloodshed.', 0),
	(26560, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I know where they\'re holding Krakauer and Danforth. We gotta hurry. They were prepping those two for a sacrifice!', 13623),
	(26561, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wha... Where am I? What happened? Messner? Jorgensen?$B$BOH MY GOSH! We have to get to Danforth! It might already be too late!\n', 13623),
	(26562, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'About damn time you sissies showed up. My arms were gettin\' tired.\n', 13623),
	(26563, 66, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Colonel Troteman salutes.>$B$BUnbelievable work, $N. You\'ve managed to rescue the entire Bravo Company from the clutches of the Blackrock orcs? With Keeshan\'s team rescued and Keeshan\'s belongings returned, there\'s no way Keeshan could refuse us.', 13623),
	(26564, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well then. Maybe you\'re okay after all.$B$BAlright, alright... don\'t get all bent out of shape. Just give me a few moments with these parts.', 14333),
	(26566, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So Mekkatorque himself has heard of my little project? Splendid! I\'ve almost finished my latest prototype, but maybe you can help me chase down those last few parts.', 0),
	(26567, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Help you? Help these people? These people that would rather spit on me than crack a smile?', 13623),
	(26568, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Troteman sighs.>$B$BI\'m not giving up on him, $N, and I\'m not giving up on Redridge. We need to boost his spirits... Rouse the slumbering monster within him!', 13623),
	(26569, 4, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fantastic work, $N! These will come in handy for our next project, the Lakeshire SUPER BRIDGE, meant to traverse the length of Lake Everstill. It should be done in 20 or so years. Give or take a decade or two.', 13623),
	(26570, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve probably bought us another day, maybe two. Nice work, $N.', 13623),
	(26571, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The gnomecorder buzzes with energy.>$B$BCome in, $N. Do you copy? Troteman here! Great job on getting Keeshan\'s weapons back! Now there\'s one final mission you have to run. Are you up to the challenge?', 13623),
	(26572, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice one, $N!  I tell ya, golden stonefish are not easy to come by so this is a nice treat.', 15354),
	(26573, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope with these items and with his crew all rescued he\'ll have a change of heart. We can\'t do this without Keeshan.  ', 13623),
	(26574, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Shadebough, $n. Lady Shandris sent word of you.', 15050),
	(26575, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $r. You\'ve done all that I can ask of you. I shall impart my favor for you to the Stonemother.$B$BMay the stone beneath your feet hold you steady during your quest for the World Pillar.', 15354),
	(26576, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings, $r. I have been told of your coming. If you wish to aid me, then perhaps I can be of aid to you as well.', 15354),
	(26577, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are Diamant\'s chosen.$B$BSo small. So fragile.$B$BDo you realize that your actions shall be the basis by which your entire, "Earthen Ring" is judged? You truly think you can stand for so many?$B$BYou are a fool. A confident fool. We shall see if you are a capable fool as well.', 14333),
	(26578, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have appealed to Diamant. He is patient. Trusting. Perhaps too much so. You have much to prove if you wish my favor, $r.$B$BStill, this is a start.', 14333),
	(26579, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You carry with you a certain degree of potency. I can find some respect for such strength, especially in your kind.$B$BMy concerns are not yet abated. Not for the source of the overgrowth, and not for you.', 14333),
	(26580, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to see you again, $g brother:sister;. I see that your efforts go well. The Stone Lords appear to be showing you some degree of trust.$B$BWe\'ve come to help. We might be of some aid in tracking down the source of this sudden growth. I highly suspect your giant friend\'s aggressions are focused in the wrong direction.', 14333),
	(26581, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You let the mist touch your skin? I hope there weren\'t any adverse affects.', 14333),
	(26582, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The stone troggs? And I am to trust you at your word?$B$BI have no love for the Verlok anyway. Suspicion is more than enough reason to lay waste to them. We shall see if your word is true.', 14333),
	(26583, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $r.$B$BGorsik shall hear of your deed. Therazane shall hear of your deed.$B$BYou are quite vicious for one so small... and so soft.', 14333),
	(26584, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done fleshling. Your presence complemented my brothers well.', 14333),
	(26585, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So your words prove true. You have my gratitude, $r.', 14333),
	(26586, 6, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Keeshan? You mean JOHNNY\'S ALIVE? You bet your sweet behind I\'ll help, but first you gotta get me out of this damned cage.', 13623),
	(26587, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'IT\'S PAYBACK TIME!', 13623),
	(26588, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N, you got one!  It\'s a rare day that I get to see such a strong, beautiful fish.', 15354),
	(26591, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If you ever get tired of your being a $c, come look me up. You seem very good with those fleshy hands of yours.', 14333),
	(26597, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '...feel strength returning....$b$bWhere might I be?  Booty Bay?  Oh my!  I had the strangest dream...$b$b...the weakness has not completely left me....', 15595),
	(26598, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Witch Doctor Unbagwa like Gorilla Fangs!  For you I talk to spirits.  Make Mokk the Savage come.$b$bYou protect Witch Doctor Unbagwa from other Gorilla-beast though or no Mokk for you!', 15595),
	(26599, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found it!  What a glorious day for ol\' Hecklebury, this is.  Getting back my chest cools some of the fire in me.$B$BBut my revenge isn\'t complete...', 15595),
	(26600, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This wasn\'t expensive, was it?  Well, here\'s some pieces of eight to reimburse you.$b$bNow let\'s get onto this revenge, shall we?', 15595),
	(26601, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mok\'rash... Negolash... Gorlash... they\'re all gone.$b$bI suppose I have no excuses now.  I can return to the high seas and a life of pillage and booty!  And it\'s all thanks to you.$b$bNow I just need to get myself a ship...', 15595),
	(26602, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t believe my fortune, $N!  Meeting you has turned my luck to the better, make no mistake there!$B$BIf I ever get a new ship and you\'re looking to sail the seas, you would be my honored guest.', 15595),
	(26603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you come to free me?', 15595),
	(26604, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s about time you returned.  I was beginning to worry that I was going to be eaten while you hunted.$b$bA cat eating a princess... wouldn\'t that be a fancy feast?', 15595),
	(26605, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Poobah surveys her belongings.>$b$bLooks like it\'s all here.  Alright, I think I\'m ready to be rescued now.', 15595),
	(26606, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N, you have saved me from a great dishonor. If it was within my power, I would offer you a place among my tribe. But for now, all I can only offer you is this token for the courage and nobility you have shown.', 15595),
	(26607, 1, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Keeshan takes the bundle from you and opens it.>$B$BMy bow... and knife! Where did you...$B$BJade\'s amulet... My darling Jade.$B$B<Keeshan picks up his red headband.>$B$BWe got orcs to kill.', 13623),
	(26608, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Fel Orcs from Outland have laid claim to the Dragonmaw? Obscene!$B$BIf Hellscream knew what was happening here, he\'d raze their city to the ground...', 15595),
	(26609, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'On top of the barrel, you discover a map with some hastily written text on it, along with some coins.', 15595),
	(26610, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sure, I remember you, $c.  Back from scouting I see....', 15595),
	(26611, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Bloodsail Buccaneers attacking Booty Bay?  This isn\'t the first time that those blaggards have tried something.  Booty Bay is impenetrable!$b$bSounds like they might be changing their strategies up, though.  Wouldn\'t put it past Firallon to try something crazy.  Very well, let\'s see what else they\'re up to.', 15595),
	(26612, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect, $n.  Now that we know their plan, it\'s just a matter of time.$b$bAnd to think the fools have dropped anchor just off the cape....', 15595),
	(26613, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good show, $n!  And just before I need to ship out too!  Can\'t thank you enough, old friend.', 15595),
	(26614, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Shiver me timbers and timber me shivers!  Ye found me beautiful eye!  Let\'s see if she still fits.$b$b<Kshhh-thunk>$b$b$n ho!  Blimey, I can see!!', 15595),
	(26616, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s orc killin\' time.', 13623),
	(26617, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That coin!  Where did you get it?$b$bBruce... yes, I see.  He was one of the Blackwater Raiders once.  One of us, before Greymane closed the Gilneas ports and held his crew captive.$b$bI know that what happened in Gilneas changed the people there, but I never expected them to change their loyalties.  Especially not Bruce.$b$bIf you wouldn\'t mind, could I keep the coin?  I\'ll pay its worth in gold.', 15595),
	(26619, 6, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N, what are your people doing? Are you attacking the Dragonmaw or are you here to rid us of Mor\'ghor\'s corruption?$B$B<Zaela listens to the plan.>$B$BAh, I see now. I like the way you think. Warchief Mor\'ghor won\'t even know what hit him.$B$BLet\'s do this!', 15595),
	(26621, 4, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve lost a lot of good orcs, but the fight is going our way, $N.$B$BMor\'ghor\'s regime is collapsing. All that remains is to destroy the beast himself.', 15595),
	(26622, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N! You have done the Horde proud in my absence.$B$BThe Dragonmaw have joined us, with Zaela as their new leader. Blood was shed, but casualties were low, and we have their complete loyalty.$B$BOur Horde grows stronger!', 15595),
	(26624, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yarr, ya made a good decision, $g lad: wench;.', 15595),
	(26625, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<Gravel solemnly nods his head.>$B$BFinally, we can move forward and rescue the Stonefather.', 14333),
	(26632, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The catapult chief gives you an appraising look.>$B$BWord of your prowess has spread ahead of you, $r. Let\'s see if you can help us keep these fungal horrors off of the front.', 14333),
	(26636, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice job, rookie. I\'m gonna go ahead and put the camo in the box. We should be ready soon.', 13623),
	(26637, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect. Those orcs won\'t know what hit \'em - literally. I\'ll need a few minutes to get these in working order and then I\'ll put them in the Bravo Company field kit.', 13623),
	(26638, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great work, $N. We need to move quickly before they send for reinforcements.', 13623),
	(26639, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brubaker is dead. It looks like the orcs are attempting to send a message with this grisly display. Upon closer examination you notice something in Brubaker\'s pouch.', 13623),
	(26640, 5, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Keeshan reads the report.>$B$BDAMN IT! This just got complicated. We\'ve got prisoners of war to rescue before we can blow up the valley. Not to mention the orcs have black dragons on their side.$B$BAre you ready, $N?', 13623),
	(26641, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll see these are burnt to ash right away, and scattered to the winds for good measure.', 0),
	(26642, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A fresh recruit from Orgrimmar is it?$B$B<Kargal sizes you up.>$B$BI\'ll take what I can get. Keeping the roads open has been a nightmare.', 14333),
	(26643, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A grim task for sure, $N, but it\'ll keep the spiders left alive from recovering. I thank you.', 0),
	(26646, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The radio on the Bravo Company field kit crackles.>$B$BLooks like the P.O.W.s are free. Time to initiate Operation: End All.', 13623),
	(26651, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And now, we blow the whole damned thing up.', 13623),
	(26656, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. Of my main strengths, speed is not one.', 15354),
	(26657, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not just fast it seems. You have some bite in you.$B$BWell done, $c.', 15354),
	(26658, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Glorious.$B$BNow we will deal a blow to the stone dragons that they will remember for the next hundred years.', 15354),
	(26659, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Impressive, fleshling. You are far more capable than I initially assumed.$B$BI will extend that sentiment to the Stonemother as well.', 15354),
	(26668, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you see those orcs explode? THAT\'S HOW WE DO IT IN BRAVO COMPANY! Now to clean up the rest of these jackasses.', 13623),
	(26692, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re closing in on the Blackrock high command. There\'s nowhere left for those dogs to run.', 13623),
	(26693, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Keeshan comes in over the Bravo Company field kit.>$B$BNow that the easy part is over, it\'s time for phase two.', 13623),
	(26694, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He teleported away? Mentioned Darkblaze? What the hell is going on here.$B$BLooks like it\'s time to strap in and finish this nonsense.', 13623),
	(26706, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did it, $N.  We\'ve started the evacuation.  If we leave soon we\'ll leave the Forsaken fleet in the dust.', 15595),
	(26708, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The only thing left to deal with now are the orcs holding out at Stonewatch Keep.', 13623),
	(26709, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You returned. This is good. The Stone Lords have been asking after you.', 14333),
	(26710, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well. Now that these rocklings are free to learn our ways, they will grow tall and strong.$B$BOne day, we will extinguish the gyreworm infestation from our realm, and these rocklings shall no longer be plagued in their youth.', 15595),
	(26711, 25, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, it\'s you, ma\'am! Sorry, I didn\'t recognize you at first with all of these commoners milling about.$B$BYou people cool your heels! $N is here!$B$BHere are your macaroons, $g sir : ma\'am;. Come back anytime if you need more.', 15595),
	(26712, 25, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, it\'s you, sir! Sorry, I didn\'t recognize you at first with all of these commoners milling about.$B$BYou people cool your heels! $N is here!$B$BHere are your macaroons, $g sir : ma\'am;. Come back anytime if you need more.', 15595),
	(26713, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Bravo Company field kit beeps loudly.>$B$BCome in, $N. Are you there? If you can hear me: Blackrock has the upper hand. I repeat. Blackrock has the upper hand. GET BRAVO COMPANY OUT OF TH...$B$B<Troteman cuts out.>', 13623),
	(26714, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<A single tear rolls down Troteman\'s left cheek.>$B$BThey died in defense of the Alliance. In defense of our kingdom! Heroes, all of them, and they will be laid to rest as such.', 13623),
	(26726, 1, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They will never be forgotten, $N. What you and the rest of Bravo Company sacrificed in order to save Redridge will be a tale told for ages to come.$B$BWhile I can in no way make up for the loss of your friends, I feel that you must be rewarded for such a heroic deed. These are Keeshan\'s possessions - the only things we found when we dredged the lake for his body. Troteman has informed me that Keeshan would have wanted you to take something as the lone surviving member of Bravo Company. Remember them, $N!', 13623),
	(26750, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you\'ve come.$B$BFleshlings just like you killed my daughter... my only daughter. With no provocation.$B$BNot sated at stripping me of my family, more of you flocked to Deathwing to serve him in ravaging my home.$B$BYou\'re quite arrogant to come before me asking for MY help. I\'m tempted to crush you where you stand.', 14333),
	(26752, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya\'ve done well, $Gbrotha:sista;. Da Stonemother be listenin\' and da World Pillar is not far from our reach.', 14333),
	(26755, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a great start, $N, but we\'re going to need you to fly over into the town and stir up some trouble.', 14333),
	(26761, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I heard about the Defias making a return. Terrible news. I wish I had better news, but it would appear that Lakeshire is under attack! We are losing citizens left and right. Our own guards are spread far too thin to handle the situation. We need a hero to step up!', 13623),
	(26762, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was a nice bit of work, $N.$B$BWith our constructs back up and running behind their main lines, it\'s only a matter of time now before we make the big push through and rescue the Stonefather.', 14333),
	(26766, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should be enough to lure the beast, $N.', 15595),
	(26768, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s see if the snare can ground something larger than a drake.', 15595),
	(26770, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A few less stone troggs is always a good thing. Glad to see that you\'re a decent $c after all.$B$BWe\'ll soon know the exact location where they\'re keeping my father captive. Hope you survive until then.', 14333),
	(26771, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N.  Here\'s to hoping the trap performs as well when we try it on Abyssion.', 15595),
	(26784, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are perfect! The restless waters of that troubled river will now do much more than move silt or stone... They\'ll move you across continents.$B$BFinish up the rest of your business here in Dragonmaw and then we should be able to proceed.', 15595),
	(26786, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your Warchief is decisive, $N. He makes things happen. I like him.$B$BLet\'s talk about this portal that he wants!', 15595),
	(26788, 21, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ornak allows the muck to drip from his fingertips.>$B$BNow that\'s the stuff! I\'ll start mixing and diluting this with gravel and water. Just a few handfuls of this can enhance enough cement for an entire stone tower.$B$BWe\'ve got big plans for this port, $N. You\'ll see!', 15595),
	(26791, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They won\'t have any more of those fungal giants to throw against us!', 14333),
	(26792, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N. We\'ve never had such a problem in Deepholm before the destruction of the World Pillar.$B$BYour Earthen Ring must repair the damage before it\'s too late.', 14333),
	(26798, 6, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$C, you\'ve returned from Dragonmaw. The portal is functioning then? Good.$B$BBefore you return to your work there, we\'ve got some dirty business to clean up right here in Orgrimmar...', 15595),
	(26799, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not even the power of the val\'kyr was enough to save these creatures.  They were doomed from the beginning.$b$bI have obtained some equipment for you, $N.  It\'s not much, but it will help.  Please, take your pick.', 15595),
	(26800, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great work $N.  I knew you weren\'t useless.$b$bHere, take one of these.  We deathguards have piles of these things just sitting around.', 15595),
	(26801, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re growing in strength, $n.  I\'ve seen your type before.  You will be moving out of Deathknell and on to greater things before long.  Just make sure you don\'t lose sight of where you started.$b$bYou have much to accomplish, $c.', 15595),
	(26802, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. This armor should help you out.$b$bHopefully, it should do you more good than the last one to wear it...', 15595),
	(26826, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So once again, it falls upon tiny Dask to get the Explorers\' League work done!  Alright... let\'s see what you\'ve got in there.', 15595),
	(26827, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done what I thought not possible. Quite impressive, $c.', 14333),
	(26828, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And so you arrive, fleshling.  As promised.', 14333),
	(26829, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Their blood upon the earth is a sweet thing. I shall cherish every moment, slowly extinguishing the stragglers from my realm.', 14333),
	(26830, 274, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sauranok, Sauranok. His own visions worked against him. Twilight\'s Hammer probably corrupted him from afar. Bah! Weak! We\'ll speak his name no more.$B$BI told him you were investigating the airship docks, $N. To flush him out. Yes, I used you as bait. You served your Horde well, and deserve a reward for outing this viper from our midst.', 15595),
	(26831, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good that you were here. I find my size to be inhibiting when it comes to dragon riding, strangely.', 14333),
	(26832, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You let Lorthuna escape? I warned you of this.$B$BStill, their forces are shattered and their resources cut off. There is little they can do to me or my allies.', 14333),
	(26833, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gorsik has arrived. All of the pieces of the World Pillar are here, thanks to you.$B$BWhat you have done for us is immeasurable.  These final moments shall be the most crucial.  I hesitate to ask more of you, but I\'d like you to stay with us and see this through.$B$BThe Twilight\'s Hammer was devastated by your attacks, but not destroyed.  It\'s no stretch to assume they will try to stop us from completing our ritual.\n', 14333),
	(26834, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you again, $N. Now we\'ll get somewhere.', 14333),
	(26835, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N, we have good news and a slight problem....', 15354),
	(26836, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N! You did it! How will we ever repay you?', 15354),
	(26840, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N! I trust Orgrimmar fares well?$B$BAs you can see, construction of Dragonmaw Port continues at a breakneck pace. If my people questioned the Horde\'s power before... the sight of this imposing edifice and the speed in which it was constructed leaves no doubt.$B$BA new day dawns for the Dragonmaw.', 15595),
	(26842, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nicely done, $glad:lass;. I could use a $c like you around here.', 15354),
	(26843, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So I was right! Now the question is what the little freaks were plotting...', 15354),
	(26844, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, good. Now we can see what\'s going on down in that mine.', 15354),
	(26845, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a gnoll head. Are you trying to pull some funny business, $N?$B$BIf you\'re not, I\'ve not the faintest idea what\'s going on here.', 15354),
	(26846, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m sure that only worked because the troggs aren\'t bright to begin with. But then again, us dwarves were once creatures of the earth as well.$B$BBeing bossed around by a kobold doesn\'t sound quite dignified, and I\'m glad we didn\'t get to find out if they could pull that off.', 15354),
	(26856, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it, $N! You\'ve upturned the Searing Blade\'s invasion before it could even start! Take this, as a token of my thanks.', 14333),
	(26857, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That ought to get the dragon\'s attention, $N.', 15595),
	(26858, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My children will sing songs of your glories, $N!', 14333),
	(26860, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Much obliged! The rump\'s part of my own secret twist on the recipe... but here\'s instructions on how to make it with any kind of bear meat.$B$BAnd here\'s a fresh batch of me own. Mind you eat them fresh!', 15354),
	(26861, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent.  When we make our move against Abyssion, we should be able to do so without reinforcements coming to his aid.', 15595),
	(26863, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you see a lot of kobolds in there? The thought of their grimy hands clawing around our mine makes my stomach rumble!', 15354),
	(26864, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gnolls and kobolds, and troggs? Oh my.$B$BI\'d laugh if I didn\'t have another twist in the story for you.', 15354),
	(26868, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Worked like a charm, didn\'t it? Maybe Kadrell will get off my darn back now what with savin\' the whole town and all!$B$BI suppose you\'ve done earned yourself some proper goods.', 15354),
	(26869, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<This is it. This is the stone Diamant sent you for.>', 15354),
	(26870, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can already feel the balance returning! Quick, talk to Muyoh to help him awaken Naralex!', 15595),
	(26871, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, fleshling!$B$BThe gyreworms are among our most dangerous enemies.$B$BThe other Stone Lords shall have trouble not turning their head to this accomplishment.', 15354),
	(26872, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your efforts shall not go unnoticed, $n.$b$bThank you for your dedication.', 15595),
	(26873, 21, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, $n. Hopefully we can use these to prevent further nightmares.', 15595),
	(26875, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Twilight forces continue to stream in, but it looks like the Earthen Ring defenders can handle them.', 14333),
	(26876, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your efforts in repairing the World Pillar are invaluable, $N.  Once the Temple of Earth\'s structure is stable again, the rift between the worlds will begin to stabilize.', 15595),
	(26878, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, $c? What brings you to this place?', 14333),
	(26881, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ashelan was good to send you. There is indeed a wicked plot underway in this corrupted place.', 15354),
	(26882, 1, 1, 5, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kelris has eluded us for quite some time.$b$bIt seems as though whenever evil made its presence known in these parts, Kelris had played a role. For some time we considered him either dead or missing.$b$bBut this makes perfect sense. By ending his reign you have spared the lives of many innocent people.$b$bTo sacrifice someone to a servant of an Old God for one\'s personal gain is beyond reproachful!$b$bYou have done a great deed, $n. I thank you on behalf of Ashenvale.$b$bIf only Thaelrid had survived....', 15354),
	(26883, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are no doubt of brave and noble blood, $n. We and all of the people of Ashenvale commend you for your efforts against evil.', 15354),
	(26884, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have undoubtedly faced great peril to obtain these.$b$bYour actions have been selfless. It is for the good of all Azeroth that you help me with my research. I thank you, $n, for all that you have done.$b$bNow if you\'ll excuse me I have much work to do.', 15354),
	(26885, 5, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found the manuscript! What a joyous day this is! I will study it exhaustively and learn all there is to know.$B$BI\'ll make full sentinel yet!$B$BYour service to us is more than you know, $N. I hope that this gift shows you my gratitude.', 15354),
	(26886, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! I hope you didn\'t get hit with too many cannonballs.', 15595),
	(26887, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'More gold! We\'ll be sure to give some of this to Mister Noggenfogger to smoothly ensure our continued relations.$B$BAnd only a little bit of it will go back to Gnomeregan for experimental weapons development!', 15595),
	(26888, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The beast is slain. I can feel his dark presence fading away forever.', 15595),
	(26889, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You know, I\'m usually not impressed when I see a $r, but I\'ve heard about what you\'ve been doin\' for the Steamwheedle. You\'re alright, kid.', 15595),
	(26891, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is exactly what I need!  A fathom core is an incredible well of information that we will be able to draw much good from.  Whatever the Twilight\'s Hammer is up to in there - and believe me when I say it is no good - my comrades and I will now uncover.$B$BYou\'ve done well here today; the Earthen Ring looks upon you warmly for assisting us.  You\'ve also helped the Horde as a whole, and for that you should be proud.', 15595),
	(26892, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can hear their cries from here! Maybe this will show them how foolish it is to wish for the return of an Old God.', 15595),
	(26897, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank Elune you\'re here! We could use all the help we can get. ', 0),
	(26899, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Flaming Eradicator appears to concentrate.>$B$BI spare your life for your help, $r. Leave now...before I change my...mind.', 15595),
	(26910, 11, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you received my note? Excellent. You\'ve proven yourself quite capable in dealing with those orcs. As you continue to grow in power, I will teach you some new techniques.', 15595),
	(26913, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re a quick learner, $N. Return to me as you grow stronger and I\'ll show you other combat techniques.', 14333),
	(26914, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see you have already mastered Immolation! I look forward to instructing you in the future. Do not forget to return for further lessons as you grow in power.', 15050),
	(26916, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you mastered the use of Arcane Missiles already? You are a quick study in the arcane arts and you have a promising future ahead. Don\'t forget to return to me for training as you grow in power.', 15595),
	(26917, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew you would master Steady Shot quickly. I\'m looking forward to showing you other techniques as you get more experienced in the ways of the hunter.', 15595),
	(26927, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Murlocs? Sure, I\'ve hunted murlocs.$B$BAnd every single stinkin\' one of them deserved what they got! You hear me?', 15354),
	(26928, 92, 397, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Phew! Ain\'t that a stench.$B$BNow you prepare yourself, because I\'m about to wow you with what\'s left of my mental faculties.', 15354),
	(26929, 7, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mighty kind of you to help out an ol\' fool like me. Here\'s your reward as promised an\' all.', 15354),
	(26932, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should help prevent disease and illness from spreading into our remaining water. Many thanks, $n.', 15354),
	(26947, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a quick study in our ways. I look forward to continuing your training in the future. Return to me when the time is right.', 14333),
	(26948, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have mastered the basics of the healing ways quickly, $N. I have no doubt that your healing skills will often come in handy. Return to me when you need further training.', 15595),
	(26960, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, Anduin will learn a lot by shadowing you.$B$BRemember, stay within the city\'s borders. Keep him out of trouble. And above all else, guard him with your life.$B$B<King Wrynn turns his attention to his son.>$B$BAnduin, no adventures! Stay close to $N and return to the keep should you see any trouble.', 13623),
	(26961, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You got them!  Nicely done, $N!$B$BAnd you don\'t look too worse for wear, even with those berserk troggs about.  I\'m going to keep my eye on you...you show some promise.', 15354),
	(26964, 5, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Most excellent! A new recruit has arrived. There is much to do... much to do I say.', 15595),
	(26965, 274, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well that was unexpected. I am not one to doubt our Warchief, but...$B$BNevermind! We have work to do. I\'m sure the Dark Lady and the Warchief will get this all worked out.', 15595),
	(26966, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve proven yourself a quick learner, $N. I look forward to training you again when the time is right.', 15595),
	(26969, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is a pleasure to teach such a capable student. As long as you continue the traditons faithfully, the shamanic arts will never be lost to our people again. Return to me when you need further training.', 13596),
	(26971, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Maruut said when all dis started dat he would gladly give his life ta see our task done. He would be proud of dis success... of dis death.$B$BDa rift be closed on dis side. Deepholm should calm down a bit. It\'ll be takin\' time for Thrall to mend da wound in Azeroth, and we\'ll be needin\' to remain until he finishes.$B$BThank you for all ya\'ve done. I don\'t tink we could have been accomplishin\' dis so soon without you.', 14333),
	(26973, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work! I just know the Light shines favorably upon us for our work. Our cause is righteous!', 0),
	(26975, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Graves bows respectfully to the Prince.>$B$BPlease understand your highness, the men are working double-shifts. The scale of your father\'s operation is enormous.$B$BBut we will endeavor to wrap things up. I give you my word.', 13623),
	(26976, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes! The Scarlet Monastery is ours! You\'re a real friend. Take this as a reward, and feel free to visit again once I\'ve taken the Undercity too.$B$BIt\'ll be a Scarlet Paradise!', 15595),
	(26977, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmmm, yes? My investigation of the Twilight\'s Hammer. Of course.$B$BYour assistance will be valuable. ', 13623),
	(26989, 1, 5, 21, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$Nnub has returned! And in one piece!$B$BDefender of Silverpine! Redeemer of the Horde! $Nnub, your bravery must be rewarded!', 15595),
	(26992, 5, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Agony abounds, friend! The land itself threatens to devour us, and yet we persist. I wonder why that is? With this doomweed and the guts and gore that T\'Veen needs, we might have something suitable to send to the Forsaken front.', 15595),
	(26993, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. How about I give you a nice reward for your work, and you don\'t tell a soul that you saw me here. Deal?', 0),
	(26994, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good. Yes, very good indeed.$B$BYour reward, as promised. No questions.', 15595),
	(26995, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! With these guts and the ferocious doomweed we\'ll be able to test out our new strain of blight. Now to select a suitable target...', 15595),
	(26996, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Dominic hands you your reward. No words are spoken.>', 15595),
	(26997, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This doesn\'t make any sense, $N.$B$BWhy was Samuelson sending us out here on a wild goose chase?$B$BSomething doesn\'t feel right. We should poke around on our own...', 13623),
	(26998, 5, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Potent enough to exterminate a thousand murlocs! I think I\'ll put that on the label. You\'ve done well, $N, and great work around here gets rewarded.', 15595),
	(27003, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Smells like someone else was in this cell recently.$b$bGross!', 15595),
	(27004, 5, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<Mowi takes a look at the plans that you hand to her.>$B$BBut... but, this is just gibberish!$B$BWhat does this even say? What language is that?', 13623),
	(27005, 5, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<The examiner takes a look at the plans that you hand to him.>$B$BThis is just gibberish!$B$BWhat does this even say? What language is that?', 15595),
	(27006, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A waygate?! The culties dug up a Titan waygate?', 13623),
	(27007, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is the place.  Our scouts confirmed the presence of high-ranking Twilight officers nearby as well as potential trogg hunting parties.$B$BBe on the lookout, $N.', 15595),
	(27008, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A waygate?! They unearthed a Titan waygate.$B$BThis is very interesting and potentially very bad.', 15595),
	(27009, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A job well done, $N. The Quilboar here can no longer be saved, but at least they are no longer organized for attack, or slaves under Amnennar\'s tyrannic rule.$B$BLeave quickly, please. Razorfen Downs is without hope. It must be purged.', 15595),
	(27010, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have the information we need.  Let\'s not tip our hand by engaging the enemy too soon.', 15595),
	(27015, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have much to cover. In time, the ways of the sunwalkers will be as plain and natural to you as the shaman\'s conversations with the elements.', 15595),
	(27016, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve killed ten already? H...hah! While you were out, I\'ve broken my previous record! To ten... hundred! Yes, ten hundred boars!$B$BA bet is a bet, I suppose... here\'s your consolation prize, $n!', 15354),
	(27019, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fantastic, I thought you looked to be the heroic type!  We\'ve got our work cut out for us $N, I\'m not going to lie to you.  If we stay focused on the task at hand, we should be able to come out on top.', 15595),
	(27020, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, $N. Return to me when you are in need of further training.', 15595),
	(27022, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Belnistrasz\'s sudden departure has left behind a burning brazier.  As you stare in to the flame, the image of a great-winged red dragon fills your mind.  A more graveled version of Belnistrasz\'s voice speaks directly to you.$B$B"Indeed mortals, you are the heroes I had hoped you would be.  Thanks to you the butchery these beasts were perpetrating is a thing of the past.  My faith in your kind has been once more renewed.  Take this as a reward befitting of a hero."', 15595),
	(27023, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have made me proud, $N. You will make a fine Sunwalker. Return when you desire further training.', 15595),
	(27024, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! Without their leaders, the Scourge will pose no significant threat.', 15595),
	(27025, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve been informed there\'s a bear warning active for the woodlands as well! They love those stabthistle seeds.$B$BIt\'s a good thing you gathered those so they don\'t attract more bears!', 15354),
	(27029, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have faith that this substance will prevent many future headaches. Thank you, $C.', 15595),
	(27030, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, you see? Goods of the finest quality. Good work gettin\' these.', 15354),
	(27031, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Beautiful. you\'ve got an eye for quality!$B$BGreat minds think alike! It\'s clear you\'ve got an enthusiasm for flight and fowl, so maybe you can help me further...', 15354),
	(27038, 1, 5, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Flintlocke greedily digs through the machine parts, tossing choice picks over his shoulder.>$B$BOh aye, \'ere\'s the stuff.$B$B<He sticks his head all the way into one of the crates.>$B$BBut where\'s me powder? Everything\'s here but for the powder. I need explosives, $gman:woman;!$B$BYou tell the King, no powder, no power. I need me some kersplosions or I ain\'t leavin\' port.', 13623),
	(27039, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Belmont gets a little nervous and sends some newbie to look for me? Listen, I\'ve been staking out the old Ivar cottage from inside this outhouse for three days. Your presence threatens the whole damn operation!$B$BThere\'s no time to explain. We have to act now or this mission will be compromised.', 15595),
	(27040, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah ha! So, that\'s it! They\'re planning on invading Uldum.$B$BWhat\'s worse is that the pyramid inside the Maker\'s Terrace at Uldum can be reconfigured to become a weapon. A weapon that is capable of destroying all life on Azeroth!', 13623),
	(27041, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah ha! So, that\'s it! They\'re planning on invading Uldum.$B$BWhat\'s worse is that the pyramid inside the Maker\'s Rise at Uldum can be reconfigured to become a weapon. A weapon that is capable of destroying all life on Azeroth!', 15595),
	(27042, 4, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s the ol\' spirit! One less nasty in this world that the little ones will have ta worry about when they go ta sleep at night.$B$BNot ta mention that we won\'t have ta be worrying about him none no more neither!$B$BNow let\'s see here. I think we have somethin\' in our crates that\'ll make a fittin\' reward fer ya.', 13623),
	(27043, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'An excellent display of $c prowess.$B$B<The Reliquary eyes you up and down.>$B$BI believe that a reward is in order. Something appropriate for a $g powerful man : lovely lady; such as yourself.', 14333),
	(27044, 16, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<On seeing the Prince Regent, Farmer Wollerton collapses awkwardly down on one knee.>$B$BY- Y- Your highness!', 13623),
	(27045, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alas, poor Yorick! I knew her, $N. An assassin of infinite courage...$B$BNow, tell me what\'s going on? What did you and Yorick discover?', 15595),
	(27046, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You wage a war that we cannot. Thank you for your help.', 13623),
	(27047, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $r. These will do well.', 13623),
	(27048, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well played!$B$BI\'ve got this pretty sweet deal going. A bunch of shmucks go up there to Therazane\'s Throne and give all kinds of gold to D\'lom for who-knows-what kinda crap. He forks all that cash over to me for these crystals. I go home freakin\' rich for a couple chunks of rock.$B$BDon\'t tell no one though. I don\'t want no competition springin\' up.$B$BThink you can come back later to help me get another load of crystals out?', 13623),
	(27049, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Once the growth starts, it is near impossible to stomp back into submission. Through persistence our realm will one day be cleansed.', 13623),
	(27050, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are proficient at stepping on things. You would make an excellent giant.', 13623),
	(27051, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $r. We will weed the rest out of their possession in time.', 13623),
	(27056, 1, 1, 274, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Crowley... A gnat. An insect, waiting to be crushed beneath my boot heel.$B$BSo he thinks to rouse the feral worgen of Silverpine? We shall show him and his allies the might of the Forsaken!$B$BBut first we must clean up the mess made by the Warchief\'s fleet. Without their aid we may lose this war.', 15595),
	(27058, 4, 17, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it! You found out what the Twilight\'s Hammer were up to and you stopped them dead in their tracks!$B$B<Mowi gets up on her tippy toes and gives you a kiss on the cheek.>$B$BNow I\'m certain that I have something around here for you.$B$B<She begins rummaging around for your reward.>', 13623),
	(27059, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it! Excellent work, $g my boy : young lady;. You found out what the Twilight\'s Hammer were up to and you stopped them dead in their tracks!$B$B<Examiner Rowe pats you on the back with his bony hand.>$B$BNow I\'m certain that I have something around here for you.$B$B<He begins rummaging around for your reward.>', 15595),
	(27060, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was a close one! I can\'t believe you stood your ground against so many at once.$B$BIt looks like this site was used for some kind of twisted Twilight\'s Hammer initiation ritual. They\'re definitely active in Stormwind. What\'s this?$B$B<Anduin finds a badge resting on the shrine.>$B$BThis badge shows a crossed axe and hammer. It looks old. If we keep poking around, we might figure out what it means...', 13623),
	(27061, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So we\'re going to have to take on Abyssion to get the fragment?  This operation just got a whole lot more difficult all of a sudden.', 15595),
	(27064, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is REALLY suspicious, $N! Samuelson doesn\'t have a shred of info here about the Twilight Hammer - it\'s almost like he\'s not investigating them. Yet he\'s got a complete catalog of the missing explosives.$B$B<Anduin pulls a medallion from the files.>$B$BAnd I found this funny badge with a symbol on it: A crossed axe and hammer.$B$BIt all means something, but what?', 13623),
	(27065, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This fiasco may go down as one of the biggest embarrassments in the history of naval warfare. How did this happen? Drunk happened. That\'s how.', 15595),
	(27068, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He\'s gone? Did he have the sword?$B$BNah...don\'t tell me. Don\'t matter no more. Mazoga don\'t care.$B$BI\'m off now, mon. De consequences of my actions await me. Take whatever I was holdin\'... I don\'t need it where I\'m goin\'...', 15595),
	(27069, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Within these crates are held STEEL THUNDER! With our weaponry returned we might have a chance to redeem ourselves.', 15595),
	(27070, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! This Tiara will grant me complete control of the water around here, and the Electrified Scale will serve to power all the machines I need to use it all to my advantage!$B$BYou\'re going to make me a very rich and powerful goblin! You can have this, it\'s nothing compared to what I\'ll have soon.', 15595),
	(27071, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You killed dem? All of dem? And you return alive?$B$BTake what you want off my body, den. It\'s mostly curse-free, Mazoga promises.', 15595),
	(27072, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You slap Bauden around until he wakes up.>$B$B$C? What are you doing here?$B$BI\'m SI:7 Agent Jack Bauden. This is the longest day of my life.', 13623),
	(27073, 25, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks as if you really gave those worgen a beating and, in the process, lifted the "shame haze" they cast over us. Perhaps the sea dogs will quit drinkin\' now.$B$BWho am I kidding?$B$BHah!', 15595),
	(27076, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow! I knew I could count on you! Here\'s something for your troubles.', 15595),
	(27082, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! Now to prepare the "meal."', 15595),
	(27088, 11, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Apothecary Wormcrud laughs maniacally.>$B$BWas there ever any doubt? An ettin is no match for science!', 15595),
	(27092, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<3 ... 2 ... 1 ...>$B$B<You wet your fingers and snuff out the fuse. The cathedral is saved!>$B$BUnderneath the powder kegs you find a heap of notes and papers. Apparently the cultists were trying to destroy the evidence behind them.>', 13623),
	(27093, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lok\'tar, $N! Once the ale wears off my orcs will be ready!', 15595),
	(27094, 5, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You rescued our orcs and killed the Skitterweb matriarch? We owe you a great debt of gratitude. You\'ve saved us all from certain execution, $N. I\'m sure we can rouse these drunken idiots now.', 15595),
	(27095, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The root of this evil must be found and destroyed! The Skitterweb matriarch must be nearby. No doubt hiding in the nearby cave!', 15595),
	(27096, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sylvanas raises an eyebrow.>$B$BSo the orcs are in order?$B$B<Sylvanas reads the commendation letter.>$B$BRecovered their supplies? Killed a dozen worgen? Toppled an ettin? Freed their soldiers and destroyed the Skitterweb matriarch?$B$BI say this rarely, $N, but I am impressed. Perhaps your ability matches your aspirations. We shall see, for now you will be tested!', 15595),
	(27097, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see everything, $N. Through Agatha all is known to me.', 15595),
	(27098, 25, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you now understand the importance of our mission here? Crowley and his Alliance dogs must be stopped!', 15595),
	(27099, 1, 1, 25, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It would seem that Crowley is more formidable than I anticipated. Still, he is a man - flesh and bone - full of secrets. Secrets that I know all about...$B$BYou have served me well, $N. I could use someone of your ability at the Sepulcher. I have a plan to deal with Crowley and his insurgents once and for all. Will you help?', 15595),
	(27100, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The notes deal with High Cultist Maziel\'s research on the elemental properties of quicksilver.$B$BHis obsession with the subject borders on the insane.', 15595),
	(27101, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Maziel\'s journal appears to be undamaged by the mercury. ', 15595),
	(27102, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve disposed of an enemy before he could grow more powerful.  By eliminating Maziel you\'ve also ensured that his powers will not be used against the Earthen Ring.', 15595),
	(27106, 274, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Samuelson - corrupted by the Twilight\'s Hammer? This must have been going on for years. Right here in my very keep!$B$BI am grateful that you and my son were able to get to the bottom of this before my city was brought to harm. I\'ve underestimated how much Anduin has grown - his command of the holy light just saved my life, if not the entire kingdom.$B$BAs for you - words alone can\'t do justice to your heroism this day. Thank you, $c.', 13623),
	(27108, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This web have lots of magic! Master will be very happy now!$B$BAnd you make Dagg\'thol happy, $r. Take this so you believe how happy you make Dagg\'thol!', 15595),
	(27109, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your work here was noble. Fret not, for Tendris\' soul was crying to be put to rest. He is thankful.', 15595),
	(27110, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We thank you, hero.', 15595),
	(27111, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You open the chest to find...', 15595),
	(27112, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your dedication will make this all that much easier.', 15595),
	(27113, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our meeting is no coincidence, $N.', 15595),
	(27123, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve arrived just in time, $N.  All our resources are tied up keeping the rift stable.$B$BWe need someone like you to help us recover the fragments of the World Pillar.', 15595),
	(27126, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t thank you enough, $c. Now, let\'s see if we can get this catapult moving again.', 14333),
	(27135, 430, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Uh oh. Sounds like he wasn\'t very happy about the situation. How was I to know? I\'m just an initiate after all.$B$BAnyway, I\'ll worry about Magmatooth later.', 15595),
	(27136, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N.  We need all the power we can muster to keep Deepholm stable.', 15595),
	(27139, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There you are, my $g boy : girl;. I have something very important for you to do!', 15595),
	(27140, 5, 6, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it!  They are defeated!  And the Gambit... did it work?$B$BVery interesting. You\'ve done well, $N.', 15595),
	(27141, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Shake it off, kid.$b$bHappens to me all the time...', 15595),
	(27142, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ten thousand souls cry out in unison, $N! You have struck a mortal blow to the Scourge and their masters.', 15595),
	(27143, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $r. Alexi deserves nothing for his foolishness.', 15595),
	(27145, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N!  It\'ll be a long time before they can grow another clutch of dragons.$B$B...At least, I hope it will!', 15595),
	(27146, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can feel my spirit healing, $N. You have done my husband and I a great service.', 15595),
	(27147, 1, 1, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the death of Kirtonos, a chapter in the horrible tale of Scholomance comes to a close. You have my deepest, everlasting gratitude for your bravery.', 15595),
	(27148, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Without a headmaster, the school will descend into chaos. It will not put forth any more of its vile \'students\' into the field. Thank you.', 15595),
	(27158, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s about time you arrived, $c.', 13623),
	(27166, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will have my fletchers get to work on these.$b$bI\'m glad to see you being so useful right away, $N.  Perhaps later I will have some more exciting tasks for you.', 13623),
	(27176, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Doctor Jones puts on his spectacles.>$b$bLet\'s have a look at this. Shall we?', 15595),
	(27177, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at all this! You were able to recover more than I thought. We can outfit a whole squad of marines with this stuff.$B$BWe have the gear. If we only had some way to bolster our numbers here in the Highlands...', 13623),
	(27178, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'ll send \'em packing, $N! Cho\'gall won\'t be able to count on the naga to back him up in this fight. From here on out, it\'s just us versus the Twilight\'s Hammer.$B$B<Simon pauses, his jaw tightening.>$B$B...And the Horde.', 13623),
	(27179, 396, 5, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'These tablets are covered with titan writings. There\'s never-before seen information here, $n!$b$bMissing pieces to an ancient puzzle...$b$bGood work!', 15595),
	(27180, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will see to it that these insignias are returned to the Undercity at once. The registrar will place their names in our records so that their sacrifice may never be forgotten.', 15595),
	(27181, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Banshee Queen\'s voice invades your thoughts.>$B$BYou have avenged the fallen, $N, but there is more to be done.', 15595),
	(27187, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The world is a better place because of your deeds here today.', 15595),
	(27192, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Truly, you have uncovered the snuff of legends. It is nearly impossible to place a value on this historical tobacco.$b$bHere, have a few coins.', 15595),
	(27193, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Banshee Queen\'s words float in your head.>$B$BThis book documents a recent meeting with Ivar Bloodfang. The location mentioned is the Deep Elem Mine. I know of this place. It has only one entrance.$B$BWe shall corner and crush them!', 15595),
	(27194, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I s\'pose we\'re to corner them first then crush, eh?', 15595),
	(27195, 5, 15, 5, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'WHAT!?$B$B<Sylvanas shrieks.>$B$BCROWLEY!!!!!$B$BBastards. Those were some of our strongest soldiers. I have underestimated Crowley and Bloodfang for the last time. Clearly they are an enemy the likes of which we have never seen - willing to sacrifice their own to set a trap like this... unheard of in Alliance warfare.', 15595),
	(27196, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Would you get a load of this place!', 15595),
	(27200, 274, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'She had me under her spell, $N. I wouldn\'t have made it out of there alive if it weren\'t for you. Thank you!$B$BMaybe the rest of the Alliance fleet can finally anchor here in peace...', 13623),
	(27203, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Thrall\'s muscles strain as primal energy flows through him.  His eyes shift your way, acknowledging your arrival.>$B$BIt is good to see you, $N.', 15595),
	(27210, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N. I think we managed to catch them off guard. Their agents probably thought themselves safe within the city walls.$B$BGiven time, the agitators will return and spread their lies again. We\'ll use the time you\'ve bought to shut out the deserters further.', 13623),
	(27211, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The SI:7 agent nods in approval.>$B$BExcellent. All that remains is to discredit the deserters so that they\'ll never gain a foothold in Theramore again, and I have just the plan to do it.', 13623),
	(27226, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A-HA! I knew it! Lesson learned, I suppose. We will not fail again. I will be sure to have some ale on hand at the front lines.', 15595),
	(27227, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Stratholme will become a paragon of all that is good in this world. You have my thanks for your part in this mission.', 13596),
	(27228, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I respect the power you demonstrated in killing Ramstein. With proper rage backing your actions, I think even the Scourge can know fear.', 13596),
	(27230, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great! Without a steady flow of their weapons, we\'ll win through attrition!', 13596),
	(27231, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Hatchet\'s communication device crackles.>$B$BHatchet here, are they all dead?', 15595),
	(27232, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Though you killed a large number of the newly turned worgen, many more are sure to appear. Still, their assault will have softened. Well done, $N!', 15595),
	(27290, 5, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well if it isn\'t $Nnub!$B$BI hope you\'re ready for battle, because that\'s all you\'ll find in this hellhole. We\'re at the heart of contested territory and these worgen mongrels won\'t give an inch!', 15595),
	(27299, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tank ya, $c. A bit of breathin\' room helps a lot.', 14333),
	(27300, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Revenge is bittersweet, but I\'m glad we be havin\' someone as powerful as you do see dis done.', 14333),
	(27301, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank the elements that you\'ve come. Did my brothers send you?', 14333),
	(27302, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that\'s what I\'m talkin\' about! Can you think of all the uses for this stuff? I definitely can\'t. But I can think of a lot, and I\'m liking the possibilities.', 14333),
	(27303, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. You are quite capable. I\'m extremely grateful that you\'ve chosen to aid us.', 14333),
	(27333, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If I could still breathe I\'d let out a sigh of relief.$B$BDon\'t get too comfortable, though, $N, your mission here has just begun.', 15595),
	(27338, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Keep your head down \'fore you lose it, $c!$B$BThis is MY beach.$B$BThe Horde WANTS my beach.$B$BThey will NOT have my beach.$B$BIs the beach situation clear?', 13623),
	(27341, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s the lay of the land, soldier. If you\'re having trouble fighting here on the coast, you might consider pitching in and helping us take and hold that hill.', 13623),
	(27342, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Belmont takes the wolfsbane from you.>$B$BGood. Now just do as Forward Commander Onslaught commands. Try your best to fit in with the rest of the soldiers. We don\'t want the Gilneas Liberation Front to get suspicious.$B$BOh, you didn\'t know they were watching us? Right now there are five different worgen spies looking down on our position. Just be calm and follow orders. I\'ll let you know when we are ready to proceed.', 15595),
	(27345, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With this device I will be able to communicate with you in the field. Now to check the rest of our frontline outposts.', 15595),
	(27349, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The F.C.D. crackles with static.>$B$BDreadwatch is lost? This is bad, $N. Real bad.$B$BIf Dreadwatch is compromised it means we\'ve lost Gilneas City.', 15595),
	(27350, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Th... Af... After we lost Gilneas City, the port fell.$B$BHU... HUM... HUMANS ARE HERE! Reinforcements from Stormwind! They slaughtered my men. Left me alive to witness their strength. To tell high command... To tell them that the 7th Legion are here...', 15595),
	(27352, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! I think the holy water will prove devastating in large volumes.', 13596),
	(27359, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh my... the banshees are very tortured souls indeed. Merely holding their essence is emotionally painful...$B$BEnough of that for now. I\'ll get to work on counteracting their magic, then we\'ll have a portal up and running in no time. Stratholme will be ours soon, I just know it.', 13596),
	(27360, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Though we were shamed in battle, the enemy was not victorious. I will not soon forget this, $N.$B$BIf I make it back to Silverpine I will likely retire from the service. War is not in my blood.', 15595),
	(27364, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The F.C.D. crackles with electricity.>$B$BAn Alliance armada is en route? How could this have happened?$B$B<Forward Commander Onslaught cuts out for a moment. You hear worgen howling in the background.>$B$BYou\'ve got to hurry, $N. We\'re being overrun up here at Forward Command.', 15595),
	(27366, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dead? By the dozen?$B$BIt\'s a start, $c. It\'s a start.', 13623),
	(27367, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$g Tarenar?: Fiona?;  Is that you?$b$bWhoever you are, would you mind helping me out of this thing?', 13623),
	(27368, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re back?!  Thank the Light!$b$bBefore you throw that acid on me, I need to ask: Are you the $g guy: girl; who was here before, or are you one of those eight-legged cowards?  I need to know whether or not I should smack you on my way out.', 13623),
	(27369, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll tear that pint-size paladin to shreds before he... wait a minute are those Banshee\'s Bells?  You brought these for me?$b$bOh, Gidwin asked you to get them for me!  That sweet little guy.  Alright.  He\'s off the hook for now.', 13623),
	(27370, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve found them, $r.  The Scourge.  How I\'ve longed for this day.', 13623),
	(27371, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Five should be good enough.$b$bYikes, look at the time!  I need to head back to camp.', 13623),
	(27372, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why, this is exactly what I needed!  Fine, I\'ll forgive Tarenar for running off.$b$b$N, you\'re welcome to join us anytime.', 13623),
	(27373, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hope the ride wasn\'t too bumpy for you.$b$bHave a look around the tower while the horses rest.  It\'s no Light\'s Hope Chapel, but I\'m sure you can find some way to keep yourself busy.', 13623),
	(27374, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, $Gbrotha:sista;. You\'ve chosen a harsh time to be joinin\' us, but that is to our fortune. We could use ya help.', 13623),
	(27375, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, $Gbrotha:sista;. You\'ve chosen a harsh time to be joinin\' us, but that is to our fortune. We could use ya help.', 14333),
	(27376, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The tentacles swept us off of our gryphons as well! They were far more nimble than we anticipated.$B$BNo matter. We were prepared for this possibility. I can summon the elemental from here if you can keep me safe.', 14333),
	(27377, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve brought you back from the brink of death, hero!$B$BDeathwing is upon us! We need your help.', 14333),
	(27378, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re awake! Thank the elements. I\'d almost lost all hope.', 14333),
	(27379, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'United with the Earthen Ring, we can survive the horrors of Iso\'rath. Now it is time to turn our vengeance upon him!', 14333),
	(27380, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You saved many of my closest allies today, $n. I can only imagine what horrors you witnessed within Iso\'rath, but you have the thanks of all of the Earthen Ring.', 14333),
	(27381, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Argus Highbeacon... that old guy on the top of the tower?  Great!$b$bA man his age must have been in the Argent Crusade for a long time.  Maybe he can put in the good word for us at Light\'s Hope.', 13623),
	(27382, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Of course a young $r like you would have no trouble taking care of a few wild animals.  With the roads clear, my journey to the next tower will be much easier.', 13623),
	(27383, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello.  I\'m Pamela, what\'s your name?', 13623),
	(27398, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your aid is most timely, $N.', 13623),
	(27401, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The F.C.D. crackles with electricity.>$B$BTORPEDOED! We had everything at the water line covered, but nothing below the line. They must have snuck in beneath our defenses and then blown our warships to smithereens.$B$BAnd now the rest of the Alliance fleet is nearly here...', 15595),
	(27405, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Forward Commander Onslaught fought until the bitter end, $N. It took a pack of bloodthirsty worgen to finally bring him down. We must not let his death, or the death of all of our soldiers in Gilneas, go in vain. Our mission MUST succeed.$B$BNow I will reveal to you why we are here.', 15595),
	(27406, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here we are, $N. He is a little rotted, but no worse for the wear. We must hurry before the Alliance finds us!', 15595),
	(27423, 274, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No time to bask in the battle glory, $N. We have a job to do. I have no doubt more of those beasts are on the way.', 15595),
	(27431, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Talk about bringing the house down...', 15595),
	(27432, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great, you got him!  And I hope you taught his gang a lesson too!', 13623),
	(27433, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh aye, tha\'s the stuff! A good engineer can make anything outta just about anything.$B$BThis here doo-jicker could recouple a busted cylinder casing... Oh! And who doesn\'t want a dongle? ...And you can fashion this jobby into a ... thing.$B$B<Flintlocke sticks one of the grease-smeared engine parts into his mouth.>$B$BYep, perfect.', 13623),
	(27438, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I had no doubt that you would succeed, $N. I hope you can understand why I kept the true purpose of your mission a secret. Should Crowley and Bloodfang have found out about our plan, they would have surely gotten to Godfrey first and disposed of the body.$B$BStand by, $N. The time of their rebirth is at hand.', 15595),
	(27442, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your aid is most timely, $N.', 15595),
	(27444, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You saw Nefarian when you fought Rend?$B$B<Acride sighs.>$B$BI wish I had accompanied you, then. I could have faced him unaware, outside his lair...but no matter. Nefarian will die by my claw.$B$BYou\'ve done well.', 15595),
	(27445, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! It is only a matter of time before the son of Deathwing feels my claws.', 15595),
	(27448, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve enjoyed having you ride with us, $N.  Hopefully, once Gidwin and Tarenar join the Argent Crusade, we can continue to travel together.', 13623),
	(27449, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, you are indeed strong... and I submit to you.$b$bI will join you and your friend, the worgen.  My strength is yours.', 13623),
	(27450, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm... they didn\'t survive the trip out of the water as well as I had hoped.$b$bOh well!  Seafood salad for Frederick tonight!', 13623),
	(27451, 274, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello!  It\'s me.  Hope you don\'t mind a little home-brewed magic to allow me to communicate with you in the field.  It\'ll save us both some time.$b$bWe\'re going to incorporate that living rot into a mixture that\'ll ruin their next batch of plague.  That\'ll show them!', 13623),
	(27452, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve got both pieces!  Good.  These will help when trying to sneak into their death camp.', 13623),
	(27453, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Uh oh... it looks like we may have gathered a little too much coagulated rot.  Oh well, we\'ll just have to improvise, then!$b$bWhat could possibly go wrong?', 13623),
	(27454, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It should take them weeks to get their operation running again.  Thank you, $N.', 13623),
	(27455, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t believe it.  We\'re literally FEET away from becoming sworn members of the Argent Crusade.$b$bWe\'d be in there already if it weren\'t for Tarenar\'s dallying.  If he doesn\'t quit chatting with the locals soon, I\'m going to head in there myself.', 13623),
	(27468, 274, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yep, one more tank limpin\' back home for repairs.$B$BAll these trees an\' stumps an\' mud an\' rock - you couldnae drive a golfball into this turf, much less a tank.$B$BWe\'re gonna need a new approach.', 13623),
	(27472, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Today marks a new beginning for the Forsaken and the end of the Alliance in Lordaeron!', 15595),
	(27485, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad Lira didn\'t scare you off. I won\'t say her concerns aren\'t warranted, but we have a common enemy. She is perhaps a bit overzealous.', 13623),
	(27486, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad Lira didn\'t scare you off. I won\'t say her concerns aren\'t warranted, but we have a common enemy. She is perhaps a bit overzealous.', 14333),
	(27490, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That must have been deadly.$B$BWhile I don\'t approve of their methods, no one can question the effectiveness of Master Mathias Shaw and his SI:7. Not to mention that you\'re here. Our victory is all but assured.', 13623),
	(27491, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That must have been exciting.$B$BDespite any losses that the Kor\'kron may have incurred along the way, no one will be able to doubt their effectiveness, nor that of Garona. And with you in the mix, it\'s only a matter of time before victory is ours.', 15595),
	(27492, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s the spirit, $g lad : lass;! Today\'s already shaping up to be a good one.', 13623),
	(27493, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And here I thought that today couldn\'t get any better.$B$BI enjoy being wrong, occasionally.', 15595),
	(27494, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Success!', 13623),
	(27495, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Success!', 15595),
	(27496, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks to you, our cannoneers hit their marks. Tell me about the situation within the Twilight Gate.', 13623),
	(27497, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I must say that I rather enjoyed the sight of their buildings being hit.', 15595),
	(27498, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The horns have been sounded. Victor\'s Point should launch their attack at any moment.$B$BNow there\'s only one thing left to take care of.', 13623),
	(27499, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The horns have been sounded.  Crushblow should launch their attack at any moment.$B$BNow there\'s only one thing left to take care of.', 15595),
	(27500, 1, 273, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<The paladin frowns.>$B$BThat\'s quite a gruesome trophy collection you have there. I would have believed you if you had simply said they were dead. Regardless, thank you for having the foresight to take care of them.$B$BThe Twilight Gate will soon be ours. Time to move up to the Twilight Citadel.', 13623),
	(27501, 11, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The noble lady grins wickedly.>$B$BThat\'s quite a gruesome trophy collection you have there. I would have believed you if you had simply said they were dead, though I do appreciate the extra effort. Thank you for having the foresight to take care of them.$B$BThe Twilight Gate will soon be ours. Time to move up to the Twilight Citadel.', 15595),
	(27502, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh no!', 13623),
	(27503, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This can\'t be good!', 15595),
	(27504, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Calen has become very trusting. It is not often that strangers are permitted within the redoubt.', 14333),
	(27505, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We will take Grim Batol back from the Twilight\'s Hammer and their allies. It may take time, but this is one charge that we cannot forsake.', 14333),
	(27506, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'In this, we deny Deathwing the destruction that he so passionately seeks. In this, life continues.', 14333),
	(27507, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have a talent for killing I see. In times like these, that has its place.', 14333),
	(27508, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t know if you did this for me or the young inside these eggs, but it doesn\'t really matter, either way it\'s clear that you want to be an ally of our flight. I appreciate that.$B$BI cannot forgive the attacks by your allies against my brood, but for now, it seems you have chosen the right side.', 14333),
	(27509, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. Thank you, $r.$B$BI will not be so foolish as to let such an oversight happen again.', 14333),
	(27511, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your exploration of the Chamber of the Stars has yielded more questions than answers...', 15595),
	(27514, 6, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aw dang crap it all. You\'re just an Alliance $c. I was hoping for a rescue.', 13623),
	(27515, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, that\'s the stuff all right! Hope ya didn\'t eat any. Gives you the cramps something awful but it does wonders for birds.', 13623),
	(27516, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N! Aiding that downed gryphon-rider has given us our first contact with the old Wildhammer clans. We\'ll be able to find out who\'s still left, and in what numbers.$B$BOur campaign is looking up!', 13623),
	(27517, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, rope! Thanks, kid.$b$bSomething tells me I\'m going to need this.', 15595),
	(27519, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $N.  Orsis was punished for not joining the forces of Deathwing.$B$BPrince Nadun has offered my people refuge in his city.  I must go there and tend the survivors.', 15595),
	(27520, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You continue to prove to be a valuable ally, $N.  ', 15595),
	(27537, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My word, $N. These elemental energies are so powerful, so chaotic - no wonder the Twilight\'s Hammer has chosen to build their stronghold here!$B$BI should be able to channel these energies into something more benign and productive though. Let\'s give it a try...', 13623),
	(27538, 6, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh... mud. You brought me mud?$B$BWow - this stuff oozes with power! I see what Thordun was saying, now. I\'ll distribute this to all of the healers. Our wounded will be on their feet in no time!', 13623),
	(27541, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Odd...$b$bIt looks as if someone used gemstones as lenses.$b$bI should be able to fix them without too much trouble.', 15595),
	(27545, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ho! I knew you were a $c I could count on, $N. Use that portal anytime you need to get from Stormwind back to the Highlands.$B$BNow then, time to get to business. We need to locate and unite the lost Wildhammer clans scattered around the Highlands. Talking with Thordun here is a good start!', 13623),
	(27549, 396, 5, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Well, kid, it looks like you\'ve done it again.$b$b<Harrison points to an image on the tablets.>$b$bThis starlight is exactly what we were missing.$b$bNow we can get to work!', 15595),
	(27555, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fiona has left some of her charms inside the caravan.$b$bAs a trader, she seems to be pretty good with money.  Maybe carrying one of her charms will help out with your finances.', 13623),
	(27557, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tarenar has laid a few holy talismans inside the caravan.  They appear to be unused.$b$bThey appear to be magical in nature.  If Tarenar isn\'t using them, what\'s the harm in borrowing one for a while?', 0),
	(27564, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope you\'re as tough as your gear suggests. The Twilight\'s Hammer have made their way within the redoubt somehow and I need someone to hunt them down.', 14333),
	(27568, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I would stay away from Oralius. Far, far, far away. He isn\'t quite right in the head.$B$BNow, let\'s get onto business!', 15595),
	(27569, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m sure you are up to the task I have for you if you\'ve made it this far in one piece.$B$B<Mayara Brightwing lowers her voice to a whisper.>$B$BBetween you and me, you may want to enjoy yourself in the Grim Guzzler while you\'re there. It could be the last drink you ever have.', 15595),
	(27571, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Dark Irons took our Thunderbrew. I\'ll never let them live after that. I\'d kill \'em all myself if I could!$B$BHowever, look ahead and you\'ll see we have slightly more dire matters to attend to at the moment.', 15595),
	(27573, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I cannot proceed any further alone, regardless of my combat experience. The Lyceum has proven too difficult for me. If you are here, though...you might be the key to all of this.', 15595),
	(27576, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You got the dragons in the game! Good on you.$B$BWe\'d already laid out plans for our ambush by the time the dragons contacted us. They\'re helping by cutting off their retreat.$B$BIt\'s not too late for you to join in on the fun though. We saved some for you.', 14333),
	(27582, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Beyond this door lies the commander of the Dark Iron Army, surrounded by trained soldiers. Are you up for a little killing?', 13596),
	(27583, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Warlord Zaela sent you? Good.$B$BIf you Horde are as strong as your Warchief promised, I expect to see some bloodshed on these shores.', 14333),
	(27584, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Gralok sizes you up.>$B$BYou\'re a true fighter, $n. I liked watching you work. Perhaps the Dragonmaw really DO belong in your Horde. ', 14333),
	(27585, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Up ahead is the Grim Guzzler. A disgusting bar full of all our enemies, intoxicated and therefore unfit for proper battle.$B$B<Hierophant Theodora Mulvadania grins.>$B$BRipe for the slaughter.', 13623),
	(27586, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh yeah. YEAH! These are DEFINITELY going to kill somebody.$B$BProbably naga.', 14333),
	(27589, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hear quite the commotion coming from the Grim Guzzler. I see you\'ve been hard at work.$B$BIf you\'ll direct your attention opposite me, you\'ll notice that we have bigger issues to worry about than toying with drunkards.', 13623),
	(27591, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I cannot proceed any further alone, regardless of my combat experience. The Lyceum has proven too difficult for me. If you are here, though...you might be the key to all of this.', 13623),
	(27593, 396, 396, 71, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A true $c if I\'ve ever seen one! You\'ve done the impossible! I knew we could count on you.$B$B<Warlord Goretooth pauses, smiling.>$B$BAnd with that, I\'d like for you to be the first to know that the Kargath Expeditionary Force is now officially back in business!$B$BI extend to you my personal gratitude for your efforts here. Remember always our motto: "First in, last out, always victorious. Remember always Kargath."$B$BYou are dismissed.', 13623),
	(27595, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Who... who are you?  Sent here... to rescue my people and fight our enemies.', 15595),
	(27602, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Though the chest is locked, there is a plaque bearing interesting hieroglyphs above it.', 15595),
	(27604, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! I suspect that without Jammal\'an\'s leadership, the trolls will fall to infighting and Hakkar will never set his eyes upon our world.', 15595),
	(27605, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You only defeated Eranikus\' Shade? This is most troubling...$B$BLet us hope that his full form does not still exist outside the Temple. Only Ysera herself is stronger than him in our flight.', 15595),
	(27606, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Boom baby, boom!$B$BWhat? You killed the Fathom-Lord already?$B$BI suppose we should stop shelling his corpse, then.', 14333),
	(27607, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good timing, $c. We were just about to unleash a counter-attack.', 14333),
	(27610, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $c. Now you know the lay of the land.$B$BIf you\'re ever having difficulty fighting here on the Twilight Shores, remember that capturing and holding the Beach Head will give all Horde forces here a combat advantage!', 14333),
	(27611, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, good. Let them reap what they sow!', 14333),
	(27621, 6, 396, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Come to join the patrol, $glad:lass;? Glad to have ya.$B$BI need some bodies helpin\' to get our defenses under control here. Help me out and I\'ll see if I can\'t find some more prestigious work for ya.', 13623),
	(27622, 4, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s right baby! That\'s right! Cold steel and hot death!$B$BWhat should we name our new creation? The Gnugatron? No - better - the $N-o-matic. That\'s got a ring to it.', 15595),
	(27623, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You place the two gems inside the sockets in the wall.', 15595),
	(27624, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work, $n.$b$b<Harrison studies the tablets.>$b$bIt looks as though our work here is nearly complete.', 15595),
	(27625, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Such aberrations in the face of the light... You are brave to face them, $N.', 0),
	(27626, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank the Light. We will not let the Forsaken have anything that can be turned against us, no matter how small.', 0),
	(27628, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is just the beginning, $N.  If Deathwing\'s minions can bury entire cities, we have little chance of defeating them through conventional means.', 15595),
	(27629, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What manner of creature are you?  You will leave the king\'s lands before...$B$BWait!  You are that $N I\'ve heard so much about.$B$BYou must pardon my lack of hospitality.  We have seen all manner of hostile intruders since the barrier around Uldum failed.', 15595),
	(27630, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'War, you say.$B$BDivinations for war are always difficult.  Some wars must never be fought, even if victory was assured.  Some wars have to be waged even if defeat is certain.', 15595),
	(27631, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No need to fill me in on the events in Orsis, $N.$B$BI\'ve heard about them already.  And about you.  Any enemy of Al\'Akir is a friend of mine.', 15595),
	(27632, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve obtained a map of the Vir\'Naal river delta.', 15595),
	(27633, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have successfully stopped Hakkar here, but I fear we are far from done. The Atal\'ai transported most of the blood they produced to Zul\'Gurub, where the Hakkari work to summon The Blood God there.$B$B$N, I do not think that this was ever meant to be the place of Hakkar\'s arrival - it was merely a test to see if the blood was potent enough! Hakkar can only be summoned in Zul\'Gurub...and I fear we may be too late to stop the Hakkari with the blood they now have in their possession.', 15595),
	(27635, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There, now you\'re fit to head off to the surface and start your new life. The High Tinker will be delighted to hear of your arrival.', 0),
	(27636, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where are the rest of my people?', 13623),
	(27638, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where are the Kor\'kron?', 15595),
	(27640, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If it\'s Dunwalds you be lookin\' for, it\'s Dunwalds you\'ve found. A couple of\'m anyway. I can\'t find me other brothers for the life of me.', 13623),
	(27641, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that\'s what I\'m talkin\' about $glad:lass;. My kinda $r.', 13623),
	(27642, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That many dead, eh? Not seemin\' likely that anyone outside of me brothers fought through it then. I guess I already expected as much.$B$BThanks for takin\' the time to look for me.', 13623),
	(27643, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hi friend! I don\'t think I know you... I\'m Donnelly Dunwald.$B$BWhat\'s your name? I don\'t think I know you... Do I know you?', 13623),
	(27644, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Of all the buildings in all the towns to collapse, why\'d it have to be this one?!', 13623),
	(27645, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well look at ya, all geared and fancy. Keely send you to keep an eye on old Cayden, eh? Won\'t be needin\' it. I got these louts handled.$B$BHahah! They chose the wrong dwarf to be ambushin\' today! Ahahahahah!', 13623),
	(27646, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found\'m! You found Beak! I like you, new friend!$B$BI\'m gonna go show Keely. Keely like Beak too.', 13623),
	(27647, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Donnelly\'s belly! That\'s more like it. Good to not be dyin\' of the thirst again.$B$BHere, have some. Good ol\' Eoin\'s never so impolite as ta not share!', 13623),
	(27648, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A thing of beauty, isn\'t it? An\' they keep comin\' back for more. Love it!$B$BI\'ll go find Keely and settle her nerves in a bit. Just one more go through the row.', 13623),
	(27649, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Woooooh! That\'s exactly what my belly needs!$B$BYou get me all the nice things.', 13623),
	(27650, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for bandin\' my brothers back together. I know they\'re tough, but they\'re even tougher when they\'re side by side, and there\'s a lot of Twilight out there.$B$BYou\'re good to put a gal\'s heart at ease.', 13623),
	(27651, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for your help. You\'ve got a warrior\'s spirit in ya - you coulda fooled me for a Wildhammer if it weren\'t for your... well.. you know.$B$BI know Firebeard sent you to unite us. My love for that dwarf runs shallow, but you know now we\'ve got plenty of reasons to make enemies of Twilight. If you see him, tell him that when the battle starts, the Dunwald family will be there.', 13623),
	(27652, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m not sure what I\'m going to do with all of these. I\'ll probably fence them and donate the proceeds to the Stormwind orphanage.$B$BNow to find someone sick enough to buy such a thing. It\'ll probably be a goblin. Or, a gnome warlock.', 13623),
	(27653, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What do you think I should do with all of these? Maybe I\'ll melt them down and have the metal imbued into a new dagger that I can thrust into Cho\'gall\'s chest.$B$BThink there\'s time for that?', 15595),
	(27654, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'None of us are too good to get our hands a little dirty. Or bloody, in this case.', 13623),
	(27655, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Feels good to get a little blood on your hands, doesn\'t it? Especially when that blood belongs to such self-deluded fools.', 15595),
	(27657, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N! I\'m glad you\'re here.$B$BOf course, I\'m more than happy to lend you whatever assistance that I can.', 13623),
	(27658, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N! I\'m glad you\'re here.$B$BOf course, I\'m more than willing to help you in any way that I can.', 15595),
	(27659, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The last portal is deep within the mine here, but we\'ll deal with that in a bit.', 13623),
	(27660, 33, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I know why you are here, $N. Your reasons sing within your fluids.$B$BI know about the dead dwarf forgesmith polluting my lake. If you want to find out what his corpse remembers, you must earn it.', 15595),
	(27661, 33, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am pleased. Lord Cannon was always an unworthy adversary.$B$BVery well, $r, I will help you gain the information which you seek.', 13623),
	(27662, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'d I tell you? Elementals aren\'t so bad after all, eh?', 15595),
	(27669, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, now. Would ya look at that!$b$bAs amazing as this is, I am confident that there\'s more to our discovery than meets the eye...$b$bMuch more.', 15595),
	(27670, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n. My men can take it from here. Let\'s focus on getting the other survivors out now.', 0),
	(27671, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I know Nevin will be pleased with all the survivors you managed to help. I still can\'t believe you managed to stay so strong down here in the radiation. You\'ve seen the shape the other survivors are in.$B$BLet\'s get you to the loading room for decontamination.', 0),
	(27674, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to see you again, $n. Without your help, we wouldn\'t have been able to get so many survivors out of Gnomeregan this time. Everyone is going to be thrilled to meet you and hear your story.', 0),
	(27679, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Reliquary agents are en route to investigate the chamber. You have more important matters to attend to.', 15595),
	(27680, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a most reliable agent, $N. Proceed to the discs and learn all you can. Report back to me immediately after.', 15595),
	(27681, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. Dig Three and any secrets beyond that door will soon be ours and ours alone.', 15595),
	(27682, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Both of these cores are still far more potent than most of the cores we use  to power our own protectors, and these are ancient devices!$B$BThank you, these will prove extremely valuable to our society.', 15595),
	(27683, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes?', 13623),
	(27685, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, finally...$b$bI don\'t know how much longer I can last!', 15595),
	(27688, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That takes care of most of their leaders outside of the Bastion of Twilight.$B$BWe work well together, $N.', 13623),
	(27689, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That takes care of most of their leaders outside of the Bastion of Twilight. Not bad work, $N. Not bad at all.', 15595),
	(27690, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Narkrall sizes you up.>$B$BAnother mewling Horde whelp? Zaela saps our strength by diluting our forces with the weak. Very well, $c. Prove yourself to me, and show me what your Horde is made of. ', 14333),
	(27692, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N. As you can see, my mere presence here has resulted in a bloom of glorious life despite my mate\'s presence. Names aside, perhaps one day you will again venture into Desolace and find it a verdant oasis free of any traces of the Old Gods.', 15595),
	(27693, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The jade statue becomes one again, and you place it in your pocket.  You hear a shifting noise in the tomb\'s central chamber.', 15354),
	(27695, 273, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That thing looks sharp. Sharp enough to the do deed, at least.$B$BBut if I\'m a judge of weaponry, that\'s not what Cho\'gall\'s after.', 13623),
	(27696, 396, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a very sharp axe. It\'ll do the job, but if I\'m any judge of weaponry, that\'s not what Cho\'gall\'s after.', 15595),
	(27697, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $N! Eliminating Vyletongue\'s presence is a key step to freeing me and, ultimately, saving these lands from corruption. Take this as a token of my thanks and an incentive to continue your work here.$B$B<You hear the jingle of coins coming from your bag.>', 15595),
	(27699, 6, 396, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'What?!$b$bGnaws ain\'t dead?!$b$bThis kinda takes the quick outta my get rich quick scheme...$b$bThem giant shark teeth are nice and all, but we can\'t stop \'til that shiney is ours!', 15595),
	(27700, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Isn\'t she a beauty?$B$BLet\'s see what she does now that she\'s free.', 13623),
	(27701, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Isn\'t she beautiful? So graceful.$B$BI hope she gets her fill of revenge and then some.', 15595),
	(27702, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our efforts to improve relations with the red dragons has really paid off, $N.', 13623),
	(27706, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So... this is what Al\'Akir wanted all along.', 15595),
	(27707, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If the prisoner\'s information is true, Tahet is in great danger.', 15595),
	(27708, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good that this operation has been undone.$b$bSoon, I must move on...', 15595),
	(27709, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The red statue falls over, and you place it back in your bags.  You hear a rumbling noise in the tomb\'s central chamber.>', 15354),
	(27711, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N, glad you\'re back! Have I got something fun for us to do!', 13623),
	(27716, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brilliant! It will take me a while to translate, but this is precisely the kind of find I was hoping for.$B$BThere\'s no knowing if we will make it out of this place, but if it comes down to it, I will find a way to float this to the surface in hopes that it will one day be found.$B$BThank you again, $n. Here... perhaps I have something that may be of use to you.', 13623),
	(27717, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brilliant! I can\'t have expected much more with the tools I gave you.$B$BI should be able to fill in the blanks and get this all written out shortly. There\'s no knowing if we will make it out of this place, but if it comes down to it, I will find a way to float this to the surface in hopes that it will one day be found.$B$BThank you again, $n. You\'re not bad.', 15595),
	(27718, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lok\'tar, $g brother:sister;! You have arrived just in time.', 15595),
	(27719, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Hammer of Twilight? And you say you got this information out of a drowned Wildhammer dwarf?$B$BYou\'re kidding, right?', 13623),
	(27720, 5, 18, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh no! My weapons and totems!$B$BThey\'re destroyed!!!', 13623),
	(27721, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We knew the Horde would send help and not a moment too soon!', 15595),
	(27722, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our world is in danger, $N! We need the help of great heroes, like you, to save it!', 15595),
	(27725, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yoro sends warning of the Horde? The Highvale have been cautious of an attack for some time now. In fact, we have been--\n\n<Screams and the clash of metal break out to the south.>', 0),
	(27726, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We knew the Alliance would send help and not a moment too soon!', 15595),
	(27727, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our world is in danger, $N! We need the help of great heroes, like you, to save it!', 15595),
	(27729, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You can add this to list of things you can tell your grandchildren that you\'ve done for them.', 15595),
	(27733, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, Mortimer just faked his own death. He\'ll probably take on his brother\'s name and continue on his \'epic schemes\'. We\'ll just have to deal with that when the time comes.', 15595),
	(27737, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank goodness! With this fire, our men will live through this ordeal!$B$BThank you so much, hero.', 15595),
	(27738, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you for what you\'ve done, $N.  You can count on my vote when High Council convenes.', 15595),
	(27739, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have performed a deed this day unlike any I have seen in my long career. Hogger\'s death will plague the Riverpaw for years to come, and hopefully put an end to their attacks on our people.$B$BGreatest of heroes, please take this as a sign of my eternal gratitude.', 15595),
	(27742, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Goldmine slyly looks at the pile of Elementium shards.>$B$BHmm, I don\'t think that stuff\'s going to sell for much. I better give you your cut right now so you don\'t feel ripped off.', 13623),
	(27743, 14, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They had it coming to them.', 13623),
	(27744, 4, 6, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'That\'ll teach \'em to move in on our territory!$B$BWhat\'s that over across the way?', 13623),
	(27745, 4, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We survived and all of the portals are now shutdown!$B$BYou don\'t think Magmatooth is going to hold a grudge, do you?', 13623),
	(27747, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes. Burn them out, as you would flush groundhogs from their holes...$B$BWell done, $N.', 14333),
	(27748, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you\'re still in one piece, $n.', 14333),
	(27750, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Griff greedily snatches the heap of food, enough to feed dozens of men.>$B$BGreat! Did you get any for yourself?', 14333),
	(27751, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Narkrall clenches the insignias in his weathered hand.>$B$BSo, $c. There\'s more to you than meets the eye.$B$BMaybe your Horde can stand with the best of my warriors. Let\'s try you out...', 14333),
	(27752, 273, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh aye ... we get a few of these kegs out to the boys on the front and we\'re gonna see some fireworks. Thank you, $N!', 13623),
	(27753, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good - hardly a worm or weevil to be found!$B$BThis is a lifesaver to the folk who fled here for survival.', 13623),
	(27754, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at that! That\'s quite a collection of trophies you have there.$B$BI\'ll spread the word. If a single Alliance $c can do this, imagine what the rest of your lot can accomplish!', 13623),
	(27755, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They couldn\'t be saved, $N.  The ancient curse that fell upon them is irrevocable.', 15595),
	(27756, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Bzzzzzzzzzzzzt.>$B$BNicely done! A clean kill. Now continue on and see what else you can find! We\'ll crack this case wide open with you on our side, I just know it.', 15354),
	(27758, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Bzzzzzzzzzzzzt.>$B$BHey, it\'s Horatio. That was intense! I\'m watching your progress on the Stormwind Communicator\'s Spyatron X3 application.$B$BThey sure are using a lot of heavily fortified doors to hide their work. Keep pushing forward and see what you find next. I bet it\'ll be a huge clue!', 15354),
	(27760, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Scanning subject...$B$BCerebral cortex diagnostics indicate the absence of "tomb curse" phenomenon.$B$BDiagnostics did reveal frequent head trauma.  The user would do well to exercise more caution around blunt objects in the future.', 15595),
	(27761, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N.  The expedition has already doomed itself.$B$BThere is no need for it to endanger the rest of the world as well.', 15595),
	(27762, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice landing!', 13623),
	(27763, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Fuselight!', 13623),
	(27764, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $r.  You may keep the goggles, as they have already served their purpose: they brought you to me.', 15354),
	(27765, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for gathering these so quickly, $N.', 15354),
	(27766, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This grisly task was necessary, $N.$b$bAll will be revealed to you soon.  For now, know this:$b$bI am no ordinary goblin.$b$bI serve a mistress of unimaginable power, and her motives here are not as dark as they might seem.', 15354),
	(27769, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My true name is Rheastrasza, and I am an envoy of Alexstrasza herself, the Aspect of the red dragonflight.$b$bWith Deathwing currently occupied with other matters, we are going to find a way to redeem the black dragonflight.$b$bAnd you are going to help us.', 15354),
	(27770, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We will find a shred of good within these dragons, $N.  Whether it is in the wild eggs you found, the bodies of the whelplings you slew, or the eggs that we have encouraged Nyxondra to lay... we will find an untainted black dragon.', 15354),
	(27771, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done everything that I have asked you, without question.  Our job here in Lethlor Ravine is done.$b$bIt is now time that I revealed everything to you.', 15354),
	(27772, 6, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ooh!  Science stuff!  Let\'s see what you\'ve got here...$b$bWild eggs?  Blech.  Useless.  These are never any good.$b$bOoooh, what\'s this?  Some sort of... pre-engineered egg?  This looks promising, but I don\'t want to know what Rhea had to do to get it.$b$bHmm... yes, some very nice corpses.  Very nice indeed.$b$bAlright, I\'ll see what I can do.', 15354),
	(27774, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I wonder where all of these ogre-magi are coming from?  Curious times, indeed.', 15354),
	(27775, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A perfect fit!  My goat puncher is finally finished!', 15354),
	(27776, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done!  I have no doubt that those goats will be back, but they\'ll think twice before they nibble my cogs again!', 15354),
	(27777, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent job, user $N.  We must obtain access to the fusion core now.', 14333),
	(27778, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am in control, user $N.  But I cannot keep the core temperature stable indefinitely.', 14333),
	(27779, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done, user $N.  I thank you for your assistance with this unfortunate task.', 14333),
	(27781, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Bzzzzzzzzzzzzt.>$B$BYou\'re nearing the heart of their domain. There will likely be an extremely fortified door protecting the inner sanctum of the entire Defias operation. See if you can find anything that might pry it open!$B$BI suggest a stealthy method!', 15354),
	(27782, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, you\'re back. We know where Cho\'gall\'s ultimate weapon is located!', 13623),
	(27784, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Hammer of Twilight floats in the middle of the altar, unprotected....', 13623),
	(27785, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Bzzzzzzzzzzzzt.>$B$BYour exploits have gained quite the following in the intelligence community, $N. Many top members of SI:7 have been earnestly watching you infiltrate the Deadmines through their own Stormwind Communicators.$B$BMathias Shaw himself wants to speak with you! I\'ll transfer you over momentarily.', 15354),
	(27787, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it, $g lad : lass;! You beat that damned gronn and sent Cho\'gall packing into the Twilight Bastion.$B$BDon\'t you worry. With your help and that of your friends, we\'ll get in there and we\'ll kill Cho\'gall once and for all!', 13623),
	(27789, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The results are in.  I\'ve identified traces of corruption in all three samples you brought me.  Rhea will be quite disappointed.', 15354),
	(27790, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You very well may have saved all of Stormwind with your efforts here today, $N. Vanessa may still be out there, but she is an insignificant threat now that the Juggernaut will be placed under our careful watch. Thank you.', 15354),
	(27791, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Titans?  You wanna know about titans?$b$bYou came to the right place, $g lad: lass;.  We\'re on the brink of somethin\' big.', 15354),
	(27792, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Chalice... worthless.$b$bVase... counterfeit.$b$bHieroglyph... interesting, but rather common.$b$bWhat\'s this?  I\'ve never seen trogg craftsmanship of this caliber!  You\'ve stumbled upon something rare indeed, $n.$b$bAlright, fine.  Let\'s talk titans, shall we?', 15354),
	(27793, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With your inspection complete, the statues return to their original positions.  Something seems different in the room, however...', 15354),
	(27794, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just one tiny little device?$b$bI never did understand those titans.$b$bVery well!  Let\'s see what this peeper can do.', 13623),
	(27796, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The statue clicks into place on the large stone slab.>', 15354),
	(27797, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The statue slides into place on the cold marble slab.>', 15354),
	(27803, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $gboy:girl;. Good to have another capable set of hands about.', 13623),
	(27804, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for your help. Every little bit makes a difference.$B$BWe\'ll keep the water going until we can push the Twilight back.', 13623),
	(27805, 275, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are very generous. Thank you.$B$BThere\'s a lot of darkness in our world these days. We appreciate the light that you\'ve brought here.', 13623),
	(27806, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings, $r. Sent by Keegan?', 13623),
	(27807, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Iain sent ya?$B$BYou don\'t look like a Firebeard to me. Why exactly should I be listenin\' to anything you say?', 13623),
	(27808, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems the Doyles suffered the worst of the attacking Twilight drakes.$B$BIt\'s clear that they fought to the end: not a single rider\'s footprint more than a few yards from his gryphon. It\'s doubtful there were any survivors.', 13623),
	(27809, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Bout that time, eh? Help us wrap things up then.', 13623),
	(27810, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s the stuff! Not half bad. You\'ve got a bit of fight in ya after all.', 13623),
	(27811, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good on you. I always feel like a part of me is missing when my gryphon isn\'t nearby. I can\'t speak for Duglas or the rest of the clan, but I\'ll be ready to ride at Firebeard\'s call.', 13623),
	(27812, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya got the Mullans. Good news! They\'re worth more than their weight in a fight, and they ain\'t exactly skinny.', 13623),
	(27813, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s more like it. Let\'s finish gatherin\' up supplies and get back to Keegan.', 13623),
	(27814, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yer a good $glad:lass;.  Have me thanks and a little gold for yer troubles.', 13623),
	(27815, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah! Looks like their raid went mighty well then. I\'ll have to buy ol\' Forgehammer a round once we finish with this mess.', 13623),
	(27816, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems you had some luck bringin\' riders back. Well timed too - we just pushed the elementals back, so we should have the arm room to lead an attack right away.$B$BThank you, $n. You\'re a good $r.', 13623),
	(27817, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that\'s how it\'s done, $g lad:lass;!$B$BWith a real gryphon wing back together, we can take the fight to the rest of the Twilight. You\'re welcome to fly with us anytime.', 13623),
	(27823, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sigrun instantly downs a dusty mug of shadowstout.>$b$bWow, this stuff is strong!  I knew they had beer, but I never expected them to have shadowstout!  That\'s my favorite shadowbeer!', 13623),
	(27824, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now here\'s some treasure!  I was beginning to worry that these weren\'t titan ruins at all!$b$bI\'ll show these to Durdin.  Thanks again, $N.', 13623),
	(27825, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I imagine those ogres weren\'t too much trouble for you.  Here - some coin for your troubles.', 13623),
	(27826, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll take that egg out of your hands now.  We need to get this egg incubated... and hidden, quickly.  There are lots of angry dragons looking for this.$b$bIt\'s good to see you again, by the way.', 13623),
	(27827, 1, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re the $r we\'ve been waiting for?  It\'s about time you got here.  My legs could use a stretch.$b$bCome on boys!  Let\'s go kill us some black dragons!', 13623),
	(27828, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m not what you\'d call "very strong" or "battle-hardened", but I get the job done my own way.$b$bLookin\' forward to fightin\' with you.  I never fought with a fancy-lookin\' $c before.', 13623),
	(27829, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'One less dragon to worry about, one step closer to redemption.  Onward, my soldiers!', 13623),
	(27830, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Two more dangerous black dragons have been removed from this egg hunt.  Your greatest task, however, still awaits.', 13623),
	(27833, 21, 21, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $r.  However, I\'m afraid I don\'t have much to give you, other than this passionate round of applause.$b$b<Terrance looks down into his bags.>$b$bOh, I do have these.  Here, take your pick.', 13623),
	(27834, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I think you\'re ready, $N.  You\'re getting the hang of this.', 13623),
	(27835, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'See?  No need to worry when Olaf is around.  Just let me know, and I\'ll protect you from the monsters.', 13623),
	(27836, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $N.  This will make our prophetic visions that much clearer.', 15595),
	(27837, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, $N.  I can feel the disruption in the river fading.$B$BYet, I feel the source of this taint still lingers.', 15595),
	(27838, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes.  The waters are clearing up.$B$BI am certain I will be visited by a vision before the High Council meets.$B$BBe warned, $r.  My vote will only be swayed by what I see.$B$BYou might have helped us greatly here today, but if the vision sways me to make a case against war then that is the way my vote will be cast.', 15595),
	(27839, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is quite timely.  I will distribute these armaments to my best men and to the laborers that you recruited.$B$BI\'ve a feeling they\'ll show as much courage as my best trained captains.', 15595),
	(27842, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do not be alarmed, $N. I am close to you, waiting in the shadows. You\'ve done well.$B$BYou must continue the mission here - I am too valuable to risk my life against petty criminals like these.', 15595),
	(27844, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My employers do not take kindly to traitors.$B$BOn the flip side, they are renown for their kindness towards the loyal! You deserve to be rewarded!', 15595),
	(27847, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brilliant! Now all I have to do is finish my work, and my Mayhem Reapers will cause...mayhem...on any Horde front!$B$BAnd there won\'t be any Defias knockoffs to steal my profits!', 15595),
	(27848, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s a shame that he was both a human and a worgen. Had he been a proud orc warrior I\'d have liked to charge into battle alongside such a fierce combatant.$B$BWe can speak of ill-fated desires another day. It is time to take what is ours from the enemy.', 15595),
	(27850, 15, 396, 153, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'COWARD!!! Vanessa VanCleef is a dirty human coward! How dare she flee from battle against the Horde and leave her unworthy subordinate to fight!$B$B<Kagtha composes herself.>$B$BNo matter. Her ship is reward enough. The citizens of Stormwind will bear first hand witness to our awe inspiring power using a ship made in part by the very architect of their city!', 15595),
	(27863, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad, friend. You might make some gold out here - if you manage to stay alive.', 15595),
	(27865, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No love in your heart for dwarves I see. You really made a mess of that guy.', 15595),
	(27866, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow! When I saw that... thing stumble into the arena, I thought you didn\'t stand a chance. But you proved me wrong. You tore it apart!$B$BGrizzly business.', 15595),
	(27867, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You really pulled that one out. I thought you were done for sure when he wolfed and started tearing up the arena. I guess I should know by now that you don\'t go down easy.', 15595),
	(27868, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like this title is yours! You really pulled that one out of the fire. $B$BCongratulations. I hope the coin serves you well.', 15595),
	(27874, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ysera herself sent you to me? Oh! It\'s an honor to speak with a representative of the aspects.$B$BIt\'s true that our shrine is in jeopardy. The harpies we once sheltered in our boughs have suddenly turned against us.$B$BBut please, don\'t rejoin the fight until you are ready. Our shrine is no mere battleground. Use its peace and power to center yourself.', 15595),
	(27899, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It would seem that I\'m not the only one interested in these obelisks...', 15595),
	(27900, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a relief. Thanks, $n.$b$bTurns out I\'ve got my hands full here.', 15595),
	(27901, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s it!$b$bGood work, $n!', 15595),
	(27903, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'According to Harrison\'s notes, placing the lens upon this dais should re-activate this obelisk.$b$bExactly what that means remains to be seen...', 15595),
	(27905, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work back there, $n.$b$bLooks like we\'ve lost them, for now at least.', 15595),
	(27912, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You peer into the chest...', 13623),
	(27917, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The scent of freshly spilled traitor blood fills my nostrils, and it is absolutely invigorating. However, my bloodlust will not be sated until Godfrey lies on the floor as a lifeless heap.$B$BHe thinks an army of mindless corpses can stop the wrath of the Bloodfang? We\'ll gnaw on their bones for years to come after our work is done!', 15595),
	(27920, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re nearly there, $N. The time is now to charge further ahead and take out Walden!', 15595),
	(27921, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Packleader Ivar Bloodfang grins, revealing his razor-sharp teeth.>$B$BIt won\'t be long now before the entire keep is ours, thanks to your valiant efforts.', 15595),
	(27922, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A djinn!  We must escape as soon as possible.$B$BThis unholy alliance of the Neferset with the minions of Deathwing does not bode well for us.', 15595),
	(27923, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes.  I hear the Neferset calling each other to the east.  This might yet work.', 15595),
	(27924, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent.  You\'ll see, this can\'t possibly go wrong!', 15595),
	(27926, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I trust that you had no troubles fitting in with our guests, hmm?', 15595),
	(27928, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, these are exquisite!$b$bThe commander will be able to make a winter uniform with these.', 15595),
	(27929, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You look a little battered. Those dwarves didn\'t give you any challenge, did they?$B$BStill, that was an impressive show.', 14333),
	(27931, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, $r, you\'re here.$B$BWe\'ll have to act fast if we\'re to prevent Therazane\'s forces from attacking.', 14333),
	(27932, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N. Without all of their giants, Therazane\'s forces will have a harder time taking Stonehearth.$B$BNow, if you please, hand back the axe. I\'ll keep it safe until you can rescue the Stonefather.', 14333),
	(27933, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These should do. I\'ll just need a moment to prepare the ritual.', 14333),
	(27934, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that the ritual is complete and you are near Avalanchion, there\'s only one thing left to do.', 14333),
	(27935, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done what few others could have. Defeating Avalanchion was no small feat.$B$BI\'m impressed, $N. Will you help us with our war against the stone troggs so that we can rescue the Stonefather?', 14333),
	(27937, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our $g hero : heroine; returns!$B$BYou have saved my people, $N. You have earned that which you seek.', 15354),
	(27938, 21, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Middle Fragment of the World Pillar!$B$BThank you, $N. I can only imagine what you had to go through to get this to us. I\'ll see to it that it\'s placed within the center of the chamber.', 15354),
	(27939, 396, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it!$b$bPerhaps I can trust you vizh more serious matters, hmm?', 15595),
	(27940, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve made the Cradle of the Ancients a somewhat less despicable place to travel through.', 15595),
	(27941, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Most efficient work, $c.$b$bYou should rise rapidly through the ranks.', 15595),
	(27942, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Zhese look to be of sufficient quality.$b$bVizh zhese, ve are vone shtep closah to zhe cleansink ritual.', 15595),
	(27943, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very goot!$b$bYou have earned yourself a place at zhe ritual.$b$bYou shall be among zhe first to velcome Gobbles back to his... original form.', 15595),
	(27944, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work on those spiders $n.  At this rate, we will be taking that forest in no time.', 13623),
	(27945, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Mallia removes her eyepatch and holds the black diamond before her empty eye socket.>$B$BWhat have we, what have we - breaches, the breaches number three. Two heads, one wholly given to its master. I see the future. A hammer united. A mountain shattered. Oh - OH!$B$B<Mallia drops the diamond to the floor, covering her face with her hands.>', 14333),
	(27947, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Eye sits before you, humming ominously with dark energies.>$B$B<Without warning, the orb rotates, as if to look at you. You sense a malevolent presence, as though the orb is alive.>', 14333),
	(27949, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May their souls rest in peace.', 13623),
	(27950, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was probably not the transformation Schnottz was hoping for...', 15595),
	(27951, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Eye glimmers darkly, colors swirling about its dusky surface.>$B$BAh, the succulent thrill of life extinguished. Do you feel it, $c? Do you relish it as I do?$B$BNo, I see not. You fight to protect the lives of others. Pity.', 14333),
	(27952, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh gosh! Someone\'s finally here to help us?', 15354),
	(27953, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, it\'s about time someone came to speak with us on matters most urgent.', 15595),
	(27954, 6, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found one? I\'ve been searching everywhere. Give it here!$B$BSome of these eyes are won over with riddles or verse. Others require magic. What did this one demand? Ah, it\'s no matter. What matters is that it\'s ours. ', 14333),
	(27955, 6, 5, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve gone pale, $c. What did the Eye show you?$B$BYou saw Cho\'gall? Wait - Cho\'gall saw you? He\'s watching us? He\'s watching us right now!?$B$BDamn this stupid dark magic! I\'m going to have to infiltrate Cho\'gall\'s stronghold myself.', 14333),
	(27956, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You didn\'t... KILL the machines to get these, right?.$b$b<Lunk looks upset.>$b$bRight?', 15595),
	(27957, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No!  You are the same as Thorium Brotherhood dwarf.$b$b"Kill dwarf.  Kill spider.  Kill machine.  Kill, kill, kill."$b$bLunk come to gorge to go on adventure, not to go on murder spree.$b$bGoodbye, $r.  You kill too much.', 15595),
	(27958, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This... this is way more than I expected.  This will last us for months!', 15595),
	(27959, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lunk is very happy that you let him ride on the spiders.  Lunk is also happy that $n was able to do $n\'s adventures without killing anything.$b$bMaybe Lunk see you later.', 15595),
	(27960, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you.', 15595),
	(27961, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve got quick hands if you were able to gather this many in such a short time.$b$bExcellent work, $N.  I\'ll make sure these ones don\'t go to waste.', 15595),
	(27962, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yup, this was Margol\'s horn alright.  No doubt about it.$b$bBarnabas was a digger, like me.  He never stood a chance in combat against the beast.  I\'m glad you were here to set things right.', 15595),
	(27963, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s see... Overseer Maltorius... we\'re quite familiar with him and his work.$b$bWhat\'s this?  The "archduke"?  That sounds promising.', 15595),
	(27964, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A... an ember?  What is this thing?', 15595),
	(27965, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do I know you, $r?$b$b<Overseer Oilfist listens as you describe what you saw within the flames at Thorium Advance.>$b$bSounds like another one of Ragnaros\' minions.  I don\'t like the sound of that.', 15595),
	(27968, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did it, $N! At terrible cost... but victory is ours.$B$BThis keep could serve well as a home for me and my pack, though we tend to prefer more natural habitats.$B$BIt may be best to leave it as a reminder of Godfrey\'s betrayal and of the Bloodfang warriors that died here in battle.', 15595),
	(27969, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Vell done, $c.$b$bZhere may be hope for you yet.', 15595),
	(27971, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work on the undead up there $n.  We really appreciate the help.', 13623),
	(27974, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, very well done! They\'ve gotten a hold of powerful allies, but clearly nothing a $c-champion of the Banshee Queen can\'t handle!', 15595),
	(27976, 1, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ye\'re a good $g lad:lass;, ye are. I got ye a lil\' present fer yer troubles.', 15595),
	(27977, 1, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fantastic work!', 15595),
	(27979, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Hansel weighs the stone in his hands.>$b$bThis thing is strange, $N.  I don\'t know what to make of it.  It ain\'t natural, that\'s for sure.', 15595),
	(27980, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'s no way you coulda killed all the spiders in the gorge, but you definitely made a dent.$b$bFine, here\'s what I promised ya.  Don\'t spend it all in one place.  Unless it\'s at Thorium Point.', 15595),
	(27981, 5, 18, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yeeeeeeowch!  Don\'t just go puttin\' this stuff into a dwarf\'s open hand.  This stuff is burnin\' up!$b$bNow me hands are gonna get even more swollen...', 15595),
	(27982, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm... the gems looked... sparklier from afar.  Up close, they look kind of dingy.$b$bAh well!  A little spit and polish should do the trick, and if not, I can use \'em to practice my disenchanting.', 15595),
	(27983, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dwarfs is going to sleep good tonight.$b$bLunk hopes you got everything you were looking for.  Now time to go off and find other adventures.$b$bBye!', 15595),
	(27984, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have accepted my fate here in this cage, but the prayer must be found.', 15595),
	(27985, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As your eyes pass over the words of Zamael\'s prayer, you feel the tablet grow lighter.$b$bA wave of warmth passes over you, and the tablet is gone.', 15595),
	(27986, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And who might you be?$b$bAh, an emissary from the Thorium Brotherhood.  They\'re looking for my support?  Fine, I might be willin\' to help out...$b$b...for a price.', 15595),
	(27987, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good job on the recovery effort $n. These cannonballs should last us a while.', 13623),
	(27988, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Cromush has both a thick skull and a fool\'s brain, and we\'ll use that to our advantage. By the time anybody finds out about the plague\'s true potency, it\'ll be far too late.$B$BThank you for keeping quiet during his tirade. I promise you won\'t regret it.', 15595),
	(27989, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Honey! Delicious honey!$B$BWell done, ugly creature! You may put the honey...put the honey down right there. No, to the left. Yes, there. Just leave it there.', 15595),
	(27990, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Auch!$b$bIf I vere an inch or two taller, I\'d be dead!', 15595),
	(27992, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These parts will really help us out, $n!  Who would have thought you can find stuff this useful in all that old junk?', 13623),
	(27993, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see ya, kid.$b$bWould\'ve been even better if you\'d have been here to help me take care of these little savages...', 15595),
	(27994, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It worked!$B$BI mean, uh, YES, the will of Ruumbo has been carried out! You have done well, creature! You may have these shiny coins!', 15595),
	(27995, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those two brats... I should have known! They were smart enough to hush whenever I went to examine the totem.$B$BI\'ll be sure to find them and drag them back to Timbermaw Hold by the ears! Thank you for looking into it...', 15595),
	(27996, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The time has come! Godfrey will fall!', 15595),
	(27997, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Emerald Circle thanks you, $n. If we all work together here, we can purge these demons from our midst.', 15595),
	(27998, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'For a moment there, I thought all was lost. Even when surrounded by the worgen in Gilneas I had higher hopes!$B$BBut you proved me wrong $N. I will see to it that Sylvanas herself hears of your triumph here today. Don\'t worry about the mess here, I will gladly see to it myself.', 15595),
	(27999, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a right shame. Stubborn as they were to speak to, they were just as stubborn in a fight. Would have been good to have \'em.$B$BOnce this is done, we\'ll have to send some boys out to bring them back for a proper send off.', 13623),
	(28000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Imps are creatures of deception. With so many of them spotted at Shadowlurk Ridge, I\'m positive something is being hidden there.$B$BOur little friend will tell us exactly how to find it... if he doesn\'t want to go back in the sack.', 15595),
	(28001, 5, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here here, WOT!? He calls ME a COWARD!?$B$BJust like a Firebeard, all hot air and not a lick of sense. I\'ve been bearing the brunt of a Dragonmaw invasion from the south, much of Thundermar is in ruins, and do any of the other clans stick up to help? NO! Ol\' Thundermar is on his own he is, and you\'d better believe I\'m usin\' everything in my arsenal just to stem the tide.', 13623),
	(28002, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm, still a bit frazzled, are they?$b$bWell, you know what they say. Time heals all wounds.$b$bExcept for those of the ambassador, of course...', 15595),
	(28028, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If nothin\' else, you bought us some time, and some room to open up our supply lines through this siege.$b$bYer a fine $c.', 15595),
	(28029, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like ye know how to light things on fire!  An admirable trait in any $r, for sure.', 15595),
	(28030, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll just divvy these up amongst the guards.  Ye have my thanks.', 15595),
	(28032, 4, 5, 273, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 'Ooh, these are nice.  Now, leave me alone with my gizzards.  I\'ve got studying to do!$b$b<Agnes starts to poke the gizzards with a stick.>$b$bYes, very interesting.  Very interesting indeed...', 15595),
	(28033, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well well well.  Look who come searching for Lunk this time!$b$bThis sounds like case for Lunk\'s unique brand of no-kill problem-solve.', 15595),
	(28034, 5, 25, 10, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did I stutter?  I believe I clearly stated that I... won\'t...$b$bWow, ye\'ve got some good moves there!  I\'m impressed!', 15595),
	(28035, 2, 1, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, Rendan\'s on our side?  About time that oaf came around.$b$bLet\'s get moving, then.', 15595),
	(28038, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey, you\'re one $gbig strong heap of:lovely killing machine,; $c. Can you handle the crucible? We got bookies standing by!', 14333),
	(28041, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You gather up the fresh carcass.>', 14333),
	(28043, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was an impressive aerial display, $N, but I wish it had come at a better time.$B$BNarkrall is a great warrior, but he\'s also an impatient fool. He\'s about to get himself killed ... and we\'re about to lose one of our most important weapons in the battle for the Highlands!', 14333),
	(28044, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Claw of Tichondrius...$B$BYou hold a piece of the very demon that led the Legion to these woods, $n. Better for it to be in our hands than with the satyr.$B$BHold still. I\'m going to pull you back to our plane and make sure you and the claw arrive here safely...', 15595),
	(28049, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh good, you\'re back! Don\'t leave me alone with her! She\'s crazy!$B$BGimme that, I\'ll have you seeing the invisible in no time!', 15595),
	(28052, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, here we are.$b$bI hope you\'re ready, $N.', 15595),
	(28053, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lunk heared that you used the stone to banish fire-lizard.  You saved Gorge, and you didn\'t even kill!$b$bLunk so proud.  Lunk happy to be $n\'s teacher.$b$bMaybe you take this.  Lunk doesn\'t need it.  Lunk too busy adventuring!', 15595),
	(28054, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done good.  I don\'t like slavery either.', 15595),
	(28055, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Strange how so many slaves cope poorly with freedom.  It\'s a shame to have to do what we do, but such are the truths of war.$b$bNow, we must move on to more pressing tasks.', 15595),
	(28056, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A fight well-fought, $N!  I\'m beginning to feel the tide turn.$b$bNow, when you\'re ready, let\'s hit these Dark Irons where it really hurts!', 15595),
	(28057, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see Evonice is up to her old tricks again.  I guess I\'ll just... um... hang onto these pillows for a while.$b$bThe important part is that you\'re here.  We\'re going to need your help.', 15595),
	(28060, 273, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Twilight\'s Hammer, eh?  I should\'ve expected as much.  I\'m glad you arrived to help them out when you did.$b$bIt looks like, despite all odds, we\'ve pressed our offensive to the doorstep of Calcinder\'s lair.  It\'s now time to finish the job.', 15595),
	(28061, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The remains of Calcinder\'s minions lie smoldering at your feet.  Oilfist will be relieved to hear that you succeeded.', 15595),
	(28062, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Archduke Calcinder has been banished from Azeroth.  All that remains is a small, ashy spot where he once stood.$b$bYour work here is done.', 15595),
	(28064, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our task is complete, and it\'s all thanks to you, $N.  I\'d like to offer you your choice from our coffers.  In addition, I intend to make you a full-fledged member of our order.$b$bWelcome to the Thorium Brotherhood, $N.  I\'m proud to call you a $g brother: sister;.', 15595),
	(28090, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good going.$B$BDoesn\'t look like much, does it?', 15595),
	(28091, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. Now we can start pushing our ground forces up towards Grim Batol.', 15595),
	(28092, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Works like a charm, every time.', 15595),
	(28093, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The gate is clear. Once your people finish clearing the canyon, we will speak to your leaders about the next move.', 15595),
	(28094, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We make it look easy.', 15595),
	(28096, 6, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So how was it? Everything that you dreamed it would be? Exciting, no?$B$BNo?$B$B<Darthalia sighs.>$B$BI can see that you\'re a true $g hero:heroine;. You need action. I guess a "desk job" isn\'t for you.', 15354),
	(28097, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The canyon is well fortified, but the distraction that the dragons are providing should be enough to allow us to break through.', 15595),
	(28099, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is, unfortunately, as I expected.  These bracers bear the indelible mark of the firelord and his minions.$b$bVery well.  With no Horde or Alliance forces anywhere near this godforsaken gorge, it falls upon the Thorium Brotherhood to stop this Archduke before he spreads any more of his evil.', 15595),
	(28100, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You... yes, you! I have chosen you, $r, as my champion! You will do the work of Ruumbo!', 15595),
	(28101, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The red dragons have agreed to help! No small feat, I\'m sure. You have the thanks of the Alliance.$B$BWe\'d already laid out plans for our ambush on a Twilight caravan by the time the dragons contacted us. They\'re helping by cutting off their retreat.$B$BThe battle still rages. You can definitely be of aid.', 13623),
	(28103, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. Now we can start pushing our ground forces up towards Grim Batol.', 13623),
	(28104, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good going.$B$BDoesn\'t look like much, does it?', 13623),
	(28105, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, $N.  We will make our way out of here soon enough.', 15595),
	(28107, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We make it look easy.', 13623),
	(28108, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Like a well-oiled machine.', 13623),
	(28109, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The gate is clear. Once your people finish clearing the canyon, we will speak to your leaders about the next move.', 13623),
	(28111, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re in a bit of a bind, $c. Sarus\' spiders are starting to get a little uppity as we\'ve been unable to feed them for days. If we leave the murlocs will overtake our post! Furthermore, Warden Stillwater over at the Sludge Fields is demanding that we send him more humans! He is insatiable! We need help!', 15354),
	(28112, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is true then?  An outsider rescued Prince Nadun from the Neferset?$B$BWe are truly in your debt, stranger.', 15595),
	(28114, 21, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! Now to place these eggs into a nice, dark alcove inside the mine and let the miracle of life happen!', 15354),
	(28115, 1, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The bear gods are cruel masters. They will continue to populate this world with bears until the end of days. It is our right as civilized people to make use of this nuisance - for the betterment of us all!', 15354),
	(28116, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful. Greta chose wisely when she asked you to perform this task. I will work the herbs immediately...', 15595),
	(28119, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will do nicely, $N.', 15595),
	(28121, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, $N! With their numbers weakened, we can soon begin our assault on their forces deep within Shadow Hold.', 15595),
	(28123, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Zaela takes the gore-spattered length of chain and wraps it around her hand and wrist.>$B$BIf the stories are true, $N, it was on this length of chain that Deathwing had once fastened the Demon Soul, forged in his bid to control the other dragonflights. The Demon Soul has long been destroyed but perhaps this hunk of elementium holds some residual power...$B$BYou\'ve done a great thing today.', 14333),
	(28126, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the braziers gone, the druids of the Emerald Circle can enter Shadow Hold and clear out the last of the cultists. In time, it may even be used as the barrow den it once was.$B$BYou have my thanks, $n. Please take this reward.', 15595),
	(28128, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The cleansing of Shadow Hold will take much time and effort, but without your defeat of the Shadow Council, it would not be possible at all. Thank you, $n.', 15595),
	(28129, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The demons begin to fall! Take heed, $c. You will find even stronger foes deeper within Shadow Hold.', 15595),
	(28130, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Told you that village was full of wackos.  Nice job clearing it out $n.', 13623),
	(28131, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another demonic menace gone. It is time to find their master.', 15595),
	(28132, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh look, it\'s one of little Schnottz\'s pamphlets.$b$bI\'ll just be taking that from you, if you don\'t mind.', 15595),
	(28133, 1, 273, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Once free of the chain, Torth died rather than submit again. I admire the creature. I will have his hide fashioned into a set of armor.$B$BThis much is clear to me now: The Dragonmaw cannot stand alone if the Alliance backs the Wildhammer. Narkrall proved that. And you have proven the might of the Horde, again and again.$B$BI will rebuild our drake wings and take up position outside the Bastion of Twilight. You should continue to help out here in the Gullet and elsewhere in the Highlands.', 14333),
	(28134, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Orsis!  Of course!$B$BHow could I not have seen this?', 15595),
	(28135, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you see what Deathwing\'s minions have done?  Great Orsis is now all but buried in the sand!', 15595),
	(28138, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will do nicely. I do wonder what the warden has planned for them. Last I heard the Sludge Fields were overrun by some very bad things.', 15354),
	(28141, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you.  The rumors I\'d heard about you are proving true after all.', 15595),
	(28144, 1, 1, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At least we\'ll be prepared for any future incidents. Moving "supplies" like this around is a risky proposition. You never know who is going to open their big fat mouth.$B$B<Keyton raises what appears to be an eyebrow at you.>', 15354),
	(28145, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N.  We might yet save Iset.', 15595),
	(28146, 1, 1, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This should keep it happy and content for a few days. You\'ve done a good thing here, $N!', 15354),
	(28147, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What did you manage to get? I suppose we can piece something together from this.$B$BAfter all, you\'re not joining the cult. We just need to fool a few ogres.', 14333),
	(28148, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will see these are burned swiftly and safely, $n. You have my thanks.', 15595),
	(28149, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dat\'s de stuff, mon!$B$BNow can you hear dem? De spirits, dey be talkin\', but dey say nothing nice.$B$BLet us bring dem to de light.', 14333),
	(28150, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is little time for talk, $c. The druids fight valiantly against the satyr, but fel sorcery blocks their path.$B$BLuckily, I have a plan...', 15595),
	(28151, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah! I\'m sure Twilight\'s Hammer wanted to number those ogres among their ranks. Now they\'ll probably have to fight them off instead.$B$BThis is good, $N. With one well-placed $c we managed to do the work of a small army. I\'ll let Warlord Krogg know of your work here!', 14333),
	(28153, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Shadow Council is broken! One task remains...', 15595),
	(28155, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Truly incredible, $n. To journey within the very lair of evil here and slay every fiend that stands before you... I am overwhelmed.$B$BThe Emerald Circle thanks you for your work here in Felwood. As for Andalar, we will send scouts to rescue him at once. He shall have a hero\'s welcome.', 15595),
	(28156, 1, 1, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you ever heard the saying "survival of the fittest?" What you\'re doing conflicts with natural law, $g buddy:lady;! This idiot should have died in the mines. There\'s no telling what kind of harm he\'ll cause to himself or another person now that you\'ve saved him from his inevitable demise.$B$BAnd you know who\'s fault that\'ll be, right?', 15354),
	(28166, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, dis be it, mon.$B$B<The lens glows brightly in Buunu\'s hands, casting unearthly rays of light across the shadowy cave mouth.>$B$BWe be ready to bring dem spirits out de shadows now.', 14333),
	(28167, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did Nevin send you ahead? That means he\'s getting ready to end the mission, but there are still survivors to be rescued. We have to help them!', 0),
	(28168, 5, 6, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Who are you? Did Sylvanas send you? Everything is FINE! Yes, perfectly fine! I\'ve got it all under control!$B$BWell, fine all things considered that is... We\'ve got a few problems that perhaps you could help with, $c.', 15354),
	(28169, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to meet you, $c. We rarely come across survivors as strong and capable as you are. I can help get you decontaminated and on your way out of here.', 0),
	(28170, 4, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You see! De dead be nothing to be scared of. You brought de light to de darkness, mon, and never flinched.$B$BWe can use dis cave now as a base of operations in de northern Highlands. You\'re de best, $N!', 14333),
	(28171, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems you are still with us. I\'m somewhat appreciative of that.$B$BThank you.', 15595),
	(28172, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will see to it that these dragons are taken care of.', 13623),
	(28173, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You seem to have made use of the disturbing implements with ease.$B$BI take solace in knowing that some tools of evil can ultimately still lead to safeguarding life. Nothing is without purpose.', 15595),
	(28174, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you\'re in, then?$b$bGood.', 13623),
	(28175, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve started a wonderful thing this day, amidst all of this blood shed.$B$BIt may take many years, but this ravaged land will be restored. It will be beautiful again.', 15595),
	(28176, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lirastraza sent me ahead to the lair, suspecting the black dragon we are seeking may still be here. Judging by the hatchlings, it seems she was not mistaken.', 15595),
	(28187, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is times like zhese, zhat one learns who his friends really are...', 15595),
	(28189, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Undoubtedly you did the right thing. Hopefully the humans that you saved will show similar mercy to you should the time of your planting ever come.$B$BThis is all assuming you rescued the humans and didn\'t splatter their brains all over the dirt - of course.$B$BKeep the shovel as a reminder of the horrors of the Sludge Fields and the depravity of mortals.', 15354),
	(28190, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My rage quells at the news... perhaps I will find it easier to rest and heal now.$B$BMaybe my stomach will settle as well. Urgh...', 15354),
	(28191, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve proven a great ally. I would have never expected such upon our first meeting.', 15595),
	(28192, 5, 1, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As you can see, they\'re all monsters! Most of my guards died and the ones that managed to escape are now holding down the barricades, preventing any of these potentially dangerous creatures from getting out.$B$BWe need your help!', 15354),
	(28193, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Zhey know nozhink, you say?$b$bVery vell, zhen. Zhe search goes on...', 15595),
	(28194, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are perfect, $c.$b$bWish us luck!', 15595),
	(28195, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good, $r...', 15595),
	(28196, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Warden Stillwater flips through the journal, reading under his breath.>$B$BRamblings of a mad man! Clearly he had been ingesting the mushrooms. It is good that you brought this to me, $N. I will burn it myself!', 15354),
	(28197, 1, 1, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! Wilkes was hanged after we discovered that he was ingesting mass quantities of mushrooms and other highly toxic substances. After he died he awoke, reborn as an undead geist. Many of my guards fell to Wilkes before he ran off into hiding. Fearing something like this might happen again, we incinerated the Clerk until only bones were left!$B$BWhy would they willingly ingest toxic substances? I have no idea! This is a farm, $g sir:miss;, nothing more!', 15354),
	(28198, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is a great honor to meet you, $N!  I\'ve heard much about you.', 15595),
	(28199, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These samples will give us a better understanding of the mindless undead. Take these coins as a reward.', 15354),
	(28200, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent job, $N.  You might not think this adds up to much, but this might very well be the difference between life and death to one of our soldiers.', 15595),
	(28201, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a born leader, $N.  It\'ll be good to have you by our side when war comes to these lands.', 15595),
	(28206, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Johnny is sobbing loudly.>$B$BTw... Twinkles!!!! Th... It killed her!$B$B<Johnny continues to cry. Little snot bubbles form in his nostrils.>', 15354),
	(28207, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Most people think the green glow is demonic corruption... but if you\'ve got an eye for shades and hues like me, you can tell it\'s the energies of the emerald dream! These little guys aren\'t being corrupted by the waters, they\'re doing their best to purify it!$B$BNow we\'ll mash \'em up and make a nice yummy paste for Mr. Tauren to eat and feel all better.', 15354),
	(28208, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Poor little kitty, suffering out there in the woods for so long! You did a good thing for it, $n. And probably for all the travelers it\'s been eating.$B$BThis tag will be handy...', 15354),
	(28209, 25, 1, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lydon takes the key from you.>$B$BI\'ll let myself out, thanks.$B$BI have never been so angry! Stillwater won\'t get away with this. I will present his head to the Banshee Queen myself.$B$BYou and I will work together, $N.$B$BI don\'t know about the little girl here, but I\'d prefer she stayed behind.', 15354),
	(28210, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well... that wasn\'t all that great, was it?', 15595),
	(28211, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at that - OW! Pointy! Hot!$B$BThese spears should cut through that dragonhide like an electric cheese-slicing apparatus through butter.', 13623),
	(28212, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Marvelous! I\'ll smelt this down into a delicious soup. An angry soup. Of molten metal.', 13623),
	(28213, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hooray! The forest will be safer now!$B$BYou\'re such a hero, $n! With everything you\'ve done for me and Mr. Tauren and the trees and animals and flowers, you deserve a reward!$B$BYay!', 15354),
	(28214, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. I\'m feeling much better now, and can appreciate the news that those abominations are gone.$B$BYou still might not want to stand too close, just in case...', 15354),
	(28215, 4, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Terrific! These coils will decompress with the force of a thousand suns!$B$BThat\'s just a rough approximation of course, don\'t hold me accountable for those numbers.', 13623),
	(28216, 274, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aye, that\'s him. Can you believe this thing was human once?$B$BThat\'s the Twilight\'s Hammer for you. What they don\'t destroy, they corrupt.$B$BThank you, $c.', 13623),
	(28217, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How noble of you... to blindly kill without question, to come for my head on the barest word of another.$B$BSheathe your fury and hear my tale first. You\'ll see what noble ignorance has done to these lands.', 15354),
	(28218, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And so my master set out to find the skull... risking his own life against an army of demons to find the source of corruption in Felwood. Imagine if he had not! Imagine what these woods would look like if the Skull of Gul\'dan had continued its work, undisturbed...', 15354),
	(28219, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The seedling pats its stalk with a rooty arm, as if full. It looks to have grown a bit, too!>', 15354),
	(28220, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The seedling coils its roots in what looks like a happy manner.>$B$BGrow... big...', 15354),
	(28221, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So happy! Can you hear us? We\'re so many friends now.$B$BBigger and bigger, with room for each friend...', 15354),
	(28222, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So warm and fresh and full of life. We love the sun, it makes us stronger.$B$BSoon now, very soon is the time of growing...', 15354),
	(28224, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes... it is time.', 15354),
	(28228, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Someday I will spread my branches across a renewed forest, full of life and hope.$B$BFarewell, $n. Have patience... and if you live long, you may see me again one day.', 15354),
	(28229, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The moonwell water quickly seeps into the ground with a soft glow. A few moments later, a rustling noise is heard, and a small sprout pops up before your eyes.', 15354),
	(28230, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Once we deal with the rest of the undead we will confront Stillwater!', 15354),
	(28231, 396, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'She may now ascend to the great horsey heaven in the stars. We will never forget you, Twinkles. NEVER!', 15354),
	(28233, 6, 396, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Don\'t be looking!  I\'m not wearin\' me pants!', 13623),
	(28234, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you!  Now turn around so I can put\'em on.', 13623),
	(28235, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now to bring Warden Stillwater to justice!', 15354),
	(28237, 1, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will deliver this head to the Banshee Queen personally. Of course I will make mention of your part in all of this, $N.$B$BAs for your reward - take from Stillwater\'s cache whatever you desire. You earned it.', 15354),
	(28238, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A ride to the Highlands, then? I\'ve just the thing!$B$BI\'ll make room for yeh in me seaplane. I\'ll have to ditch the cat-food I was packing, yeh know, in case we crash in the mountains and ain\'t rescued fer weeks.$B$BOn second thought, jes\' keep the cat food on yer lap, aye. ', 13623),
	(28241, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Eye sits before you, humming ominously with dark energies.>$B$B<Without warning, the orb rotates, as if to look at you. You sense a malevolent presence, as though the orb is alive.>', 13623),
	(28242, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Eye glimmers darkly, colors swirling about its dusky surface.>$B$BAh, the succulent thrill of life extinguished. Do you feel it, $c? Do you relish it as I do?$B$BNo, I see not. You fight to protect the lives of others. Pity.', 13623),
	(28243, 6, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found one? A gen-u-ine Eye of Twilight? Lemme see.$B$BOh Gods. It\'s lookin\' at me. It\'s lookin\' right back!$B$BI need a drink. Can you face that thing toward the wall or somethin\'?', 13623),
	(28244, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What did you see, $N? Cho\'gall? Wait - he saw YOU!?$B$BOh aye, that wee sneaky eye! It looks both ways. That cheeky looker! Where\'s me hammer!?', 13623),
	(28247, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You killed Obsidia within her own lair? Impressive, $r. I\'m sorry that I could not be there.$B$BYou\'re true to your word, and you most certainly have the bite to back your bellow. Thank you.', 15595),
	(28248, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, $n. We\'re in the process of preparing the attack now.', 13623),
	(28249, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, $n. We\'re in the process of preparing the attack now.', 15595),
	(28250, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You showed those thieving little scoundrels!  Great job.', 15595),
	(28256, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now you are beginning to see...', 15354),
	(28257, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you see now? For doing what was needed to drive the demons from these lands, my master was banished.$B$BNow these druids pick up the pieces, patting themselves on the back for scrubbing the remaining vestiges of the legion\'s forces.$b$BBut that is not why I killed them.', 15354),
	(28261, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Enough! Your enthusiasm is impressive, but foolish. Gazing through the veil for too long without practice will break your mind.$B$BThe rest will be mine, $n. For now, I summon you back to me.', 15354),
	(28264, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I find it hard to believe everything you say, but the body of that demon is grim proof.$B$BI will order an investigation into the druids at Jadefire Run right away, and make sure my higher-ups know the demon hunter may be content to remain in exile.', 15354),
	(28267, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, this Schnottz character is working with Deathwing!?$b$bThis is even more distressing than you think...', 15595),
	(28269, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, glad you could make it.$b$bI could use a hand here.', 15595),
	(28271, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good job with Schnottz\'s men.$b$bSounds like you gave them something to think about.$b$bHopefully it bought us the time we need.', 14333),
	(28272, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Harrison quickly skims through the scrolls.>$b$bYes... yes... perfect!$b$bI\'ll need some time to make sense of these, but the information is there.$b$bGood work, $n!', 14333),
	(28273, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome $c!$b$bYou and I are going to be good friends! I can tell already.', 14333),
	(28274, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here we are, $n!$b$bGreat things will happen here... magical things!', 14333),
	(28276, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aren\'t they beautiful?', 15595),
	(28277, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad, huh?  Maybe you can put a word in with the high commander.$B$BMaybe he\'ll put us in charge of our own squad!', 15595),
	(28280, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it, $N! Alliance ingenuity to the rescue.$B$BOf course, I don\'t have anything to help you fight the dismounted riders now that they\'re on the ground. You\'re a $c; improvise!', 13623),
	(28281, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You sure know your way around a battlefield, $c. It looks like they\'re about to fall back.$B$BAll we need is one decisive blow...', 13623),
	(28282, 4, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did it, $N! Narkrall Rakeclaw lies dead at my feet, and Thundermar has weathered a storm of drakes!$B$BThis wouldn\'t have been possible if it weren\'t for the help of the Alliance. I owe you a debt that I don\'t think can ever be repaid.', 13623),
	(28291, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Salhet?  A tactician, you say?$B$BHah!  Very well, if you\'ll vouch for him, we might be able to arrange something.', 15595),
	(28292, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Uldum? What about it?', 13623),
	(28293, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Uldum? What about Uldum? Speak quickly!', 15595),
	(28294, 3, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello, $c! Keegan Firebeard here has told me all about your heroics down south. Thank you for all of your efforts on behalf of the Wildhammer.$B$BI see Colin Thundermar is right behind you. The summit is ready to begin! Please stay and let\'s see how things unfold...', 13623),
	(28295, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Harrison sent you, hmm?$b$bHow fortunate!', 13623),
	(28305, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, hi! Did Farlus send you? I\'m so happy he remembered!$B$BBloodvenom Post is all overrun with awful slime thingies, and this poor tauren is the only one left! We\'ve got to help him!', 15354),
	(28324, 5, 6, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh my. 250? This thing doesn\'t go past 250. How are you still standing? You should be a puddle of goo by now. Sylvanas will be most displeased with this information. There might be some things we can do to reduce the lethality levels of the area by a few decades, but that still leaves us out by about a hundred or so years.', 15354),
	(28325, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $N. You are incredibly resilient to this blight. We\'ll have to take you in for testing some time.', 15354),
	(28331, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As I said, the rod giveth to our dark rangers and doth taketh away from our enemy!', 15354),
	(28332, 274, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We should have killed Bloodfang in Silverpine. It\'s a shame he still lives. It\'s an even bigger shame that we have as of yet been unable to turn worgen into undead. Surely there is a way...', 15354),
	(28337, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is but the first strike.', 15354),
	(28341, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can tell just from the size of these that the fel taint is healing. Slowly... but significantly.$B$BThank you, $n. I will ensure these are properly purged.', 15354),
	(28342, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to see someone who cares about keeping the forest clean. Thank you, $n.', 15354),
	(28346, 6, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What? Kurdran\'s talkin\' marriage!? Didn\'t he just see me an\' ol\' Thunderface tearing each other new ones?$B$BThe only eligible Thundermar is Fanny. Now, I\'ll give you this, she\'s got the looks allright. All lumpy in the right places, if you hear me. But she\'s not got that somethun\' somethun\' a Firebeard looks for in a woman, right?', 13623),
	(28349, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There $g he : she; is! I think you\'re going to like this!', 15595),
	(28350, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work, $gmy boy: little lady;!$b$bYou\'ll master this trapping skill in no time.', 14333),
	(28351, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Splendid!$b$bThis is shaping up to be better than I had dared to dream!', 14333),
	(28352, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it!$b$bI now have camels to spare. Perhaps one day we shall take our show on the road!', 14333),
	(28353, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alright, kid.$b$bMy research is complete. We\'re about ready to activate the final obelisk.', 14333),
	(28356, 5, 274, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'HAH! Those naga have some balls on them! To think that they could take Southshore from us in our own territory! Such a preposterous notion.$B$B<Helcular laughs.>$B$BYou have done well to thwart their attack - though I do wonder if they could have survived for even a minute in the blight.', 15354),
	(28358, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you for hunting in my stead, $c.$B$BI\'ve found I must pace myself... finding too much thrill in hunting demons is a dangerous path.', 15354),
	(28359, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This foul chunk is what those warlocks sought year after year. I will protect it myself, or destroy it if possible, and ensure Kroshius never rises again.', 15354),
	(28363, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You know, I believe I have just the thing!', 14333),
	(28367, 153, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah!$b$bI heard it from here! I wish I could\'ve been there to see it!', 14333),
	(28369, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Me brother sent you? Good! I could use a $c. Can ya hold yer own in a fight?', 13623),
	(28376, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Quite an accomplishment, $n.$b$bI\'ll be certain that this gets to Harrison when his expedition here is concluded.', 15595),
	(28377, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to have you fighting at my side again, $N!$B$BAnd I see the Firebeards have come as well. I suppose they\'ll provide a distraction while me and my boys do the heavy lifting.', 13623),
	(28378, 4, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fanny is safe! I hear Firebeard was in there with you? Nice to hear he\'s finally pulling his weight.$B$BWait, why are you looking at me like that, $n? Do you know something I don\'t? ', 13623),
	(28379, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Har! My men could learn a lot by watching you work. Well done.', 13623),
	(28381, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to the home of my pack, $c. Prepare yourself for war.', 15354),
	(28382, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May their blood water our tree. You fight well, $n.', 15354),
	(28383, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. Now the Horde will not be able to defile these poor spirits to aid their brutish ways.', 15354),
	(28384, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to the pack, $r. Let\'s hope you don\'t mind getting a bit uncivilized.', 15354),
	(28385, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You flip a few switches on the pump and crank a large handle all the way to the right. There\'s a shuddering rumble in the nearby walls.', 15354),
	(28386, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect. I\'ve had the pack gather explosives from the rest of the camp as well, and with these, we\'ll have just enough to get things started once the oil is flowing.', 15354),
	(28390, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps one day, we shall slay these stone troggs more swiftly than they can breed, and in so doing, end the line of fungalmancers forever.$B$BIn time.', 15595),
	(28402, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alright, $n.$b$bI think everything is in order. Let\'s do this!', 14333),
	(28403, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Okay, $n.$b$bI think I can do this manually, but I\'ll need your help.', 14333),
	(28404, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should do it.$b$bStand back!', 14333),
	(28407, 15, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Fanny throws her arms up, exasperated.>$B$BYou, Kurdran, Firebeard, and now my brother - everyone\'s got wedding fever!$B$BFine, fine, I\'ll marry Keegan Firebeard. But only \'cuz he\'s strong and handsome, with a jaw that can cut gravel and an arse like an anvil. Not for any political reasons.$B$BWe\'re going to need your help, though. We got a whole lotta wedding to put together, and not a lot of time to do it.', 13623),
	(28408, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, you work fast. Bold feathers for a bold woman. Well done!', 13623),
	(28409, 6, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, Russell the Bard is always raving about Thundermar Lager. I guess it doesn\'t have the kick of a good Wildhammer brew, but he goes on and on about the "body" or "flavor." I guess we\'ll find out, eh?', 13623),
	(28410, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, aye! Kilts for the gents, gowns for the bridesmaids.$B$BJust don\'t tell the ladies they\'re wearing clothes fit for a blimp.', 13623),
	(28411, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lookat that! You\'re practically bent double under the weight of all that meat. I\'d better get my people cooking.', 13623),
	(28413, 6, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, it\'s catchy, that\'s for sure.$B$BBut is it a classic?', 13623),
	(28460, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks so much, $N! Now I can get back to work here.$B$BDid you find anything of interest at the Winterfall camp?', 15354),
	(28464, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Inside the cauldron bubbles a rotting, repulsive-smelling substance...', 15354),
	(28466, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Without those weapons, the Dark Irons will never be a match for the Horde. You have served your brothers and sisters well this day, $N.', 13623),
	(28467, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Disturbing news indeed. This stuff\'s much more like what you\'d see in Felwood than in Winterspring...', 15354),
	(28469, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Donova examines the contents of the crate.>$B$BI wonder if consuming this substance makes the furbolg more aggressive. They do seem much larger...', 15354),
	(28470, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you so much, $N. I hope to get back to my studies without worry that I will be ambushed. Please accept this as a reward.', 15354),
	(28471, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I wonder what all of this means... I can\'t make anything out...', 15354),
	(28472, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, if you let me examine this for a while, I might be able to translate it for you.$B$B<Kelek flips through the pages.>$B$BWhen I am able to look over this fully, I will send word to you.$B$BThank you for sharing this with me, $N. Very little is known about the Winterfall furbolg.', 15354),
	(28479, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Pity me, stranger, and all the Highborne, for it was here our folly began... our folly that cursed our children, and our children\'s children, to this day.', 15354),
	(28480, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a valuable ally, $N.  We are one step closer to defeating the enemy.', 15595),
	(28482, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Glad you could make it, $n!', 14333),
	(28483, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent job, $N.  Our troops will hear of your deeds.', 15595),
	(28484, 24, 274, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I... um... well... turns out he doesn\'t need the hearts anymore. Sorry about that! Hope it wasn\'t too inconvenient! A deal\'s a deal though, so here is your reward. You can go ahead and keep the yeti hearts. I hear they hold excellent nutritional value - if you\'re into eating.', 15354),
	(28485, 273, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So it\'s true, you did kill the beast! The people of Hillsbrad are indebted to you, $N. You have made the land safer for our citizens.$B$BTake whatever you may desire from our coffers.', 15354),
	(28486, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it, $N!  Excellent!', 15595),
	(28487, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N! I promise you that this is the last time I take this gear off.', 15354),
	(28489, 4, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a hefty load you\'re carrying. It should keep my customers satisfied for the time being.$B$BHere is your pay, as promised.\n', 15354),
	(28490, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, the king has heard our plea? Thank Elune! We can use all the help we can get.', 14333),
	(28492, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you come to help us fight back against the forces of the Horde? Every blade and spell will be needed!', 15595),
	(28494, 66, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You look competent with a weapon or a spellbook. We could use your help in driving back the quilboars in these parts.', 15595),
	(28495, 5, 20, 274, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'WHAT!? No, don\'t tell me that, $N! It can\'t be true! My... I... I would never...$B$BI won\'t give up, $c. Just you wait and see. I will save those fawns!', 15354),
	(28497, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $n.$b$bNow let\'s see if we can make our way up there before they\'re able to recover.', 14333),
	(28498, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent.  Let\'s see if we can find anything of importance.', 15595),
	(28499, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps you are as powerful as I\'ve heard afterall.$B$BYou have our gratitude.', 15595),
	(28500, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is true then?  It does exist!', 15595),
	(28501, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did it, $N!  We held Nahom.', 15595),
	(28502, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $N.  These savages must be punished for what they\'ve done here.', 15595),
	(28513, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Crystal of Zin-Malor was stolen from a far-off temple without remorse. Its ability to control the arcane was too tempting, and when it was toyed with, its shattering cursed us all. Kel\'theril suffered until the Sundering destroyed it for good.$B$BThe curse of Zin-Malor binds all who seek its power here. I was the first to fall to its temptation. Thousands of years later, our long lost descendants would be next...', 15354),
	(28517, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This oak was grown through the aid of the druids from a seed taken back on Gilneas. It stands for all that we\'ve endured, and all that we\'ve accomplished.$B$BMay it serve to remind us that our curse is also our blessing.', 15595),
	(28518, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We were shocked before we died. Shocked that one among our noble and austere kind could descend into vicious obsession so quickly. We died as naive fools, the victims of our own blithe assumptions.$B$BThe living would know that these events would play out yet again... both here, and among the entire elven race with the fall of Quel\'thalas.', 15354),
	(28519, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The living farstrider who sent you here could not bear to see our fate. He ran... a wise decision.$B$BIf one now holds the Crystal of Zin-Malor again, it will spell the doom of all around them. It should never have been reassembled.', 15354),
	(28520, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done.  We have defeated the Neferset inside their own city.$B$BI wish I could say that there is peace for my people at last, but I only foresee more bloodshed.', 15595),
	(28522, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for what you have done, as saddening as it is.  Accept this as a token of thanks.$B$BI would ask of you to please continue helping us, $N.  We have very few allies on which to call upon, and without your aid, the threats against my tribe would surely be too much for us to handle alone.', 15354),
	(28530, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s quite a bit of it... the Winterfall are slipping further and further. And now we\'ll have to worry about the other wildlife as well, in time.', 15354),
	(28531, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can get you to Nijel\'s Point quickly! We need all the reinforcements we can get.', 0),
	(28533, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well, it looks like it\'s time.  Stay and watch if you so please.', 15595),
	(28534, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We were proud and noble. Our faith in the light protected us, and with the Sunwell, we wanted for nothing.$B$BBecause of that blindness, we came here to repeat the tragedy of history, as our entire race would in time.', 15354),
	(28535, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We were not naive, as our forefathers were. We were suspicious and cunning and ready for betrayal at every turn.$B$BYet our pride and greed drove us to ruin once more. How many more will be lost to Kel\'theril?', 15354),
	(28536, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The shade! Yes, I saw it too!', 15354),
	(28537, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let me see... faintly written, among the engraved incantations, is the name of its master!$B$B"Umbranse..."', 15354),
	(28539, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Horde has bored a giant pass into the mountains, and we have few enough sentinels to spare. We have to find a way to stop them!', 0),
	(28540, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dis is nice, big heart! If you be interested, Mau\'ari tell ya how I be gettin\' de E\'ko....', 15354),
	(28543, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is much work to do here. The forest is on the mend, but without our help, it will take generations to restore this once-sacred wood.', 15595),
	(28544, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank goodness you\'re here. I\'ve discovered the secret of the fierce Winterfall furbolg.', 15595),
	(28548, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You... arrived just in... time...', 0),
	(28549, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve no doubt seen what the Alliance has done to the Barrens, $c. If we don\'t act, there may not be a Horde presence here much longer.', 0),
	(28550, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We face heavy Horde counterattacks daily, $c. We need every pair of hands we can get to keep them at bay.', 0),
	(28557, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You could be one of the very first mortals to set foot in Uldum in millenia. Just think of the treasures that await us!', 15595),
	(28559, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you\'re here to help? Well, there\'s plenty to do...', 15595),
	(28561, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N!  It\'s you!  My regiment was ambushed on our way here.$B$BOur captain was slain, leaving me in command... until you got here, that is... sir!', 15595),
	(28574, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you come to help us against the Wildhammers? The Warchief knows that what happens here will be important to the Horde\'s future.', 0),
	(28579, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You must be here to help Fuselight! Let\'s get you to the Badlands right away.', 13623),
	(28583, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s this? The "$N-o-matic:" a shredder with an integrated missile platform?$B$BBah! Already patented by Labor Captain Grabbit in Azshara. Worthless!$B$BWhat I really need is a machine that knocks dwarves from the sky.', 15595),
	(28584, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There you go. Now hows about we use this blast tape on Rothman\'s mouth?', 15595),
	(28586, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks, $N! Now if we could just get the Krazzworks stable so that our people would stop being thrown off of the platforms.', 15595),
	(28588, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You got the chops for killing dwarves, that\'s for sure, $N. This is a good thing.$B$BNext up, more dwarf slayage!', 15595),
	(28589, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s the spirit! Must be pretty humiliating being shot down by junk.', 15595),
	(28590, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to have you, $n. Ready to sow some chaos?', 15595),
	(28591, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Marvels of modernized goblin destructivity, eh? I love these babies.', 15595),
	(28592, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hahah! Wonderful show.$B$BThat should be a proper welcome to the highlands.', 15595),
	(28593, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brilliant! Krazz will love you something mighty for bringing this one home. Good on you.', 15595),
	(28594, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And that\'s how it\'s done. Scattered to the wind. Not quite the fighting force they boast themselves to be, eh?', 15595),
	(28595, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that\'s what I wanted to see! I\'ll have this fleet back up in no time with this beauty.$B$BYou know just how I like it, $n. I know just how you like it too - take this.', 15595),
	(28596, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s more like it. We should be able to mop this up from here.', 13623),
	(28597, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aye, that\'ll do \'er.$B$B<Flintlocke stuffs some of the powder in his mouth.>$B$BOhhh, fresh. Heady. Redridge fine grain with a hint of Westfall sulphur and a mild aftertaste. Highbank gets the good stuff. ', 13623),
	(28598, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Flintlocke wipes tears from his eyes.>$B$BOh, $N. $N!$B$BThat ... were beautiful.', 13623),
	(28599, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The King himself sent you? Good to hear that Stormwind is secure.$B$BI was expecting more in the way of troops, but word is that the Alliance fleet was ambushed by the Horde on the way here. They gave as good as they got, but the fleet is in shambles.$B$BIf we\'re to make any forward progress here in the Highlands, we\'re going to need the help of heroes like you.', 13623),
	(28608, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Exactly what I needed.  You\'ll be an asset to the Forsaken, $N.$b$bYou know, word has it that you were quite the $c in your previous life.  Perhaps I should assign you to a more exciting task.', 15595),
	(28609, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lilith wants a boulder moved inside the observatory, eh? That\'s my business: consolidated materials. I usually don\'t get individual buyers, but hey, I won\'t ask questions.', 15354),
	(28610, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like a good amount! Here\'s your pay, as promised...', 15354),
	(28611, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The waters of the river are nearly cleansed.  Our prophetic visions will soon return.', 15595),
	(28612, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lucky fer you, this ol\' dwarf\'s still got a few tricks up his sleeve!$b$bHeehee! ...shoulda seen tha look on yer faces!', 14333),
	(28613, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So far, so good...', 14333),
	(28618, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, you actually brought the boulder! I\'m a bit surprised.$B$BStand back and witness the pinnacle of craftsmanship.', 15354),
	(28620, 6, 25, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That imbecile finally sent help, did he? These two orcs are a lost cause. They are stricken with something that I have termed "Durnholde Syndrome." They were both locked up for so long that they grew an affinity for their captors. Now they sit upon my couch with their big, iron balls and cry.$B$BHopefully you will prove to be more useful.', 15354),
	(28621, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Of course I have a plan for moving the coffer.$b$bSomeday, maybe the old coot will learn to trust me.', 14333),
	(28622, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work, $glad:lass;.$b$bLooks as tho everything made the trip in one piece.$b$bI\'m beginnin\' ta see why junior keeps ye around.', 14333),
	(28623, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve arrived just in time, $N.  ', 15595),
	(28624, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They want a tree now? Let\'s see what I got.', 15354),
	(28625, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not a bad haul. Maybe we should look into growin\' those treants instead...', 15354),
	(28626, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alright! Stand back now and watch what a true quality weapon can do!', 15354),
	(28627, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, it\'s you again! I\'m so surprised!', 15354),
	(28628, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect. Now you\'ll see what really matters in a weapon... finesse.', 15354),
	(28629, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These furs are perfect, $N. We\'re off to a great start here!', 15354),
	(28630, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Part of this machine is still moving, but on closer inspection it\'s been severely manhandled. The metal is dented and cracked, and there\'s huge footprints in the snow all around it.$B$BIn fact, it sounds like something\'s approaching right now...', 15354),
	(28631, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t wait to show my friends! Now, just wait a moment while I attach these...$B$BPerfect!', 15354),
	(28632, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad! Let\'s hope they don\'t ask for lava or something next, right?', 15354),
	(28633, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Of course! I had a hunch this is what we\'d find.$b$bHad no idea about the organic transformations, though, I must admit.$b$bThere\'s more to this old relic than I\'d dared to hope.', 14333),
	(28634, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The itching has stopped - for now - but they will return.$B$BOh yes, they will return...', 15354),
	(28635, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Haunted? Ye could say that!', 15354),
	(28636, 1, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They fight for their land even after death - much like the Forsaken. I will report back to high command that Dun Garok is uninhabitable. Let them keep what they hold so dear.', 15354),
	(28637, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Simply splendid! I\'ve been watching the Captain bring bear after bear back to camp and I can\'t wait to see them thrown on the smoker.$B$BPerhaps I\'ll have a taste of them raw...', 15354),
	(28638, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Captain\'s been bringin\' back bags full of owl, and I can\'t wait to try it! Maybe Mr. Fancypants Francis here will even try some.', 15354),
	(28639, 274, 5, 479, 14, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ursius is... not delicious.  He tastes like a combination of pinecones and curdled milk, only... oilier.$b$bAre you sure this is Ursius?  The big bear?  In the cave?$b$bThis is horrible.  It honestly tastes like his meat has been steeped in urine.$b$bI don\'t feel like I\'m getting any stronger.$b$bUgh.  It\'s really bad.  Do you want to try some?', 15354),
	(28640, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alright! Don\'t stop now, we\'re after the big ones next!', 15354),
	(28641, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Beautiful! I\'m watching the Captain drag this all back right now and it\'s a gorgeous sight.$B$BAnd the next course...', 15354),
	(28643, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Zephyrus was a mighty adversary. Surely the remaining elementals will challenge you further!$B$B<You open the guide that Jekyll gave to you.>', 15354),
	(28644, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Teracula was an even mightier adversary than Zephyrus.$B$B<You open the guide that Jekyll gave to you.>', 15354),
	(28645, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now you know why the monster was called Bloodvenom. What challenges remain?$B$B<You open the guide that Jekyll gave to you.>', 15354),
	(28646, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Though you have defeated the four elements, one final challenge awaits. What could it be?$B$B<You open the guide that Jekyll gave to you.>', 15354),
	(28647, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is the first time anyone has actually completed the challenge. You truly are a powerful $c, $N. As promised, choose your reward.', 15354),
	(28652, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes?  And who might you be?', 15595),
	(28653, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings, $N.$b$bI see you wield a weapon.  Can you fight?', 15595),
	(28654, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Bout time ye showed up, $glad:lass;.$b$bNow let\'s get goin\'! There be work ta do!', 15354),
	(28655, 4, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did it, $N! Fighting that ... thing side-by-side really brought all the Wildhammers together. The heads of the families are more united than I\'ve ever seen them. Drink up, $N, and celebrate!!$B$BOf course, our work is only beginning. I\'ll rally our new Wildhammer reinforcements with the rest of the Alliance and prepare to storm the Twilight Bastion.$B$BI\'m sure we\'ll meet again soon. ', 13623),
	(28656, 2, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s dis? You got de smell of de E\'ko on ya! Let Mau\'ari tell ya a little bit about de E\'ko and what it do.$b$bYou\'re lucky, $r. De E\'ko searched you out. A troll like me\'s gotta go find de E\'ko herself.$b$bAll de creatures of Winterspring have E\'ko. De furbolg, de chillwind, de shardtooth... even de Ice Thistle yeti! You kill dese creatures, and sometimes, a bit of E\'ko comes out. Different creatures... different E\'ko.$b$bGo on now. Go find de other E\'ko!', 15354),
	(28657, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You actually killed him?!  I can\'t believe it!', 15595),
	(28658, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like you were able to get the croc hides that we needed.  Thanks $n, your contributions will not go unnoticed.', 15595),
	(28659, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those filthy alliance never stood a chance.  Nice work, $n.', 15595),
	(28660, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You made it back out alive?  You are a stronger man than I, $n.', 15595),
	(28661, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Galus is dead?  Fantastic work $n, now we can send down the cleanup crew and get that cellblock ready for new prisoners.', 15595),
	(28662, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These journals are in excellent condition $n.  We will begin deciphering them immediately.  Only time will tell what secrets they hold.', 15595),
	(28663, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'D-Block is all clear?  Good work, $n.  We will send down a crew to start cleaning up right away.', 15595),
	(28664, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Svarnos is finally dead?  Looks like we can finally get to work setting up that cellblock then.  Thank you $n.', 15595),
	(28665, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The shackles!  We will begin the process of destroying these shackles immediately $n.  Thank you for your help.', 15595),
	(28666, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s time for the Blackrock orcs to feel the full wrath of the Alliance. They will pay for what they\'ve done.', 13623),
	(28668, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You cleared that area out?  Looks like you might be more useful to us that we thought, $r.', 15595),
