	(28825, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May your sense of honor and duty serve Azeroth well, $c.', 15595),
	(28826, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that your eyes have seen the truth, where will you choose to serve?', 15595),
	(28827, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All of our war ships are off fighting the Horde. You\'ll have to take the mercenary ship.', 15595),
	(28828, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice. Eggs.$b$bThese will go great with a little bear bacon.  Hey Francis, got any bear meat left over?', 15354),
	(28829, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My honor is restored.$b$bPartially.$b$bMy tale continues, $c, for I have left portions of my honor elsewhere in this forest.$b$bIt has not been a very easy journey for me.', 15354),
	(28830, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Be glad that the adult giants are trapped on the other side of that gorge. They are far hardier than these tumblers you fight.$b$bI feel rejuvenated by your courage, $c. Perhaps all hope is not lost after all...', 15354),
	(28831, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If I survive my wounds, I will always remember your name, $c.$b$bWhenever the wind whistles through the trees, I will always hear your name.$b$bThank you.', 15354),
	(28832, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You two are the last thing I expected to see fall from the sky. Highbank is under attack!', 13623),
	(28833, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What is this? You... rescuing me?$b$b<Erunak smiles at you.>$b$bThis will take some getting used to.', 15595),
	(28837, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s see what I can do with these...', 15354),
	(28838, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. It is just as Jaron described it.', 15354),
	(28839, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The dreamcatcher is charged.  We are nearly ready to retake Mazthoril.', 15354),
	(28840, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Haleh applies the water to your dreamcatcher.>$b$bYou\'ve done well, $N.', 15354),
	(28841, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It will take some time for Mazthoril to recover... but she will.$b$bThe blue dragonflight is far from dead.', 15354),
	(28842, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have our thanks, $N.', 15354),
	(28843, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hellscream shall know of your deeds here, $n.$b$bWithout you, things here would be far worse.$b$bLok\'tar ogar, my friend!', 15595),
	(28845, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You actually came here looking for me?', 13623),
	(28847, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are $N, yes?$b$bGood, you will serve well. I require the aid of a $c such as yourself.', 15354),
	(28848, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Umbranse... I see. I will carry this information onto my people.$b$bYou will be contacted if you are needed again.', 15354),
	(28849, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another $c for the Highlands? Here, sign this indemnification waiver...', 15595),
	(28850, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greymane\'s right.  These beasts do not give a damn about our politics.$B$BGilneas needs to stand together.', 15595),
	(28853, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Tooranu looks over the documents you discovered.>$B$BIt\'s all here, $N. Details of how the cult is tearing up the Highlands, who they\'ve sent, where they are, and what they plan to do. Invaluable.$B$BI shall distribute this knowledge to the rest of the Earthen Ring at once. Thank you, friend.', 15595),
	(28854, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So it is done.$B$BWould that I could bring this entire mountain down upon itself, I would.', 15595),
	(28856, 2, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Cenarion Hold.$b$b<Windcaller Proudhorn brushes some snow off of your shoulder.>$b$bYou\'ve certainly come from far off.', 15354),
	(28866, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s about time they sent someone to help.$B$BMillhouse Manastorm?  It sounds like we\'re both after the same person.', 15595),
	(28868, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $N. That\'ll teach them not to mess with us in our home!', 15595),
	(28869, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Pebble seems quite happy to meet you.>', 15354),
	(28870, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hail, $N.  Nadun spoke highly of you.$B$BAre you here to aid us?', 15595),
	(28882, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s that smell?  Ah.....Smells like victory.  Your efforts in Tol Barad are a great triumph for the entire Alliance, your contributions will not be forgotten.', 0),
	(28884, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You bring word of victory, just as I expected!  Any triumph in Tol Barad is in turn a triumph for the Horde.  Have no doubt, your efforts here will be rewarded.', 15595),
