	(29036, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Honor the Deepholm flame.', 15595),
	(29066, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What? Blackhorn helped you combat the inferno but escaped in the process? That crafty weasel!$B$BIt\'s not your fault, $N. He\'d probably been plotting this the moment he saw the flames begin creeping up the mountain. We\'ll have to deal with him later.', 15595),
	(29071, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Veterans of Northrend, King Wrynn and the Alliance need your help! Stormwind and the Alliance face unprecedented threats from Deathwing and his Twilight\'s Hammer minions!$B$BPlease find the enclosed hearthstone and use it to transport yourself to Stormwind. The crown has arranged lodging for all returning heroes at the The Golden Keg in the Dwarven District.', 15595),
	(29078, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve bought us a little time, $n, but we\'ve got even bigger problems to deal with now.', 0),
	(29079, 21, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n. You\'ve turned out to be quite an asset to this garrison. It\'s time for you to train!', 0),
	(29080, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s true, we were ambushed. I don\'t dare send any more soldiers out there and risk losing them too. I need a volunteer. Someone willing to risk their life!', 0),
	(29081, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That will teach those monsters! They\'ll think twice before taking another mercenary job for orcs.', 0),
	(29082, 273, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I think you now understand the power of the Light. The Light giveth hope, $g brother:sister; and the Light taketh from the darkness! BLESSED BE THE LIGHT!', 0),
	(29083, 1, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With your help we have managed to secure the northern and western sectors of Northshire. We still have a rather large contingency of Blackrock orcs to the east and they\'ve begun burning down the forest!', 0),
	(29092, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is grave news indeed. We must do everything in our power to stop this war from coming to pass.', 15595),
	(29101, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Mylune\'s voice echoes in your head, along with an unwanted image of playful kittens.>$B$BYou saved the wee turtles, $N! I hope you gently, lovingly kicked them as hard as you possibly could.', 15595),
	(29122, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hooray! It just goes to show you, when a turtle puts his mind to something -$B$B<Mylune is distracted by a butterfly and never finishes her thought.>', 15595),
	(29123, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well-fought, $N. Take a break from the flames for a while.$b$bHyjal will live to see another day, and when that day comes, I will need you alive.', 15595),
	(29125, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Immediately after touching the final spirit of Malorne, you hear Matoclaw\'s voice.>$b$bWell done, $N. With the horns of Malorne on our side, we stand a chance against one of the Firelands\' most difficult foes: Galenges.', 15595),
	(29126, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Galenges has fallen, the unbreakable is broken... but our work is not done.', 15595),
	(29127, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well-fought, $N. Take a break from the flames for a while.$b$bHyjal will live to see another day, and when that day comes, I will need you alive.', 15595),
	(29128, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A job well done, soldier. While our mission in the Firelands is critical, we must not forget about the well-being of Hyjal.$b$bSpeak with my brother again tomorrow, and he will have another squad prepared for you.', 15595),
	(29129, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is no whimsical dalliance that brings you here, mortal.$b$bMuster every fiber of your courage for what you are about to behold.', 15595),
	(29134, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Now, $r, you know the reasoning behind your summons.', 15595),
	(29137, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re grateful for your support. Your presence on the battlefield gives us the time we need to refortify. Your efforts make all the difference.', 15595),
	(29138, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I saw several of our warriors make it back to safety shortly after you departed. It seems your efforts were quite effective. Thank you.', 15595),
	(29139, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We will win this battle. Whatever it takes, we will not let these elementals back into Hyjal.', 15595),
	(29141, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The elementals shall grow to fear you.', 15595),
	(29142, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Our enemies now know that our strength is to be feared.', 15595),
	(29143, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $c. I\'ll have to make more use of your skills in the future.', 15595),
	(29145, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n. It is good to see you again. Our gate is nearly opened.', 0),
	(29146, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was great! I even learned how to control the rocket and everything! Did you see how I saved us? I\'m gonna be a rocket pilot when I grow up!', 15595),
	(29147, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Amidst the chirps, hoots, and frenzied caws of your fellow birds, you hear the voice of Matoclaw speaking to you from afar.>$b$bWell done, $r. Now that the flock is assembled, we strike.', 15595),
	(29148, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, champion.', 15595),
	(29149, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well-fought, $N. Take a break from the flames for a while.$b$bHyjal will live to see another day, and when that day comes, I will need you alive.', 15595),
	(29156, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh good, a $c.  Maybe you\'ll have better luck in dealing with these trolls.$b$bSee what they want and then try to get rid of them.', 15595),
	(29159, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! The more spiders we clear out, the easier it will be to push forward.', 15595),
	(29160, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful work, $c. Let\'s hope those little spider bites aren\'t infectious.', 15595),
	(29161, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Mylune\'s thoughts echo in your mind, along with unwanted images of flowers and squirrels.>$B$BOh, you did it, $N! The baby bears are so happy.$B$BI\'m beginning to think they\'ve started doing this on purpose.', 15595),
	(29162, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh NO you\'re covered in SPIDER-SPORCH!$B$B<Mylune hides her eyes from the sight of you.>$B$BYou\'re such a brave $r. I hope you\'ll go into the Firelands soon and step on ALL the spiders.', 15595),
	(29163, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well-fought, $N. Take a break from the flames for a while.$b$bHyjal will live to see another day, and when that day comes, I will need you alive.', 15595),
	(29164, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Matoclaw\'s familiar voice enters your consciousness.>$b$bYes, $n, you are ready. Now, we strike against Lylagar.', 15595),
	(29165, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I heard your triumphant cries echo across the mountain cliffs.$b$bI also heard Lylagar utter a... different type of cry.', 15595),
	(29166, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will have these packaged and shipped off right away.', 15595),
	(29167, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'She\'s just as fierce as I thought she\'d be! But that ambassador sure got real mad when I started talking to Lady Sylvanas.', 15595),
	(29176, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Someday, I\'m going to be a great warrior, just like Cairne or the warchief. Everyone will remember my deeds, and the ancestors will welcome my spirit too!', 15595),
	(29177, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $c. I hope you don\'t forget about us here in the Hatchery.', 15595),
	(29179, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your continued efforts are appreciated, $c. We will win this war as long as people like you stand beside us.', 15595),
	(29181, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see. I can\'t say I\'m eager to bring my flock to the Firelands, but I knew it would become necessary at some point.$B$BWe will be there, $c. Thank you for carrying the message.', 15354),
	(29182, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These skies are indeed oppressive, but we\'ve been able to navigate them for the most part.$B$BWe may need your help to secure additional landing territory past the Furnace. I will call for you when we are ready.', 15354),
	(29189, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our lost allies have already made it back. They are shaken, but alive. Thank you for rescuing them.', 15595),
	(29190, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for the kite, $N. Every time I fly it, I\'ll remember the day you gave it to me!', 15595),
	(29191, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I think that\'s the first time I\'ve ever seen a goblin making food that didn\'t involve a big, noisy machine with a lot of smoke. Maybe more people would like their food if they just made it like normal people... or like mages! That ice cream was so good!', 15595),
	(29192, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am impressed, $c. Your deeds will be remembered among the Shadow Wardens.', 15595),
	(29195, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Leyara... she lives. I sense Fandral\'s hand at play here...', 0),
	(29196, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What happened up there? I saw fire and... never mind, you can tell me later. We have other, more immediate matters to attend to.', 0),
	(29197, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n! You\'re back!$b$bThey\'ve pushed us back to the Sanctuary. We are vastly outnumbered. At this rate, the Guardians of Hyjal stand little chance of survival.$b$bI\'m glad you\'re here with us.', 0),
	(29198, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Malorne\'s strength alone may have just saved Kalimdor. To imagine, Malorne has returned today, after so long an absence...$b$b<Malfurion surveys the area.>$b$bWe\'ve taken heavy losses. Though the immediate threat is no longer present, our forces will need time to heal, and to put out any remaining fires here in Hyjal.$b$bOur attack on the Firelands will have to wait.', 0),
	(29203, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Leyara\'s tale is a tragic one. It pains me that it came to this.$B$BStaghelm must be stopped, before he drags anyone else down with him.', 15595),
	(29205, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $c. This should prove a good staging ground for pushing further into enemy territory.$B$BI sense Druids of the Flame nearby. Perhaps we shall have some sport of them as well.', 15595),
	(29206, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Glad to see the Skylord was finally able to get someone capable through without wings. Our flight has been of little use to us in these confined spaces and amidst the thermals beyond this ridge.$B$BLooks like we\'ll have to resort to more conventional tactics. You game?', 15595),
	(29210, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done!$B$BThey\'ve been attempting to start rituals of this sort all over the Molten Front, but we\'ve been able to thwart them every time so far. Hopefully you will be present in the future to help us keep up that trend.', 15595),
	(29211, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is destroyed? Good. I doubt this will deter Fandral for long, but we must gain every advantage we can muster.', 15595),
	(29214, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see. It is time for us to join the hunt in the Firelands then. My sisters will be with you, $c.', 15354),
	(29215, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello, $n. It\'s good to see you again.$B$BYou needn\'t worry. We\'ve settled in quite well. I\'ve dispatched several of my wardens to assist in hunting down the Druids of the Flame, and I\'ve drawn assault plans for the Forlorn Spire. When the time is right, perhaps you will join us there.', 15354),
	(29219, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dere ya have it, $n.  It look like we gonna lead an assault on da Gurubashi in Zul\'Gurub.$b$bDese be dire times for us Darkspear.  But dey be even more dire for da Zandalar.  Dey goin\' too far.$b$bYa been good to Bwemba, hopefully ya gonna continue to help out all of Stranglethorn.$b$bSpirits be wit\' ya, $n.', 15050),
	(29220, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems da spirits be wit\' you, $c.', 15050),
	(29221, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for da help, $n.  Dese serpents, dere don\'t seem to be an end to dem.', 15050),
	(29222, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Venoxis... Dis can\'t be good, $n.', 15050),
	(29223, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We know all about the serpents, $n.  But there is something else out there lurking...  The jungle has come to life, $c!', 15050),
	(29226, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Shhh.... ', 15050),
	(29227, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like the real Mauti was tracking Grent Direhammer all along.  Clever cat.', 15050),
	(29228, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We be here... Da hunter, he be in da cave.  Da beast... Sometin\' ain\'t right about her...', 15050),
	(29230, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'High Priestess Kilnara be behind dis abomination.  Dis ain\'t looking good.  We should see to da dwarf and then make our way to see what other trouble be going on.', 15050),
	(29231, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh... Me spine...  Brother, is that you?', 15050),
	(29232, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Th-thank ye, $g lad:lass;.$b$bPappy...?$b$b$bIs that...$b$b$b$byou...$b$b$b$b$b...', 15050),
	(29233, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'First we had snakes, then we had panthers, now we have blood-thirsty trolls.$b$bIt\'s good that you\'re here, $c, there are plenty of trolls to kill.', 15050),
	(29235, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These trolls just keep coming, $n.  I love it!$b$bLike I said before, the Darkspear emissary was here for a small amount of time.  He warned us and then left.$b$bThysta, our Wind Rider Master, helped get him to his next destination, maybe she can help you out.$b$bHappy hunting, $n.', 15050),
	(29236, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dis don\'t look very good, $n.', 15050),
	(29237, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We done enough, $n.  We can\'t keep fighting dese zombies.  We need to figure out da source of dis voodoo.  An\' I tink I know where to start...', 15050),
	(29238, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Zanzil... Dis is all startin\' to come together now.  If I can find my contact den we can formulate a plan of attack.  A way to end dis madness.', 15050),
	(29243, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well done, $n! This should delay them significantly.$B$BIf we keep this up, we can easily push the fight back to Ragnaros himself.', 15595),
	(29245, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fascinating! It appears to be an acorn!', 15354),
	(29246, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I must get to work preparing the salve immediately. These reagents lose their efficacy by the minute.$b$bThank you, $N.', 15354),
	(29247, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Many thanks, $c.$b$bYou do the war effort a favor. Burn victims have a notorious appetite for bandages, and Hamuul is no exception.', 15354),
	(29248, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a compassionate $r. With this many scales, we won\'t have to cut him again for another day, at least. Perhaps two.', 15595),
	(29249, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A red flower pops its head out of the soil.', 15354),
	(29250, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I be tellin\' Baron Revilgaz about da Zandalar threat now...', 15050),
	(29252, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You killed them all?  I wish that would ease my mind, but these guys seem to have a habit of coming back from the dead.$b$bAh, but what\'s that you have?$b$bYou say it might keep them out of Booty Bay?$b$bNow we are talking!$b$bOh right, I said I had a reward for you?  Sure... Just give me a minute to find it.', 15050),
	(29253, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Loot at last!', 15050),
	(29254, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh my! Who\'s your little friend? It followed you, you say?', 15354),
	(29255, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It isn\'t very pleasant-smelling, but this should fix the Lasher right up.', 15595),
	(29257, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N. I will start analyzing these samples at once.', 15595),
	(29263, 11, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah knew Ricket\'s bombs\'d come in handy. Twas just a matter ah findin\' somethin\' big enough to explode.', 15595),
	(29264, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I like the way you work, $N.', 15595),
	(29265, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These things never cease to amaze me. Whether they\'re actual plants, or just delicate stone formations, the fact that they can grow in such hostile conditions astounds me.$b$bI\'ll have these sent to Avrilla for analysis right away.', 15595),
	(29268, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The panther cub looks at you with a look in its eyes that says, "Will you be my new $g dad:mom;?"', 15050),
	(29272, 11, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You! You\'re the one who saved Anren. My best friend, Anren.$b$bWe got separated in that cave. I didn\'t know what to do without Anren.$b$bYou are a resourceful $c. We may call upon you later to assist us in our reconnaissance missions. With your help, Anren and I might no longer face the terrifying risk of being separated from one another.', 15354),
	(29273, 1, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These results will go a long way to help us understand the fire hawks, and - more importantly - Alysrazor, their new, fiery queen.$b$bTholo and I are thankful that you\'ve been helping us out.', 15595),
	(29274, 11, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This ash may seem indistinguishable from any other type of ash you find on this forsaken island, but trust me... you have found the right stuff.$b$bWe will have it analyzed immediately.$b$bReturn again soon. While I do enjoy spending time with Anren, we also appreciate your company, $N.', 15595),
	(29275, 5, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Anren, look what $N found! This is exactly what we needed!$b$bIt will take us some time to look through these supplies. For now, you have our thanks.', 15595),
	(29276, 2, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are an asset to our cause, $N. Tholo and I thank you.', 15595),
	(29278, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fantastic! Now ah kin get ta work.', 15595),
	(29279, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Of course. I will see to it that the sacred waters are transported through the portal right away.$B$BThank you, $c.', 15595),
	(29280, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You will be pleased to know that the waters arrived safely. With the moonwell filled, and the shade of the Sentinel Tree upon us, I can almost forget we\'re in the Firelands for moments at a time.$B$BI\'ve spread the moonwell\'s blessing upon these trees and bushes. Take the fruit with you before you venture out. It is more refreshing than you can possibly imagine.', 15595),
	(29281, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was wondering if those two would come in handy. They\'ve seemed quite out of place ever since they arrived.$B$BI saw Ricket around here just a moment ago. I\'ll gladly send her back through the portal with you. She\'s less likely to be blowing up any local plant life on that side of things anyway.$B$BLet\'s see... where is she...', 15595),
	(29282, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey you! Good to see you again!$B$BI\'m settled in good and fine, actually! It\'s good to be with good old Damek again. I never thought I\'d be mixing with a dwarf so well, but he and I, we\'ve got like minds on all the important stuff.$B$BYou go do your thing. Don\'t be worrying about us. If we cook up any good toys for you, we\'ll be sure to let ya know!', 15595),
	(29283, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I understand. We are prepared. We shall join the march and meet you on the far side of the portal.', 15595),
	(29284, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You chose a wise time to call upon us, $c. I was concerned for our ability to stand against the elements in this realm, but the protection of the Sentinel Tree has proven far more than sufficient shelter.$B$BWe will do anything we can to aid your efforts here. Witherbranch has met with your other allies and is discussing a way to corner some of Ragnaros\' lieutenants. You should speak with them when the time comes.', 15595),
	(29287, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will do perfectly! Come see me again in a day or two and we\'ll see how things have progressed.', 15595),
	(29288, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They look to have singed your gloves a bit, but I don\'t see any damage otherwise. Well done, $c.$B$BCome by again within the next few days to see how the training has gone.', 15595),
	(29290, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I take it your assault was a success! Brilliant. This could be a key moment in opening up Ragnaros\' defenses.', 15595),
	(29293, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Several of our brothers and sisters passed by while returning to the safety of the Sentinel Tree. You did very well out there, $n. Thank you.', 15595),
	(29295, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This\'ll do. Nice work, $N.', 15595),
	(29296, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n. It\'s good to know I can count on you.', 15595),
	(29297, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those blasted burds are dead? Good riddance!', 15595),
	(29298, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What have we here? A necklace? No, a locket...$b$bOh, my...', 15595),
	(29299, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did it work? So my theory was correct?', 15595),
	(29302, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If Leyara bore witness to the War of the Shifting Sands, then it seems likely she knew Fandral - and his late son, Valstann - far more closely than any of us suspected.$b$bIt would seem that your journey does not end here, $n.', 15595),
	(29303, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If the vision is to be believed, Leyara\'s ties to the Staghelm family were quite strong. It\'s no wonder that she clung so fiercely to Fandral\'s new order of flame.', 15595),
	(29304, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, $c. The enemy may be tough, but you have proven today that you are tougher.', 15595),
	(29305, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well done, $n! This should delay them significantly.$B$BIf we keep this up, we can easily push the fight back to Ragnaros himself.', 15595),
	(29310, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'First Valstann, now this...', 15595),
	(29311, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, I knew Leyara, and I was aware of her anger even before she joined the Druids of the Flame. She was a promising young druid, once. Unfortunately, the bonds of family are often stronger than the power of reason, and ultimately, she chose to follow Fandral down his treacherous path.$b$bYou should keep this locket, $N. May it remind you that each of us walks our own path through life... and that some paths are easier than others.', 15595),
	(29314, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You lay out the rice cakes around the shrine, which begins to glow softly. A faint sense of approval washes over you.>', 15595),
	(29315, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These smell absolutely wretched. Perfect!', 15595),
	(29316, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It takes a lot of effort to ensure that there\'s enough flour for everyone\'s needs. Thank you for your help, $N.', 15354),
	(29317, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah! THERE it is! How ever did you find it?$B$BWell, no matter. My apprentices weren\'t able to recover the head despite hours splashing about in the slime, though they DID recover this bag of shiny things... perhaps you\'ve a use for what\'s inside?$B$BMy thanks.', 15595),
	(29319, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $N. I\'ll see that these are, ah, disposed of immediately.$B$BAfter all, what would our fine apothecaries want with an army of monstrous, poison-spitting, flesh-eating super-toads?', 15595),
	(29320, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a fine, fat pike, $N.  Well done.', 15595),
	(29321, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yuck, they\'re so gross-looking, but they\'re my brother\'s favorite. Thanks for sparing me from that messy job!', 15354),
	(29322, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These slimes look perfect.  I will send these along to Eunice for preparation, thank you.', 15595),
	(29326, 274, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It can\'t be over. We mustn\'t give up hope!', 15595),
	(29327, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What is this... water?', 15595),
	(29328, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Air, water... now earth?', 15595),
	(29329, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Aggra clenches her fists, and stares at the spot where Thrall stood moments ago.>', 15595),
	(29330, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Despite all odds, Thrall has been saved. Aggra was right to hold out hope for the world-shaman.', 15595),
	(29331, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks to you, my friend - I live again! And due to the combined efforts of the Cenarion Circle and the Earthen Ring - the World Tree will bring new life to Azeroth as well.$b$bWhile Deathwing and the rest of our foes remain to be dealt with, I wish to share something with you.', 15595),
	(29332, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, what a luscious batch of lilies. Bravo! I\'ll boil them down right away...', 15595),
	(29333, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You must be quite the swimmer... all I can manage is the dead man\'s float.$B$BIn any case, excellent batch of snails you\'ve gathered. Thank you.', 15595),
	(29334, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, and just as I was nearly out. Thank you!', 15595),
	(29335, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You feel the wind racing over your arms, your face, your weapons and armor...>$b$B<Cyclonas is looking you over.>', 15595),
	(29336, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will do what I can to aid you, $c.', 15595),
	(29337, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I already know what it is you seek, fleshlings. And I have chosen to aid you.', 15595),
	(29338, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Be ready, $N.', 15595),
	(29345, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $N. It\'s up to all of Thunder Bluff\'s fishers to keep this vicious creature out of Mulgore\'s waters.', 15354),
	(29346, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found my ring, did you? I\'m most grateful.$B$BTo be honest, I\'ve no idea why I keep the thing. I\'m not even certain how I acquired it... I suppose I am simply a creature of habit.$B$BStill, as I said, I am grateful. Say... I found these things while searching for it myself. Perhaps they\'d be of some use to you?', 15354),
	(29354, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My, those are some very lovely stones! They\'ll make perfect shiny baubles, thank you.$B$BHere... Kah told me you\'d be by with the stones, and to give this to you upon your arrival.', 15354),
	(29358, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You work so quickly!$B$BI\'ll see that these are distributed to the various chefs and bakers of Thunder Bluff.$B$BThank you!', 15354),
	(29360, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah!  Perfect!  Fat, slow and ready to be eaten!  Next up, we will feed them to our spiders.  Fatten them up, and then, we feed the spiders to the frogs...$b$bListen to me go on.  You don\'t need to know all the details.  This is just a small step in a grand cuisine in a grand scheme.', 15595),
	(29361, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The dead feed the flies.  The flies feed the spiders.  The spiders feed the frogs.  The frogs feed our moat monster... It\'s a beautiful circle of life with the goal of ending life.', 15595),
	(29362, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $N! I\'m sure these will impart a simply magical taste to whatever dish they\'re used in.$B$BWhat? Stop looking at me like that!', 15354),
	(29363, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ooo, that bread smells delicious. You are quite the baker, $N.$B$BWho knows how far these exquisite loaves will go... I hear it\'s even popular among the draenei of the Azuremyst Isles!', 15354),
	(29364, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Much work is required to grind enough cornmeal for everyone\'s needs. Thank you for your help, $N.', 15595),
	(29365, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Aska examines the ingredients you have chosen.>$B$BMmmhmmm. Yes. Well done!$B$BI could not have chosen better myself.', 15595),
	(29389, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for answering our call for aid, $n.', 0),
	(29412, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is GREAT! You did it!$b$bThanks, $gmister:miss;!', 15595),
	(29433, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you seek out worthy challenges, or did you simply find some field of boars and slaughter them?$b$bThere is a reason I am the strongest.$b$bPerhaps, one day you will see just how strong I really am, $c.  Until then, keep pushing yourself.  But don\'t forget to take a break from time to time.$b$bLike now.  Here, enjoy the Darkmoon Faire.', 15595),
	(29434, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An impressive display!$b$bHere\'s your reward.', 15595),
	(29436, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Five points?  Good job!  Here are your prize tickets.$b$bEnjoy the rest of the Darkmoon Faire!', 15595),
	(29438, 21, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew you could do it, $c!  Here\'s your prize.  Enjoy the faire.', 15595),
	(29439, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It would appear my message has been heard in Stormwind.$B$BThank you, $n. Let us get to work...', 15595),
	(29440, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see my message has reached Orgrimmar.$B$BThank you, $n. Let us get to work...', 15595),
	(29443, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where did you get this crystal?$B$BThese are very rare and much sought-after by collectors. I would like to study this one and display it at the Faire. Would you accept a generous number of Darkmoon Faire tickets in trade?', 15595),
	(29444, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where did you find this egg? There\'s sure to be something monstrous and wonderful inside! It will make a great addition to our zoo. Are you willing to part with it for a generous number of Darkmoon tickets?', 15595),
	(29445, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A strange grimoire, how interesting! I don\'t think I\'ve seen its like before. I\'d love to have it for my collection. Would you be willing to accept Darkmoon tickets in exchange?', 15354),
	(29446, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where did you find such a wonderful blade?$B$BThis is a work of astounding craftsmanship and worthy weapon for any champion. I would love to have it for display.$B$BWould you accept a generous number of Darkmoon Faire tickets in trade?', 15595),
	(29451, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t know how you got your hands on this, and I know better than to ask. Could I convince you to part with it in exchange for Darkmoon tickets?', 15595),
	(29452, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us begin, mortal.$b$bThere is little time to spare.', 15595),
	(29455, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew you could do it!$B$BWe\'ll take any extra rings you might have, and give you your prize ticket.$b$bHave fun!', 15595),
	(29457, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is a remarkable example of an Alliance officer\'s insignia. While many of them visit the Faire, none are willing to part with their badges. Would you be willing to accept some Darkmoon tickets in trade?', 15354),
	(29463, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you have managed to defeat the gnolls.  It felt good, didn\'t it?$b$bHere is your prize.  Enjoy the rest of the Darkmoon Faire!', 15595),
	(29464, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where did you find this collection of runes? I haven\'t seen anything like this in years. It\'ll be a splendid mystery to unravel!$B$BWould you trade these for Darkmoon tickets?', 15595),
	(29509, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are perfectly cooked, $N. You\'ve done an excellent job.', 15354),
	(29510, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will help maintain my supply. Anytime you want to help, just look up old Sayge while the Darkmoon Faire\'s in town.', 15354),
	(29520, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for helping with those banners. You have quite a talent for needlework. Next time the Darkmoon Faire\'s in town, why not come by and help again?', 15354),
	(29528, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew I could count on you!$B$BWith their forces in disarray, we can really get this invasion going. ', 15595),
	(29529, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So it\'s true. The fel orcs and the Burning Legion are working together in some capacity.', 15595),
	(29538, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Out-frikkin-standing! As of right now, you are my eighth favorite person on the smoldering remains of this sorry planet!', 15595),
	(29539, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, '<You tell Gunny everything you saw in the Blood Furnace.>$B$BYou brought back some loot for ol\' Gunny, right?$B$BNo, no, you\'re right, clearly I owe you a reward for all your hard work. Not like Gunny didn\'t arrange all this and send you in there in the first place.', 15595),
	(29540, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Really? You want a reward for killing an orc? As in fame and riches and noble steeds?$B$BBack in my day killing orcs WAS the reward!', 15595),
	(29543, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That Altumus is certainly a gem, isn\'t she? But there won\'t be any of us left alive out here if we aren\'t successful in our efforts in the ramparts.', 15354),
	(29563, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'The loss of life...it pains me.$B$B<Watcher Jhang sighs.>$B$BThank you, $N. When we are all reunited, the naga won\'t stand a chance.', 15595),
	(29564, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mennu\'s death will not fix the broken backs of my family and friends, but it will give them a chance to live the rest of their lives free.', 15595),
	(29565, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad that their spirits are now free. I wish we could say the same for the rest of their kind.$B$BThere is still much work to be done, especially elsewhere in Coilfang.', 15595),
	(29567, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'The Black Stalker is dead!  Normally I would not revel in such butchery, but the pain that the great mother and her brood have put my people through over the centuries is unspeakable.$B$BYou have my deepest thanks, brave $c.', 15595),
	(29568, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done all of Zangarmarsh a favor this day, $N. The spore giants may be naturally aggressive, but they\'re still a vital part of the ecosystem.', 15595),
	(29570, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Soon we\'ll all be together again, and I owe it all to you!$B$BWe\'ll bring the naga down before you know it, they don\'t stand a chance!', 15595),
	(29573, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Splendid! Haramad will be delighted to hear the good news! All of this ripe for his taking!', 15595),
	(29574, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These samples are absolutely fascinating. They\'ll work very nicely.', 15595),
	(29575, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I didn\'t honestly think a $r would be able to defeat a Nexus-Prince. You\'ve surprised me, and you\'ve earned the handsome reward you were promised.', 15595),
	(29583, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was truly hoping that the gnome I sought out would be the one to answer my call.$B$B<Artificer Morphalius looks you over.>$B$BI suppose you\'ll do.', 15595),
	(29590, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps now we can finally be at peace.', 15595),
	(29591, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The dead belong in the spirit realm. Just as you belong in this one.', 15595),
	(29594, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! The long term effects of this attack will be far worse than slaying a few orcs could ever be.', 15595),
	(29596, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done our realm a great service. You will not be forgotten.', 15595),
	(29605, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Knowing that Lakka is free means I can cut the rest of my ties to the Sethekk.$B$BPart of me will never forgive myself for Syth\'s death, but it had to be done. When I reach Skettis, I will perform the death rites for him.', 15595),
	(29606, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I may never truly be forgiven for my role in the crimes of the Sethekk, but perhaps by restoring the relics of Terokk to my people, I can begin to redeem myself.', 15595),
	(29607, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are marvelous. Well done!$B$BHere\'s your cut, as promised.', 15595),
	(29608, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Dalaran! This inn is part of the Silver Enclave, the headquarters of the official Alliance presence in our city.$B$BDon\'t forget to bind your hearthstone here for easy travel to the city and access to the portal to Stormwind next door.', 15595),
	(29613, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I wish it had not come to this, but the naga refused all attempts to negotiate.', 15595),
	(29614, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad we were able to contain this before it spread across all of Zangarmarsh or further. Thank you.', 15595),
